INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1, 1, '\nWhat is the most important animal in your country? Why is the animal important?', '"Many animals like tiger, cow, dog, and cat have an importance in the various aspects like as keeping guard over night and cultivating the soil, not to mention keeping the ecosystem.  Despite that, if I should choose one animal among them, dogs are the most significant in my country, Korea in terms of emotional development of children and dogs’ faithfulness. \n\nFirst of all, dogs are really helpful for the emotional development of children. That is, in the recent Korean society, parents are too busy for their work to take care for children and finally likely to make children selfish and rarely realizing the importance of sincere attention toward others.  In the case that children spend time with dogs while parents are not with them, however, they learn the spirit to consider others from dogs with giving a love to them like feeding, washing, wearing them.  Actually, one survey reported that Korean children grow up to the generous and mild character after living with dogs.\n\nMoreover, dogs are faithful and give a lesson to many Korean people.  There is the famous saying in Korea like “The faithfulness of dogs is better than people.”  As this saying means, they are extremely subordinate to their master and even if they are thrown a few miles away, they desperately come back to their master even without eating anything.  Actually, one dog called as “Jin-do” is the representative dog of Korea, a symbol of faithfulness.  Therefore, dogs’ unchangeable love and trust to their master give many Koreans to a meaningful lesson like as the trust among people. \n\nAccordingly, dogs are considered as the most important animal in Korea.  Than any other animal, they more contribute to the formation of the good character like considering others and the demonstrator for the faithfulness among people."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(2, 1, '\n"It has been said. ""Not everything that is learned is contained in books."" Compare and contrast knowledge gained from experience with knowledge gained from books. In your opinion, which source is more important? Why? "', '"There is a saying ""Nothing outlives book."" Since the creation of letters, people have started to record mysterious happenings, marvelous things, religious beliefs, historical events etc., in books. In this vantage point, books are not but  sums of human knowledge gained and experienced by people from ancient times to these days. However, knowledge and experiences in books have been ceaselessly refined and finally lost its crudity. As a result, knowledge gained from books are likely to be more abstract and indirect than knowledge gained from experience. \n\n       When we learn something by experience, it means that we happen to get a lesson about it by using our own body and soul. In contrast, when we learn something in books, it means we happen to know that by using only our brain. This is a great difference. For example, we can easily find books which say touching a burning pot could hurt you. However this kind of warning doesn''t make good effects because it is very abstract. On the contrary, if a person who happen to touch a burning pot by mistake, easily learns it is very dangerous to get closer to hot objects. Moreover he will memorize it for a long time. Therefore knowledge learned by experience is more realistic. \n\n       In addition, knowledge in books is apt to be biased. Knowledge and information in books are tend to reflect their writer''s point of view. It is not surprising to find various history books which witness the same historical event but show great different perspectives. Writers can deftly manipulate knowledge by hiding some or over-emphasizing a fact or another. This kind of cheating is easily overlooked by readers who are prone to believe that writers tell the truth. On the other hand, knowledge learned by experience is more direct. so there is no loophole for manipulation. For example, reports by press on damage or death toll for wars or disasters are often less precise than those by witness who experience the events in the place. \n\n       In my opinion, knowledge gained from books provide us basic and broad back ground information, But knowledge gained from experience give us more realistic and direct ideas for affairs. Therefore, I think knowledge learned by experience is more important and precious. Even though, knowledge in books seems to be better arranged and selected, we also have to listen carefully to vivid and living lessons of experience. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(3, 1, '\n"Some students prefer to study alone, while others prefer to study with a group of poeple. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer. "', '"When the issue on the study method is discussed, almost all people, especially student, have their respective answer. This means that it takes greater important to them than any other. I also have a special way of study, which is rightly by study group. Although there are a lot of benefits in studying by oneself, I prefer to study group for following reasons. \n\nBefore we consider the way to study, it is very reasonable to know what purpose of study is. I means by the purpose of study that it indicate not only preparing the exam, but also recognizing the facts, such as historical events, mathmatics, economic and so on. To recognize the facts is impossible by oneself because there are many view-points among people. The most fundamental aim of the study is to understand other''s respective opinions. Therefore, we can obtain the truth by accepting or considering opinion of another person. \n\nNext, I cannot help raising following question ; how can we do when we have a question or problem? There are several answers about above question, such as using Internet, reference book and so forth. But, I think that the best answer is asking other persons about problems. As you know, when other persons like friends directly help one with problem, it is most effective way in solving that. \n\nIn sum, different people have different answer due to their respective point of view. From what has been discussed above, I can draw the conclusion that studying with group is more beneficial than with alone. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(4, 1, '\nA company has announced that it weshed to build a large factory near you communiry. Discuss the advantages and disadvantages of this new influence on your community. Do you support or oppowe the factory? Explain your position.', '"     If a company were to announce that it wished to establish a big factory in my commmunity, I think I would have mixed emotions because there are advantage and disadvantage to building a factory, especially in a medium-sized town like mine. However, I think disadvantage affects to my town much more than advantage does in repect of pollution. \n     \n     \n     The main benefit of a new factory is obvious: increased jobs. During IMF, some TV program I was used to enjoying introduced one city experiencing some changes after a factory established in it. Before a factory entered, many of the heads of the families in the city were not able to get jobs because of ''System-Control'' of the government. So many families underwent financial straits, and mood at home was heavy. Some of patriarches tried to deal with their mind as drinking, and fights were often occur on the street or at home. However, after building a factory, many jobless persons could get jobs and work on it. Families were released from financial pressure more and more and the atmosphere at home became warm. Also patriarches were not drinkers at all. All of the good changes originated from a new factory. \n     \n    However, there is another concern about building a new company : pollution.   My city has many lakes and streams. I would want to know if they would be affected. Could you remember the happening ''itai-itai disease'' in Japan from 1955 to 1957? The people in Doyama in Japan, especially old women, realized that their legs more and more bent into the inside. With getting worse the symptoms, they walked with faltering steps like a duck, ultimately, they went died on a bed with crying ''itai,itai''(It means I''m very sick)  Do you know the reason of that?? It was ''cadmium'' drained by the factory nearby the river in town. Cadmium overflowed by the plant streamed and entered the river in town and the persons were affected while they didn''t perceive. Finally, the factory destroyed the town. I don''t never want to happen something like this in my community. \n     \n\n      In conclusion, a big factory could give my community both advantage and disadvantage ; job and pollution. However, now most of the people in my community have jobs, so important thing is preserving natural environment in my community. Therefore, I opposes that a big factory should be established in my community. \n\n"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(5, 1, '\nSome people believe that students should be given one long vacation each year. Others believe that students should have several short vacations throughout the year. Which view point do you agree with? Use specific reasons and examples to support your choice.', '"  In modern society, we are running for some purpose such as good score, university in school, Regardless of the period of the vacation, the vacation enables students wearing out due to hard work to take a rest and  could be vitamin to recharge our battery. When we find life a bore, I will have a long vacation in that it give students the chance which they can have the board outlook on life by a long trip and the time to prepare for the tests of special purposes. \n\n\n      On the one hand, a long vacation give us the chance which we can have the board outlook on life by a long trip. Long vacation enables students to travel to a region far away from their towns. During an adolescent period, taking a long trip is very useful. Through that, they can learn the wisdom of life as well as the wide knowledge that they could not learn in classes. For example, I traveled to Austrailia and worked as volunteer in  ATCV(Austrailia Trust Conservation Volunteer) for two months by using my first university summer vacation. Through the trip, I learned not only the world view  but also the importance of the nature by experiencing ATCV in Austrailia. Therefore by providing the chance to have a long trip, they can widen their outlook on life. \n\n     On the other hand, a long vacation could be used as the time to prepare for the tests of special purposes. As you see, there are some tests needing long preparation times for special purposes such as foreign language ability and professional technique. However, if the time to be given were so short for preparing the test,  they cannot concentrate on the test and the possibility which they can pass the test could be smaller. For instance, there is my brother who studied computer software for a technical license for two months by using winter vacation, finally he could get the license, he was employed at one of the most famous computer companies. Consequently, through a long vacation, students can prepare for the test of special purposes and develop their special abilities . \n\nIn conclusion , I  have an opinion that if students use their long vacations effectively, they can broaden their experiences through traveling and enhance their special abilities by getting la long vacation  make students’ outlook more wide and give them the opportunity to prepare  for the  tests of special purposes. ful  for if students use their long vacations effectively, they can broaden their experiences through traveling and enhance their special abilities by getting licenses of the tests.  Plus  I call a long vacation  as Vitamin in our life. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(6, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? People behave differently when they wear different clothes. Do you agree that different clothes influence the way people behave? Use specific examples to support your answer. \n\n"', '"There are many kinds of cloth for many specific situations. when I play sports, I wear some comfortable clothes that don''t annoy movement. As you know, ceaseless movement is needed to play almost sports. For even some stationary sports, it is very important to feel comfortable for a good result. Then, why don''t we always wear some comfortable clothes? It is because there is social restriction about clothes. then, why do this exist? what I want to say here starts from this question. \n\n        Clothes can affect our behaviors. As I mentioned above, when we play sports, we wear comfortable clothes to be free from disturbing our movement. And, we can move more actively. It will make a good result at the game. Is it impossible to wear a suit and a hat instead of a baseball uniform and a cap? Of coursem, not. But, they can not do well because of the uncomfortable clothes. So, I can say that cloth can affect our behaviors. \n\n        Moreover, I can find out one more fact that is about the relationship between cloth and behavior, from the example that I mentioned above, sports game. You know that sports players wear uniforms when they play a game. They wear uniforms which are same color, same design. Each element of the team would realize that they belong to same team. This feeling about belonging can help to make better cooperation for the players. Not only sports players, whoever belong to same organization feel this from uniform. And it can affect their behaviors to make a good result. \n\n        In conclusion, I mentioned some examples that show relation between clothes and behavior. It is obvious that different clothes influence the way people behave. So, good selection of clothes for proper situation would be very important. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(7, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? People should read only those books that are about real events, real people, and established facts."', '"There are two worlds: the world which is, and the world which might be. Nonfiction deals with the former, which is happening and happened, and fiction deals with the later, which the writer create. some people think they should read only those books that are about real events, real people, and established facts. But from once upon a time, we have read fiction such as detective novel, science novel . There is no reason to restrict our reading to nonfiction such as real events, real people, and established facts. In my case I voice a counterargument that people should read fiction too because reading a fiction make us to be imaginative and is one way of a rest in order to get out of  stresses.   \n\nFirst of all,  reading a fiction  make us to be imaginative in our life. When we were children, we enjoyed reading novels such as fantasy novel, detective novel and watching an exciting cartoon on TV. Because some sort of fiction make an effect on our dream, we dream of pilot,  president, a detective , scientist and so on.  As you see, the imagination play an important role as motive power which our dream come true. For example, after I read Gullivers’ travel written by Jonathan swift, for long time a deep impression and excitation didn’t disappear. Whenever possible I dream of the adventure and oversea travel, So far I traveled several countries such as Austrailia, America, India, Nepal, Thailand, Japan  and got precious ones through travel. Above I mentioned, reading a fiction make an good effect on the power of imagination  in our life. \n\nNext, reading a fiction is a good way to take a rest and get out of stresses. With a developing industry and tight schedule of our modern life, we are having a trouble with stresses which make us so tired physically and mentally , even which induce the disease  like  cancer. By using spare time, when we read fiction, we can relax us without a pill of tranquilizer and get out of stresses effectively. To illustrate, while I worked hard in graduate school due to a heavy burden of a national research project, I am in bad condition both mentally and physically, even while a mere trifle irritate me. I start to read novel “The Lord Of The rings” for a solution to get rid of my problem. It results in a good success. Even though tough research project and tight schedule, I can have a tranquil heart without stresses. Under mental stresses, sitting on the bench, let’s read an exciting novel, and then you feel free, comfortable. \n\nIn sum up, for the above-mentioned reasons, I support the idea that reading a fiction is beneficial for enhancing the power of the imagination and a good rest and the removal of our stresses. On top of that, we can say that these benefits from reading a fiction are priceless. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(8, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? People should read only those books that are about real events, real people, and established facts. \n\n"', '"Why is it so important to acquire knowledge that is true and real? Imaginative and creative people do not prefer to live in mediocre life. To be successful in these days, people must think unique and rare ideas. Therefore, I do not agree that people should read books which are published by real events, people, and facts. \n\n        Knowing only how to think common thought, people do not know methods of surviving in a real life. Let’s think that one has never imagined anything and has learned about only real facts.  He will be a very weird person in society; for example, he will believe nothing before he sees it if people tell stories which they experienced. Consequently, he will be not only isolated from others but also a doubtful and cold person. \n\n        For children, ability of imagination and creativity is a significant trait. Most mothers try to listen to music and read books before babies are born. This occurrence is all for developing baby’s ability to think imaginative ideas. However, if children read only non-fictional books, they will become ordinary and standard people in the future. In addition, creative people remain to be remarkably successful by inventing unique items or extraordinary business plans. Hence, being creative and imaginative is important nowadays. \n\n        In conclusion, people do not need to read only books about real events, people, and facts because it can reduce an ability to imagine ideas and make people unemotional. If you want to success in your life, read fictional books instead of non-fictional one and become creative and imaginative! "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(9, 1, '\n"Schools should ask students to evaluate their teachers. Do you agree or disagree? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer. \n\n"', '"  In Korea society, most social system was under the influence of the Confucianism, so the authority of the teachers was so strong that we could not help obeying the order and the teachings of them, moreover evaluating them is not allowed. But as the time goes on and on, Viewpoint of the education is changing. Now, we can say and I agree with the above statement , ”Schools should ask students evaluate their teachers.” In that evaluating their teachers improve their skills and the quality of the education through the competition and is a good way for school administrators to evaluate teachers efficiently. \n\n\n     In the first place , evaluating teachers improve their skills and the ability of the education through the competition. As you see, the profession like teacher is stable and there is few possibility to be dismissed , on the other hand they are apt to fall in the period of a lassitude. Because teachers also are human being, they could get lazy and difficult to control their first minds, back to basics.  To get rid of this kind of a lassitude, evalutation about teachers give them some sort of incentives which refill with a passion. To demonstrate,  in our uviversity, the system of evaluating professors was introduced two years ago. Before it  was introduced, the atmosphere of the lecture room was changed into a big enthusiasm, so we can learn a lot. Finally, without being restricted from leftovers of  Confucianism and thinking twice, the introduction of  the system of evaluating teachers is beneficial to rational education to enhance their skills and quality of the education through the competition. \n\n     In the second place, it is a good way for school administrators to evaluate teachers efficiently. When the school administrators evaluate the achievement of teachers, so many factors are included to it. In my thinking, one of the most important factors is whether students are satisfied with the lecture of the teachers, which show us the ability and the quality of the teachers. For example , Korea Information and Communication University used this system four years ago. The teacher who  get the worst score of evaluation receive some penalty, In viewpoint of efficiency of the organization, they succeed in it. If glancing, evaluating other people might be seen to bad thing, but it could contain more positive effects. Therefore we call evaluating teachers as a good method for managing the school organization. I think there should be no exception in every organization . \n\n\n     To sum up , I take the review that evaluating teachers is necessary for improve their skills and the quality of the education through the competition and is the efficient method for school administrators to evaluate teachers. Furthermore the good quality  of  the  education system which we will get by evaluating teachers absoulutely contributes to the developments of korea "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(10, 1, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Parents are the best teachers. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"What do you think of learning? There could be plenty of answers to this question. Some can say learning means aquiring some kind of knowledge, while others regard learning as being harmonious with friends, family and neighbers. In my view, learning is the process of establishing relation with ohters. In this sense, I think we can learn more by parents because parents know us better than any other teachers in the world. What''s more, parents give us love and affection that is indispensible for us to make good relation with others. \n\nFirst, as is mentioned above, there is no teacher who knows children better than parents. This is because parents have spent most of their time with their children. Although it is difficult for parents to give their children specific knowledge, information or skill, the very fact that parents know their children very well make them the best teachers. For example, teachers have no way to find out what their students need before students ask teachers what they want or need, because there are many students and few teachers. In addition, teachers can not spend most of their time in taking care of just one student. On the contrary, parents can spend relatively much time to their children. Thus, by spending a lot of time with their children, they can easily find out what children want to do, what they feel, and which they like more. \n\nSecondly, there is powerful device that make parents the best teacher such as love. Although there are many good teachers in this world, who can love their students more that their own children? Plus, in most case, the relationship between teachers and students are over when students graduate from school. Without personal affection to certain students, keeping touch with them is not as easy as we think. On the contrary, parents, the best teacher who love their students keep in touching with children with great concern before they die. \n\nIn sum, it is not easy for us to conclude that parents are the best teacher because they can not teach us proffesional knowledge. However, the fact that parents understand thier children better that teachers and they love their children make parents the best teachers in this world. In this sense, I strongly agree with that statement."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(11, 1, '\n"Some people prefer to live in a small town, Others prefer to live in a big city. Which place would you prefer to live in? Use specific reasons and details to support your answer. \n\n"', '"   I had lived in a small town until in high school, after that, I has lived in a big city. So I could experience all advantages and disadvantage of a small town and a big city. When I was in a small town, I thouht a small town was better that a big ciry, but after I moved to a large city, I never imagine that I return a tiny community. \n   \n     Initially, in a large city, people could have many cultural opportunities more easily. For example, a few weeks ago, I and my friend living in a small town far from a large city went to the theater to watch very famous musical, ''Cats''. In my case, it took me about half of an hour to go to the theater by subway, but my friend spent almost 3 hours arriving in the theater by car because she lived in a tiny community. She exhausted valuable time in which she did something different and more money so that she drove a car operated with oil. In her small town, there were no theater for musical or play and many of the town were not interested them. So all she could do was that she went to a large city for seeing musical or play. If she had have born in a big community, she could have enjoyed musical and play as much as she wanted. \n\n     Next, much more medicine service is given to people living in a large city. Now I can imagine one documentary televised on TV last year. On documentary a story of one men preparing ''Disabled Olympic'' was introduced. The men had blindness of one eye. According to his words, it originated from a unexpected accident. When he was a child, he and his friend played the game using a toy sword. The game was very exciting and they more and more fell into it. While they enjoying the game, the accident succenly occured. The sword of his friend stung his right eye deeply. He felt a extreme pain on his eye, and cried loudly. No sooner took him to the hospital in town than his mother saw his hurtten eye but doctor said that he should go to the bigger hospital in a big city. So He and his mother went to the hospital in a big city as soon as possible, but he lost his eyesight during going to there. Through this case, we can know why people prefer to live in a big city. \n\n     In conclusion, I prefer to live in a big city that living in a small town. Of course, living in a small town has the advantages ; clean air, pure water and stablility  earned from living with nature. However, when considering that I am young and health also now I need the advantages of cultural chances and medicine servise, it is obviousely much better for me that I live in a large city. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(12, 1, '\nPeople attend college or university for many different reasons. Why do you think people attend college or university?', '"   These days, more and more people have been attending University or college. Some are attending University without certain purpose and just follow people around them, while others enter college to prepare their jobs or to study deeply. I think people attending University because they want to have more profound knowledges about their careers and enhance the levels of their cultures. \n         \n               First of all, University helps students to be competent worker by studying their major. There are lots of faculty who have been studying specially and rendering remarkable achievement to their fields. By taking their classes, students learn professors'' accumulated knowledges and wisdom. Also, friends in same major can share informations about goals that they want to achieve in the future. In short, students can develope themselves as a good worker through studying in advanced classes of their major with students who have common interests and goals. \n        In addition, University helps students get common senses and develope sociabilities which are essential to become cultured men. There are many club activities which are helpful to develope ourselves. In my case, I attained intellectual cultures by doing newspaper club activity and became sociable by getting along with various kind of people in the club. Plus, central library in University has many books about liberal arts  available for students who have difficulties in buying expensive books. Shortly, people can cultivate themselves better by attending University.           \n               \n             To sum up, in my opinion, people want to enter University for career preparation and being well-grounded men in various fields. As the society become more complex, university will perform important role of making professional worker and cultivate people. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(13, 1, '\n"It has been said, ""Not everything that is learned is contained in books."" Compare and contrast knowledge gained from experience with knowledge gained from books. In your opinion, which source is more important? Why? "', '"          People learn constantly from their birth to death. Not only school education or books but also things we see, hear, touch are good materials to get knowledge. Among them, I think knowledge of experience is more important than knowledge of books because of its durability, and it teaches us precious values like cooperation and flexibility. \n         \n               First, we hardly forget what we learn from our own experience. For example, we learn importance of money and difficulty of earning money in capitalistic society by studying economics through books. Also, we memorize how money circulates between producer and consumer written in textbooks. However, we usually forget about it as time passes. On the other hand, we can learn hardship of gaining money or way of profiting in person through part-time job. The reason is that they are more practical, and as we learn it using five senses. In short, knowledge of experience are more important because it''s unforgettable.   \n        Secondly, knowledge of experience offers a sense of cooperation and flexibility which are important to build up one''s character. Even if we can gain boundless knowledges studying books about astronomy, mathematics, and so on, it''s no use if we bury ourselves in pedantic or impractical theory neglecting the value of cooperative spirit and flexibility, which can be gained by social experience like contacting directly with other people and various circumstances. To sum up, getting knowledge from experience is good to develop cooperative and flexible attitude.     \n         \n                In conclusion, if I have to choose between knowledge gained from experience and knowledge gained from books, I would choose the former. The reason is that it''s lasts longer, and gives us cooperative and flexible mind. However, what we don''t have to forget is that both knowledges of experience and books must be in balance.   "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(14, 1, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Television has destroyed communication among friends and family. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"People have invented new machines and materials to make our life more convenient and joyful. Among them, television is one of the most effective inventions. In my opinion, I don''t agree with the statement television has destroyed communication among friends and family because it gives people common subjects to talk about and time to get together.\n         \n              First of all, a family can have time to be with by watching television. These days, each individual is busy doing his/her own work and has different interest. However, after dinner, most family gather in the living room to watch TV. In my case, my family has talked about each others'' daily life while watching television together. On the contrary, when my father puts the television away to prevent my eyesight from weakening, my family members did their own business in their own room. Shortly, television provides time to communicate with family.     \n\n        Moreover, we can get some topics of conversation from television. There are lots of interesting and up-to-date informations that most people can share and enjoy. For example, a popular soup opera ''A lover of Paris'' of SBS provided intimate and funny subjects to talk with friends. Also, television shows us about current issues so that we can discuss about it. In summary, whether that kind of topics are vulgar or not, it''s certain that television helps people communicate with others by giving common interests and topics.     \n         \n                 In conclusion, I think television is serviceable stuff in the aspect of helping people communicate with their family and friends by giving chances and subjects to talk. Lastly, what I want to suggest is that people should control themselves to do not addict to watching television, and use it wisely to have better communication with others. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(15, 1, '\nSome people prefer to watch movies in a theater. Other people prefer to stay home and watch movies on video. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Since movies of these days offer quiet a good way to spend time, many people take watching movies as their hobby. Some of them like to watch movies at home sitting on the sofa and some others want to watch them at a theater. As a mania for movies, I prefer the latter, which is the more attractive way to enjoy movies. \n\nFirstly, theater has a good environment to concentrate on movie. We can enjoy powerful sound and a big screen. Also the inside is dark enough. These are necessary if you want to enjoy the movie thoroughly. Although there are some equipment like home theater to provide similar environment to houses, because of the magnitude of the room the quality is much lower than the theater can offers. \n\nSecondly, you can have your own time in a theater. No one disturbs you by asking you ""What happened just before?"" or ""I don''t like that actor.” You can just enjoy the movie alone and can talk about it after the screening is over. Those conditions cannot be accomplished if you are watching it with your family or friends at home. \n\nSo if somebody wants to enjoy a movie, I would recommend him to go to a Movie Theater even though he has to pay for it. Because it is worth paying to guarantee pleasant facilities and one''s own time. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(16, 1, '\nSome people prefer to eat at food stands or restaurants. Other people prefer to prepare and eat food at home. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"When it comes to decide whether to eat at restaurant or at home, it is hard to do so because both have their own good and bad points. But I prefer to eat out due a lot to the convenience which is the most important condition for me in this case. \n\nFirst, as I mentioned it is much more convenient to eat out side. We don''t need to prepare dishes for a long time and is cleaning needed neither after finishing the meal. And various choices are possible if we go to the place like food court. It is for sure that eating out is better when we don''t have enough time to eat and prepare good quality of food. Eating at home can be very time consuming work to people who are busy at most times. \n\nSecond, another merit if we eat at restaurants is the mood and environment we can enjoy there. Home can be a comfortable place to eat, but a restaurant which has a waterfall and some paintings at walls for example, gives us kinds of pleasure that we are enjoying food around a good landscape. \n\nIn summary, eating out is a convenient and pleasant way to enjoy food. Of course we cannot have food out every day but if conditions are appropriate, wouldn''t it be happy to enjoy new food and new environment? "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(17, 1, '\n" Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? People should read only those books that are about real events, real people, and established facts. Use specific reasons and details to support your opinion."', '"There was an argument regarding to the issue that people should read the books that are about real events, real people, and established facts. Books have usually had writer''s insight. From my perspective, I think that we can read the books that are about a fairy tale or science fiction to develop with a good dream and a desire. Moreover, however historians have written a history, Historians'' opinions have always affected the history. \n   \n\nFirst of all, fairy tales and science fictions have impressed the children. If children read fairy tales, they can easily realize good and evil. Besides, we read open science fictions to develop our hope. When I went to the elementary school, I open red science fiction. I could learn a lot of science common senses because science fictions had generally common senses and have the dream that I want to become a doctor. Fairy tales also teach children good and evil and children know what bad is or what good is.  Fairy tales and science fictions was written by fictions but those help us to have hope. \n   \n\nMoreover, history has  written by historians. History have the fact. However, history have open historian''s subjective view. Each persons can concludes the same historical fact to different opinions. For example, The Korea war have two different opinions. One is that the Korea War helped the country to develop economy because it could start  foreign trade. Another is that the Korea War destroyed Korean economy because most of factories was extremely ruined. Many historians have obviously different thoughts. Thus, however History was written about the fact, The fact isn''t all of contents. \n   \n\nIn conclusion, I don''t agreed to read the books that are about the facts. Fairy tales and science fictions give children dreams and desires. Moreover, histories aren''t composed of all of the facts and we can''t read books that are about the facts. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(18, 1, '\nSome people believe that students should be given one long vacation each year. Others believe that students should have several short vacations throughout the year. Which viewpoint do you agree with?', '" The vacation is the opportunity for students to do something special they cannot experience in school. It is important to determine how long the vacation is more efficient for student to relax enough and prepare the next term and to learn the real life from parents and the real society behind school. I believe that long vacation each year can be more helpful for the student than several short vacations throughout the year. \n\n     First, they can do something sufficiently they cannot do during the school time when they have long vacation like learning sports or traveling. When I was freshman in university, I desired to travel European country with back and went around the country with great satisfaction during 2 months summer vacation. If there were only 1 month vacation, I may have not traveled fully and have regretted the lack of time. \n\n    Second, they can be taught from their parents during vacation, and the home education is as important as the school education. When the students have enough long vacation, they can spend more time with their parents besides their other activity. When I was high school student, I helped my mother’s house choirs and my father’s work during winter vacation for 3 months. Before that time, I thought that I was deserved to be taken care of by my parents. But, though the experience, I felt really how difficult was my parents working, and I realized truly I had to respect my parents. It was through my real experience in home that I recognized sincerely respecting my parents. Eventhough I always learned from the teacher that I had to have regard in high my parents. \n\n    In addition, it is necessary for the students to prepare the next term. If they have only short vacation, they cannot have enough time to learn the real experience which cannot be taught from the school and relax at the same time. During vacation, they have to have the time not only doing something they would like to do but relaxing to prepare the next term. If there is only short vacation, they will be too busy to finish the vacation good and get ready the new school semester. \n\n     In conclusion, I am firmly convinced that the long term vacation is essential each year for the students to try what they would like to do which they cannot do during the term and have the opportunity to be trained at home. In addition, through the long vacation, they can complete the vacation well and plan the next term.       "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(19, 1, '\nPeople recognize a difference between children and adults.What events make a person a adult?', '" A differebce between children and adults is not obious. People who live in each different cultures have various events, such as having ''Maturity celebrate day'', tatooing, that become adults. It is considerd that high school graduation and performing liavility for military service are essentiol in Korea. \n       \n      Children have to be admited by a law for becorming a adult. High school graduation means that a child become a adult by legal difinition. Child cann''t buy tabacco and alcohol drink. If he commit a crime, it is parent''s responsibilty. While, if he is adult, he can buy tabacco and alcohol. And when he commit a crime, he will go to prison by a law. Although a person cann''t mentally mature well, he is considered a adult by a law after high school graduation . \n\n      Performing liability for military service is another event made a person a adult. Korea men that are twenty years old have to perform liability for military service for two years old beacuse Korea is divided country. They have to endure a yearning by living in others place from their family, friend and lover. Also They learn a patience by enduring a harsh weather. Those processes mentallly make a person a adult. So people consider that perfoming liability for militery service is big evets which is made a person a adult. \n\n      It isn''t easy to deside a difference between children and adults. However, every country  have various ceremonies and events that make a person a adult. I believe that high school graduation and performing liavility for military service are essentiol  to allow a adult in Korea."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(20, 1, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? A person''s childhood years (the time from birth to twelve years of age) are the most important years of a person''s life. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"   Almost people don''t remember their childhood years; what they did, what they thought, and what happened. They were too young to remember everything. When we forgot the old memories, the only way to find out what happened before is to ask to our parents and our acquaintances who have known us since we were so young. our old memories are fading away even right now. Then, do the childhood years mean nothing? Absolutley not. \n\n        Firstly, the period that we got socialized is our childhood year. It means important. We learn the customs of the community which we belong to. That is, we learn who we are, what we have to, and what our society is. From learning things like this, we get a position of our society. And then, we can play our roles in the society. Through interaction with other people in the society, each of  us makes personality. It a part of the concept of socializaion. All these things happen in our childhood years. \n\n        Secondly, we get some tools needed for social activities. One of the most important thing is language. we have at least one language that is used our society, And, we speak our mother tongue. The era that we learn the language is also our childhood year. Moreover, we learn basic knowledge concerned science and mathematics in the elementary school, which is needed for the study and research that we are going to do. So, we have to take some tools like language and basic knowledge for our future. Unintentionally, and naturally, we learn those things in our childhood years. \n\n        Conclusively, if some person has bad time in the childhood years, his all life would be unhappy. It may not true, but he has more chance to be unhappy than normal people. It is because that something wrong in childhood years can influence to his life; bad socializazion or lack of knowledge. In short, childhood years can determine the whole life. So, the most important years of a person''s life are the childhood years. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(21, 1, '\n Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? Parents are the best teachers. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '" There are a wide range of controversies about this statement that parents are the best teacher. Some people think that parents are the best teacher because they give their children many wisdoms of living which they experienced, and they well know their children any other in the world. Others say that parents do not become the best teacher for their children because they really love their children so they can not realize their mistakes, and they are not expert in all fields. However, I disagree that parents are the best teacher. \n\n  First, parents do not point out their children’s mistakes because they have love and attachment for them. They do not see their children with objective views, so they find their children’s mistakes as well as correct their faults. When I ate with my family, children run around the restaurant and made a noise as if it is their house. Although the children’s behaviors had bad influences on other people, their parents do not scold them and angry to people who scold their children. \n\n  Second, parents are not the best teacher because their knowledge does not cover all fields. Although they have various experiences and wisdom for living, they lack expert knowledge on diverse areas such as art, science, and history. Therefore, they could give their children an erroneous knowledge or information, so it may have negative effects on them. If your children ask you what you do not know, you can not give them the right answer. Consequently, your children are disappointed with you, and you might lose your authority as parents. \n\n  In conclusion, it is fact that parents play an important role in their children’s life. However, they are related their children so closely that they overlook their mistakes or faults. Although parents give us much love and consideration, I disagree with this statement for the reasons I have mentioned above.     "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(22, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? People should read only those books that are about real events, real people, and established facts."', '"There is a saying that ""There are two sides in each question"". This reflect that it can be correct whether reading books that based on real event or reading fiction. Some people think that reading real event is better to develop knowledge, while others say that reading fiction is better. From my point of view, reading a fiction is better in terms of inventiveness and fun. \n\nTo begin with, fictions enable people to enjoy a book. For instance, most children do not like read a book Especially children who are in educational growing level. However, cartoon or fiction is diffent matter. A number of studies indicated that children do not want to read history. This reflect that children are like to read fiction. Authors can write their utopia to book. Thus, many people enjoy reading fiction. In this manner, people read a fiction or cartoon. \n\nIn addition, fictions allow people to grow up imagenation. According to the survey conducted by ministrey of Infant Education in Korea more than 70percent of parents and children replied that fiction is better than book which is based on reality such as history. For example, fictions are composed of many lively description. It can help people building up good creativity. Also, fictions stimulate people to invent a number of worlds that anyone has never thought. Furthermore, cartoon, not based on real event, is one of the great sources of creativities. Children read even cartoon, their ability is gradually growing up. In this regard, people should read a book that is not based on reality. \n\nAll in all, given the opportunity to choose between read a real and read a surreal, I would choose a surreal because fictions not only offer people fun but also develop creativity. We should keep in mind that what is more benefit for you."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(23, 1, '\n"People do many different things to stay healthy. What do you do for good health? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.\n\n"', '" I think that health means not only physical health, but also mental health.  Thus, if we maintain our healthful condition, we should carefully concern both conditions in our life.  There are many kinds of activities to maintain both our mental health and physical health.  However, in my case, be in my case, I mainly prefer to exercise in inline-skating and jogging for keeping my physical health, and prefer to listen to music and watch movies for keeping my mental health. \n\n        To begin with, I mainly practice inline-skating and jogging for an hour every day. Both activities are good choice for maintaining my health, and they are also inexpensive sports.  If you decide to enjoy inline-skate or jogging, you should buy some equipment such as inline boots, repairing tools, body-protectors, and a helmet for inline-sports, or jogging shoes for jogging. It would require some money to buy these things. However, when you buy these equipments, you don''t need to spend any more equipment.  For example, a golf club membership in Korea is very expensive. Average prices of the golf club membership are at least eight millions won, so most people in Korea who already have basic golf equipments could not play golf. Of course, the basic golf equipments in Korea are also more expensive than any other country. However, inline-skating and jogging are not expensive sports in Korea. It is also fun and you don''t have to pay extra money for skating or jogging. Moreover, both activities are very good for our health. Many doctors say that both sports are good for strengthening respiratory organs and heart, and both also good for improving muscle system of our body. \n\n        In addition, to relieve mental stress, I prefer to listen to music and watch movies. I am one of the jazz fans and movie fans. When I am stressful, I often go to the movie, or borrow some DVD from DVD store around my home, or listen to jazz music. When I hear jazz music or watch movies, I can relieve my stress and feel comfortable. Actually, I believe that most people do same act like me, because when people listen to merry music or movies, they can alleviate their bad feelings. Moreover, most doctors and psychologists agree that the effects of music and movies can help alleviate one''s stress and even cure some serious mental disease such as manic-depressive psychosis, and melancholia. \n\n        In brief, No one may deny that importance of maintaining physical and mental health is essential for our life, and I believe that Inline skating, jogging, enjoying music and movies are best choices to maintain my life in best way. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(24, 1, '\nSome people prefer to spend time with one or two close friends. Others choose to spend time with large number of friends. Compare the advantages of each choice. Which of these two ways of spending time do you prefer? Use specific reasons to support your answer.', '"When we spend time with large number of friends, we get the chance to meet various kinds of people. This ables us to train social skill to easily adapt ourselves to different culture or taste. Also, gathering involving many people have a exciting atmosphere that can''t be found in groups of small number of people. But I prefer to spend time with one or two close friends for the following reasons. \n\n  Firstly, spending time with small number of friends provides the comfort and intimacy that gathering of many people might lack. We often feel distressed from the overloaded work and become annoyed with so many people making noises in the restaurant. The comfort and intimacy we get from the gatherings of small number of people might relax our fatigue. \n\n  Secondly, during the time spending with one or two close friends, we can talk about serious matters and share useful information. Such serious problems seem hard to be shared among large number of people. Talking about problems with one or two close friends might be a good way to release the pressure of the problems. We might even realize the key to the next step of solving the problem. \n\n  Although there are a lot of advantages in spending time with many friends, I think the advantages of meeting one or two close friends overweigh them. And that is why I prefer to spend time with small number of friends. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(25, 1, '\n Is the ability to read and write more important today than in the past? Why or why not?', '"Recently, our society is getting more and more complex and developed. There are so many attractive matters that we can see, hear and feel that it is easy for us to believe that reading and writing are not important as ever before. However, as far as I know, reading and writing are basic and fundamental tools for expressing oneself and understanding others because they help us arrange one''s thought. In addition, as before, the most important way to give others information is not TV show or radio talk show, but reading materials such as journal or books. Thus, I think reading and writing are more important, and here are some reasons for my decision. \n\nFirst, it is usually helpful for us to write down what we think or imagine. This is because we can not wirte about something without considering and re-arranging one''s idea. For example, every time I prepare test, without re-arranging class note, I could not make a good resualt. It seems that while I try to write down what I read form my class note, text book or some kind of material, the process of writing helps me establish heirachy of knowledge, which make it easy for me to memorize or understand information. \n\nSecond, although seeing, hearing and feeling are important tools of understanding complex and huge amount of information, reading and writng are also important to transper one''s knowledge or thought to others. This is because such media as TV, radio and movie can not be easily and deeply understood because we can not memorize or understand them relativly short period time. We can read or write until we fully understand or express. However, due to its speed and duration, it is hard for us to concentrate on that matter. \n\nIn sum, althogh traditional way of understanding and expressing, reading and writing, seems somewhat outdated, they are fundamental and crucial tools of interacting with others. Think of the world without no chance to read or write. How can you express or understand your own or others'' knowledge, information, feeling and so forth?   "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(26, 1, '\n"Smoking should not be permitted in restaurants, and laws that prohibit it should be upheld. "', '"Smoking in restaurants is a selfish and disrespectful action for other people who came to the restaurant to enjoy their meal. There must be some people who dislike the smell of smoking so much that they can not have a meal with the smell of smoking. Also, it would disturb the people, who are trying to quit smoking. \n\nMoreover, as we all know, smoking affects second hand smokers in more harmful way than those who actually smokes. Because the restaurant is a place to enjoy a healthy meal, they are expected to be the places in a cleaner and better condition. It is obvious that no one likes to have a meal with the full of smoking. \n\nAs a matter of fact, it is also very harmful and unhealthy for the smokers to eat their meal while they are smoking. By restricting the laws that prohibit people to smoke in the public area, the government or state leister can expect a less number of people who smokes, to keep a society and citizens away from bad influences and effects and also to help smokers quit smoking more conveniently. \n\nNot only a restaurant, but also other public buildings should not allow people smoking, and more importantly, smokers should realize that their actions of smoking where other people are, is irresponsible therefore should feel ashamed and guilty. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(27, 1, '\nIt is better for children to grow up in the countryside than in a big city. Do you agree or disagree? Use specific reasons and examples to develop your essay.', '"I agree that it is good for children to grow up in the countryside that give many good points. Although people know that the nature is the best textbook for children, they cannot give it to them for many reasons. The good points which can could gain from raising children in the countryside are the life in the natural which give a rest and a health, the friends who have a intimate friendship, and the best educational experiences which can not imagine in the city. \n\nThe children in the city are dependent and weak even in mental. However, the children in the countryside are independent in whatever they do and strong in not only physical but also mental. While the children in the city are surrounded by bad air, various accidents in daily life and many dangerous things, the children in the countryside can have a nice day with a fresh air, a beautiful natural and a peaceful mind. \n\nThe friendship in the city’s children is changeable and beatable by trivial reasons. For the children in the city can have many various friends as like videogame which can be exchanged when they disgust it, they could not make a real and deep relationship with their friends. In the countryside, for the children have not sufficient toys as city’s children, they have to have perseverance and a faith to make a friend. The friendship which be formed by this course is strong and would be sustained for a long time. \n\nWhile the children in the city have knowledge which learn from a textbook or an Internet, the children in the countryside can have knowledge from a real experience, which cannot do, in the city. The city’s children have only fast and useless knowledge, however the countryside’s children can have a live and real knowledge by their experience with the natural and self-stimulation. \n\nIn conclusion, Although I have a difficulty in making a decision to raise children in the countryside for job and relationships with colleagues who I have known for long time, if I have a chance and make up a mind resolutely, many good things would be returns for children and also me; the children could obtain a health, an intimate friendship and a best educational environment in the countryside. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(28, 1, '\nYour school has enough money to purchase either computers for students or books for the library. Which should your school choose to buy computers or books?  Use specific reasons and examples to support your recommendation.', '"  I think that both to buy books and computers have some advantages and disadvantages. If my school has a plan to buy something for the school library between books and computers, I would suggest to buy computers for the library, because computers are effective and convenient equipments for most students in terms of accessing up-to-date information, processing information quickly, and utilizing many kinds of school works. \n\n        First of all, students who work with computers can access up-to-date information. For example, our university library already has a wide variety of books, but most books only contain out-of-date information. Thus, students without computers hardly catch up with up-to-date technologies. Of course, students can ask a librarian to apply some books, which students need, but the process is mostly complex and time-consuming. However, if students can use a computer, these inconvenient things would be solved by computers, because students using computers can easily connect a school network system and Internet, and they can easily find information, which they need. \n\n        Secondly, students who work with computers can process much information in real time. For instance, if you want to find some books without computers in the library, you would spend a lot of time to find an index card, and to know that the book is still there or lended.  Maybe to find a book would take at least ten minutes without help of the computer. However, if you use a computer, you can direct search the book that you need, and you can get the book in no time. Of course, if you use Internet, you can also find a wide variety of information such as research papers, latest articles, and news in no time. Thus, students with computers can access information more quickly than students without computers. \n\n        Lastly, computers can be used in a wide variety of school works. For example, now, nowadays students use computers for research and word processing needs. Some teachers use computers for providing their course homework and information.  Moreover, many universities in Korea require students to learn computer, because the process of application of the course are completely computerized. My university also has computerized enrolling system. If the university buys many computers, students who don’t have a computer would be easily enrolled in the course, which they want. \n\n        In conclusions, I strongly believe that computers would be best choice to greatly improve the environment of the library. Even though books are simple to read, and they do not need such knowledge of the computer, I am sure that quickness-ability, access-ability, and wide application-ability of the computer are more valuable than books. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(29, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? People should read only those books that are about real events, real people, and established facts. Use specific reasons and details to support your opinion. \n   "', '"It is needless to say that most books are written by those who have their own respective thoughts and want to have the books to be read by many other people. Simultaneously, the contents of the books should be different to each other. I am for sure it is good to have plenty of thoughts and philosophies in the world so that we can share them. Therefore, I am for the statement that people need to read both fiction and non-fiction for a couple of reasons. It will be viewed from following two aspects. \n\n  Firstly, one of the critical reasons why people should read both books about real events and unreal events is that we can learn to know what other people are thinking by reading the both kinds of books. The thoughts of other people could be about real phenomena or creative ideas. For example, had it not been for the novel of Aldous L. Huxley, Brave New World, we couldn''t even have a chance to imagine how tragic the world would be if the science technology had been developed without conscience. Thanks to the very creative fiction, people in 1932 could be inspired to think about the future. I don''t think any other facts in the book can do better to do it than the novel. To sum, people had better have access to other people''s creation by reading various kinds of books not just by reading non-fiction. \n\n  Secondly, the creative thoughts of children should be boosted by a lot of great fiction. We all know that children have much curiosity and try to meet their needs by reading, watching and tasting and so on. I think novels, such as science fiction and fables are very much adequate to satisfy kids. My brother, who majors in shipbuilding technology at the moment, dreamed about becoming a good scientist when he was very young with reading various kinds of scientific novels. I think this could be a good example how much children are affected by creative works of good authors. The creative thoughts of children should not be eroded; instead, it has to be enhanced by good fiction. \n\n  In conclusion, people have to read fiction as well as established facts because all people want to and have right to share ideas with other great contemporary thinkers and writers. Futhermore, vast imaginary stuff in fiction can develope creativeness of children. That we have many a good novels, which stimulates our imagination, is very adorable in this mechanical and highly standardized society. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(30, 1, '\nMany people visit museums when they travel to new places. Why do you think people visit museums?', '"When you travel to new place, where is the first place that you want to visit? Answer to this question depend on the characteristics of site. If you are in the area that is famous for beautiful beach, your first trip is possibly the beach. Then, what could be your first stop, if there is no such famous place that attracts you? In my case, generally I take museum as the first stop for my visit because I can understand that area easily, fast and effectively. In addition, museum gives me unforgettable memories. \n\nFirst, the most fast and easy way to understand a certain area is to visit museum. We can learn brief history of that area by seeing historical stuff displayed at the museum. What''s more, we can find out how that area''s economic and cultural status is. In most case, if a certain local government is not in good cultural or economic state, the government tend not to invest on such faculties such as museum. It is because, to them, there are many things they have to invest first. On the contrary, if the local government and that area is flourishing, it is clear that they cherish their historical stuff. \n\nIn addition, we can make some memories about certain place by visiting museum. We can see valuable historical remains that can not be seen at the other area. Furthermore, considering that museum plays an important role of being landmark of the area, we can experience fantastic building and landscape. For example, when I visit "" the Louvre"", what makes me exciting is not only its stuff, but also its building including glass pyramid. If I toured the city without visiting that museum, half of my memories could be lost in my mind. \n\nIn sum, although visiting museum might seem to be somewhat boring, it is quite a useful way of understanding certain area. Museum is abstract of the area''s history, culture and life. Without visiting local museum, how can you say that you visit and learn lots of things on that area? \n\n"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(31, 1, '\nEnglish as an official language.', '"Korea achieved brilliant success last 30 years. This miracle was come from perspiration of all people in Korea, especially the laborer who worked at the factory paying low-wage and poor environment. As economy grows rapidly, people concern about whether Korea can become more affluent or not. In Korea’s circumstance where natural resources are limited, talented people need to be trained. With part of that worries, some people urge to use English as an official language. It is inevitable to Korea to survive from globalization which accelerates competitiveness among the nations. How ever, in my opinion, finding our national characteristics is more important than following advanced nations recklessly. \n\nOne of the biggest concerns is that we could lose our emotion of nation. We have more than 2,000 years of history and always proud of our nation. In 2002 World Cup, for instance, Korea showed intensive nationalism throughout the world. We all dressed red shirts and proud of what we made. Another example of our self-esteem is ‘Han-Gul’ which is Korea’s official language. Han-Gul is the perfect language that expresses every human feelings in words and also write every language that people use all over the world. It is a creditable invention that the world language experts acclaimed it. \n\nIn addition, imagine of how impractical of using English in Korea society. How do you going to write Korean’s peculiar thinking? As an example of Korean novel, there are good novels in Korea which could not award novel prize at literature, because Han-Gul could not interpret properly. \n\nIn conclusion, Using English as an official language does not mean fostering national competitiveness. Korea government should devise other alternatives that increase national benefits such as improving educational surroundings or lessening restrict policy to companies so that they can help domestic consumption. Also, People should conserve their cultures and prepare for the globalization. If not, we could be a cultural colony of other advanced nations. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(32, 1, '\nSome people prefer to eat at food stands or restaurants.  Other people prefer to prepare and eat food at home. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"As many people are becoming busy with their jobs,hobbies, they tend to go out and eat food from restaurants or fast-food store. They like those place because thay can save time and don''t have to worry making food. Despite opposition from many, I prefer to eat food at home. \n\nFirst of all, I am able to save a lot of money. Because I''m student, I am not able to afford food price at restaurants 30 days a month and 12 months a year. It was  always my parents who gave a pocket money to me. I realized that the older we are , the more difficult we get a money from parents. Even if I have money to go chow hall, I have tried to keep the money in bank for my future. When we eat food at home, It’s possible to store food that we left. It’s a common sense that most of restaurants have dumped the food away right after customers set off from restaurants. It not only made environmental problems, but also raised the food price. I saw one article in newspaper that government and private companies spent two billion won to recover the environment. I also want to mention about tip culture. It’s recommended to leave 10~15% of your whole food price on the desk, when you leave the restaurant. If the waiter impressively served to you, you would like to leave more money than regular tips. \n\n  Secondly, eating at home is more safe than restaurant, or food stall. Generally speaking, most restaurants more interest money than any other things. One broadcaster reported the news that most of the fast-food store’s sanitations are terrible. Part time job members usually didn’t  wash their hands when they start working and didn’t use a plastic glove.  A  worker said that a host just always has pushed him to work quickly and didn’t say anything about safty of making food. As you can see, your mother always tries to make healthy food for family members. Whenever she was about to buy some ingredients, she looked carefully about the expiration and the condition of food not the price of that. As a result, Family members are able to feel mother’s love. \n\nThirdly, family members can share the feeling of membership. We are so busy with our own businesses that we are no longer interested with  the lives of our near and dear ones.  So I think  that the best way to solve this problem is to make a custom about eating at home at least one time a day. I am sure that they will feel the safety and comfort  each other. \n\nAs we have seen above, there are many benefits eating food at home. It’s not only good to your health, but also good to relationship of family members. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(33, 1, '\nIt is sometimes said that borrowing money from a friend can harm or damage friendship. Do you agree? Why or why not? Use specific examples to explain your answer.', '"There is an argument regarding the issue that lending or borrowing money from a friend can damage the friendship. Some people maintain that this behavior don’t affect friendship. However, in my opinion, borrowing money from my friends can affect negatively our friendship because this can damage my friend’s financial statement and might break confidence between friends. \n    First of all, if a person borrow some money from his or her fiend, it can give trouble to the friend because of the financial problem. For example, I am a university student and I earned money by doing part-time job to afford my tuition. In this case, I always have trouble in my financial statement. Two months ago, one of my friends answered me to lend one hundred dollars and I lent the money despite my condition for my friend and consequently I got in financial trouble. Hence, through the experience, I learned that borrowing money from a friend can damage the friendship. \n    Moreover, borrowing money can attack the confidence between friends. If a friend who borrowed some money don’t pay back the money, people might think that the friend doesn’t consider them. According to the research done by the Seoul National University in Korea, people feel sorry when their friends don’t do thoughtfully. To make the matter worse, once the truth is broken between friends, the relation can’t maintain as before. After all, friends break up the relationship each other. Therefore, I think that borrowing money can harm the relationship between friends.   \n     In conclusion, I agree the statement that borrowing money from a friend can affect negatively friendship. This is because of the reasons mentioned above that borrowing can affect directly the financial statement of a friend and might reduce the belief between friends. We should make an effort not to borrow money from friends to keep the friendship.   "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(34, 1, '\nSome people believe that students should be given one long vacation each year. Others believe that students should have several short vacations throughout the year. Which viewpoint do you agree with?', '"A vacation is time to rechage life of students. During a vacation, Students can do something that cann''t do in a semester, shch as supplementing a subjet and preparing the next semester and having a rest time. Students need one long vacatoin to perform these things. But several short vacations are too short to do them. It is important for students  to have a vacation as rechaging time. so, I think that students should be given one long vacation each year. \n\n      There are no one that undstand perpactly all the subjects in semester. So, students that have a vacation supplement their depiciency of a subject in a semester. It also means that students prepare next semester. To perform these things, students are reqired many times. If student are given Several short vacations, just they have to supplement a subject and prepare next semester. Students don''t  need only astudying time but also  a enjoying time. \n\n      Students have a right to enjoy their life because they are not studying machine. Students have their times that they can utilize after ending a semester. In this time, they can do many things. For example, some students travel with a friend and some students learn to play the piano that cann''t do in a semester. students that cann''t live with family in semester have a happy time with thier family during a vacation. Students are helped mentall and physic growth throgh these process. If students are given a short vacations, these things are impossible because of too short time. That''s reason why student should be given one long vacation. \n\n     If it is considered only by quantity, both several short vacatoins and one long vacation are same. However,  Several differences Beteen several short vacatoins and one long vacation clearly exist. A vacation is essencial time to rechage life of students. Therefore, I think that students should be given one long vacation each year. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(35, 1, '\n"Holidays honor people or events. If you could create a new holiday, what person or event would it honor and how would you want people to celebrate it? Use specific reasons and details to support your answer. \n\n"', '" Have you ever heard about Taekwondo? I think you have probably heard it before because it is one of the most famous fighting arts and it is selected an offical game of the olympics. In my country, korea, there isn’t a holiday for Taekwondo even though it is very important for us. If I can make a holiday, I really want to choose Taekwondo. And I want to celebrate it with advertising and making a world tournament \n\n     Taekwondo is a fighting game from Korea. It looks similar to Kungfu from China and Karade from Japan. However, it has own arts. Especially it use legs very efficiently and fantastically. So many people fall in love with wonderful skills and it has become one of the famous games all over the world. In the world, there are a lot of branchs of Taekwondo. One of my European friends, from Latvia, he used to be a Taekwondo player. He had trained it for 7 years so his body was great. In korean opinion, how proud it is. I have never thought many of the world people love it. Even it is now a famous game in Olympics. There are many fighting games but just Taekwondo and Boxing are selected as official games in Olympics. In these point, we korean feel proud about it. It is important for us, neverthless, in korea there isn’t a holiday for it. So I need to make a holiday for it. \n\n   If  I made a holiday for it, I should make events for it. How to? I think it has become a famous game all over the world. So I would make a world tournament. Of course there is other worlds tournaments like olympics but I want different kind of competition. First, I need to advertise it. In my country sometimes something weird events have happened. They were very important but the administrator of the events didn’t prepare for the events and didn’t advertise very well. Eventually the events caused anger from people. I have seen many times like it. So I would try to advertise efficiently for it such as TV commercials. \n\n    If  I can make a holiday for something, as I said I would make Taekwondo day for my country and korean. Because we korean feel proud from it. However we don’t have a holiday for it. So I think It is actually needed thesedays for Korea. To celebrate, I would make a world tournament. How great it is, it is for korean but also it can be a celebration all over the world’s people. \n\n"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(36, 1, '\nWhat are some of the qualities of a good parent? Use specific details and examples to explain.', '" These days there are a lot of education systems. They teach how to teach their children and to educate them to make smart. However, it is pretty hard to find about some materials which explain about being a good parent. So I wanted to say what some of the quialities of a good parent are. I think good parents have to show their passion about what they are doing, generosity and they have not to make an unhappy family. Let me tell you specifically about them. \n\n     One of the features of the good parent is that they show that they are doing their best whatever they do. It is really important. From a baby to adult, children see his parents during his life. As growing, children are realizing what they should do from their environment. One of the most important things which effect them is of course his father and mother. If his father shows that his best and passion about something. It will effect his sons and daughters as good advantages. \n\n    Another point I think is that usually good parents are very generous. If father shows mercy for the poor, children will learn how to mercy someone. If he shows just his passion about something, his sons and daughters will learn just a passion from his father and mother not generosity. It means it is possible children will be selfish. \n\n    The last point I think is that the good parents don’t make unhappy for their family. Economical capablity is also important and their personality is also important. However, I think the most important thing is that good parent make their family very happy. Some good parents never fight in front of children. It is sure that they are trying to make a happy family. Usually a guy who does criminal is from an unhappy family. When parents fight each other, statistics shows children suffer a lot of stress. It makes them to go out of the houses. \n\n     To be a good parent, they should make happy family. To be a good parent, they have to show their passion to their children. Itself will be a good education. To be a good parent, they should teach what generosity is to prevent their children from being selfish. What are more important? I think that these are the most important things to be a good parent. I don’t mean there aren’t other important things. But I believe when a good parent shows these for their children,  their children will grow happily and learn how to live will in a society. \n\n"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(37, 1, '\nSome students prefer to study alone. Others prefer to study with a group of students. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your anwer.', '"  This topic has been pretty contraversial. Many students have insisted on studying alone is better but others have affirmed conversly. Which opinion is right or better for us? Maybe it depends on student’s style. However, for most students, I recommend them to study with a group. Thesedays I have studying alone. I, however, feel that I can study more efficiently. How? I think if I study with a group, I could tell what my problem is so I could think logically. I could enjoy studying. And I could study efficiently? How and why? Let me tell you my opinion. \n\n      As you might know, now I am studying TOEFL and preparing for some tests. These test are not easy and I sometimes feel embarassed because of hard questions which require highly logical thinking. For example, at reading parts on TOEFL, I usually have some problems on inferrence questions. Sometimes I can’t solve and understand even if I see the answers. What do you think of my problem? I think this problem is caused by a lack of logical thinking. I have thought if I have a group studying with me, we could make discussing and tell what our problems are. I believe we can make better logical ability by great discussing. \n\n     Who does love study and want to study? Actually there aren’t students like that. Sometimes we could feel that a part of study is very interesting. However, It usually can’t last for a long time. I think when we study alone, we could feel very bored. Sometimes we need to discuss and ask someone about hard questions. When we meet hard questions which we can’t solve by ourselves, we feel bored and frustrated. At this time we lost our interests for studying. Sometimes we need a rival and want to enjoy a competition. Like that, we can match with my friends in the group. It would be good reason to study for bored students. \n\n     There is another reason I prefer to study with a group. This makes studies very efficiently. How did we do? We made penaltys. What kinds of penaltys? Let me tell you. When I studied with my friends, we made a penalty like paying money when we couldn’t memorize vocaburaries for homework. It was not big money. However, for us, it was big deal even if the money was not expensive. So we  could study them very hard and eventually memorize a whole vocaburary book. How useful it is! In this point, if there is spontaneous penalty, it would make our study more efficiently. \n\n     If we can make better logical thinking, if we can prevent to study from boring, and if we can make study very efficiently by a penalty, then we could study very interestingly and hard. History and statistics have shown appropriately strict rules and competitions make our ability for something better. As I told you, these reasons I think are significantly good ways to study if we can. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(38, 1, '\nSome students prefer to study alone. Others prefer to study with a group of students. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your anwer.', '" To study effectively, some students prefer to study alone, and others prefer to study with a group of students, If I have a chance to choose between studying alone and studying with friends, I would choose a group study, because later has more advantages than studying alone. \n\n        To begin with, a group study can help students improve effectiveness in the study.  For example, when you study alone, it would be very hard to collect many kinds of research materials in short time by him or her. However, if you study with a group of students, the group member can split and share their school-assignments and research materials.  Thus, each member of the group can save his or her time to finish homework, and can get much information in short time. Moreover, many students can get their research from different sources such as newspapers, Internet, and books, so they can get also a wide variety of information in no time. \n\n        In addition, students who joined a group study can improve his or her social skills such as interpersonal relationship, intercommunication, and friendship. For instance, students who study with friends can learn responsibility by taking a position in the study group, so the student can develop a sense of responsibility. Moreover, they can learn how to organize the study team, the way to study, and study time. If a student only prefers to study alone, he or she can’t get a chance to learn social skills and improve intercommunication abilities. \n\n        For these reasons, I prefer to study with a group of students. Group study can give students many opportunities as I mentioned above. Students who do group study can learn social skills and can work efficiently. Of course, studying alone would be a good choice for some students who are very shy or don’t want to be interrupted by other students. However, in my case, a group study is best choice for me. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(39, 1, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? parents are the best teachers. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"People has regarding the issue that parents are the best teachers. some people think that parents doesn''t offer children good education. while, others have opposite opinion. I believe that children are learned by their parents who are best teacher for children because parents not only know their children but also  lead them very well. \n     \n    First of all, parents allow their children to find their talent or interest .In general, children have spent a lot of time with their parent from the day of birth. as parents live with their children together for a long time, they can look for everything about their children as well as this can take full advantage of  children''s ability. for example. I''ll take personal experience. during my high school years, when I was wondering  about my future, my parent were good assistant since they give me information that I don''t know yet such as my interest, appeals, talent and so on. as a result, I could easier make a plan than others of the same age. this shows that parents helps their children to recognize themselves. \n\n   Second, because of unconditional love, children can follow their parents willingly. generally speaking, children not only spend most time with their parents but also they are related by blood with each other. thus both parents and children become having belief. It is certain that children depend on their parents. for good education, between teachers and students should be based on these relationship. in other words these relationship offer them lots of care and love. parents can lead easily their children. \n\n   In sum, I know that the best teachers are parents because parents know their children. in addition, they can easier guide than others. it is necessary to be a good teacher. for better education, teachers should know that students need continuous concern and love. \n\n"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(40, 1, '\nSome people believe that students should be given one long vacation each year. Others believe that students should have several short vacations throughout the year. Which viewpoint do you agree with?', '" What would you do during vacation if you were to come back to school days? People have different ideas depending on their situations. I believe that one long vacation, not several short vacations, should be given to students because one long vacation can give time to build up work experience, time to travel and time to study their subjects. \n\n    First, students can have an opportunity to work as an intern during long vacations. By doing so, they can apply what they learn at school to a real working situation. If you are majoring in advertising, then you can work at advertising firm, such as LG Ad (well-known advertising company in Korea), as a creative designer, and really involve in making advertisements. I also had worked as an intern at a consulting firm during my vacation in my junior year and it was really a great time. \n\n    Secondly, one long vacation is good for students to travel around to the places they want to know more. As you may know, when you work with a company, you cannot have your time for a travel. In Korea, workers can take a trip for 7 days to at most 10 days in a consecutive. On the contrary, students can make the best use of their vacation to visit cities abroad. If you are interested in making movies, I strongly recommend you look around MGM studio and Universial studio where you can find how the movies are made.  During my freshman, I had a good chance to go to America. At that time, I visited the Ivy League School, for example Harvard University, Yale University and Princetone University and so on. I could see the beautiful campuses and also could talk with students there about their school life. \n\n    Finally, students can review what they learnt during their previous semester and make up for what they missed. In addition, students can work in advance what they want to study and prepare for the next semester. One friend of mine took a summer course to make up for what she failed at a freshman year, and eventually she could raise up her graduate point average to the level she wanted. \n\n     In short, I agree with the statement that one long vacation would be good for students because students can have working experience, visit countries they want and study what they learnt and prepare for the next semester during that time. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(41, 1, '\n"In some countries teenagers have jobs while they are still students. Do you think this is a good idea? Support your opinion  using specific reasons and details. \n\n"', '"Many people say that having jobswhile they are still students are not good for disturbing the study. However, l think that having a job while they are still teenager is a good ideat that have many advantage. There are several reasons to support my opinion. \n\nFirstly, as having a jobs during teenegers, they can catch the thing what is really they adapted. Almost people who are just learn their study in school tend to can''t find eaily what kind of job is the most adatped to them after graduate school. However, people have an experience like having a job in teenager, he or she can know about their temperament. For example, whether they like to follow the commend of boss or not. In addition, they may catch what kind of work they like. For instance, when a boy work in fast-food during teenager, he know about whether he likes and is good at selling articles.\n   \nSedondly, having a job teenegers in still students is a good idea because they can have an experience before they got a fail in real society after graduate a school. When a teenager who want to get a whose food-market, he or she get a job relative with food-market when they are teenager. As having that kind of a job when he or she duing still student, he or she can learn many knowledge such as the most important things or threaten things before the person manage own the food-market. \n     \nThirdly, having a job teenagers in still stuednt is a good idea because they can apply the knowledge that was learnd in the class to real situation. For instance, a curious teenager is taughted about the supply and demend in an economy class. While he or she have a job that can get a item from a firm and sell to people, he or she can know certainly what is the real supply and demend. \n\nIn sum, having a job when they are teenagers is good idea because they can have not only an opportunity to find what is their fiber, but also an experience apply their knowledge that are taughted in class to real circumstance. In addition, they can have an pre-exercise that can reduce the possibility to fail rather than they are graduate their school."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(42, 1, '\n"Some students prefer to study alone. Others prefer to study with a group of students. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer. \n   "', '"There are many ways that we can study. It is very important how to study. some people say that students should study alone with high concentration. However, from my point of view, studying in a group of students is better in terms of saving time and sharing imformation.  \n\n   To begin with, not all students solve problems. That is to say, every student has a advantage and a disadvantage in study skill. Hence, studying in a group enable students to save of time by effective ways. For my experience, I study TOFLE in a group which is 8 members together. Due to I have a more ability in listening comprehention than others, I can teach other members. In contrast I can learn part of others. We able to save many times because We only catch our unknown problems. We need not to consider unsolved problems. in this regard, group studying help us saving of time. \n\n    Moreover, group studying allow students to feel interesting. in other words alone studying is very boring and have a loosing mind. For instance, our study group have a pop quiz every mornig. pop quiz enable us to study hard. also it give us some of belonging. hence we can more good results. also as we debate a difficult problems with our diverse opinion. In this regard, study group is necessary with effective studying. \n\nIn short, I firmly believe that students should study organization making in a study group. this is because studying all together is effective ways in terms of saving time and interesting studying."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(43, 1, '\n"Many people have a close relationship with their pets. These people treat their birds, cats, or other animals as members of their family. In your opinion, are such relationships good? Why or why not? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer. "', '" Since ancient times, many people had close relationships with their pets such as birds, cats, and dogs. Thus, I agree that to have close relationships with their pets are good for both people and animals, because such relationships contain some advantages. \n\n        To begin with, close relationships with their pets can help some people having serious mental disease to alleviate it, because when they spend their time with their pets, they can feel more comfort than before. For these effects, most psychologists suggest their patients to raise pets, because raising pets can slow disease rate, alleviate bad mood-condition, and even cure disease. For example, I have a grandmother who had a serious breast cancer. Two years ago, she had a big surgical operation, and finally, she can remove cancer from her breast. However, after a medical operation, she got a serious pain. She wanted to relieve pain, so she used many kinds of medicine, but there were no way to alleviate her pain by medicine. However finally she overcame a pain, because she decided to raise dogs. After having a close relationship with her dogs, she can forget her pain and concentrate her interest of her pets. \nNowadays, my grandmother sometimes feels pain, but now she feels better than before. \n\n        In addition, close relationship with their pets can prevent loneliness. For example nowadays many people live alone, and most people want to seek a way to forget loneliness. For these reasons, some people spend their time to meet other people, or more concentrate their jobs. However, the most popular way to overcome loneliness is buying a pet such as a dog and cat. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(44, 1, '\nTeachers should not make their social or political views known to students in the classroom.', '"At the same time as the advancement of the society, the argument as to the scope of a right for teachers to express their political viewpoints in classroom has taken place. Regarding this, some people are advocating that teacher is able to show their opinion on political issues during classes. However, I am of the strong belief that the opposite is right due to its power to distort the class and the student''s susceptibilty  to the teacher.\n \nThe first reason which is exceptionally evident is that political view in class could distort the contents of the academic subjects such as ethics, history, and so on. To be specific, if the teacher gives a lecture about some social issues or literatures adding his or her own political meaning, the students are likely to accept academics in a biased position. From my persnoal experience, my history teacher in high school usually taught us a few important historic events from the progressive viewpoints. Because of this, we used to think that our society should be drastically changed in most fields without rational reasons. In this regard, teaching with political stances would have a negative impact on the growth of the youth''s mind.\n \nAnother equally important reason is that the student is very susceptible to teacher''s thoughts. To elaborate, the students who are not mature enough to judge social or political phenomenon tend to follow teacher''s opinion blindly, which can be an obstacle to the development of democracy in our state. According to a study conducted on the politics of adult by the Korea University, it has been reported that nearly 55% of the adults who are now a member of political parties responded that their politics have been significantly influenced by the teacher''s political view in classes. As can be seen, it is obvious that teacher''s social or political thoughts could affect students.\n \nTo wap it up, admittedly teachers have the rights to hold and mention their opinion on social or political things. However, looking at all statements above, if in the classroom, it is undeniable that its negative effects outweigh the favorable outcome of it."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(45, 1, '\n"“In difficult situation, the teacher who give me hope and dream”"', '"When I was the third grade of high school, I got an extra-curricular English teacher. And I worked harder, but it was not able to pick up my English grade.\n \nI failed to get into the college and then I had to repeat college entrance exam. I went to my parents and I said “ Dad! Mom! I will take up the challenge of retaking the entrance examination! ” and then my mom and dad had no say and there was silence in the room. I expected a positive answer. But my parents said that “Young Suk, It is not a good idea, we can’t agree with your opinion. If you would repeat college entrance examination, It is not guaranteed to improve grade for 1 year.“ this answer did not satisfy me.  My parent‘s character is realistic and skeptical. Sometime it hurts me.\n \nAfter I seriously struggled with the matter, I decided to try to repeat college entrance examination through self-teaching myself, despite of the objections of my parents. I told my parent about my plan. My parents did not say anything.  I was to study the reading room near my house. I went there with pack lunches, because I did not have money. I studied alone except for English. I had courage to call my extra-curricular teacher who taught me before and I called. At that instant, the telephone was trembled as my heart. Though the receiver, I said “Teacher ! I am Young Suk. I decided to study for college entrance examination again. But, it is difficult to study English alone . Can you help me? Actually I don’t have any money but If you help me, I will repay for your favor!!”  Centainly it was rude request to teacher. I felt shame and nervous . But I had  little hope.  Surprisingly, the teacher’s response was favorable. Teacher said that “ Are you trying again examination for college entrance? Oh I feel sorry. Okay let try again with me! After 10 minutes, can I meet you at McDonalds on the Academic streets?” I was very surprised and I replied loudly “Yes, I can!!” After a while, I went to McDonald on the Academic streets. Even my teacher arrived faster than me. I opened the door with a heart pounding. I greeted gladly teacher. “Hello! Teacher!!! It is been a long time. Nice to meet you” my teacher was reading the English newspaper and said “ Hi ! Young Suk!! “\n \nWe were going to have one study meeting per week, because he was a postgraduate student at that time. I thanked him a lot. Thanks him, I felt that I could pass the examination right now. After we ended our talking, we walked on the Academic streets. When I walked alone on the Academic streets, I always felt lonely. However, today, thanks to the teacher walking with me, I felt better and more confident than ever before.\n \n The teacher always taught me English thoroughly and efficiently. And when I asked something about English he always taught kindly like an older brother. Once, I could not remember a certain word exactly. I tried remembering the word exactly. However, I was not able to remember the word. Eventually, I sent the clues about the word the teacher. And then after a while, he sent the exact word. The teacher was so nice to me. I appreciated a lot of the teacher and I decided that “I will repay for his kindness and I should be the man like him”\n \nHe majored in Economics at the University. When he had to decide, he always thought rationally. When he bought products, after comparing product’s price and function thoroughly, he decided to buy. Once, we went to market to buy Coke. After he compared bottle Coke’s price, quantity and can Coke’s price, quantity, he said “Both price were same.” And then he picked up the can Coke. I was wondering and I asked “Many people like the bottle Coke. But why do you choose the can Coke?” And he replied “Both Coke’s price is same. The bottle Coke easily exit the bubble, while the can Coke do not get out of the bubble easily. And he said “Many people buy products without price comparison. Young Suk, when you buy a product, it is not wise to buy without price comparison. It is the theory of the price comparison in Economics.” After that, when he purchased products, he liked mathematical calculations. He was so nice to me and he was very rational person\n \nHe sometime taught me the theory of Economics and introduce that Economics is how useful in everyday life. He looked like so smart through my eyes. At that moment, I thought that “I should be the man who is smart and kind like my teacher. And I will major in Economics!“ and As I told him that I will major in Economics, he really was pleased and encouraged me “ Young Suk, I am sure that You will be the best Economics student !” He always encouraged me.    \n \nOur class was continued in September. Although from September to November, I had to study alone, I did not feel lonely or fear. Instead of that, I felt confident. In November, I applied for the Korea SAT. And then I received my report card. At the instant, I could not stop talkin. My grade was improved especially in English! I decided to apply for Economics at University. My parents seriously worried that about my applying because It was difficult to admission to Economics. However, this time, my parent believed me. My admission was not guaranteed. The day of the announcemen, I tried to check my result with trembling heart. As the result, I got a admission in Economics! I was very happy. That night, my family enjoyed the party. And I reminded my teacher.\n \n After my admission, I could not reach him because he went to U.S.A. at the university first day,\n I thought that “I should be the wise man like the teacher as well as the man who help another people.”"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(46, 1, '\nSports are popular all over the world. Explain why sports are so popular. Use reasons and specific examples to support your answer.', '"  Many people think that the reason of popular about sport is that sport is interesting because whenever playing sport like a abaseball, many people always concentrate about the game. However, I strongly believe that the reason of sports are popular, we get a lot of positive things during playing a sport because when we play game, our body is much healthier than before and we can get many relationships.\n \n           First of all, when we play sport, our body is always getting healthier. In my case, when I was middle school student, I was week. My lung is too week to run long time. At that time, my father recommended me to jog every morning. Actually, first I started jogging, I couldn’t finish the goal. However, whenever I jogged, my lung and my legs were getting stronger than before. Finally, I could get to the goal without problems. As a result, I went to the Il-san Marathon in Korea and I got a second prise. This say that because many people know that sports make them healthier, sport is popular.\n \n           In addition, while we are playing a sport, we can get huge relationships because, if we go to the sport club, we can meet a lot of people. In my friend’s case, his hobby was hiking and he was a member of Clark Hiking Club. So he usually hiked the mountain with his friend’s. Whenever he hiked, he could get a lot of friends. At that time, his mother was hurted by a huge car accident, he met a huge problem about taking care of his mother. It was very hard work, however, his hiking club friends started to help him treat her. As a consequence, his mother was healed perfectly. This fact claim that a relationship while hiking with his friends is one of the reason that why sport is popular.\n \n           In short, while we are playing a sport, we can get a lof of possitive things for two essencial reason. If you start to exercise something, you can know why sport is popular."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(47, 1, '\n"In order to stay well-informed, people should get information from various news source."', '"There has been an argument regarding the issue that people who want to stay well-informed should get information from various news source. There are myriads of people insist that people in modern days get too much information, so it is enough to read one kinds of news. But, from my perspective, it is essential to read various kinds of news source to get well-informed.  \n\nFirst of all, todays news sources are specialized in their particular fields. A economic newspaper is write the article especially about the economic issues. In case of sports and entertainments are in the same situation. If people want to we-informed, people should earn information from different kinds of news source. To illustrate, research conducted by Korea University verified that specialization of news sources are getting deeper and deeper. That means if people want to know properly, it is necessary to get information from a wide array of news sources.  \n\nSecondly, many news sources are reflecting the certain social tendency. If we keep getting information from one news source, there are possibility to affect our idea to be bigoted. To be adequately informed, people should get to know the different viewpoint of sources from different kinds of news. For example, South Korea News Committee informed that the tendency of news sources of South Korea is divided into 3 categories. Their character reflects the owner''s certain viewpoint about the politic. That illustrates that in order to get balanced knowledge, people try to understand various of viewpoint from various news source.  \n\nTo sum up, it is imperative to get information from different kinds of news source. It is because that todays news are too specialized, and some news sources are bigoted. By getting information from different news sources, people can stay well-informed. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(48, 1, '\nReading books is a more satisfying pastime than watching movies.', '"Some people might argue that watching TV is a more useful hobby than reading books. It is because people can get rid of stress when they watch TV. However, I believe that reading books is a more fulfilling hobby for two reasons. First, people can broaden their views. Second, reading books improves work efficiency.\n \nFirst of all, reading books can allow people to broaden their horizon. By reading a lot of books, they can learn about different worlds of lifestyles, basic customs and cultures. It is obvious that they may go through trial and error. However, they can learn to embrace diversity through this experience. For example, when I had a part-time job, there was an Ethiopian girl who brought home-cooked meals for lunch. She ate with her hands without using utensils, and other students who had never seen such a scene kept their distances from her. On the other hand, being educated on Africa and African table manners through various books, I was perfectly understanding and comfortable with what was taking place.\n \nIn addition, reading books can encourage people to work with more passion. This is attributed the fact that it can serve as one of the key motivators for them to perform better and to improve themselves. With such motivation, they put in more effort, concentrate better on their tasks, and feel a greater sense of responsibility for their work. According to a research conducted by the Ministry of Labor in 2009, there was a huge difference between two groups of employees in relation to their achievement. Employees in Group A who regularly read books and those in Group B did not. The researchers showed that the former group spent 25% more number of hours on working and performed higher than the latter group. In particular, the employees in Group A followed instructions, submitted assignments on time, and participated actively in group meetings. On the other hand, those in Group B dozed off and lacked focus while working. It can be inferred that reading books frequently has a direct correlation with the amount of effort and energy that employees invest in working.\n \nAll in all, the importance of my view cannot be underestimated by the fact that it can kill two birds with one stone for the reasons I have mentioned above."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(49, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree?\nUniversities should spend as much money on sports as they do on libraries."', '"Some argue that university is designed for academic reasons only. Advocates of this argument would resist the idea of university expanding budgets for promotion of physical activities. However, I believe that physical health which is promoted by sports activities lead to better academic performance and triggers healthy social network and relationship with one another.\n\nGood physical condition which leads to excellent academic performance is well-proved concept through many studies. One research revealed that students who worked out regularly had much better academic performance by 20% than those students who didn''t. The study further explained that physical activities lubricates the brain to function in perfect condition, making it in perfect condition to study better. This is why universities should not underestimate the effect of investing money on sports activities. Therefore, universities should provide proper environment for students to exercise on regular basis by putting much money and effort on sports.\n\nNot only sports activities promote physical condition which eventually affect positively on academic performance, it also triggers healthy interaction between students. Most sports games such as soccer and football are designed to play in group. Thus, while playing with many people, students naturally interact with each other and easily make friends. For example, football season was the one of the best time in my college life, as it was good opportunity for me to hang out with friends and meet new people. Bunch of friends went to the football stadium and watch the game cheering our team together. It was a chance to get closer to friends I have, and build new friendship.\n\nTo sum up, universities should put enough money to provide adequate environment for students to work out. This is as important as investing money on library since physical health is relevant to better academic performance and sports offer students to socialize. In this regard, I completely agree with the statement.\n\n"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(50, 1, '\nIt is better to work three days a week for long hours than to work five days for shorter hours.', '"First of all, it is much beneficial for today`s people to work three days a week for long hours because they can be allowed to take a long distance trip. It means that they are able to take a trip all around world because visiting other countries requires at least three days, which would be impossible for people who work five days a week. In addition, as they visit many other countries, it can make them to improve their perspectives greatly and help them to reduce their mental stress from work. For example, since a friend of mine works on his own business, he can manage his leisure time well as he wants. So, he have visited many other countries, which as a result it allows him to better understand other cultures, perspectives, and to meet a lot of new people from other countries. These experiences really help him to broaden his social network and to be successful in his business. Through this experience, I strongly believe that spending three days a week has more positive effect on people.\n\nsecond, going to workplaces for five days a week really makes people tired and to get stressed. In modern society, most people have their own cars and there are scores of transportation such as buses or taxies. So, it can be frequently seen that traffic jams during rush hours, which as a result causes people to get stressed. Stress is the main cause of diseases, short life span, and dissatisfying life. Therefore, working five days a week have negative effect on people`s lives. According to the study done by New York Times, it revealed that the most contributing factor to make workers to get stressed was a traffic jam during rush hours. They also answered that staying at their own cars or buses for long times on the road made them really tired. Through this study, it is clearly proved to me that working five days a week is much beneficial."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(51, 1, '\nAdvantages of Group Work vs Disadvantages of Group Work', '"The lecturer argues that group work has a lot of disadvantages such as free rider, less-rewarding and low performances. These came out from one experiment which is taken by 6months to indicate the performance of group work. This directly contradicts the reading passage''s claim that team project could offer several advantages by their collective intelligence.\n\nTo begin with, the lecturer says that more people take more time to make consensus. As many people participating with one group project, various opinions make a lot of troubles to coordinate people''s idea into one specific provision. This casts doubt on the reading passage''s claim that wide range of people can make a speedy decision making and creative solution.\n\nNext, the lecturer provides one assumption that one or two influential people would handle whole project without gathering whole participants'' ideas. As he said, influential person would decide or drop some object without considering others creative opinions. This counters the reading passage’s claim that participant who suggests good idea will be easy to get reward.\n\nFinally, the lecturer claims that group work is not risk free project, whole participant must take entire risk. Not like individual project, group project is commonly big so far its risk is more than individual thing. If project fails, every participant cannot be free from blame. This contradicts the reading passage''s claim that group work can scatter their responsibilities into tiny one."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(52, 1, '\n"These days, decreasing birth rate is a serious crisis in Korea and other rich countries. The problem is expected to greatly damage the countries’ economies. What are the ways we can solve this matter? Use specific details to support your answer."', '"Decreasing birth rate is similar as an arrow. It’s affecting our country so badly. Due to the decreasing number of newborn babies, a big portion of Korea’s citizens is aged 65 and older. This matter can damage our economy badly because the country should invest a lot of money on taking care of retired seniors. Also, since there aren’t enough babies being given birth, Korea cannot raise new workers of the future. Isn’t there any way we can escape from this situation?\n \n The first thing we can do to solve problems related to the low birth rate is to encourage mothers and fathers to give birth to more children. The biggest reason why parents aren’t having children is because of the amount of money they should spend to raise them. (education fees, money to buy their clothes, etc.) The money spent to raise a child is impossible to be calculated, and parents are concerned if they would face hardships in managing their budgets. In this situation, the government can support them in spending money for their kids. Currently, the government of the Republic of Korea is funding fees spent for a third child in a family. Our country needs to come up with more ideas like this one in order to attract mothers to help increase the birth rate.\n \n The second solution is to let citizens know more about the seriousness of the decreasing birth rate. A lot of parents in Korea aren’t aware of the reasons why low birth rate is such a serious crisis. They don’t know that when a big number of citizens become 65 and older, our nation’s economic growth can slow down because we cannot raise enough workers for companies, and the government needs to spend a big part of people’s taxes for healthcare and retirement life of seniors. In this situation, we can write more news articles and books about the birth rate issue. Then, people who read these would be able to learn how serious the problem is.\n \n Low birth rate is a serious problem in our nation these days, and we have to come up with solutions to it. We can encourage parents to have more children, and write books and show news broadcasts about the issue in order to let the public realize that it is a huge matter. Personally, I think one of the reasons why it is hard to increase the birth rate is because not every citizen of our country is participating in coming up with solutions. It wouldn’t be hard to solve the crisis if all of us help bring our birth rate back to normal. Come on! Think of an idea! There isn’t anything impossible!"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(53, 1, '\nTV programs and movies are obliged to show that good people are rewarded and bad people are punished. Do you agree or disagree?', '"Some argue that TV programs or movies we watch should be free from any restriction society puts, giving total allowance to express director/artist’s view. However, in my opinion, TV programs should have some extent of obligation to include common moral value or decency to protect young viewers. Further, these video images affect our view on society both consciously and unconsciously.\n\nTV program producers or movie director should consider moral value in their creation because it affects young viewers’ behavior. It is well-known fact that children have tendency to imitate adults’ behavior. It is also applicable truth when they watch TV programs or movies. Especially, many TV programs and movies star celebrities which young people idolize. If such video images contain morally vague concepts, it would affect the youth negatively due to their tendency to emulate role models. Furthermore, the young tends to be less concrete about their morality, not knowing what is good or bad, and have vulnerable mentality. In this case, exposing them to morally ambiguous images damage their morality severely.\n \nOn top of that, these morally ambiguous images, which bad people get rewarded and good people get punished for example, would not only affect the young but also provoke adults. Visual images have tremendous impact on people. To elaborate, when exposed to these images without knowing it, it would unconsciously have effect on people. One study revealed that a person who watched violent movies have higher tendency to display violent behavior than that who did not. Therefore, putting images such as good people getting punished instead of bad people would damage people’s faith that good deeds result in luck and reward. If such belief continued among people, it would bring serious moral hazard to the society as a whole.\n\nIn conclusion, creators of visual images on screen are obliged to contain morally accepted consequence in the story they produce to protect both the young and old. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(54, 1, '\nA nation should require all of its students to study the same curriculum until they enter college', '"The different viewpoint on how to educate students has been a lingering question for all nations. Some argue that setting a fixed curriculum covering various subjects for all the students is more effective than adopting different curriculum for each one. However, in my opinion, opposite is right because each student has their own unique talent which cannot be same with others, and teaching the same curriculum lacks room for creativity.\n\nAs mentioned above, teaching the same curriculum for every highschooler is ridicule due to their unique talent of each and everyone. Some students might have artistic potential and others might be math prodigy. These two types of students cannot be taught in the same way. That is, a person who has better potential in art field would be better educated with classes of extended and deeper understanding of drawing or design, and math genius would be much more suited with classes with numbers and calculations. In this way, they can pursuit what they want to achieve in the future more effectively and successfully.\n\nAnother equally important reason is that teaching the same material to all the students discards the chance of creativity. Set out curriculum means all the study material is fixed-prepared for the students to be acquired. Thus, all students have to do is to memorize what they are taught. The tests will be given to measure students’ understanding of limited coverage of that study only. Therefore, there is not much room for the learners to perform their intellectual mind.\n\nTo wrap it up, all the students studying the same curriculum in high school is ineffective educational structure. Rather, government entity relevant to the education system should come up with better way to stimulate creativity and new ideas among endeavors and expand the room for them to play during the learning process."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(55, 1, '\n"It is better for governments to spend their funds on the exploration of outer space than on earthly matters. Do you agree or disagree? Use specific reasons and details to support your answer. You’ll have thirty minutes to plan, write, and revise your essay."', '"There is no doubt that our planet Earth is highly contaminated these days. Due to the increased amount of greenhouse gasses being released into the atmosphere, our world is suffering from global warming and destruction of the ozon. In order to avoid this situation, many scientists are thinking of ways to find a planet everyone can migrate to when it becomes impossible to live on Earth. This is one of the reasons why people are investing a huge amount of money on outer space exploration. However, it sounds more ideal to spend governments’ funds to deal with earthly matters, not space exploration.\n \n To begin with, it isn’t easy to find a planet we can move to in the future. As I have mentioned above, planet Earth is greatly polluted nowadays. It is expected that in a few decades or so, it would be impossible to breathe in fresh air and drink clean water on our planet. Since they are too worried to face the future, people are in search for planets we can move to. However, it is very difficult to find our ideal planet. Until now, scientists weren’t able to find an appropriate planet for humans. Nearly every planet they discovered lacked water and air. Also, even though they have found an alternative home for people, it would take countless light years for us to get there. Instead of spending time and money on looking for a new planet, it would be easier to engage more in bringing our nature back to its original condition.\n \n Moreover, it is easier to find new resources on Earth than in outer space. Many people agree that one of the reasons why people are investing a lot of money on space exploration is because they want to find new materials there. Since we lack coals and other natural resources, a lot of countries think that they would be able to find alternative energies easily off Earth. However, I disagree with this. Even though we discover planets with rich minerals and energies, it still takes a lot of time and costs a lot for us to go there and bring those resources to Earth. It is better to think of more ways we can use nature (sunbeam, wind, water, etc.) to create new types of energy because it is much faster than space exploration.\n \n  It is more ideal for governments to spend their funds on problems related to Earth, not ones about outer space. This is because it isn’t easy to find a planet to migrate to, and it is easier and faster to discover new energies on our planet than in space. I don’t mean that we shouldn’t have any curiosities about other planets and stars. I mean that we should care more about our planet Earth, which is suffering from global warming and other natural crisis. If we do so, we wouldn’t have to abandon the planet and move somewhere else."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(56, 1, '\nUniversities should spend as much money on sports as they do on libraries.', '"Some people think that universities should spend as much money on sports as they do on libraries. As far as I am concerned, I am in complete agreement with the argument. The two ideas stated below can be sufficient evidence to support my agreement.\n\nTo begin with, students have to take physical activities, such as basketball, football and tennis. This is because these sports can be revitalizing, offering an effective outlet for releasing stress and tension. As society becomes more complex and faster changing, students are increasingly tied up by heavy workloads including lectures, assignments and group studies. The result is frustration, as we feel pressure to handle tons of work. Because taking exercise is a refreshing activity, however, it can help students relieve their tension and stress. In this context, spending time on sports is a great way to relax. For example, when I was in college, I discussed same topic with my professor and friends, and they agreed that working out at the gym for a while and trying to relax are very good way to make balance between work and life. Even if it is only for a brief moment, they also mentioned that we can feel deeply composed and successfully gain some distance from out stress ridden daily routine. With these advices, I started to take jogging and hiking regularly, and I have felt energized and ready for another day of struggle with hustle and bustle of life. This is the reason why I strongly recommend for universities to invest more budgets on sports.\n\nOn top of that, doing sports for relaxation is useful in that it encourages people to have stronger ties with others around them. In todays'' competitive society, we are under great pressure to outpace others, and thus lack time to be with our friends. As a result, we are less emotionally attached to our colleagues than we were in the past. By doing physical activities together and sharing our fun, however, we can sustain solid relationship with other people as well as friends. Therefore, the value of physical activities for relaxation should not be overlooked. This the real value of sports that libraries cannot provide for students. According to a recent survey carried out by Harvard University, nearly 80% of students replied that they could restore their bonds with colleagues through sports. This survey also shows that these 80% could exchange ideas and develop sympathetic bonds while doing exercise together. This increases emotional attachment and, by extension, social awareness.\n\nTo sum up, because of the reasons mentioned above, I firmly believed that putting as much money on sports as on libraries by universities should not only be allowed, but encouraged. It allows us to release the stress caused by life in the campus and to improve our relationship with our friends."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(57, 1, '\nTelevision has destroyed communication among friends and family.', '"It has been decades since television was distributed every single household, but its power over people became stronger than ever. Then why do people love TV so much? Some say endless entertainment attract people and others say easy access to education and information which was dominated by selected ones for centuries were the key fact to be loved so much. Nevertheless, I think disadvantages of TV overpower its favorable function especially lack of communication among friends and family.\n \nFirst of all, TV attracts every attention toward its programs, so it can interrupt communication while watching them. There might be someone who resists admitting and saying they can perform activities perfectly while watching TV such as having meals and speaking on the phone. But they would finally admit the quality of doing will go down. They don’t taste of food much and don’t know how much they eat. And also they might experience either their conversation on the phone end up or they mute the TV to remove possible interruption. So does conversation with friends and family. People can talk over and over while watching TV, but usually topics of conversation might end up all TV-related. Fortunately non-TV related conversation has started it is hard to get it off one’s chest while watching it.\n \nLast but not least, TV kills time without meaning, so precious time with people who you love is wasted. In modern society, people are extremely busy and they have limited span of time to be with their family or friends. But we generously allow our time to watch TV. What a waste?  I have experienced the same. I flipped through the channel with the remote and spent meaning less time with my family and finally went to bed without talking much. Only conversation I remember was: “Is there any other program? Why don’t we turn on the channel X?” So I lost my precious time watching idiot box instead of sharing my opinions and emotions with them.\n \nIn conclusion, TV destroys communication among people you love as well as relationship with them. We should understand the value of communication with them and make the most of it instead of killing time to watch TV. To do so, we need to use TV smartly. We can make rules to set time limits and choose programs in advance to avoid inevitable watching especially for children who are heaviest viewers among family."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(58, 1, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Grades (marks) encourage students to learn. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"There are many students who have been studying to get a high grades from their classes. We are able to find that whether it is true or not in library on midterm or final test period. Grades not only make students study hard but also can show them their current academic abilities. There are many reasons to support that sentence.\n\nTo begin with explanation that students study for grades, from my experience, when I was in high school, my school had a lot of tests which estimate student''s abilities about how the students are understanding from each classes. I wasn''t such a model student but I have needed to study because my overall GPA wasn''t able to be qualified to apply for the college that I wanted to attend. So I have studied so hard to earn achievement like getting better grades. The more I''ve spent time on learning eagerly, The higher score that I could get was there written on my grading paper. I was getting encouraged about learning. Finally, I got an score qualified for applying to the college.\n\nThe second reason is that Grades can show us our current abilities about how are we understanding about what we are learning. To take a personal example, when I was learning about calculus that I have been going through harsh time, I couldn''t even know such as which part of questions I am weak and Is it right way to solve this kind of problem ?.After that, I have decided to take a self test to check my circumstance about what I am studying. I asked my math teacher to give some of questions that I have studied and I have taken that test for estimating my abilities. Consequently, I could find what kind of problems are hard for me to solve by myself and I have spent more time on them. Finally, I could overcome those problems and I got high score I saw for myself that Grades can show me current skills and give me what to do.\n\nIn conclusion, Although we do not study for score itself, we are able to receive exact and a lot of pertinent feedbacks which give the way how to study for weak part of what we are learning and time allocation from grade"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(59, 1, '\n" Because the world is changing so quickly, people now are less happy or less satisfied with their lives than people were in the past.  "', '"I agree with the statement that people now are less happy or less satisfied with their lives than people were in the past. Actually, compared to the past few decades, people are living in the best comfortable world. People who live in modern society can buy anything and live great life than past world. However, we are no longer happy and not satisfied with our lives. People are unhappy.\n\nFirst of all, because we have to compete with people around us, we are so tired and depressed. For fast development, competition is very effective method especially to the company. In capitalization society, people should compete with their coworkers, other company and other countries. It is also realized in the school. For example, when I was a high school student, there were a great deal of competition among students to go to the good university. At that moment, I competed one of my classmate and she really hated me because I got better score than hers. One day, she stole my books that contained a lot of important things about the exam. Thanks to the CCTV, I could get it back. However, I felt so bad about her and this social system. This competition makes a innocent high school student criminal. Therefore, I think too much competition make this world really stressful and depressed.\n\n Secondly, the weakness of family bond makes people really unhappy. People are social animals and they live with their lovely family. The familiarity of family members plays very important role in our happy lives. However, in this fast changing society, family is breaking rapidly. According to the research of the Seoul University, the divorce rate increased fifty percent compared to the last 1990s. This research shows us that so many couples broke up and so did the family. In the past, only few couples got divorced easily. Increasing divorce rate also means that many children are living in one parent family. In this environment, children can not grow well. This family bankrupting is very important reason why we are unhappy.\n\nIn conclusion, we who live in fast changing society are not happy compared to the people who live in the past. Not only competing society, but also family destruction is very important reason\n\n"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(60, 1, '\nThe best way to learn about foreign country is by reading newspapers and magazines.', '"Some people might say that books could provide more information about foreign countries than any other sources, and other would say that watching movies or soap operas is the easiest way to understand the countries. However, as far as I''m concerned, reading newspapers and magazines would be a best way to know about other countries for two reasons: to convey up-to-date information and to be easy and efficient way to know other countries.\n \nFirst of all, newspapers and magazines give new information quickly. Of course, learning the history of the foreign countries would be a good way to understand rooted emotion of the nation, but our fundamental purpose is to win in the competitions with them or to work with them. At this time, what is more important is knowing the situation at present,not their history. To be a book is published, a significant time is consumed; on the other hand, newspapers or magazines allow us to know affairs which happened yesterday or even today. According to a survey conducted by the management department of California university in 2009, the 75 percent of the people working in the field of trade were subscribing more than 2 kinds of news papers or magazines from their partners'' or competitors'' countries. They said that from that kind of media, they can grasp the countries'' market situation and overall atmosphere at present. They also said that the resouces have the most important role in making strategies to working with them. In this sense, using newspapers and magazines is a great way to know foreign countries. \n \nAlso, getting information from newspapers and magazines is an easier and efficient way compared to other ways. Some people say that watching some movies or soap operas would be easier since the characters starring in them use easy words. However, sometimes watchers of other countries only feel significant cultural gap, and do not understand the characters'' feelings at all. Not only that we can not gain enough information when considering the time we spent waching them. Other people would say that having penpal friends who live in abroad, but this way also has a serious problem because we tend to get knowledge which is skewed by our friends'' worldviews. This will disturb to understand the foreign country objectively. In the case of books, we would feel difficulty although they might provide us a lot of information, since the context is used to contain the knowledge which can be exactly understood only when we have background knowledge. Compared to that, when we try to use newspapers and magazines, we can get understandable as well as significant amount of information in a comparatively short time.\n \nIn short, although there are various information sources, in that newspapers and magazines convey new information faster and easier, as well as effectively since they are written in order to be read by most common people, and they are published in a short time.  "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(61, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? With the help of the internet, students can learn more effectively."', '"In this recent society, many people adamantly believe that students can take advantage of the internet when they want to learn something. However, there exist many side effects of the internet that actually hamper effective learning. Therefore, I disagree with the statement that students can learn from on-line.\n\nFirst and foremost, the internet provides too much information. This means that it contains invalid and incorrect information which could mislead students. When students are faced with invalid information, it is highly like that they cannot distinguish it from other reliable information but just accept it. For example, when I was high school student, I relied on the internet to finish my literature homework. I decided to log in one literature forum and ask some question related to Korean poetry in 20th century. I believed that people in the literature forum knows about questions that I asked. However, I realized that answers from the internet were absurd in some parts. Now, I can see that not every person in that forum was good at literature. I believe that their fragmented information hampered my learning at that time. As seen from this compelling example, students can gather unconvincing information from the internet and that information could disrupt effective learning.\n\nSecondly, students could not be inculcated with the way to think by themselves because the internet provides answers within a few seconds without providing room for thinking. In other words, students could not rear the ability of abstract thinking and inference which is essential for the effective learning. This idea was reflected on the recent study conducted by 100 teenage students. A group of students who do not use the internet for their study got high scores in an inference ability test whereas the other group of students who use the internet got relatively low scores. Therefore, the internet could not help the real learning because it cannot offer chances of making one’s own thought.\n\nIn conclusion, using the internet is not helpful for student’s learning. It not only provides low quality information and misleads students but also takes away chances of having logical thinking. "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(62, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? With the help of the internet, students can learn more effectively."', '"Some argue that Internet is unreliable source of information so that it is not a good resource for learning. However, I believe opposite is the case due to tremendous amount of information that Internet contains and quick and easy access that it allows.\n \nFirst of all, Internet allows students to access pool of information around the world. Therefore, endeavors can learn more on the material as they want. If students want to learn more on the subject, they can search further on the matter and can have deeper understanding on the subject. From my personal experience, for example, when I had to do a research on history of Australia during my college year, Internet offered me more information than books in library. To illustrate, books provided limited information on the matters I was looking for, so I had to go over many books at the same time to gather complete set of research. It was both time-consuming and ineffective. On contrary, Internet had useful information more than enough to put in my research paper, but also sufficed my personal interest on the matter.\n \nOn top of that, Internet is quick and easy method to search for information, making it very effective tool to learn. Students can access information they are looking for through simple typing and clicking using computer at home. To elaborate, search engines such as Google and Yahoo offer endless list of webpages in a second on the subject typed in. Students can go on to the link and read the articles or research papers related to their research. Moreover, information is accessible anywhere around the world as long as there is online connection. This quick and easy availability of information makes Internet powerful tool to educate endeavors.\n \nTo sum up, Internet is very effective way for students to learn due to its amount of information available and quick and easy accessibility. In this regard, I agree with the statement completely."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(63, 1, '\nThe scientific technology has made people happier than before.', '"Some people say that technology has brought about many side effects like environmental problems and depletion of resources. However, I believe that such adverse effects are overwhelmed by its benefits which science technology has gave us like that it allows us not to do repetitive or dangerous work by making machines done it instead; to communicate each other easier.\n \n First of all, technology has made us safer and not bored by using machines in risky or tedious tasks. In that when people do dangerous tasks, they are likely to hurt or lost their lives; when they do boring work, they tend to be lethargic, technologies have strongly helped people to become happier. For example, in the past, when people needed to make tunnels, workers had to do perilous tasks including breaking stones with tools in person and conveying them. Through the processes, many people got hurt and dead because of unfortunate accidents. According to the record which is calculated by the Ministry of Labor of Korea, in 1950s, the number of workers who dead in tunnel construction sites was about 3,500. Compared to that, at present, there are much fewer people lost their lives while doing construction work. This is absolutely because construction technologies have advanced. In other words, technology saved lives of a lot of people. In that anyone''s life is directly concerned with other''s happiness, science technologies have improved our lives.\n \n  Also, science technology let us communicate each other much better. The Internet and cell phone have been widely spread throughout the world. Since such devices allow us to communicate each other very easily and fast, even though we live far apart each other, we can make conversation as frequently as they live near our houses. According to a survey conducted by sociology department of Texas University, people are making contact with their family or friends about 70 percent more, compared to 40years ago. This increase has occurred more sharply when the Internet appeared, and until now, the rise has continued. In that the fact proven by various psychology experiments that true happiness comes from interaction with other people, no doubt, technology has contributed to happiness of people.\n \nIn short, by employing science technologies, people come to be significantly free from risky tasks, as we can see the decreased number of deaths of construction workers. Moreover, development of telecommunication has allowed us to make conversation easily which will also help us to make deep relationships. For these reasons, I strongly believe that technologies have made our lives blissful.   "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(64, 1, '\nA person''s childhood years (the time from birth to twelve years of age) are the most important years of a person''s life.', '"Confucius, the greatest philosopher of ancient China said, ""Childhood is the most important time of your life."" This points out the significance of youth in one''s life, Having said this, childhood years especially from birth to twelve years of age are important because it is the time when one''s personality is shaped up and one absorbs knowledge faster than any other time in life.\n\nTo begin with, childhood holds significance due to its impact on forming a child''s personality. When a child is born, psychologists claim that his or her mind is like a ""blank slate"" meaning that a child''s personality is not yet determined at birth. Thus a child develops own temperament as he grows up. Therefore, what a child sees, hears, and feels in childhood all add up to become one''s personality. Consequently, a child''s youth is important because it is the time when a child''s personality is determined.\n\nSecondly, children absorb knowledge faster than any other time in their life. Thus children should constantly be exposed to new information during childhood years. The capability of children to learn about new knowledge cannot be compared to that of adults''. For instance, when a child is sent to another country, he picks up the language very fast and naturally assimilate into the new culture. On the other side, adults are slower at learning a new language and a culture. Scientists explain that a child''s brain is like a sponge as it absorbs new information very fast. Thus it is the reason scientists emphasize on the importance of education at an early age. All in all, youth is significant because it is when children learn new things very fast.\n\nIn conclusion, childhood years are influential to children''s lives because their personalities are shaped up at that time and they pick up new knowledge faster than any other time in their lives.     "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(65, 1, '\na person''s childhood years (the time from birth to twelve years of age) are the most important years of a person''s life.', '"Some argue that childhood years are the golden years of one’s life due to its particular tendency that in those days, people start to learn and form personality. However, in my opinion, that is not always the case. There exists more crucial life periods rather than child hood. Further, children tend to experience limited surroundings that cannot be defined as the most important time of life.\n \nFirst and foremost important fact here is that there are more times to be emphasized than childhood years during the lifetime. Adolescent years for example, are one of these crucial times growing into adult mentally and physically. Moreover, college years are another particular years since it offers many chances to meet new people and travel around the world. In the same vein, how about retiring periods or career-pursuing –after college years? In this regard, it is obvious that childhood years are not the only times that are important in life.\n \nOn the top of that, most of the experiences that people go through during the childhood years are limited. Children do not undergo so many things as adults do. They go to school in the morning, and come back home afternoon. They might enjoy some extracurricular activities or hang out with friends, but those activities are not to be compared with the things adults do. To elaborate, adults can go travel around the world and experience new culture. They fall in love with another and build new relationships. Pursuing their own career or dream is also one of these experiences that only adults go through. Therefore, it is undeniable that only little taste of life is allowed during the childhood. Thus, childhood being the most important time of life is overstatement.\n \nIn conclusion, childhood years are not the most important years of a person’s life because there exists more crucial years ahead, and childhood experiences are narrow and limited compared to other times in life. In this manner, I disagree with the statement."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(66, 1, '\nIt is more important to give students awards for their effort rather than give awards for achievement.', '"All people try their best to obtain their aim, but most of them fail to get the success even though they work really diligently. Furthermore, some people acquire unintended result though they do not work hard. It is quite unfair for those who study rally hard. Therefore, we should recognize the effort of journey of people. In that way, we could hearten people to try their goal again, and be more helpful in the future. Lastly, realizing only success is malicious way of assessing person''s nature.\n \nIf we encourage people who fail to obtain their achievements, it would give them a tremendous effect. For instance, he could get the willing to try again and overcome this complicated situation whenever he faces it. In contrast, we did not try to recognize the effort of failed person, it would trigger detrimental consequences. In Korea, most of high school students have gotten innumerable pressures from their studying. They work really hard to go to famous university. However, this reason sometime bring bad situation like committing suicides. The most adequate reason to explain their suicide is their parent. Their parent only seeks the better grade then the student gets and seeks the good result. This greed of student''s parent led their children to die. If they just hearten their children to try again. Their child does not need to commit this perilous behavior and successfully achieves their goals.\n \nMost of people get the energy or motivation through people they love or respect. This willing is really tremendous, so it makes people to not relinquish again when they conflict the situation they struggle with. If not, they could be obsessed with success and finally undermine the situation. Therefore, we should realize the effort of one’s. The person with successfully overcome the intricate situation is more likely to success, because they know how to deal with problem they encountered before. In other words, they endure their problem by other’s encouragement.\n \nEvaluating people with their fortune and property is vicious way to assess people. All people have totally different characteristic and way of thinking, so we should carefully judge people. There is some old fairy story that perfectly matches with this idea. Long time ago, there is a very rich old man. He does not know how to socialize with other, because he spends his whole life to make money. After the rich man retires from his work, he decides to make friends. As time goes by, the rich man successfully makes two friends. His first friend uses to avoid pay money, while his second friend is willing to pay the money during playing time. One day, the rich man loses his all money to defrauder. He does not have any place to sleep. Therefore, we go to his first friend’s house, but he refuses the rich man to sleep at his house when he hears the story. The old man gets shocked and he finally realizes that he was wrong. At that moment, the second friend finds the old man is sitting on the street. He brings the old man without asking why and let him to live in his house until he catches the defrauder. Throughout this happening, the old man recognized how to assess the people.\n \nMost people work really hard and some of them succeed in obtaining their goal, while the others fails to achieve their aim. When one of our surrounded people faces this happening, we should hearten them to try again instead of compelling them to try again."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(67, 1, '\nUniversities should spend as much money on sports as they do on libraries.', '"Some people think that universities should spend as much money on sports as they do on libraries. As far as I am concerned, I am in complete agreement with the argument. The two ideas stated below can be sufficient evidence to support my agreement.\n\nTo begin with, students have to take physical activities, such as basketball, football and tennis. This is because these sports can be revitalizing, offering an effective outlet for releasing stress and tension. As society becomes more complex and faster changing, students are increasingly tied up by heavy workloads including lectures, assignments and group studies. The result is frustration, as we feel pressure to handle tons of work. Because taking exercise is a refreshing activity, however, it can help students relieve their tension and stress. In this context, spending time on sports is a great way to relax. For example, when I was in college, I discussed the same topic with my professor and friends, and they agreed that working out at the gym for a while and trying to relax are very good way to make balance between work and life. Even if it is only for a brief moment, they also mentioned that we can feel deeply composed and successfully gain some distance from out stress ridden daily routine. With these advices, I started to take jogging and hiking regularly, and I have felt energized and ready for another day of struggle with hustle and bustle of life. This is the reason why I strongly recommend for universities to invest more budgets on sports.\n\nOn top of that, doing sports for relaxation is useful in that as it encourages people to have stronger ties with others around them. In todays'' competitive society, we are under great pressure to outpace others, and thus lack time to be with our friends. As a result, we are less emotionally attached to our colleagues than we were in the past. By doing physical activities together and sharing our fun, however, we can sustain solid relationship with other people as well as friends. Therefore, the value of physical activities for relaxation should not be overlooked. This is the real value of sports that libraries cannot provide for students. According to a recent survey carried out by Harvard University, nearly 80% of students replied that they could restore their bonds with colleagues through sports. This survey also shows that these 80% could exchange ideas and develop sympathetic bonds while doing exercise together. This increases emotional attachment and, by extension, social awareness.\n\nTo sum up, because of the reasons mentioned above, I firmly believed that putting as much money on sports as on libraries by universities should not only be allowed, but encouraged. It allows us to release the stress caused by life in the campus and to improve our relationship with our friends."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(68, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with that the opinions of celebrities, such as entertainers and athletes, are more important to younger people than they are to the older people."', '"In current days, lots of celebrities give own opinions about diverse topics including politics, environments, or health care. It is controversial that for which ages, between young people and older people, celebrities'' opinions are important. I believe that the opinions of celebrities would be more important to youngsters. It would be more influential and persuasive than opinions from others for them.\n\nTo begin with, the opinions of celebrities are influential, especially for young people. For these days, many celebrities try to communicate with their fans by using SNS(Social Network Service; for example, Facebook, Tumblr, and Twitter). The major user of this service is young people. In addition, the characteristic of young users is fast forwarding, sharing speed. Thus, what celebrities say spreads fast. According to the result conducted by Korean National University, only one hour is required to spread some news into all 20’s in the world. On the other hand, three days are needed to spread same news into all 40’s in the world. In other words, lots of young people can be assimilated with what celebrities say.\n\nFurthermore, the opinions of celebrities are persuasive. Generally, the more people are young, the more likely to imagine of what they want to be. Hence, lots of youngsters follow celebrity trends. They even try to share emotions or feelings of celebrities. This is why young people are easily moved from what celebrities say. For example, until a Korean famous singer insists that pets be well-treated more than current condition, most people except who loves pets were indifferent about animal cruelties. After the singer’s opinion, lots of young people including their family members, relatives participated in the signature-collecting campaign for protecting abused pets.\n\nA strong word can change public opinion. Celebrities’ opinions can be a strong word because their saying is influential and convincing. Remember, the opinions’ power of influence and persuasiveness are being originated from young people. Taking all above things into account, celebrities’ opinions are more important to young people than old people."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(69, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement?\nA person who drives his or her own car during rush hour in a crowded city should be charged a fee."', '"Some people argue that driving private automobiles during rush hour is selfish conduct, so that it should be restricted with extra charges. However, in my opinion, such resolution not only perturbs personal freedom to own and drive cars, but also ineffective solution to the traffic congestion.\n \nThe first and foremost reason why people should not be charged with driving their own private mobile during rush hour is because it is against the basic principle that personal freedom should be protected. It is citizen’s freedom and their own will to buy cars and drive them. In addition, it is wholly their choice of freedom to drive anytime anywhere. Such basic rights of freedom should be protected under any circumstances. No society or authority has given rights to interfere such choice. Charging fees on driving their private cars is one of these acts that go against the principle. Therefore, the charge should not be put on any given situation.\n \nOn top of that, charging on driving their private mobiles is not a good way to solve deeper problem which is traffic congestion. I believe that the idea comes from the chronicle trouble that every city goes through which is traffic congestion. Making drivers to pay extra charges is only a temporary solution to this problem. That is, some people will still want to drive their mobiles even though they have to pay few extra charges because it is just more convenient, leaving the problem unsolved. Therefore, better solution should be implemented such as installing more traffic roads or improving public transportation system. In this regard, charging fees on drivers is short-sighted decision. It is obvious that there is a better way.\n \nIn conclusion, people’s freedom of rights to drive anytime anywhere should not be perturbed by charging fees and there exists better ways to solve the deeper issue that is traffic congestion. For these reasons, I disagree with the statement."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(70, 1, '\nTelevision advertising directed toward children under the age of five should not be allowed.', '"There has been an argument regarding the issue that television advertising targeted to children under the age of five should not be allowed. There are myriads of people who insist that advertisement for children under five years old should be allowed because it is the basic right of commercial company. On the other hand, from my perspective, Television advertising for the children under the age of five should not be allowed because of the reasons below. \n\nFirst of all, television advertising badly affect to children''s mind whose age''s are under five. Children under 5 years old have no sense of rational judgement and and also vulnerable to stimulation. Commonly, television advertisements whose target are especially children under 5 years old, tend to be extremely stimulating and it might devastate children''s plain spirit. For example, my cousin whose age is 4 had exposed to a lot of violent television advertisement. Some advertisement showed him that the hero killed the enemy by using the sword that they want to sell. Consequently, my cousin struck his younger brother by using wood stick and he screamed the name of the toy sword''s name. He did not think this behavior was bad because he saw the similar scene at the television advertisement. \n\nSecondly. television advertising cause unnecessary consumption. The advertisement aimed for the children skillfully stimulate children''s will of possession. The children who obsessed with those advertisement''s fancy lure, has no choice buy continuously requests their parents to buy those products. This cause unnecessary buying of products no matter it is necessary or not. According to the research conducted by Korea University, advertisements for the children are the most effective promotion method of companies. It is because those generation is easily captivated, effectively create the profits. Only thing the greedy companies'' concern is to lead the young children cry for their parents to buy products. \n\nTo sum up, television advertising badly affect the children''s pure mind, and it cause unnecessary consumption. Hence, I strongly emphasize that television advertising directed toward children under the age of five should not be allowed."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(71, 1, '\nThe best way to travel is in a group led by a tour guide.', '"Someone says that group tour is quite convenient and useful. However, in my opinion, a group tour has more disadvantages than advantages. To be specific, group tour might reduce the opportunities for both flexible schedules and in-depth-studies for tourists.\n \nTo begin with, I hope to clarify the definition of the travel. It is the opportunity to see extraordinary environments and cultural monuments with relaxed mind. In other words, the first purpose of travel for tourists is relaxing. When it comes to think a group tour, however, you can easily imagine the time tables and schedules for accommodations, museums, transportation and meals, which were already fixed before departure by tour guide. Just last summer, my family traveled China by using group tour service. It was horrible for my family; the schedule was too tight to relax. Even my younger brother had a severe diarrhea at that time, we could not relax at the hotel because of the reserved transportation to go the other city. This shows the direct disadvantages of group tour. Of course, group tour is cheaper than individual tour. If you consider the first principle of traveling, you are better to travel by individuals.\n \nIn addition, as I mentioned in previous paragraph, during traveling, we would like to see exotic things such as architectural forms, cultural heritages, and traditional rituals. As we well know, group tour cannot provide various options to see those things; they only provide limited routes for glancing some popular things, without consideration of tourists'' interests. Even if the group tour company gives a chance to see some specific monument, the tourists have only small amount of time to glance it. One might say that this type of traveling is a ""get, glance and go"". Unlike group tour program, individual tour makes more flexible time to enjoy the exotic features. You can enjoy your time at your favorable space; you can grab a chance to watch MLB at the stadium, without watching some boring national history museum.\n \nAs I have stated, the group tour has a more disadvantage than advantage because of the inflexible and pre-planned schedules. This is why I strongly believe that individual tour is better to relax and enjoy the traveling for tourists than group tour.\n "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(72, 1, '\n Hard work has more to do with success than luck does.', '" As the world continues to undergo economic recess, the number of people who want to make a lot of money easily and fast by luck. They argue that there is nothing much better than success with their luck because they do not have to go through difficult hardships. However, I strongly believe that people can have a more successful life not by their chances but by their hardwork since success based on hard work lasts for a long time and is much more satisfying.\n\nFirst of all, if people work hard to achieve their dreams and goals, they are more likely to be successful for life. This is because while people do their best at their work and in their study, they not only gain great rewards but also  valuable assets such as diligence and time management skilles which would help them persistently. On the contrary, the successful result obtained from just luck is temporary. For instance, when I took a math test at middle school, I got good grades even though I guessed many answers because I was not prepared much. It was just a luck but it made me lazy studying, which led to poor grades on the next step. I realized that I should not depend on my luck and therefore, I stuied very hard by planning ahead and practicing a lot of mock exams. In doing so, I learned study skills and hard working spirit as well as gained much better grades on exams.\n\nSecond, if people succeed due to their efforts, they are more likely to treasure their success. That is, people who performed their best are happy and satisfied with what they earned while those who readily got what they want without any hard work do not value about it since they did not earn it by doing on their own. According to a recent study, most of the lottery winners are having a miserable life, even worse than before they did not win the lottery. They are having family ploblems, huge debt and mental diseases. This is due to the fact that they became bored with ordinary things and tend to look for only better luck, not thinking about working hard. As a result, they lose true happiness with their lives and their seemingly success was disappeared fast as it came fast."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(73, 1, '\nIt is better for children to grow up in the countryside than in a big city. Do you agree or disagree with the statement? Please included specific reasons and details to support your answer.', '"Some people think that it is better for child to grow up in a big city, not grow up in the countryside. However, from my perspective, I firmly believe that it is better for children to grow up in the countryside because children can think more and children cannot control their parents.\n\nFirst of all, it is advantageous for children to grow up in the countryside rather than in a big city because children who live in countryside relatively do not affected by their parents, so they can think deeply. To illustrate my point, there was a boy who lives in rural area. He always gets along with animals such as sheep and cow. Later, he had broadened mind and better thinking. This is because by living animals, he always spent time for himself such as wrote daily schedule and practice instruments. Those can be cheer for him and bring about his personality largely. Due to these facts, there are no doubts that it is advantageous for children to grow up in the countryside.\n\nFurthermore, it is undeniable that it is better for kids to grow up in the countryside than in a big city because children who live in near the capital always repeat same schedule, so those works cannot develop children’s mind. In a recent research conducted by the Education Department of South Korea, it stated that 78.9% of elementary school students who live in Seoul were very busy daily lives. This is because their parents have proud with their kids, so many parents dominate their children such as teach varieties of education system. This is not an isolated incident, similar researches were conducted in many other Asian countries such as Japan and Taiwan and the results were for the same reasons. In this sense, it is undeniable that it is better for kids to grow up in the countryside than in a big city.\n\nTalking all of these into consideration, I strongly believe that it is beneficial for youngsters to grow up in the rural area rather than in a big city for the reasons I mentioned above."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(74, 1, '\nGovernment should pay attention to health care /not environmental problem', '"Many people argue that government should pay more attention to health care because keeping people healthy is more important than maintaining clean environment. Nonetheless, I strongly suggest that government put environmental problems before health care because reduced environmental problems can mean less health care burden for government and a large portion of environmental problems cannot be treated individually whereas people can individually care for their own health.\n\nFirst of all, if government pay more attention to environmental concerns, health problems will naturally decrease. Environmental pollution is one of the leading factors of disease nowadays. Therefore, if government increase its investment in environmental protection and enforce stricter laws, it can consequently cut its budget for health care. For instance, if someone suffers lung cancer which is usually known to be caused by air pollution, this person will probably rely on government subsidies to receive expensive treatments. If government had paid more attention to regulate environmental pollution in the first place, government would not have had to spend a dime on this person. Consequently, government should pay more attention to environmental concerns as a long term solution to health problems.     \n\nSecondly, environmental issues cannot usually be handled individually while each person can look after own health. Environmental problems are global concerns which require the initiatives of government. For example, the deforestation in Amazon is causing severe global scale problems such global warming. However, there is a limit to what individuals can do to stop these without the help of  government. On the other side, health problems can be dealt individually by regularly exercising and maintaining healthy diet. There is nothing much government can do except for financially subsidizing patients. Having said all, government should prioritize environmental problems. \n\nIn conclusion, government should take environmental issues more seriously than health care because reducing environmental problems can be a solution to health problems and health care can be done individually.  "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(75, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement?\nThe extended family is less important now than in the past"', '"Some argue that the extended family is not as important as it used to be because people’s lifestyle has changed according to development of urban city, which small-sized family is more adaptable. However, in my opinion, there should be more emphasis on the big family in contemporary society. That is, children can improve their social skills from the youth in the extended family and people feel much happier and have more of sense of security.\n \nTo begin with, the extended family provides much better environment for children to develop their social skills. That is, from the very early age, children get to build relationships with different types of people including grandparents, uncles, aunties, and nephews. Such family members are belong to different age groups and each relationship is different and unique from each other. Therefore, children naturally learn how to communicate with the younger, older, male, or female, developing communication skills dealing with various types of people which they will encounter in the society. Such skills are essential part of life for children to live harmoniously. For example, my friend Min-young was born in the extended family which includes many family members. Her personality is always outgoing, very sociable and popular among friends. I believe such character of her comes from her background having extended family.\n \nOn top of that, people who grew up in extended family tend to be much happier and feel sense of security more than those people who grew up in the nuclear family. To elaborate, people who belong to the big family have surroundings which they can always get support from. If one is in difficult situation and experiencing hard times in life, he or she can discuss with family members. Since there are many family members who went through many things in life, one can get useful advices from them and overcome difficulties easily. Moreover, family members will not only support physically but also mentally. They will provide emotional support and assistance which would lead to sense of security and comfort. Such comfort is very important living in the stressful contemporary society. Therefore, it is understatement that extended family is less important now than in the past. It is as equally important now as it was in the past.\n \nTo wrap up, it is obvious that extended family is as crucial as in the past now because it offers better environment for children to improve social skills, and it provides sense of security and comfort to people. In this regard, I completely agree with the statement."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(76, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with that the opinions of celebrities, such as entertainers and athletes, are more important to younger people than they are to the older people."', '"These days people can easily express and share their opinions about certain subjects via SNS such as Twitter and Facebook. Obviously, entertainers were one of those who actively put their opinions regarding controversial issues, and I believe that those famous people played a pretty important role in making the younger generations than older ones get interest in these issues.\n\nFirst of all, younger people pay attention to and care about the opinions and thoughts of celebrities than older generations. This can be seen among the teenagers most of the times, since teens tend to have a longing for certain celebrity they favor and idolize them; hence, feel curiosity towards the thoughts and perspectives he or she has and easily are influenced by these thoughts. For example, an entertainer brought up an issue about animal abuse, and left a sentence saying animals should be treated well since they are also living creatures that have feelings on her own homepage, with a photo she took with her pet dog together. This was noticed by many people who agreed with her view and took part in spreading it to more people, and most of them were teenagers and young people in their 20''s, who cared about this celebrity much.\n\nIn addition, younger generations are more familiar to using electronic devices and sharing ideas through them, which older people usually are not very interested in. With the drastic development of Informational Technology, younger people were born and grew up with electronic gadgets as more options were attached to them year by year, and ostensibly many celebrities who dominantly use SNS based on the Internet as a way to express their ideas are the young ones who consist this generation. As a result, younger people would look into celebrities'' opinions more and be much more exposed to opinions of celebrities than older ones who hardly get a chance to do this; and eventually, younger ones who frequently watched famous people''s views would be affected at least to some extent.\n\nTo sum up, with the drastic improvement in technology combined with usual attention of younger generations towards their objects of observation, famous, unreachable and respected people, it made the celebrities'' perspectives very influential to younger people. This point seems obvious, if it has acted rather as a negative or positive way to us."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(77, 1, '\nPeople who do not accept criticism from others cannot be successful at working in a group.', '"There has been heated debate over the issue of whether people who do not accept criticism from others cannot be successful at working in a group. While there are many good arguments for both positions, the following argument will explain in detail why I agree.\n\n  My first argument for the influence of people should be espoused. This is because people play critical roles in developing our untapped talents. Modern-day people live hectic lives because today''s globalized society is increasingly competitive and constantly changing. Consequently, it is difficult for people to discover their personal interests and pursue the fields of study that they prefer. This makes it crucial for people to help us to develop our talents and tap into our full potential. Therefore, people'' influence cannot be overlooked in this context. According to a group of education experts at Columbia University, people who are under the close guidance of their co-workers and boss at their workplace decide on their future careers and develop their potential faster than people who are not. The majority of education experts argued that people are likely to be unproductive if they do not fully receive the advice and help of their peers and boss, especially when they are in their potential stages.\n \n  Moreover, my strong support for people'' influence can be rationalized. This is attributed to the fact that people, with their years of experience, can offer lessons on morality and ethics. People who are not still mentally immature have long way to go before they become experts in their fields. During this long journey, they tend to make many mistakes and are prone to misbehave. However, people can be guided by their closer friends and mates, who can teach them about etiquette and social norms and can thus become good models for society. In this respect, people exert good influence on us. For example, undeveloped people may give in to the temptation of playing computer games all nights long because they are too immature to judge right from wrong. This is why people'' influence is an urgent need. With the guidance of them, such as co-workers or boss of us, we can learn how to avoid such temptations and become law-abiding citizens, by listening our advisers'' descriptions of their own experiences. Through such lessons, we can become holistic beings.\n\n  In a nut shell, my discussion above presents two stronger arguments for people'' influence which I believe effectively convince the reader."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(78, 1, '\nLetting a friend make a mistake is better than taking action that risks destrotying a friendship', '"Some people believe that allowing a friend making a mistake is better idea than trying to prevent him or her from it. This is because they think another person''s advice may not always work out sometimes. However, I firmly believe that even though it would be risky that destroy a relationship, people should take action for their friends for following reasons: First, one can''t make wise decision alone and second, it will worsen a friendship if something gets wrong with a friend.\n\nTo begin with, every human being is not perfect creature. Which means we always can''t make smart decision by ourselves in all situations. That is why a good friend exists. People should help their friends to do right thing when others seem to walk along the wrong path. For example, I have an old friend named Jihee. Since Jihee has always felt that she needs to study more, she decided to study abroad in United States after she graduated college. After getting in graduate school in California, everything seemed going well with her. However, one day I realized via her friend that she got addicted to alcohol because she could not get used to new life in strange country and had heavy pressure under the a lot of tests she had to pass. As one of closest friend, I was worrying about her situation. So I flew to her place and persuaded her to take off the school for a year and come back to hometown. At first, she refused to take my advice, but she soon went back to Korea with me and got some therapies for her alcohol addiction. If I had not taken any action for her situation, she would be in serious trouble by now. Therefore, it is important to guide friends into right direction rather than sitting back and watch them making wrong decisions.\n\nOn top of that, just letting a friend decide any choice can worsen relationship sometimes. If a friend''s decision get wrong and something bad happens to her, she may blame on me having not told any advice to her. Thus it would break our friendship. For example, when I was in high school, I used to have a friend Nancy. At that time Nancy was considering breaking up with her boyfriend because he would not respond her messages and calls for two weeks. Even though I saw that guy walking with a strange girl at the shopping mall, I didn''t give her any advice because it could hurt her feelings. Also I thought all matters were up to Nancy. However, after she realized the boy was cheating on her, Nancy suddenly blamed on me that I haven''t told anything I knew to her. After for a while, Nancy apologized to me about being dramatic, but we could not get along well as we used to. This example implies that sometimes letting a friend making own decisions is not good idea and may break a relationship.\n\nTo sum up, I agree with the idea that taking action that risks destroying a friendship Is better than letting a friend make a mistake. Since people usually can''t make smart decision alone, friends need to guide that right direction. Also, sometimes sitting back and allowing a friend decide whatever they want will worsen a friendship if something gets wrong with her."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(79, 1, '\n"The extended family (grandparents, cousins, aunts, and uncles) is less important now than it was in the past."', '"Some people might say that the extended family is important. They could say they can learn about a profound family culture as one of reasons. However, I believe that the extended family is less important now, compare to the past decades. This is because people generally do not live with their extended family. Also, people in these days are too busy.\n\n \n\nTo begin with, it is not common that living with their extended family, or living close to their extended family today. Around two decades ago, it was common that living with or living close to a lot of family members including grandparents, aunts, uncles, and so on. However, as time goes by, the size of family has been decreased, and the frequency of meeting extended family has been decreased, too. This situation naturally discourages people communicate with their extended family. In a nutshell, it will be no difference between extended family and strangers in near future. Considering current trend, I believe that the importance of extended family is just an illusion.\n\nSecondly, nowadays, people live in a big competition. All the things related to their life belong to the matter of competitions. For example, teenagers compete their academic grades, a business man compete their companies. There is no enough time to looking how their family lives well or similar things. According to the research conducted by Korean University in 2010, eighty-percent of people talks with their extended family once a month. Furthermore, half of the people who are in the eighty-percent answered that they do not care about their extended family because of their tight life. This result shows the fact that people do not consider their extended family as cherish human beings in the world, contrast to the past tendency.\n\nTo sum up, family separation has brought less communication and indifference to the extended family. Struggle for hot competition in these days prevents people from paying attention to their family members, especially to the extended family members. Taking all these things into account, I think the extended family is less important now than before."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(80, 1, '\n"In today’s world, it is more important to work quickly and risk making mistakes than to work slowly and make sure that everything is correct."', '"Modern technological development has made our lives faster than ever before. Under this circumstance, people nowadays tend to live with the faster face, and people are now concern more about efficiency. As a result, doing things slowly and making almost everything correctly seems to be sort of out of date. In a modern society, people should, I believe, work at a higher speed and risk taking mistakes.\n\nFirst of all, the development of modern technology has made our life faster than ever before. With the assistance of modern techniques, we consequently should work faster than ever before. For instance, in the old days people made their own clothes by hand. However, now machines in the factories have made sewing and weaving at a great speed and of great quality. We do not have waste any time doing cumbersome works because of the modern technology. Therefore, we should not insist to work at a slow pace instead of enjoying convenience that is brought by technology.\n\nAnother important aspect is, now we are living in a society which develops rapidly. To meet the rapid change and improvement, all of us need to improve our own efficiency. As we can see, almost every factory wants to increase its productivity and almost all the employers to generate greater value within the time limitation. Nobody wants to be a loser in the society, so the only way to keep pace with the whole society is to accelerate, which is, working faster. Admittedly, it is highly possible for us to make mistakes when working as a high speed. But in fact, we human beings make mistakes, so even if we work as slowly and carefully as possible, we still risk making errors. However, by taking the advantage of high self-efficiency, we can do our work more precisely than ever before.\n\nAll in all, in todaty’s world, people should work as a higher spped. It is so important that everyone in a modern society should be like that. It is a general tendency of the world."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(81, 1, '\nShould children learn about the notion of managing money? Do you agree or disagree?', '"Some people might think that children do not have to learn about the notion of managing money because how to manage money can be educated by confronting the real situations in their future. However, I disagree because by learning managing money, children can practice to avoid monetary problems like bankruptcy and make their life be in high quality through the money.\n \nTo begin with, learning how to manage own money can reduce the possibility of falling monetary problems. We can see surround people who are in stress because of losing money. Most of this happening exists due to the wrong management. For example, people sometimes invest their money without profound consideration. Another case, someone lend their money to their friends without official documents. To prevent these situations, people should know how to manage their own money since they are young.\n \nMoreover, people who manage their money well can enjoy their life with high quality. Even though pocket money cannot cover the expense of enjoying high quality life, such as travelling, learning, going concert, if money has been well managed, this life can come as reality. Let us suppose two persons. They get same amount of money from company once a month. One person saved one third of money, and spent remaining in buying necessary things. The other spent all the money for temporary amusements. One year after, the first person plan to world trip with saved money. The other also wants to go but he cannot do because he already spent all the money. However, he does not remember what he has spent in. This shows the problem of spending money without managing, in comparison with the effect of managing money.\n \nTaking all these things into account, I firmly believe that learning to manage money from the age of child is significant. It helps us to avoid monetary problems as well as to enjoy their life in future."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(82, 1, '\nYoung people do not give enough time to helping their communities.', '"In old days, the society has not been developed much. So, almost everyone think that their communities need to be developed at that time. Then, they tried to put a lot of time into their communities to live better lives. However, the society has changed a lot, so that young people who live in modern age are not interested in their communities. Rather, they think things related to themselves more important. I also think more about individuals than groups.\n \n Nowadays, young people are concerned about their future because companies have reduced employment recently. Then, many young people should compete against each other to get a better job. To survive in the competition, they have to prepare for an English score and the internship and even voluteer work experience. Otherwise, their future might be unclear. So, that’s why young people focus on themselves rather than communities.\n \nI am sure that another reason is that the technology has been developed a lot nowadays and it made our lives more convenient. Let me give one example of a mobile phone which is well-known as one of the most developed inventions in modern times. Young people spend a lot of time on doing their mobiles with a variety of applications. There are SNS(social network service), e-book and the Internet. They can find some information that they want and make new friends from other countries now. There are so many things to do using a mobile phone in modern days.\n \nTaking these two reasons into account, I agree that young people nowadays do not give enough time to helping their communities. A majority of young people who want to get a good job should try hard to win the competition. In lifestyle, the technology has been already made breakthrough, so many things that we can not imagine in the past can be happened using a mobile phone."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(83, 1, '\nShould teachers be paid based on students'' performances for the benefits of both students and teachers?', '"Some people say that when teachers are paid based on students'' performances, the education of school would be improved since it is clear that we are living in materialism society. However, as far as I''m concerned, teachers should not evaluated only by their students'' grades for two reasons: teachers have to pay attention to not only how to teach effectively, and students would not no longer thank teachers'' efforts on class. \n \n First of all, teachers should also give attention to character education as well as class. This is very important and time-consuming education while the result rarely appears to be good grades. The purpose of schools is not only in improving students'' intellectual ability, but also growing them as good members of society. Since we are living together having interactions, there is more possibility that success in life is up to one person''s character like responsibility, morality, not rely upon how much knowledge they have. For example, There is a hairdressor from Korea who succeed in Philippines as a boss of tens of shops. Actually, he was not a honor student because he didn''t like studying general subjects. However, he met a homeroom teacher when he was in middle school who always encouraged him to find his talent and emphasized and let know like growing leadership, time-management skill, and endurance are so important in life than winning good grades. He said that from the teacher, he got courage, got to know how to live an independant life, and he found his flair and decided to be a hairdressor. Even he said that his enterprise at present would not exist if she did not encouraged him. In this sense, we can know teachers'' education much affect one''s life,and this is not knowlege, but wisdom. Wisdom does rarely appear as students'' grades, but it is essential for teachers to teach. When teachers are evaulated and paid only with their teaching skill, they are more likely to spend less time how they can make their students wiser and good members of society. Thus, I strongly believe that teaching skill cannot be a standard how much they get paid.\n \n Also, the relationship between students and teachers would more likely to be superficial. This is because students would think that the reason teachers spend long time how to teach effectively is only for his or her better finance, not from love for students. There is believe that educators are the people who educate students to cultivate good social being, so pupils respect their teachers since they feel teachers love their being although they get salaries. If such policy come to be true, they would regard the teachers who put a lot of efforts into class just instructors, and pupils would not also realize the true heart of educators to enhance their intellectual ability which let them live with widen perspectives. According to a survey conducted by psychology department of Chicago university, There was huge difference between two groups: A group of schools enacted the salary policy based on students'' performances, and B group did not. The students of the schools of A group tended not to follow educators'' advice, and the rate of the juvenile delinquent was higher about 30 percent more. Moreover, they were thinking teachers only educate for their financial condition, and they are not loved by them. In this sense, how well teach students should not be a criteion for educators'' salaries.\n \n In short, if educators get paid based on students'' peformances, for their high salaries, they would not spend enough time making students suitable members of society, and students would not appreciate their teachers'' endeavor to develop teaching skill because they would think their effort is for money, not for love for pupils. For above reasons, I firmly disagre with the statement that teachers should get paid accoeding to their students'' performance."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(84, 1, '\n"At universities and colleges, sports and social activities are just as important as classes and libraries and should receive equal financial support."', '"Some people claims that universities and colleges should not spend a great deal of money om sports and social activities, as their budgets should prioritize classes and libraries. However, as educational institutions, universities and college have an obligation to provide a wide range of knowledge to their students to help them deveop academically and socially.\n\nFirst of all, more and more business require people who are not only specialists in their fields, but also skilled in social interaction. In the rapidly changing environments of science and the economy, no task can be done by a single person. Given the need for collaboration, social skills and team spirit are necessary qualities for any successful person. Clearly, sports and social activities in universities and colleges provide students with the perfect settings to practice their social skills. By playing football on a team or joining in a protest, for instanace, students can develop a sense of belonging and experience team spirit, both of which may prove very important in building a career.\n\nIn addition, sports and social activities can greatly improve student’s efficiency. Students need not play sports or participate in social activities at the expense of their academic study. Indeed, for some students, playing sports and joining in social activities are good stress reducers. Even the most enthusiastic people feel tired if they focus on their one thing for too long. Frustrated and tired people can do nothing well if they do not recover from their bad situations. Students who have been frustrated in their academic work would be well-advised to play some sports or join in social activities. This demonstrates that universities  and colleges should spend adequate money on academics as well as sports and social activities.\n\nTo sum up, I maintain that universities and colleges should spend enough money on academic education and social movements to prepare students for their future development.  "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(85, 1, '\nTeachers should not present their personal views on politics in the classroom.', '"Various opinions may exist over whether teachers should not present their personal views on politics in the classroom. As far as I am concerned, I am in complete disagreement with the argument. The two ideas stated below can be sufficient evidence to support my disagreement.\n\nMy first argument for teachers'' personal views on politics should be espoused. This is because they help students to be well-balanced. While students grow up, they are exposed to certain types of the information and knowledge about the world, through education at school as well as at home. The problem with this is that most of information and knowledge is conveyed from one source''s particular viewpoint. Given this, in order to be well-informed, students try to learn about different viewpoints through their teachers'' personal views on politics. In my case, I acquired information about exploring space by chatting with my friends. Due to the friends, I came to be fully exposed to the great achievements of governmental space projects. However, my perspectives on these governmental projects could not be solely positive when I knew the difficulty of exploring space and frequent struggles with political parties involved through my teacher''s views on politics in the classroom. Without these political view points, I might have held a slanted view of what was going around me.\n\nMoreover, my strong support for teachers'' private ideas on politics can be rationalized. This is attributed to the fact that they can allow students to get the latest information. Our world is evolving at a surprising speed. As a result, students may have difficulty understanding all of the changes and new events come about. Given this context, it is important that they try to keep current by learning about changes and events through their teachers'' personal views on politics. In a recent survey carried out by Harvard University, nearly two thirds of surveyed students felt that they could update their knowledge and successfully adjust themselves to the changing social trends through different views on politics by their teachers in the classroom. According to the surveyed students, these personal political views prevented them from being confined to an outdated world. It is no surprise that there has recently been a drastic increase in the number of students who love to hear their teachers'' personal views on politics to gain the latest knowledge of the world.\n\nIn conclusion, it is undeniable that students can become well-rounded by accepting their teachers'' personal views on politics in the classroom. By doing so, they can also avoid becoming biased and outdated. These two reasons both connect to students'' increasing need to accurately understand the world around them."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(86, 1, '\nIt is more important to give students awards for their effort rather than give awards for achievement.', '"All people try their best to obtain their aim, but most of them fail to get the success even though they work really diligently. Furthermore, some people acquire unintended result though they do not work hard. It is quite unfair for those who study rally hard. Therefore, we should recognize the effort of journey of people. In that way, we could hearten people to try their goal again, and be more helpful in the future. Lastly, realizing only success is malicious way of assessing person''s nature.\n\n If we encourage people who fail to obtain their achievements, it would give them a tremendous effect. For instance, he could get the willing to try again and overcome this complicated situation whenever he faces it. In contrast, we did not try to recognize the effort of failed person, it would trigger detrimental consequences. In Korea, most of high school students have gotten innumerable pressures from their studying. They work really hard to go to famous university. However, this reason sometime bring bad situation like committing suicides. The most adequate reason to explain their suicide is their parent. Their parent only seeks the better grade then the student gets and seeks the good result. This greed of student''s parent led their children to die. If they just hearten their children to try again. Their child does not need to commit this perilous behavior and successfully achieves their goals.\n\n Most of people get the energy or motivation through people they love or respect. This willing is really tremendous, so it makes people to not relinquish again when they conflict the situation they struggle with. If not, they could be obsessed with success and finally undermine the situation. Therefore, we should realize the effort of one’s. The person with successfully overcome the intricate situation is more likely to success, because they know how to deal with problem they encountered before. In other words, they endure their problem by other’s encouragement.\n\n Evaluating people with their fortune and property is vicious way to assess people. All people have totally different characteristic and way of thinking, so we should carefully judge people. There is some old fairy story that perfectly matches with this idea. Long time ago, there is a very rich old man. He does not know how to socialize with other, because he spends his whole life to make money. After the rich man retires from his work, he decides to make friends. As time goes by, the rich man successfully makes two friends. His first friend uses to avoid pay money, while his second friend is willing to pay the money during playing time. One day, the rich man loses his all money to defrauder. He does not have any place to sleep. Therefore, we go to his first friend’s house, but he refuses the rich man to sleep at his house when he hears the story. The old man gets shocked and he finally realizes that he was wrong. At that moment, the second friend finds the old man is sitting on the street. He brings the old man without asking why and let him to live in his house until he catches the defrauder. Throughout this happening, the old man recognized how to assess the people.\n\nMost people work really hard and some of them succeed in obtaining their goal, while the others fails to achieve their aim. When one of our surrounded people faces this happening, we should hearten them to try again instead of compelling them to try again."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(87, 1, '\nBeing different from others is helpful for achieving success.', '"There is an argument over whether being different from others is helpful for achieving success. Some might argue that being same with other people is better. However, in my view, it is better to be different from others for success. There are several reasons that I could support my argument so I will limit the discussion to the two that I feel are the most relevant to the topic. First, people can save money. Also, people can get expertise.\n\nTo begin with, the most important reason for my feeling this way is that people can save money. Most often, money tends to be very important in our everyday lives. If people are different from others, they will make the most of their money. Take my uncle, for example. It is very efficient to be different from others. My uncle did not waste money for drinking when he was in college. In contrast, his friends were drinking every week like other people. Thus, they spent much money when they were college student. Unlike his friends, my uncle did not spend money for drinking for 7 years and made their own restaurant by using that money. This result clearly shows that being different from others help people become successful because of efficiency.\n\nMoreover, another reason which proves my point is that people can get expertise. Commonly in society, many accomplished people tend to have expertise. Therefore, people can succeed if they are different from others because it help them get expertise. A really good example can be seen in Minhan Kim. I read online that Kim, the CEO of the CS company, achieved great success because he was different from others. Kim, using this expertise, transformed his company one of the most profitable software enterprises in Korea. When he was high school student, he did not study to go to university like other students in Korea. He did not go to university, but made programs on and on. As a result, he made a great program and earned prestige. This example clearly shows that it is better to be different from others because of expertise.\n\nTo summarize, I believe that being different from others is helpful for achieving success on the grounds that people can save money and also people can get expertise."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(88, 1, '\nWhat are some important qualities of a good supervisor(boss)? Use specific details and examples to explain why these qualities are important.', '"There are some crucial aspects to become a good supervisor. I strongly believe that someone who wants to be a great boss should have diligence, confidence and warm heart. These three traits are the most necessary components for a good supervisor.\n \nTo begin with, diligence is the most significant thing among many other qualities because there would be no success if someone is very lazy. There is a proverb that ""Early bird catches bugs"". Likewise, it is the most fundamental quality for supervisor who manages many people under his or her hand. If a company have an idle boss, it would ruin very quickly. For example, there was a chairman of some company, he always drank every night and did not care any tasks of the company. Eventually, he got fired because his subordinates completely hated him.\n \nAlso, confidence is substantial trait of a good supervisor''s requirement. Generally, a supervisor manages a lot of subordinates under his feet. To lead many people''s opinion, the leader should have great leadership that never sway by other assertions. If he would not decide his will or would not gather other people''s diverse arguments, the company''s policy would face a lot of problems. For instance, when I was a chairman of the committee at my work, I did not make a crucial decision due to some subordinate''s opposition. However, that hesitation resulted in a bigger confusion.\n \nIn addition, a warm-hearted mind is needed to someone who would like to be a great supervisor. This characteristic can obtain much better respect from subordinates. In all likelihood, no one would not like the supervisor who has a nice manner and is very kind. It is said that someone gives a goodwill to others, he will return it as much as he was given. Therefore, if someone utterly wants to be a great boss, he should have a thoughtful mind to others.\n\nTo conclude, there are some indispensable elements to be a good advisor. they are diligence, confidence and warm heart. If someone has these traits already, he would be a truly fine supervisor."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(89, 1, '\nThe best way to relax and reduce stress is by spending some time alone.', '"As to the statement that the most appropriate methods to relieve stress is to have personal time, I strongly agree with it. That’s because it is more easier to enjoy free time and there are lots of recreations that one person can enjoy.\n\nFirst, If people have a pastime alone, they do not need to be careful about other things. Specifically, playing with friends require to arrange meeting time, places and what they will do. This is possible to cause additional stress for an individual because it is time-consuming and hard to reconcile the options. For example, I have always loved to go hiking in mountains, and if I go there with someone, I would feel uncomfortable since I should consider the routes and how much we will walk. However, when I go hiking alone, I don’t need to worry about specific plans. I am able to choose courses to which I am attracted. In this regard, I believe that spending leisure time alone allows people to enjoy more easily.\n\nSecond, nowadays, people don''t need to find friends purposely to be recharged. It was fairly common for people in the past to have their free time with others, as going to beach or playing group sports. On the other hand, in today’s society, there are numerous entertainment every person can enjoy without gathering other people. For example, my father used to play soccer after school because it is hard to find a variety of pleasures in his town. He virtually did not have choice but to play physical activities. In contrast, in modern society, people have made various pastimes such as computer games, watching shows and doing something through smart phones. These are sometimes more interesting and don''t require other person. This is why I don''t think that group activities is necessary to relieve stress.\n\nTo sum up, enjoying pastimes alone is more better in some ways because people can arrange their time comfortably and there are many enjoyments that only a single person can enjoy."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(90, 1, '\nIt is more enjoyable to have a job where you work only three days a week for long hours than to have a job where you work five days a week for shorter hours.', '"Some people might say that working five days a week for short hours is preferred because they can work with strong but short concentration. However, in my opinion, working three days a week for long hours is better for following reasons: We can relieve our stress by enjoying a hobby or having a journey.\n \nFor the primary reason, people can enjoy their hobby with enough time. Enjoying own hobby has an influence on psychological happiness. Thus, having a hobby is the best for spending holidays. However, there are things to do during holidays such as home chores, meeting friends. It is not easy to make time for enjoying own hobby. For example, in my country, people generally work for five days a week. It is rare to find people who enjoy their hobby within the two other days because most of the people think these holidays fly easily, just for taking a rest or having time with their family. Of course some might say working five days a week for short hours can use their after-working time, which is relatively longer than working three days a week, but it is not easy to manage after-working time as they think due to getting tired. Enjoying own hobby has an influence on psychological happiness Therefore, I prefer to working three days a week for long hours.\n \nMy next reason for supporting working three days a week for long hours is because workers can go travel during their holidays. Travel allows people not only to stress out, but also to increase productivity. To be specific, through travelling, people can enjoy their life at a distance. Seeing a wonderful landscape and eating a delicious food will give a sound body with a sound mind. They will be ready for getting back to work place with good condition. Good condition will bring a strong passion and enthusiasm. They will work hard even they have to work for long hours, and this will affect their future promotion. Following this repertory, people will be full of positive mind and praise their life. This is my reason why working three days a week is good.\n \nTo sum up, working three days a week for long hours is better option than the other because this option enables workers to manage their time easily. Making/enjoying a hobby or going travel really works for stress-out and this allows people to fall in love with their happy life, even their jobs."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(91, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement?\nMovies and television have more negative effects than possible positive effects on young people."', '"Some people argue that watching televised programs on TV would have positive effects on youth because it enables them to experience the world indirectly so that it is educational. However, I am of believer of the opposite is true. To elaborate, TV programs nowadays contain inappropriate contents and it is addictive in a way that it prevents the young to have healthier activities outdoor.\n \nTo begin with, visual images on TV in recent years display quite violent and inappropriate images for the youth to watch. The problem here is that these images will have negative effect on teenagers and adolescents because their mind is not as concrete as those of adults and they are vulnerable to these images in a way that it will affect their future behavior. To illustrate, one research done by Seoul National University of South Korea, those teenagers who watched violent images such as gunshots or fistfights showed 80% higher tendency to display violent act than those who did not. Therefore, TV programs today which depict much of these images will have definite negative effect on the youth.\n \nAnother equally important reason is that watching TV can be addictive so that it prevents teenagers to have healthier outdoor activities. TV programs are becoming bolder and bolder in its way of expression to attract more viewers. That is, they try to capture people’s eyes constantly to keep them in front of TV. Such despicable effort will lure young people to watch TV for all day long, resulting in unhealthy habit sitting face-to-face with TV screen every day. Such habit would eventually lead to reduction of physical health and solitary life style.\n \nIn conclusion, I believe watching TV programs for teenagers only brings negative results, because TV programs illustrate unhealthy images for the young and it lures vulnerable mind of teens to stare at the screen all day. In this regard, it is imperative to say that advantage of watching TV outweighs disadvantages."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(92, 1, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement?\nYoung people enjoy life more than older people."', '"Some argue that when people get older, there would not be many excitements and leisure activities to enjoy as much as when they are younger. However, in my opinion, elderly would have their own time of their lives and enjoy much as they did when they were young. That is, older people spend their leisure time in different way than younger people. Moreover, they are much more satisfied and experienced than the young so they know how to please themselves.\n \nTo begin with, the elders spend their leisure time different from the young people have good times. To elaborate, the youth would spend their time pursuing excitements such as drinking, clubbing, or active sports such as football, tennis or soccer. In contrary, older people pursue peaceful and relaxing leisure such as reading in café, playing poker games, or just a simple walk during on a warm day. Such activities are enough for the old people to enjoy. For example, when I went to Bali, Indonesia, there were many retired elderly who visited. They were having time of their lives enjoying beach walk, having good conversation in cafes, and reading while sunbathing. In this regard, I do not think that the young will have more fun than the old.\n \nOn top of that, since old people are more experienced and satisfied, they can enjoy more comfortably. To illustrate, most of the elderly underwent many things so they know what they want. They probably tried many leisure activities and know exactly which activities they themselves enjoy or not. Therefore, there is no waste of time or money to discover which is good for them. Moreover, most of them have already achieved their goal or dream, so they are more satisfied with their life than the young. As their satisfaction level is higher than the youth, they will spend their extra time much happier.\n \nTo wrap up, I am a strong believer of old people enjoy life as much as young people do. Since the old people are more experience and knows what they want in addition to the fact that they are much more satisfied with their lives, and they have different way of relaxing and enjoy from the young, it is wrong to say the young have better way of enjoying life."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(93, 1, '\nIn twenty years there will be fewer cars in use than there are today.', '"Along with the development of technology, many people have their own cars compared to the past twenty years. Then, what would happen in next twenty years? While some assert that in the future there will be fewer cars in use than are today, others argue in the opposite perspective opinion. Personally, the latter opinion seems much more persuasive for development of cars and economical reasons. \n\nTo begin with, in twenty years, every person can buy the cars because of their cheap prices. This is primarily due to the fact that development of alternative energy such as hydrogen, sunshine power and water. To be specific, these new cheap energy will replace expensive fossil fuel energy. Actually, the cost of using car is highly expensive because of the continually increasing cost of fuel; therefore, cheaper fuel would lead to increasing consumption of cars. A research on fuel was carried out at Seoul University. According to the study, 78 percent of 20s people would buy their future cars if the fuel is cheaper. This result clearly shows that in twenty years many people will afford to buy their cars.\n\nSecondly, car is the most convenient transportation and it will be same in twenty years either. To illustrate further, although developed technology made airplanes, we do not use airplane in our daily lives. This shows that driving car is the best for our routine lives. In twenty years, there might be a new fascinating transportation; however, using car will be the most suitable method to go near places. For example, most people use their car when they go other places, especially in Korea. According to the study of Korean University, 89 of people responded to use their car among 7 transportations and they said that it is because car is the most convenient and comfortable for them. The research demonstrates that most of people feel comfortable regarding cars.\n\nIn conclusion, even in twenty years, there will be more cars in use than today. This is because the price of using car will be decreased and the car is the most convenient transportation for people.  "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(94, 1, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? High school students should be allowed to choose some of their classes.', '"Some argue that it is better for high school students to study fixed curriculum because it will teach them necessary education, therefore better prepared for college. However, I am of a believer the opposite is true. Having to choose courses offer students to figure out what their real interests are. Moreover, it is much more effective in terms of learning, because they feel more responsibility.\n\nFirst of all, giving freedom for high school students to choose some of their classes will provide them opportunity to find out what they are really interested in. To elaborate, since students are not fully aware of their true academic pursuits, having choices what to study will provide them to get a taste of many fields so that they can find the particular study that they want to go deeper. A research done by Department of Education of Korea, students who went to school where students had some freedom of choosing course had 40% better academic achievement compared to students who went to the school where had fixed curriculum all along. The department concluded that the reason for this better academic achievement was students who had choices what to learn during high school realized their career goal earlier than those who had not. Looking at this research result, it is obvious that it is better for high school students to have some extent of freedom to choose their classes.\n\nMoreover, it is much effective way of learning because students would feel responsible to their choices. Since they chose their courses by themselves, they will have much more responsibility to be good at it than studying what they are given. Therefore, they will put more effort on the class. For example, I exerted bigger effort to the classes that I chose than the one that was fixed during my high school years because I wanted to be responsible to my choice.\n\nIn conclusion, it is clear that advantages of choosing some classes for high school student outweigh the disadvantages."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(95, 1, '\nTeachers should not make their social and political views known to students in the classroom.', '"As to the statement that teachers could express their own opinion in regard to  certain social or political events, in my views, it has some problems and teachers should avoid showing their personal thoughts about these things. There are two reasons: students are so young and susceptible to a teacher’s words that students can have biased view and imparting specific knowledge is educator’s primary duty.\n  \nFirst, teacher’s remarks about sensitive issues are very influential to their students, so they would be likely to grow concept that is similar to their teacher’s idea. It is evident that if one teacher supports one particular party or one-sided position, it definitely leads students to take a stance analogous to teacher’s thoughts. For example, according to research by the Korea University, in the test, researchers set two divided classes. One teacher explained the Iraq War as a way to attain world peace, while the other one portrayed the war caused by the invasion of the US to obtain Oil. Surprisingly, after each teacher finished their descriptions, students followed the positive or native view against the war at high rates. It demonstrated that how partial and biased view can be made by teachers’ own perspective.\n\nSecond, not only does it disrupt students to cultivate impartial view related to political and social events, in term of a teacher’s duty, it also can not be allowed to let students know what the teacher’s view is. That is, most students come to school to learn specific knowledge so that they are able to prepare easily to pursue a future career or to enter into top universities. However, if teachers focus on imparting ambiguous ones, which contain political perspective, some of students would regard it as a waste of time because it may not be helpful to prepare their crucial exams. This is true that students are require to grow their own view about social affairs since they are also one of the members in society, but I am convinced that it is not the teacher’s job.\n\nIn summary, if possible, teachers have to avoid showing their personal perspective toward sensitive subjects like political or social affairs. This is because students are highly influential to teacher’s words and because teachers should concentrate on giving practical learning."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(96, 1, '\n"Should government support athletics like an Olympic team or should they support art, such as museum and exhibit?"', '" At the time that countries were having war with each others, it was mandatory for them to expand their territories and colonize other country in order to expedite their strides. Furthermore, indoctrinating their cultures or languages to country that they successfully colonized is essential works because of forestalling the rebellions of colonized country. However, we are living in peaceful and cohesive society nowadays, so most of countries are competing with each other by showing their athletic skill or their unique style of art. If government should support one between them, they should endorse the arts rather than supporting the athletics. Supporting arts is not only teaching lesson about history and culture, but also it could promote the tourism.\n \n First and foremost, tourism is crucial task for countries to show their traditions and efficient way to afford the money. Furthermore, arts could enhance the tourism by showing the greatest work from famous painter or writer from the past, so it could expedite the stride of countries’ economy. Italy and England is perfect example of this case. Almost million people are dropping by these countries in order to appreciate or see the works of Leonardo da Vinci or William Turner etc. Furthermore, the visitor often purchases the monument of hallmark of the region. Throughout this process, countries are earning tremendous of money unless these greatest works are stolen by thief. The government can facilitate the money that they obtain from tourism by augmenting more public infrastructure or ameliorating the service of tourism. \n \n Most of art pieces reflect the life style of people in era that they involved and the tradition that people possess. For example, if one country suffered from colonizing of other country, the art works of colonized country would mostly show the dark or gloomy atmosphere, and sometime show their tradition stealthily. In contrast, the artworks from well-developed country could display the elegance and grace side atmosphere. When Korea was colonized by Japan, many ceramists were kidnapped and compellingly went to Japan in order to teach the techniques of making Korean ceramic. After Japan took a advantage of Korean ceramist, they killed the ceramist mercilessly. Therefore, the ceramic from colonized period show erratic and blunting surface, and most of them engraved Korean traditional painting.\n\nIn conclusion, arts is not only shows the tradition and culture of country, but also it could provide the many beneficial aspect. Therefore, government should spend money on preserving their art work, and people should be proud of what our ancestor leave.      "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(97, 1, '\nGovernment should pay attention to health care /not environmental problem', '"Many people argue that government should pay more attention to health care because keeping people healthy is more important than maintaining clean environment. Nonetheless, I strongly suggest that government put environmental problems before health care because reduced environmental problems can mean less health care burden for government and a large portion of environmental problems cannot be treated individually whereas people can individually care for their own health.\n \n First of all, if government pay more attention to environmental concerns, health problems will naturally decrease. Environmental pollution is one of the leading factors of disease nowadays. Therefore, if government increases its investment in environmental protection and enforces stricter laws, it can consequently cut its budget for health care.  For instance, if someone suffers lung cancer which is usually known to be caused by air pollution, this person will probably rely on government subsidies to receive expensive treatments. If government had paid more attention to regulating environmental pollution in the first place, government would not have had to spend a dime on this person. Consequently, government should pay more attention to environmental concerns as a long term solution to health problems. \n \nSecondly, environmental issues cannot usually be handled individually while each person can look after own health. Environmental problems are global concerns which require the initiatives of government. For example, the deforestation in Amazon is causing severe global scale problems such as global warming. However, there is a limit to what individuals can do to stop these without help of government. On the other side, health problems can be dealt individually by regularly exercising and maintaining healthy diet. There is nothing much government can do except for financially subsidizing patients. Having said all, government should prioritize environmental problems. \n \nIn conclusion, government should take environmental issues more seriously than health care because reducing environmental problems can be a solution to health problems and health care can be handled individually.\n\n"', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(98, 1, '\nPeople who do not accept criticism from others cannot be successful at working in a group.', '"There has been heated debate over the issue of whether people who do not accept criticism from others cannot be successful at working in a group. While there are many good arguments for both positions, the following argument will explain in detail why I agree.\n \nMy first argument for the influence of people should be espoused. This is because people play critical roles in developing our untapped talents. Modern-day people live hectic lives because today''s globalized society is increasingly competitive and constantly changing. Consequently, it is difficult for people to discover their personal interests and pursue the fields of study that they prefer. This makes it crucial for people to help us to develop our talents and tap into our full potential. Therefore, people'' influence cannot be overlooked in this context.  According to a group of education experts at Columbia University, people who are under the close guidance of their co-workers and boss at their workplace decide on their future careers and develop their potential faster than people who are not. The majority of education experts argued that people are likely to be unproductive if they do not fully receive the advice and help of their peers and boss, especially when they are in their potential stages. \n \nMoreover, my strong support for people'' influence can be rationalized. This is attributed to the fact that people, with their years of experience, can offer lessons on morality and ethics. People who are not still mentally immature have long way to go before they become experts in their fields. During this long journey, they tend to make many mistakes and are prone to misbehave. However, people can be guided by their closer friends and mates, who can teach them about etiquette and social norms and can thus become good models for society. In this respect, people exert good influence on us. For example, undeveloped people may give in to the temptation of playing computer games allnight long because they are too immature to judge right from wrong. This is why others influence is an urgent need. With the guidance of people around us  such as co-workers or boss of us, we can learn how to avoid such temptations and become law-abiding citizens, by listening to our advisers'' descriptions of their own experiences. Through such lessons, we can become holistic beings.\n \nIn a nut shell, my discussion above presents two stronger arguments for people'' influence which I believe effectively convince the reader.\n "', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(99, 1, '\n"For success in school or work, having ability to adapt to changing conditions or circumstances is more important than having excellent knowledge of a field."', '" Various opinions may exist over whether having ability to adapt to changing conditions or circumstances is more important than having excellent knowledge of a field for success in school or work. As far as I am concerned, I am in complete disagreement with the argument. The two ideas can be sufficient evidence to support my disagreement.\n \nMy first argument for having excellent knowledge of a field for success in school or work should be espoused. This is because it helps us to be well-informed for success in school or work. While we grow up, we are exposed to certain types of the information and knowledge about the world, through education at work as well as at school. The problem with this is that most of the information and knowledge is conveyed from one source''s particular viewpoint. Given this, in order to be well-informed, we try to learn about different viewpoints from information through excellent knowledge of a field. In my case, I acquired information about space exploration by taking society class at university. Due to the class, I came to be fully exposed to the great achievements of governmental space projects. However, my perspectives on these governmental space projects could not be solely positive when I knew the difficulty of exploring space and huge budgets involved through doing my class assignments. Without these excellent knowledge of a field, I might have held a slanted view of what was going around me.\n \nMoreover, my strong support for broad knowledge of a field for success in school or work can be rationalized. This is attributed to the fact that it can allow us to get the latest information. Our world is evolving at a surprising speed. As a result, we may have difficulty understanding all of the changes and new events come about. Given this context, it is important that we try to keep current by learning changes and events through having excellent knowledge of a field. In a recent survey carried out by Harvard University, nearly two thirds of respondents felt that they could update their knowledge and successfully adjust themselves to the changing environments through having excellent knowledge of a field. According to the respondents, these broad knowledge prevented them from being confined to an outdated world. It is no surprise that there has recently been a drastic increase in the number of people who have excellent knowledge of a field to gain the latest knowledge of the world.\n \nIn conclusion, it is undeniable that people can become well-rounded and successful by having excellent knowledge of a field. By doing so, they can also avoid becoming biased and outdated for their success at work as well as in school. These two reasons both connect to our increasing need to completely succeed in school or work."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(100, 1, '\nUniversity athletic departments should receive the same amount of funding as university libraries. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Usually, libraries have been considered to be the yardstick judging academic width and richness of the universities. Even though facilities, systems and the amount of books in libraries have been considerably factored in by each college, athletic facilities and the importance of maintaining students'' physical health were not deemed to be significant. However, now is the time that universities equally fund athletic departments and libraries, since physical health is seriously interwined with mental health as well as academic motivation, and there are many learners who learn much more effectively during/after moving their body.\n \nFirstly, athletic department should be equally supported as library because funding support in athletic department can directly lead to improvement of university''s diverse extracurricular activities about exercise, and athletic equipment and facility, which will greatly benefit the whole students'' health. Since physical health hugely affects mental health and academic motivation, more funding for athletic departments will surely improve overall happiness and efficiency in learning. My friend was too obsessed with getting high score on the test once before, so she studied all days except for the meal time without moving her body. As a result, she sufferred from illness, as well as lost momentum in studying. Later, when she tried to regularly exercise, all the problems were solved.\n \nSecondly, it is said by the pedagogists that a type of learners learn more effectively when they move their body. It is very likely that this kinesthetic type of learners are more included in athletic departments than in other majors, and this can be a just reason claiming the need to fund the athletic departments to the equal degree with libraries, since both of them are there for the same reason: to facilitate students'' effective study.\n \nTherefore, universities should equally fund athletic departments and library because increased funding for athletic departments will enhance general athletic facility and exercise activity which will improve overall physical and mental health, as well as academic motivation of students, and kinesthetic learners will benefit from increased funding. Just as libraries, forming supportive environment on campus for exercise and athletic activities can significantly enhance students'' quality of campus life."', '2013-12-13 13:14:46', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(101, 1, '\nWhich is better for children to grow up in the countryside or in a big city.', '"In these days, people attend college or university for a lot of reasons. those depend on their indivisual view. But, In my case, I think that people want to attend college to learn something what they do easily or systemically, to get oppotunity for their future job,and to get to meet peer group who is student with same major.\n\nFirst, many people attend college to learn something easily. If you study somthing what you intersted by youself, you may do very hardly. But professors who is specalist give you systemic information. If you have some question, you may ask them and you may use library in university to find answer. \n\nSecond, the career what graduated college can give more chance when you get a job. If you get the diploma fo high school, you can''t find the job what you desired. For example, if I want to get registerd nursing job, I can''t submit my resume to hospital where I want to work. Because they want registered nurse who graduated university as employee.\n\nThird, When you attend college, you may chance to meet peer group who have same major or interesting something. Because there are a lot of clubs in the college. You can attend anywhere you intrested easily."', '2013-12-16 18:05:38', 'Tagging', 'toefl', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(102, 1, '\nSome people believe that scientist should not take responsibility for their inventions when they have the potential to be dangerous to humans because this people think that inventions which are developed by scientists are so useful for living of human.', '"In these days, people attend college or university for a lot of reasons. those depend on their indivisual view. But, In my case, I think that people want to attend college to learn something what they do easily or systemically, to get oppotunity for their future job,and to get to meet peer group who is student with same major.\n\nFirst, many people attend college to learn something easily. If you study somthing what you intersted by youself, you may do very hardly. But professors who is specalist give you systemic information. If you have some question, you may ask them and you may use library in university to find answer. \n\nSecond, the career what graduated college can give more chance when you get a job. If you get the diploma fo high school, you can''t find the job what you desired. For example, if I want to get registerd nursing job, I can''t submit my resume to hospital where I want to work. Because they want registered nurse who graduated university as employee.\n\nThird, When you attend college, you may chance to meet peer group who have same major or interesting something. Because there are a lot of clubs in the college. You can attend anywhere you intrested easily."', '2013-12-16 18:05:38', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(103, 1, '\n"The best way to truly relax and to reduce stress is to spend time alone.\n\n"', '"This essay could be better.  Your points are pretty weak, so if you want to be convincing you have to support them better.  Also, your second point gets lost in the third paragraph and becomes a different point.  You need to organize your thoughts a little better."', '2013-12-16 18:05:38', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1144, 2, '\n"Plants can provide food, shelter, clothing, or medicine. What is one kind of plant that is important to you or the people in your country? Use specific reasons and details to explain your choice."', '"There may be many plants that is important in every country. Although there are a lot of essential plants in Korea, I think a white cabbage is the most critical plant to the people in my country because of some reasons; a white cabbage is used for making Kimchi, a Korean tranditional food and curing a cold and flu, in Korea.\n\nA white cabbage is the main part of making a Korean conventional food; Kimchi. Kimchi has been eaten by Korean people for a long time and actually is a basic side dish in Korea. In fact, all most Korean family has eaten Kimchi even today. Besides, now Kimchi has been exported to other countries such as Japan and China, and make an amazing profit to my country. To illustrate, according to the Korea Trade Institution, Kimchi takes 50 percent of all export in agriculture. In this respect, a white cabbage is important plant to my country.\n\nIn addition, a white cabbage is used for folk remedy in Korea.  An old book about folk remedy in Korea, Myungsimbogam, represents that a white cabbage is good for curing a cold and flu. Actually, it is common method to cure a cold or flu by by boiling a white cabbage with water in Korea. As an example, when I was a high school student I couldn''t to see a doctor due to the lack of time. In Korea, high school student must study hard to enter the university, thus doesn''t have time to be prescribed some drug. At that time, my mother boiled a white cabbage with water and have me drink it. Surprisingly, I was able to be good in shape because of the effect of a white cabbage. Thus, I believe that a white cabbage is essential plant being used for healing.\n\nConsequently, I strongly believe that a white cabbage is critical plant in my country in that people make Kimchi, a long-historical and fundamental food in Korea using a white cabbage as well as use it for remedy of a cold and flu."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1145, 2, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? With the help of technology, students nowadays can learn more information and learn it more quickly. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer."', '"According to the development of technology, students can take lesson more information and learn it faster. Some people disagree with this situation but I agree because it can share technological information from Internet and learn more easily through TV and radio.\n\nTo begin with, Internet can make share people many technologies. If I want to know scientific technology or semiconductor, I can know instantly it through Internet search. Even I can know much information on the other side of the globe and ask though e-mail. For example, when I was high school student I had to take assignment with a large encyclopedia or in a library. It took a long time and couldn’t give correct information. In addition, with limited time I couldn’t search enough information. However, the more developed is Internet, the easier is searching information and it can be used anytime and anywhere. As a result many students reduced their time and can search correct information.\n\nAnother reason, TV and radio can help students study easily. As broadcast is various and useful programs are established, we can increase chance indirect experience. In addition, as a professional program is made we can study with a small amount of money. For example, when I was elementary school I liked insect. However, I didn’t have chance to meet an insect because I lived in Seoul, metropolitan and capital of Korea. I often saw “World of insect” on TV and it filled my curiosity and was interesting. In addition, people in Seoul have very high concerns about education. Thus annual private educational expanses are spent much. If professional education program is made, not only reduce would private educational expanse but also people would increase chance studying a second language such as English and French.\n\nIn conclusion, with the development of technology, today students can learn more information and learn it faster. Also, Internet can make them search on the other side of the globe, and TV and radio can help them easy to study with less spending. So I agree this statement."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1146, 2, '\nSome people think that they can learn better by themselves than with a teacher. Others think that it is always better to have a teacher. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons to develop your essay.', '"During my school days, I often studied myself about physics, mathematics, and so on. Some people insist that students should have teachers and be learned by a teacher better. Others think students study themselves somewhat. I prefer to second advocacy than first it.\n \nFirst of all, teachers couldn''t adjust to all students. Some students need teaching more, other students need considerable expertise in a class. For instance, in a class, if a student needs more explanation about a easy problem, and if another student asks a more advanced problem, what will a teacher do? A teacher wants to teach all students'' curiosities, however, the time providing a teacher will not be infinite. Thus, students who want to learn more things about their questions study themselves during free times.\n\nSecond, students don''t develop their characteristics. In a uniform class, all students learn and act the same things. Though a student wants to act different ways, the student has to allow a teacher''s teaching. I heard that some children living in the U.S don''t go to school. Instead, they learn something to want at their home. Of famous scientists, some scientists, including Einstein, Edison and so on, didn''t go to elementary or middle school. However, they could grow up so nice.\n\nIn short, I disagree with the fact that students always have a teacher. This is because they don''t develop their characteristics well and learn better about extra courses. However, I don''t think that students must not have a teacher. I believe that one of the best ways to improve educational environments is that two ways are mixed."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1147, 2, '\nYour school has enough money to purchase either computers for students or books for the library. Which should your school choose to buy computers or books? Use specific reasons and examples to support your recommendation.', '"Given the chance that my school should choose to buy computers or books, some people choose books because they can increase thinking ability. In my opinion, however, I choose computers because they can be basic for education. In addition they can be used to find for searching enormous information.\n\nTo begin with, these days computers are basic in job as well as education. Many schools are used to education though computers and it is more efficient for students. According to the Josun-Ilbo, the best-known newspaper in Korean, nowadays elementary school must practice image education for students to elevate ability. Students also like these method much more because it is easy and interesting. For example, my son who is elementary school doesn’t like education of school. He learned image education though computer, and then began to have an interest on school education. Moreover computer’s skill is foundation to business. Most of companies make file using computer and give and take e-mail and files. Thus I recommend computers.\n\nSecond, people can search information though internet. Internet includes more information than books do. Therefore when you want some information you are able to find them though internet. For example, once I must make a paper about M&A. At first, I was very embarrassed because I did not know economics which was not my major. However I could finish and won the praise of many people through computer.\n\nIn conclusion, if my school has enough money to purchase either computers or book my school should choose computers. The reason why I think like this is because not only can computers be standard in education and job, but they also can be used to search information."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1148, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? : Boys and girls should attend separate school. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Some schools usually teach only boys and girls under their regulations. These system has some advantages in enhancing the learning productivity, however, coed school should be recommended due to the following reasons.\n\nFirst, coeducational system can help the sound development of student''s emotions. In the wake of studying together, boys could take naturally girls'' emotional advantages. According to some studies, children who are raised in the co-ed schools have shown less violent characteristics than the otherwise. Coeducation is necessary for the healthy growth of the students.\n\nSecond, students can recognize the other-sex friends better through the attending together. The half of all the humans are women for men and vice-versa. The education system which separates boys and girls would distort the conception of theirs over the human. Coeducation is required for the children when it is viewed of recognition development process.\n\nFinally, God created men and women who must live together. Men and women are given birth to respect and cooperate each other, not for the purpose of separating themselves. All the lives on this planet are getting along with one another regardless of the sex. Coeducation is appropriate for the will of God''s creation.\n\nBoys and girls are distinguishable for the role of the human beings, however, not separable from each other. Coeducational system is more beneficial to the wellbeing and sound development of students than the another."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1149, 2, '\n"Should governments spend more money on improving roads and highways, or should governments spend more money on improving public transportation (buses, trains, subways)? Why? Use specific reasons and details to develop your essay."', '"The choice is difficult whether governments should spend money improving either roads or public transportation. Personally, I agree to develop public transportation. When governments develop that, the air pollution of a city and rates of using natural resources are waned. Moreover, citizens'' welfare is increased.\n \nFirst of all, if governments improve the quality of public transportation, like increasing buses, taxis, and subways, citizens feel more comfortable. Especially, during rush hour, people aren''t hustled by others and don''t feel angry any more. Moreover, because of increasing public transportation, a city can earn more transportation fees than the past. So, a city makes an effort to develop citizens'' welfare and qualities of a city. Thus, citizens feel more happy, comfortable, and refresh.\n\nAlso, if governments increase the number of public transportation, people use them more than the past. Therefore, in the present, one of the greatest social problems, the air pollution is decreased. In addition, another great social problem, deficiency of natural resources is solved automatically. If public transportation is more comfortable than the present, people won''t often use their own cars. Thus, the air pollution is waned and rates of using natural resources are decreased, also.\n \nTo sum up, if governments improve public transportation, our lives in a city are more comfortable. We don''t have any chance of being stressed by public transportation because of crowding in a bus and a subway. Moreover, environment will be cleaner than the present. Thus, we feel more comfortable."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1150, 2, '\n Some famous athletes and entertainers earn millions of dollars every year. Do you think these people deserve such high salaries? Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"There is an argument whether athletes and entertainers should earn such a huge amount of money. I am writing to say that they deserve it, with regard to their efforts and characteristics of their jobs.\n\nFirst of all, it is true that people living in the world have their unique talents. However, the development of their abilities depends on how many efforts they make for a certain period, usually when in school. There must have been many distractions which made them confused, disturbed, or uncomfortable before they become successful. Yet, they have finally overcome difficult situations. I ,therefore, agree that they deserve high salaries ,because it is only fair that people should earn money as much as they dedicate.\n\nSecondly, there are some disadvantages of being both athletes and entertainers. For athletes, it could be fatal if they get physical problems, such as backache, or obesity. There might be nothing to do with them. Therefore, with consideration of this they should earn money enough to be able to live, for the case that they lose their physical abilities. For entertainers, they are always under pressure, because people watch them wherever they go and whatever they do. As a result, they feel much more stressed than ordinary people. By this I mean, they also deserve earning more money than normal people, because they usually suffer from illnesses mentally.\n\nFor these reasons, I strongly believe that entertainers and athletes deserve a huge earning as they make greater efforts and could get physical or mental illnesses more easily than ordinary people."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1151, 2, '\n"You have been told that dormitory rooms at your university must be shared by two students. Would you rather have the university assign a student to share a room with you, or would you rather choose your own roommate? Use specific reasons and details to explain your answer."', '"There is important to meet a variety of people in my life. In the university life, we can also meet several people when we participate in club activity or have some classes. If we have a plan to live in the dormitory, we also have a chance to meet a new people unwillingly. In the dormitory life, I think more good point that we are assigned a new friend as these following reasons.\n\nAbove all, we have a chance to meet a new friend. She may study another thing. She can be older or younger woman than me. If she comes from others country, she can show me different cultures and languages. When I met a new roommate at second grade, she was ready to go to study abroad. From her, I heard many things related to studying in USA. After then, I become to have a dream to go to new country as they can show me more lager world.\n\nMoreover, meeting with a variety of people make me flexible. As we know, no one has the same habits and interests. Sometimes, her behavior makes me angry and also I can make her inconvenient. My roommate and I have another life time, and so I used to go to room when she already sleep. Then she used to wake up for me. We sometimes battled for it. Of course, we tried to have a harmonious point to us.\n\nIn conclusion, a chance to meet a new roommate has some good part to us. It make us more flexible and to have a wide sight in the society. Therefore I would like to be assigned roommate by the university in order to meet new people."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1152, 2, '\nSome people are always in a hurry to go places and get things done. Other people prefer to take their time and live life at a slower pace. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"""Hurry up! Hurry up, please!!"" This sentence is sometimes famous and becomes social issue in Korea. What do you think so? I always remind myself of slow pace and surplus. These conditions help us in a daily life. Two reasons are listed by the following paragraph.\n\nIf you do somthing in a hurry, like preparing a presentation or studying an exam, you may be hurry up. However, your working is clumsy, and you are so embarrased. In this case, I always think ""Slow is the best."" If I must do something in a hurry, at first, I effort to become pacify ,and then I think my duties slowly and deliberately. What I couldn''t think because of embarrasing is realized. Moreover, I can think better solutions or ways than when I was upset. ""Don''t hurry and become pacify"" is my first advocacy.\n\nIn the present, because of developing many technology, a lot of things are much faster than past.  So, many people want that allthings become faster and faster. If poeple don''t have much time, they feel angry, impolite and upset. People anger their around people in that they lay in shortage of times. However, more think, people are not worried about a shortage of times. If they think different way, like the fact that they have much time even though not having much time, they are more lavish in the life.\n\nNow, we find two fortes. Surplus in a life is more important than any other thing. Surplus make our life lavish and happy. As the saying goes, ""If you are in a hurry, you circumvent"', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1153, 2, '\nHow do movies or television influence people’s behavior? Use reasons and specific examples to support your answer.', '"""Television is an idiot box."" It is a widely known fact. However, most people cannot stop watching TV. The reason is that it also includes positive effects although someone is addicted by it. In other words, it has both positive side and negative side.\n\nIn the one hand, television provides us with a great variety of information. For instance, Headline News is updated everyday. Watching it, we catch what we need. Though we gain news from newspapers, TV is more effective to know it exactly like the proverb ‘Seeing is believing’. This summer, it rained cats and dogs, so there was fIood in some areas. We felt problems of sufferers from the flood vividly as watching disaster situation. There was a poll, ‘which mass media is the most credible?’ TV was the first credible one.\n\nIn addition, we have a great indirect experience through just watching TV at home. If we long for seeing Europe, we can also see it. People who have never been to abroad even know what other countries look like. Besides, we recognize how people in different classes live. After acknowledging it, some people help the poor abate their pains as contributing money or others to them.\n\nOtherwise, it makes side effects. Some experts say that one of the most important factors of increasing juvenile crime is TV. In fact, some adolescents imitated to commit crimes through TV. Last winter, a high school student blew grenade out in a public place. Consequently, one person who passed there got hurt severely. The youth stated that he just wanted to experiment the same way that he watched on TV. Yet, TV is not responsible for his crime perfectly. His parents should have controlled him.\n\nLike the common fact that ‘TV is harmful for us’, it may cause bad effects if we use it in wrong ways. Nevertheless, it is the one of the most useful invents because we obtain benefits as using it effectively. Therefore, the effect of it is up to attitudes of its viewers."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1154, 2, '\n"What do you want ''most'' in a friend-someone who is intelligent, or someone who has a sense of humor, or someone who is reliable? Which ''one'' of these characteristics is most importtant to you? Use reasons and specific examples to explain your choice."', '"A person has met many people through his or her life. Someone of them become good friend to a person sometimes. No one want to be a friend with a person who he or she doesn''t like. To be a friend to someone, he or she should have characteristic, such as humor, reliability or intelligence. Although some people want most intelligence or something in a friend, what I most want in my friend is reliability because I can be offered by my friend in hard situation and tell my secret without hesitation.\n\nFirst, I can ask for help to my reliable friend when I get in difficult circumstance. As the saying goes, ''A friend in need is a friend indeed''. I''ll take an examples of my experience related to this; since I live on my own, I have no choice but borrow some money when I have no money. One day, I needed money urgently because my pet became sick. However, some of my friends hesitated to lend money to me. At that time, a friend of mine gives me some money for curing my pet. What made me surprise is that not all friends could be help for me in harsh circumstance. In this manner, I want reliability most in a friend in that only reliable friend could give a hand in severe situation.\n\nSecond, I can tell my secret to my trustful friend and this is the reason why I regard reliability as the most wanted characteristic in my friend.  It is not easy to say something like a secret to someone because the secret could be spilled out. Nonetheless, it is easier to tell a secret to a trustful friend because a person is sure that a reliable friend never spii the beans. For example, I have some secrets of my familly. However, I couldn''t tell about this though I want someone who listen to my secret and understand me. At that time, I met a friend who is trustful and could tell my secret. In this respect, because a reliable friend can hear my secret and I have no doubt that my friend doesn''t say my secret to the others, I want reliability most in a friend.\n\nTo sum up, I want someone who is reliable to be my friend than any other type of people in that a reliable friend of mine gives me a help in difficult environment and I can say my secret with no hesitation."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1155, 2, '\n Some people prefer to eat at food stands or restaurants. Other people prefer to prepare and eat food at home. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Although there are many restaurants in modern society, people are inclined to cook some food at home because they think food made in a restaurant are not as good as that made at home. Nonetheless, I prefer eat out because it is convenient not to make some food and I can taste food which is rare to eat.\n\nThrough eating out, I can be free from making some food. Cooking some food is the most arduous and annoying house task, so I always want to escape the situation to cook, and eating something at the restaurant is the most efficient method to be free from the task. As an example, I was tired because of my heavy homeworks, but I had to cook since my mother went to shopping. At that time, my brother and I went to the restaurant near my house and ordered a pork steak. It is hard to say how I was relieved because I did not have to make food. In this manner, eating out makes me convenient not to cook some food.\n\nIn addition, I can eat exotic food by going somewhere to eat. As a rule, it is seldom to eat foreign food at home. For example, I went to the restaurant with my family, because the day was my father''s birthday. We were able to eat Robster and it was too big to prepare at home. Thus, I prefer to eat food at a restaurant in that I can taste food which is rarely seen and eaten in usual.\n\nConsequently, I preper to eat out for some reasons; convenience not to make food and chance to experience new and fresh food for me."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1156, 2, '\n"When people need to complain about a product or poor service, some prefer to complain in writing and others prefer to complain in person. Which way do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answers."', '"As a customer We have many chances to complain on a certain events or products on a daily basis. Some people like to complain by writing a letter. However, the others like to speak face to face on matters. In my case, I prefer to write a letter for the reason of relationship for the future and organizing systematically.\n\nFirstly, I believe, the basic reason of writing complaint letter is advising bad conditions of the company to be fixed as a customer and also partner. Once I purchased holed clothes in a department store. Right after I found that, I ran into the shop and complained about that hole. Being overly reacted on that matter, I couldn''t control my anger and it made me spoke out harsh words. Eventually, this led me not to go and buy from there. Thus, Rushing into that matter without considering is evident to damage the relationship between customer and company. \n\nSecondly, Writing a complain letter can be more organized and arranged. Usually when we write letter, we tend to make a summary what we will say and take unnecessary words off from the list. It contributes for you to say the essential part of the damage that you have. Similarly, one organized letter can be over thousands of words.&nbsp;&nbsp;and well arranged complaint letter can make the relationship stronger than before.\n\nTo sum up, as the saying goes: Silence is gold. I confirm that the well organized letter and advising complaint letter for the future aspects will achieve more than gold does."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1157, 2, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? Atteding a live performance(for example, a play, concert, or sporting event) is more enjoyable than watching the same event on television. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion. "', '"As I am growing up, I have a plenty of money to enjoy some activities, such as viewing a sports game, attending rock concert. Some people who have money like me enjoy themselves by attending a live performance, while others don''t. In my case, I am disagree with the opinion that a live performance is more fun than watching the same performance on television because I can not concentrate on the game, see the stage and singer, and listen to well, especially in case of music concert.\n\nFirst, owing to less concentration, I am disagree that a live show more joyous than watching the same show on television. For being more delightful, concentration on the performance is the basic factor. I''ll take an example of my experience related to this; in 2002, the Asian games were held in Korea and I went to gymnagium for watching a real game, female soccer between North Korea and South Korea. At that time, although I wanted to join together with other people I couldn''t concentrate on the game because of noise. It is needless to say that I couldn''t enjoy the game. I regreted that it would have been more fun if I had seen the sports game on television. In this manner, watching the same game or show on television is more enjoyable.\n\nSecond, I can see the stage and singer''s face as well as hear songs well when I watch a music concert on television. For example, when watching a Jaurim''s concert, a famous rock musician in Korea, I could see her face very well and listen to her moderate voice exactly. Not interrupted by anyone, I had a special time by watching a music concert program on television at that time. In this respect, I disagree with the statement attending a live show is more delightful than watching the same show on television.\n\nTo sum up, I am against going to a live performance in person to gain much pleasure in that I can not concentrate on the performance and actually, I can see stage and listen to the sound of the show more perfectly by watching television."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1158, 2, '\nPeople do many things to stay healthy. What do you do for good health? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"As the old saying - A sound mind in a sound body - goes, it is very important to maintain health and people do many different things to stay healthy. They run in a park, go to a gym, climb a mountain, take a special nutrient medicine. Among them, as far as I am concerned, I will do a regular exercise and have a balanced diet for good health,\n\nFirst, needless to say, a regular exercise is the most important thing to be healthy. Many people do their exercises to keep in shape, but often do not exercise regularly. The studies have shown that a regular exercise, for example running or swimming everyday or twice a day, is more efficient than doing it 3 days consecutively and resting 4 days in a week. The regular exercise makes the muscles of our body developed continuously and be healthy.\n\nSecond, with a regular exercise, a well-balanced diet also plays an important role to stay healthy. Like fuel of an engine, foods which we eat and drink are energy sources of our activity and exercise. If they consist of a biased diet, For example a fat-riched fastfood, they cannot provide enough energy that our muscles need. Then, although we exercise regularly, our body cannot be developed well because the lack of necessary nutrition ingredients: hydrocarbon, protein, and vitamin.\n\nIn sum, I would say that doing a regular exercise and having a balanced diet are what I will do for good health, as I have mentioned above. With a harmony of these two things, we will be able to keep our bodies in good shapes."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1159, 2, '\nWould you prefer to live in a traditional house or in a modern apartment building? Use specific reasons and details to support your choice.', '"Between a traditional and a modern house, if I should choose one, I would select a traditional house. Of course, a traditional house has many not only advantages but also disadvantages. Howeve, I prefer to live in a traditional house because of following two reasons.\n\nA wall doesn''t exist or is very low. Moreover, it is made up of wood, so ,if you want to destroy it, you always do it. However, because of this wall, our ancestors are familiar with neighborhood. Moreover, it means that they always welcome strangers or visitors. If a wall , like modern it, is made up of stone, concrete and iron, probably our ancestors don''t make friendly releationship with neighborhood or visitors. This is the first reason why I prefer to live in a traditional house.\n\nUsually, a traditional house has a ample courtyard and ground to cultivate vegetables or fruits. Nowadays, many people raise their pets in an apartment. However, it is very impolite and insolent to their neighborhood. If you live in a traditional house which have a sufficent ares to raise pets, you do it without disturbing. It helps your childred to improve their emotion and friendship with other living things. Moreover, you cultivate vegetables and fruits yourself.\n\nIf I am asked ""Which prefer do you live in a traditional or modern house?"", I always say ""I want to have a traditional house."" In that, I raise my pets freely, farm vegetables myself, and more learn about living things. It''s a fantastic and exciting. First of all, in modern society in which love, friendship, etc. are disappeared, we could learn more things which are not educated in school."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1160, 2, '\nA friend of yours has received some money and plans to use all of ti either or to go in vacation or to buy a car. Compare your friend''s two chocies and explaing one you think your friend should choose.', '"Both going on vacation and buying a car seem attractive enough for me to make a tough decision. However, in my case, I would suggest my friend to buy a car. It is because that a car would bring two speicific advatages : convenience and preparation for a financial problem.\n\nTo begin with, my friend can go anywhere with a car.  In other words, he does not need to take public transportaion, meaning convenience. For example, last Christmas season, I was at a shopping mall buying lots of Christmas gifts. After I finished my shopping, I realized I bought so many gifts that it was too heavy to carry. Unfortunately, because I had no car at that time, I had to take a bus with all my lugage. That heavy burden annoyed me and I desired to have a car. This experience shows how people can have benefit with a car. \n\nMoreover, buying a car may be a great solution for unexpected problems. Because I can sell my car amytime, I may use this advantage for my financial problem in the future. For instance, three years ago, one of my cousins ran out of business unexpectedly. He scoured many ways to overcome this predicament but there was only one way to concuer his situation: selling his property. Thus, he solved everything including his car and was able to start a new business.This example shows another advantage of having a car.\n\nFrom what has been mentioned above, I firmly believe that buying a car is more beneficial than going on vacation. I strongly suggest my friend not to spend the money on temporary excitement, vacation, but to purchase a car."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1161, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Businesses should do anything they can to make a profit. Use specific reasons and examples to support your position.', '"Businesses is work to make a profit. If people force to work without their own profits, nobody would not work. However, for busubesses'' profit, using of bad sources, faking by wrong information, or afflicting employees illegally sould be punished.\n\nIn the news paper, an article says, ""A lot of big companies like Nike hire under age people for the companies'' selfish profit."" The companies do even not pay minimum paypent which is seven dollar per hour, and press to work the workers for more than 12 hours.\n\nOf course, I understand businesses can work well on&nbsp;&nbsp;their profit, but the profit should be on the right way for human being. Moreover, the under age workers in the article are also one of the member who works for his or her company, but the company''s profit is not fairly shared for all of the members.\n\nThus, I disagree with that businesses should do ""anything"" they can make a profit; I agree with that businesses can make their profit if the profit is made fairly, legally, and conscientiously."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1162, 2, '\nYour school has enough money to purchase either computer for students or books for the library. Which should your school choose to buy – computers or book? Use specific reasons and examples to support you recommendation.', '"Computers and books do the same thing if you think about the fact that they both give information. But books are much better when you compare the effectiveness between those two. So I strongly recommend the school to buy books instead of computers.\n\nFirstly, computers need to be upgraded while books don’t.  A computer becomes a thing of the past unless you keep upgrading them every 3 years or so. But books do not need to be upgraded. As a matter of fact, there are many novels that have been read from a hundred years ago and that are still being read – Tom Sawyer, Robinson Crusoe, Sherlock Homles. These books do not become a bunch of useless paper a few years later unlike computers which become heavy useless metal.\n\nSecond, schools do not need computers. Almost all the students have their own personal computers at home with better devices that they use all day after coming home from school. And they already use the computer very well without the school and teachers helping them. But students do not have enough books to read at home. So the school should provide what the students really need.\n\nLast of all, only one person can use one computer at a time and even that person cannot use the computer any longer than one class.  But if you use the money to buy twenty 5$ books instead of one 1000$ computer, a lot more people can use the information at the same time for as long as they want. As you can see, this is much more effective because you already have 600 books that everybody can use instead of 30 computers that only one person can use at a time and have to go in a couple of years.\n\nPeople say that students aren’t reading enough books nowadays. But this is partially the teachers’ and school’s fault because they were buying computers which has a life cycle of few years, which students already have at home, and which could have been 20 books per computer instead."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1163, 2, '\nMany students have to live with roommates while going to school or university. What are some of the important qualities of a good roommate? Use specific reasons and examples to explain why these qualities are important.', '"Due to long commuting distance between their school and home, or due to financial problems, many students have to live with their roommates in a boarding house to save money. But it is not easy to find an appropriate person for your roommate and even harder for you to set those qualities for a good roommate because it completely depends on what kind of school life you are going to have.\n\nYet when it generally comes to the important qualities in choosing a roommate,  it is needless to say that you should choose a person who doesn''t make any noise and problems because it will be very annoying if he or she tries to do something very noisy when you are about to study. And it''s even more with the case when you are taking exams at school. Suppose that you have to study hard for the mid-term exam but your roommate keeps on talking on the phone for many hours. How annoying it would be! So I will choose being quiet is the most important factor among the qualities of a good roommate.\n \nSecondly, being clean is also an important quality of a good roommate. If the roommate is the kind of person who keeps on making a mess in your room, you''ll just end up cleaning your room everyday, which is waste of time. Meeting a roommate who pursuits cleanness as the top priority in his life makes your dormitory life refreshing and satisfying, I think.\n \nThere is one thing that you should keep in your mind. That is, you should not demand your roommate be clean and quiet when you make a mess and a noise, which will just make your roommate hatred towards you. Before you demand such things from your roommate, be a silent and clean roommate yourself First!"', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1164, 2, '\n"Some people think governments should spend as much money as possible exploring outer space (for example, traveling to the Moon and to other planets). Other people disagree and think governments should spend this money for our basic needs on Earth. Which of these two opinions do you agree with? Use specific reasons and details to support your answer."', '"Exploring outer space can not be done by a few people, a company or a labratory because it requires a lot of money, advanced technology and a long period of performing projects. Thus, it is smoetimes said that aids of governments are essential for completing the lagre projects. However, I think that spending money for exploring outer space is not a prior duty of governments.\n\nThere are still many basic needs to be solved in our world, Earth. Not a few problems in our world and society are so serious and emergent that governments should be in a major role to slove them. Environmental crisis, poverty, diseases, war and other issues are always around us. For governments, the first thing to do is settling the better world for all people. Thus, it is not proper to invest for outer space without solving basic needs on Earth.\n\nOther important reason to oppose spending much money for exploring outer space is that the exploring can be used for military purpose. Actually, some countries are competing with each other to have the most dominant power to conquer the outer space. Sending sattelites and other space facilities are necessary for expanding range to search information of opponent countries. Thus, if it is not for the pure science research, exploring space is not desirable for making peace of world.\n\nIn conclusion, governments should as much money as possible for important problems for people instead of investing for outer space. If the reason of the exploring is mainly for military purpose, the choice of governments is much more apperant. It should be reminded that governments exist for people, society and world on Earth."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1165, 2, '\nParents are the best teacher.', '"Generally, children learn a lot of knowleadge from their parents. However, I disagree with that parents are the best teacher, since there are some problems for parents to teach their children. For instance, most parents have a limited quality of knowleadge and a limited suppy of free time to teach thier own children. So I strongly believe that teachers are more good at teaching children.\n\nFirst, many parensts are not specialized on teaching someone else. Some of them might have only basic knowleadge which is not enough to teach their children. For example, a boy who wants to know thow to differntiate, and if his parents haven''t learned differnetiation, he will be not able to learn it from his parents. However, a Mathematics teacher can teach the boy about not only differentiation but also integration, because he or she has mathematical knowleadge. Since teachers uaually have a higher level of knowleadge, teachers are more helpful for children.\n\nSecond, most of parents are too busy for doing their jobs. They don''t even have time for having conversation with their children. On the other hand, teachers are always waiting for children to teach them about what they know. They also want to help children about anything. For teachers, teaching children is their job. They are trained to educate children which means they are the best teachers. Recently, both Mom and Dad are working in the number of families, which makes it harder for them to teach their children.\n\nIn conclusion, I disagree with that parents are the best teacher. They don''t have much knowleadge to teach special fields such as Biology, Chemistry, Accounting and so on. They are not free enough from their jobs or housework to help their children. Well- trained teachers, who love children as much as children''s parents, are the best teachers in the world."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1166, 2, '\n Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? Grades (marks) encourage students to learn. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"Grades denote student statements of the studying. Statement of the student is significant for student who receives good grades or middle grades or bad grades. I consider that grades are not all but important things because they are almostly impartial consequence.\n\nFirstly. Grades can give student the pleasing. It activate to student to encourage studying. The students who take mathmatics grade A are happpy because that is a fair consequence for their effort. And then they can determine that in more much effort they will be good student than now.\n\nSecondly. On the other hand, there are pupils. They might be study a little or nothing. they also receive impartial consequence for their efforts. they maybe sad or nonchalant. Sad students must resolve the problem. And then if they want. they can be good students. The others indifferent students and not resolving the problem are not almost solved by grades and other.\n\nMarks for students are always accompanied during student periods. Students who receive this fact can be good students . They are genious not sagacious. They will know the quality of efforts and theirselves happyness. This is actually expensive for students."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1167, 2, '\nSome people believe that a college or university education should be available to all students. Others believe that higher education should be available only to good students. Discuss these view. Which view do you agree with? Explain why.', '"Here in Korea, to enter a college or university, students stay up nights and go into the dog eat do world. The thing is students are only concerning on getting high scores and it eventually turns into no good to anyone. If a good student in this above statement means that of korea, I don''t agree with a statement that only a good student should be allowed to get high-level education.\n\nTo begin with, What is a good student?  I am sure that a good student is the person who is eager to learn no matter how his or her grade is good because the point is how arduous they are. For example, a good student in korea is the one having good number on their report card. I''ve seen a lot of them whom are so used to choosing right answers on exams without knowing and even thinking the procedures. Thus, I believe the chance of education should go to everyone who wants to learn even if the person is not titled as a good student.\n\nAdditionally, endowing the chance of learning to all is an important factor which leads into whole nation grows. Being taught by academically, social members in a country will form their values through education generally. The one that has given the chance to people to learn is a country but after all, the one that will get its result is a nation itself. Once I read a article about a man who was so poor in his childhood that couldn''t get the proper education. However, with the help of government, succeeding all academic courses, gives back all the money he has earn to his patron. Similarly, investing the money to grow the person who needs to country is not useless.\n\nTo sum up,&nbsp;&nbsp;when it comes to high education, I believe, the chance should go to all equally because it is a wise way of invest for the purpose of growing the intelligent, and also nourishing a real good student without the matters of number."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1168, 2, '\nSome people prefer to live in a small town. Others prefer to live in a big city. Which place would you prefer to live in?', '"I have lived here, a small town since family came near the Seoul. While Seoul is big city, my town, Suwon is so old and small city but developing. Many people like to live in a big city like Seoul, However others hope to live in a small town, like me. Although both them have good parts, more people live to a small village as it has clean environment and kind neighbors.\n\nBig cities have lots factories, transportations and apartments where people live. Most factories and methods of transportation make bad air and contribute to the pollution. Also people take out their fluent garbage. Otherwise small towns have a little them relativity. In my case, I felt very pollution in there when I went to go big city. In my nose, it is very dirty and has black dust. My collar became the black by polluting materials. But in my town, I need not clean my shirts everyday.\n\n We will meet very kind people when I live in a small town. Nowadays many people do not greet to neighbors and even they do not know who live next door. When my family moved to now home, neighborhood came to my home firstly and say hello to us. They sometimes gave us their making food. When I had a celebrating for graduation, they gave a pleasure to me and were happy with my family.\n\nI heard that many older persons want to live in a small town and go to the hometown. Most hometowns are so small. As these towns give fresh air and have more chances to meet kind people. So I would like to live in a small town if I have chance to select my habitat."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1169, 2, '\n It is sometimes said that borrowing money from a friend can harm or damage the friendship. Do you agree or disagree?', '"I oppose that borrowing money from friends can harm my friendship. It is because that lending money from them may be a great solution for my financial situation and paying back their money shows my responsibility.\n \nTo begin with, borrowing money from my friends is sometimes very helpful, especially, for the emergent situation. For example, last Christmas season, I was at a shopping mall looking for the Christmas gifts for my parents. Accidentally, I lost my debit card there. Because the day was Dec.24th, it was the only time to buy the gifts. Thus, I borrowed money from my friends and I was able to finish my shopping on the same day. In other words, with the money that I borrowed from them, I solved an unexpected problem.\n\nMoreover, as I pay back the money, I may become a responsible person. If I do not pay back their money on time, I will be blamed and my friendship will be harmed. On the other hand, repaying the money will show how I feel about their aid. For instance, after the last Christmas season, I pay backed the money to my friends right away. I even added interest because I really appreciated their help. My friends were also surprised by my behavior and impressed. My experience shows another advantage of borrowing money from the friends.\n\nFrom what has been mentioned above, I strongly oppose the idea: borrowing money form a friend can harm the friendship. I do not believe that money, which belongs to a human-made substance, is much less important than any abstract subjects, my friendship."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1170, 2, '\n"You have been told that dormitory rooms at your university must be shared by two students. Would you rather have the university assign a student to share a room with you, or would you rather choose your own roommate? Use specific reasons and details to explain your answer."', '"If I decided to live in dormitory, I would rather have the university assign a student to share a room with me. Some people might think it would be uncomfortable to share a room with someone unknown. And they would possibly prefer to choose their own roommate. However, I still can see some merits to share a room with an unfamiliar person.\n\nObviously, it would not be easy to live with a stranger. At first, I would feel awkward. But I could use this situation as an opportunity. I mean, as we know, I can hardly get a chance to live with someone unknown. Actually, In my case, I have never lived with someone, who is not my family member. So If I had shared a room with someone unknown, I would be able to learn how to live with people cooperatively. In other words, I would be more considerate and tolerate so as to get along with her well. This experience would be very valuable in my life. Sometimes, my individualistic characteristic can appear to others as indifferent. But If I had a chance to regard for other''s feeling deliberately, I guess that would be helpful to improve my characteristics positively.\n\n&nbsp;&nbsp;And there is another reason I would have a university assign a student as my roommate. I have seen so many cases, once friends lived together, and Then they had big conflicts. Finally, they stop keeping touch each other. If I chose my roommate, I would definately want to live with my friend because I would not need to take care of my roommate too much. I could freely behave and relax in my room. This was the biggest mistake of most of unhappy roommates. They wanted to live with a friend so as to feel comfortable. But this caused a lot of problems, because they did not take care of each other while they were in the same room. Frankly speaking, I guess I would make the same mistake if I were in that situation. And I do not have any confidence to make much efforts on living with my friend harmoniously. I think this is ironic. I feel so free to be with my friend so I can hardly take care of her a lot. So I would rather prefer living with a student assigned by a university.\n\nIn conclusion, there is no doubt that living with someone is difficult. But after the time, I am certain we would be able to learn something significant. In my case, I guess I would be able to learn how to respect other''s feelings and get along with other cooperatively. Even though, there must be some disadvantages to share a room with a student assigned by a university, I would like to try this. That is because I believe this would bring me more desirable effects."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1171, 2, '\n" Imagine that you are preparing for a trip. You plan to be away from your home for a year. In addition to clothing and personal care items, you can take one additional thing. What would you take and why? Use specific reasons and details to support your choice."', '"If I have a chance to be away from my home for a year, I would like to take a laptop computer besides clothing and personal care items. A computer is very important in my life and all of my daily activities are going on with my not book computer. Through several definite examples, I will demonstrate that a laptop computer is the best thing that I would like to bring with me for my a-year trip.\n\nFirst, I can mail to my family and friends using my laptop computer. With the help of the Internet, it is very easy to correspond with my family and friends. Once I was in Canada for 1 year, I used to use e-mail to contact my family and friends. It is very fast and cheap. Besides, there are some kinds of messenger service, which enable people to chat in the Internet. I usually chat with my family and friends with messenger service. It is free of charge and real time.\n\nMoreover, it is very easy to get the travel site information through the Internet. There are a lot of web sites that are provided by travelers, travel companies and local government agencies. I can make a use of it not only for gathering the general site information but also for cutting down my travel expense by adopting the best way to travel, which a lot of former travelers have been experienced. Before taking a trip, I usually visit website to get information. But for a 1-year-long trip, I would like to bring my laptop with me and check the information day by day whenever I want to move another place.\n\nLast but not least, I can record my journey. It is one of my hobbies to keep the record of my journey. There will be a lot of things that I want to memorize, but I cannot remember all happenings and all information. Using my laptop computer, I can write down my daily schedule, my feelings about the places that I visit or stay. After returning from the trip, it helps me to review and recall my trip.\n\nTo sum up, if I bring a laptop computer, I can have a lot of benefits from it. I can get a lot of information about the travel place, I can send and get mail easily, and I can keep the record of my journey. With these great advantages, why not take a laptop computer to your trip?"', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1172, 2, '\n You have received a gift of money. The money is enough to buy either a piece of jewelry you like or tickets to a concert you want to attend. Which would you buy? Use specific reasons and details to support your answer.', '"If I received money as a gift from somebody, I would buy a piece of jewelry. There are several reasons why I want to buy the jewelry rather than to go the concert. Here I will demonstrate the reasons with definite examples.\n\nFirst, a piece of jewerly can be a fortune. Anybody has a possibility to be in difficulties in his/her life. When people are financially trapped, they can sell the jewelry they own to have a liquidity. For example, when I was a high school student, my father''s business was almost bankrupt due to korea''s financial recession. At that time, many people in korea lost their jobs and business owners downsized their companies and employees. My father was no exception. However, the jewrly my mother possessed helped my father to save his business. From this exprience, I realized the jewerly is valuable for our rainy days. Therefore, I prefer buying a piece of jewelry to attending concert.\n\nSecond, I can watch the concert on TV even though it is not vivider than on the spot. As the technology in audios and videos is getting developed, we have better chances to see&nbsp;&nbsp;performances and listen to the music through the media than ever. Whenever we turn on the TV, we can meet many celebrities who we may wish to meet. For instance, when I went to the concert of Jo Sung-mo, one of the most famous singers in Korea a few years ago, I was really disapointed because I was too far from the stage to see and enjoy the concert. Watching it on TV was much better at that time. Therefore, I would rather buy the jewerly than go to the concert.\n\nIn short, If I have a money received from someone as a gift, I would buy the jewerley because I can use it when I have a financial difficulty. In addition, I can enjoy the concert through TV or radio."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1173, 2, '\nYour school has received a gift of money. What do you think is the best way for your school to spend this money? Use specific reasons and details to support your choice.', '"If my school has received a gift of money, I recomme my school to spend this money in the exchange of the old computers. I think in university it is the most effective way to invest money in the computer systems. There are three reasons: we can accquire the information fast through the computer, and the computer make us do various tasks, and we can get the job easily for the computers.\n\nTo begin with, I recommend my school to spend this money in the exchange of the old computers. Nowadays, the importance of getting information is increasing greatly. Today is the day of the imformation. Especially, through the Internet we can get a variety of the information fast and wide. However, the computer systems in my university are so out of date that I can not obtain the information fast. Many students in the university complain about the slowness of the Internet due to the out of date computers. Therefore, I strongly believe that the brand new computers can make it possible for us to get the informatio fast and wide, and this can add to the prestige of my unversity.\n\nApart from the covenience of the Internet, the new computer can make the students do a lot of things. There are many things for us to do by computers. As a whole, most of the students make the reports by computers, and some of the students use the computers for their graphic designs. However, the brand new computers are so expensive that many students can not afford to buy it. As for my university, although the computers system is rather out of date, many students want to use this. Thus, the computer rooms are always packed with the students, and many students wasted their time in waiting the lines. Therefore, I recommend my school should buy more computers to satisfy the need of the students.\n\nFinally, the computers are also useful for getting the job of the students. Nowadays, many firms want to recruit those students who are expert in the computer skill. If my university is well furnished with the new computers, the students are able to get the precious experience with it. Thus, the students of my university get the more opportunity to have the good jobs.\n\nTo sum up, investing money in the computer systems is the most effective way in my university because we can accquire the information fast through the computers, and because the computers make us do various tasks, and because we can get the job easily. Why not buying the computers?"', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1174, 2, '\n Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? People are never satisfied with what they have; they always want something more or something different. Use specific reasons to support your answer.', '"In general, people are not satisfied with what they have. In many religions, because of this tendency, people can never feel happy. Perhaps, that is true. But the other side of the coin of the fact is that people have developed themselves so as to get something more. I mean this tendency encourages people to try harder to develop themselves in both positive way and negative way. So I think it is worth thinking about the reason people are never satisfied with what they have.\n\nNowadays, it has been a boom of lottery in Korea. Surprisingly, according to the statistics, there were some rich people, more than average, won the first prize. In other words, even though they were considered rich enough, they bought a lottery. Why is that?? I think it is because people normally compare a person, having something more or better than them, with themselves. Therefore, in spite of being considered rich, as long as there is more rich person, he or she can never be satisfied with what they have. Actually, most of human being has a kind of instinct to be better than others. So they can not give up trying to get more than others. In this respect, people can never reach the peak of their hope or goal in whole life.\n\nIn academic field, this tendency could play an important role. People want to know something more than others. They are never satisfied with what they have already known. So, they try to study many scientific aspects and social events. I guess people base this tendency on basic curiosity. When they are born, they do not have any knowledge of the world, such as the reason, if they touch hot water, they feel hurt. But as they are growing up, they have learnt a lot from experience or books. But these sources are also not enough to fulfill their basic curiosity. So because of their curiosity, people can never been satisfied with what they have already known. They need something new and different from previous knowledge.\n\nIn conclusion, it has both positive and negative aspects that people can not satisfied with what they have. But I think both aspects are kinds of basic human instinct. I mean people want to be better than someone else so they want to get something more. And also, people have much curiosity to know about the world so they try to have more knowledge. I think that is why people can never stop trying to get something more and different."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1175, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? It is more important for students to study history and literature than it is for them to study science and mathematics. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"In general, the knowledge can be divided into two types: natural knowledge and social knowledge. Science and math are important components of former, while history and literature are essential parts of the latter. We may find that our personal interests draw us to one field of study more than any other. But I believe that no one can argue that it is more important to study any of these fields over the others.\n \nFirst, only complete knowledge can make a really knowledgeable man/woman. We know that the world consists of not only the object studied by the subject like science and math, but also invisible things studied by the subjects like history and literature. Lack of knowledge will lead to an incomplete view about the world. For example, a student specializing in the mathematics will need in-depth understanding of philosophy and its history.\n\nSecondly, the social knowledge and natural knowledge are both necessary for the continuation of our civilization. Science and mathematics form the foundation of all our physical structures. Without these fields we could not have buildings, automobiles, airplanes and all the myriad machines necessary for them to run successfully. However, without understanding of the world and humanism earned from the social knowledge, the civilization could be dangerous. As science develop, the horror of a mass destruction weapon is getting to increase. If we don’t learn the value of life from the literature and a risk of such weapon from the history, the third world war can happen on the earth again.\n\nIn conclusion, I disagree that it is more important for students to study history and literature than to study science and mathematics. The world and its history cannot be divided into neat categories. I think that it is essential to have a balance in the study of the natural and social knowledge."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1176, 2, '\nSome high schools require all students to wear school uniforms. Other high schools permit students to decide what to wear to school. Which is better?', '"In Korea, most high school students have to wear school uniforms. However, I&nbsp;&nbsp;think that the students need to decide what to wear to school because it is part of education and the cost of uniforms is expensive.\n\nFirst, the students could learn about how to express themselves while they choose their clothes.  In general, clothes are very important in that people can know about others throughout not only their impression but also their clothes. For example, if I met someone who wear jeans, I could guess that he likes comfortable things. Thus, people need to learn how to express themselves with clothes and what kind of design and color suit for themselves. Even though reading, writing and studying is more necessary for students, thinking about themselves is also important.\n\nFurthermore, some parents have to spend a lot of money to buy their children''s uniform because it is very expensive. In Korea, the cost of uniforms is about two hundred thousand one and it is almost same as suits for adults. Also, students throw away their uniform after graduating school. If they wear freely, a lot of money could be saved or used for more effective things. When stuents have things which they like to wear anywhere, they could use them long enough.\n\nEven though school uniform have many merits, I think that students need to choose how to wear and think about what clothes suit for them because it is sort of learning themselves and they could save money. If Korean student wear as they want to do, they could feel more free about themselves."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1177, 2, '\nWhat are some important qualities of a good supervisor(boss)? Use specific reasons and examples why these qualities are important.', '"In our daily work of lives, we always have our supervisors who control us, scold us, and predict orders to us. And by them, our works can be enjoyable or hateful. So I think some important qualities which a good supervisor must have are objectiveness and a sense of responsibility among several qualities.\n\nFirst, a good and admirable supervisor should have objectiveness. In most our business lives, we are judged by the efforts that we have invested and the results that we have got. So unless they are judged objectively by the supervisor whom we work for, we cannot feel a sense of accomplishment and will not follow the orders from our boss. Then it will be evident that our work office or factory cannot get the progress because our effort and capability are not admitted well.\n\nSecond, a sense of responsibility is needed to a good boss. We, as a human, do not everything perfectly and may fail or make a mistake. At that time, a good supervisor should be able to hide our small faults and even take all responsibility for us. In doing so, we will trust him and can work better for him.\n\nFrom these two reasons, I feel that a good supervisor should have both objectiveness and a sense of responsibility in order to lead his followers well. From him, we can learn the valuable things which we should know to become a good business man, and our work will be enjoyable working with him. Furthermore, we will be able to be the ideal model as a good boss to our would-be followers in the future."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1178, 2, '\n" In general, people are living longer now. Discuss the causes of this phenomenon. Use specific reasons and details to develop your essay."', '"In the consequence of technical development, things have changed a lot. So as to this change, human-beings live longer than the past. Of course there are a lot of reasons, I think both the improvement of medical techniques and the nutritional diet tables cause this phenomenon. To illustrate why I convince my point, I will treat only a few significant reasons with my vivid experience as follows.\n\nAbove all, I want to point out break-though development in medical techniques. For example, according to a medical magazine, surveyed in 2003, human-beings'' median life span is 88 years old. This scrutiny shows the life span has increased more 20 years than the past. It causes the development in treatment for patient. Therefore, I am of the idea that improved medical techniques help this phenomenon.\n\n Another reason is eating habit. As human-being live in comfortable circumstance, they have concerned with the nutrition in foods. So, when people think of profusions, they often envision nutrition which these foods contain. And, they usually have habitual eating time for their health. In addition, they prefer to eat vegetables, rather than to eat meat. Because vegetables prevent fat, and enable people to clean their blood. In other words, to eat nutritious and balanced diet tables keep them more healthful. Thus I think balanced and nutritious diet tables help for people to live longer than the past.\n\nAll in all, I strongly think that human-beings live longer than the past. The reason why I think like this is not only because the medical techniques have improved, but also the diet tables have more nutritious than the past. Of course there are a lot of reasons to consider, I believe there is no substitution for afore-mentioned things."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1179, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Children should be required to help with household tasks as soon as they are able to do so. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"In the past in Korea, children were valuable workers. Therefore, parents had the tendency to have more children. In the course of time, However, parents had fewer kids than before and seemed to cherish them. That is to say, children were hardly expected to become a energy source. However, if kids did not help household chores, they would not lose the important factors such as the relation and respect.\n\nFirst of all, household things need conversation. It means that the relation between family members could be better than before through talking about each other. For example, my father was always a being hard to say something related with family affairs. But, as time has passed, I had the chance to settle this chilly relationship through having a dialogue from simple to complex. Now, I have the good relationship with my father. If I did not assist household matters, it would be impossible for me to recover this situation.\n\nNext, housing chores such as doing a laundry and dishes are not simple. However, If I did not directly practice them, it would be impossible for me to know how complex they are and what kinds of knowhow I need to settle the problem. Although they do not appear complex, they have a procedure and method. Only parents know this kinds of the procedure and method. As learning them, I came to respect our parents again.\n\nTo make a story to short, as a coin has two side, there are pros and cons about bring children to clean house chores. Although, now it is not in the past, other sorts of mediums make us to earn important components including relationship between family members and respect for their parents. If I did not choice them, I would maybe earn merit; good relationship and reverence."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1180, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Playing games teaches us about life. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"In these days, gamers tend to increase gradually. Some people say playing games don''t have benefits at all; I don''t think that. Through playing games, I could learn about coordinating. In addition, I delete stress which I received in daily lives.\n \nHave you ever play a on-line game?  On-line games are developed recentely. What''s the on-line game? The definition of a on-line game is that through an Internet, they play a game with other people. They can chat and play with other players. So, if they want to play with others nice and interesting, they must keep politness. In this situation, they can learn about politeness.\n\n For a long time, ancestors have played games, for they wanted to treat stress. While they worked, studied&nbsp;&nbsp;and so on hard, they had suffered from stress. So, many games have been developed in many countries. For instance, our ancestors in Korea had many games, playing four traditional musical instruments, Ca-jyun Nol-yi etc. When they watched them, they felt exting, fun, extreme and so on. Through games, they treated stress received in daily lives.\n\nI think that if persons play games, they can much learn about lives. Above mentioned it, they can learn politeness and eliminate stress. I want to tell you; if you have a problem in lives, how about playing a games some of the times? I think that you say ""that''s a good idea!.""."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1181, 2, '\nSome people believe that a college or university education should be available to all students. Others believe that higher education should be available only to good students. Discuss these views. Which view do you agree with? Explain why.', '"In these days, higher education can be available to all student in Korea because the recognition that people who want to be educated are eligible to study spreads society. However, some people say that higher education should be prepared for good student. In my opinion, college or university education should be open to all student in that education should be fair in any case and we could discover some talents we miss.\n\nFirst, education should be open to every student because everyone has the right to be educated. I think, if the society does not gives people who want to study the chance to be informed, it is not for the everyone. It could be said unfair society. For example, Choseun Dinasity, Korea 500 years ago, gives the right to be educated only to selected people, Yangban. However, there is no difference between selected people and non-selected people In fact. Although non-selected people had the right to be educated, people at that times didn''t know how important the right is. Consequently, Choseun Dinasity had fallen down slowly. Does the society at these days make that mistake, too? In this manner, though it sounds theoretically, because everyone has the right to be informed education should be given to every student.\n\nSecond, if we offer higher education to good student we can''t find the talents we omit. Some students who are proved ''not good'' could have some talents in other areas. For example, a friend of mine who couldn''t go to university because of her low grade in high school possesses the ability to draw something like people''s face and movement artically. Nevertheless, she was not admitted to study art more since she was not successful in mathematics and science. In this respect, I think higher education should be available to every student in that we can see the capacity which can be lament now.\n\nTo sum up, I think higher education should be offered to every student because of the right to be educated in modern society and the ability we could miss. The more education, the more talents we could discover."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1182, 2, '\n"Some people think governments should spend as much money as possible exploring outer space (for example, traveling to the Moon and to other planets). Other people disagree and think governments should spend this money for our basic needs on Earth. Which of these two opinions do you agree with? Use specific reasons and details to support your answer."', '"It becomes to be a heatedly debated issue whether governments should spend exploring outer space or not. Some people hold the opinion that spending money for our basic needs on the Earth. However, others insist that exploring outer space is quite important for people in that maybe there are some intelligent lives in space. If I should choose one of these positions, I choose the latter. I have specific reasons to support my argument.\n\nAs you know, Earth’s resources such as gas, coal and iron is limited. According to some article of some scientific newspapers, we will use all of resources we have within 100 years. Some scientists say that big wars for obtaining resources will start. It is a catastrophe to all. However, we have one solution through exploring outer space. There are 7 planets in our system and there are a lot of stars in our galaxy. In some planets or stars, there are good resources we can use. Exploring outer space not only give us resources but also prevent our catastrophe.\n\n Another reason that can be seen by every one is meteolites. There are a lot of meteolites between planets. Most of the meteolites are far away from the earth, but some can be close to the earth. As you know, before advent of human beings, Earth is the dinosaur’s world. But when a single large meteolites clash with Earth, they were extinct. It can recur to human beings. To preclude impact of meteolites, it is worthy to spend money for exploring outer space.\n\nAdmittedly, to explore outer space we should spend so much money. However considering exploring space is what we do to survive. I believe it is wiser to spend as much money as possible exploring outer space."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1183, 2, '\n A company has announced that it wishes to build a large factory near your community. Discuss the advantages and disadvantages of this new influence on your community. Do you support or oppose the factory? Explain your position.', '"It causes many advantages to build a large factory near my community; such as more jobs and increased revenue. However, it has another aspect; environmental problems, congested traffic. In my view, I approve to build a factory near my town. Now, let''s look into my opinions.\n \nIf a company has announced to build a large factory near a town, residents living in a town oppose to build it at first. They think that a factory destroy their environments such as air, water, and plant. Moreover, due to the fact that more trucks drive in a town than the past, traffics of the town are more increased. Thus, people feel more uncomfortable and they regret to permit to build a factory.\n\nOn the other hands, if a company building a factory invests more money to develop roads in a town, to purifying environment and to eliminate industrial waste, residents are more fresh and comfortable. Moreover, a factory pays many revenue to a local government. Therefore, a local government invests more money to improve residents'' welfare. If so, community grow more fast and quality of residents'' lives develop better; such as more fresh environment, comfortable town, and a lot of amenities. Also, young people''s employment opportunities increase, too.\n\nTo sum up, if a factory engage to build purifying systems of environment, I always agree to build it. There are a lot of advantages. Benefits are greater than dangers. I support to build a factory and hope that readers accord my opinion."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1184, 2, '\n"Should governments spend more money on improving roads and highways, or should governments spend more money on improving public transportation (buses, trains, subways)? Why? Use specific reasons and details to develop your essay."', '"It is difficult to choose whether goverments should spend money improving either roads or public transportation. Personally, I agree to develop public transportation. When goverments do that, air pollution of a city and rates of using natural resource are waned. Moreover, citizens'' welfare is increased.\n \nFirst of all, if goverments improve qualities of public transportation, like increasing buses, taxis, and subways, citizens feel more comfortable. Especially, during rush hour, people aren''t hustled by others and don''t feel angry more. Moreover, because of increasin public transportation, a city can earn more transportation fee than the past. So, a city makes an effort to develop citizens'' welfare and qualities of a city. Thus, citizens feel more happy, comfortable, and fresh.\n\nAlso, if goverments increase a number of public transportation, people use them more than the past. Therefore, in the present, one of the great social problems, air pollution are decreased. In addition, another great social problem, deficiency of natural resource are solved automatically. If public transportation are more comfortable than the present, people don''t often use their own cars. Thus, air pollution are waned and rates of using natural resource are decreased, too.\n\nTo sum up, if goverments improve public transportation, our lives in a city are more comfortable. We don''t have any chance of stressing by public transportation because of crowding in bus and subway. Moreover, environments will be clearer than the present. Thus, we feel more fresh."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1185, 2, '\nHow do movies or television influence people''s behavior? Use reasons and specific exmaples to support your answer.', '"It is easy for young people to get influenced by the media. Nowdays young kids spend more times watching movies or television than they spend times with thier family, they learn things that are inappropriate for themselves, such as taking drugs or smoking cigarettes at the young age. For young girls, they get to have the wrong definetion of being pretty from the idol movie stars among the young girls.\n\nMy friend''s brother, Eric is a fifth grade kid who thinks of himself as one of the coolest persons in the school. His behaviors towards his friends or teachers are very impolite, and he believes that smoking cigarettes and taking drugs with several older kids in the school are the only way to become popular. Whenever his sister, Marta tries to talk to him about his behaviors in the school, one of the famous lines that has always been come out of his mouth is, ""I do those kinds of things because I saw people doing on television shows or movies and they seemed cool."" He has gotten some immoral ideas of being a popular, good student through the unintelligent TV programs or movies.\n\n My younger sister has been complaining about her body shape and face, lately. She skips the meals to get skinny like a stick, and urges my parents to let her have a plastic surgery so that she can be satisfied with much bigger eyes, a higher nose, thicker lips, and a smaller face than all of hers. All the famous stars on television or movies have the perfact image-the Barbie doll type, and these young girls definetely believe that in order to be called as a beauty, they need to look a like superstars. They do not pay attention how to be healthy, they only care about how to look beautiful to the people.\n\nThere are many unintelligent programs and movies that can lead young people''s mind into the bad direction. Since young people does not have the ability to judge what is wrong or bad, young kids tends to take wrong inpressions from what they see on TV and movies. In some what ways, Media needs to concentrate on better contents for young people."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1186, 2, '\nA company has announced that it wishes to build a large factory near your community. Discuss the advantages and disadvantages of this new influence on your community. Do you support or oppose the factory? Explain your position.', '"It is often argued that having a large factory in my community has more advantages or more disadvantages. The following essay outlines the pros of building this in my community and the cons of.\n\nOne of the most outstanding cons is that it can lead to serious pullution in my town, including water, soil, and air pollution. As a result, it can possibly affect the ecosystem badly, which should be preserved safely. It is possible that we might not be able to drink, breathe, or raise some vegetables in our land.\n\n There also must be more people in my town than ever, when we decided to agree to build a large factory. The more people there are, the more problems there are. Like this sentence just mentioned, there will be more crimes ,because criminals usually go common places where people are bustling to get a better chance to steal money readily.\n\nHowever, it could be helpful for the economy of my town to have such a large factory. When we had a large factory, people around our town would assemble ,and so consequently they would have to spend their money to buy something to eat, to entertain themselves, or to support their families.\n\nTo conclude, although it can contribute to develop the economy of my community, I firmly believe that the disadvantages of having a large factory clearly outweighs the advantages of it as it can bring about the ruin of our ecosystem and lead to more crimes."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1187, 2, '\nSome people prefer to spend their free time outdoors. Other people prefer to spend their leisure time indoors. Would you prefer to be outside or would you prefer to be inside for your leisure activities? Use specific reasons and examples to explain your choice.', '"It is true that society has been developed a lot in so many areas, such as education, environment, and entertainment. This advancement has brought us opportunities to enjoy ourselves indoors. Actually more than two-thirds of people in my country spend leisure time indoors, usually doing computer games. I, However, do not think that spending free time inside is mroe favorable than doing it outside, with regard to more benefits it can bring to us.\n\nFirst of all, people can make friends more easily when they do sport.  It is an absolutely good way to get on well with other people through sport. Moreover, doing sport can improve our health, even though it needs physical efforts. People do not have to consider their health seriously which is becoming a great issue in society.\n\n All people who own their company also has to spend their time outdoors. They are supposed to have the leadership which is a really important skill to run their companies. By means of doing sport, they can make the leadership stronger than ever. Therefore, even if their companies are put into a difficult situation, they can get over it with the strong leadership.\n\nHowever, some people believe that it is also a good way to spend their free time playing computer games without any distractions. I, Nevertheless, do not assert this statement. They become isolated although they do not realize it, and as a result they can probably loss their social skills.\n\nFor these reasons, I can say that I prefer to spend my free time outdoors without hesitation, and I strongly believe that people should spend their time outdoors as there are definitely more benefits and nobody should be isolated from society."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1188, 2, '\nWhat is the most important animal in your country? Why is the animal important? Use reasons and specific details to explain your answer.', '"It is widely accepted that the most important animal is a dog in my country. The following essay explains why I think a dog is the most improtant animal.\n\nTo start with, a dog is more familiar with human beings than any other animal. It is really a crucial point to my country which has become a industrial country. People living in a complex country usually feel lonely, so they tend to find something enough to make them joyful. I believe that a dog is really suitable for it, as a result more than one-thirds of people in my country have dogs, especially in a complex city.\n\n Another point to bear in mind is that a dog can prevent my house from robbery. Actually, there are some reports about these cases. Therefore, when an owner has a dog, the owner can pay less attention for the house while the owner is out of the house, because of the dog which is always attentive. Moreover, having a dog can be educational for children. Due to the lack of friendship with other children, children might not learn social skills. Even though a dog is not a human beings, it might be helpful for children to get along with other pepple.\n\nFor these reasons, I firmly believe that a dog is the most important animal as having it can obstruct people from feeling lonely and it can keep a house safely."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1189, 2, '\nThink of the most interesting class you have ever taken. Why did you enjoy this class so much?', '"It was a really exciting experience to get into an English conversation class in a private institute, located in near my home. As soon as I got out of military service, I decied to learn how to speak Engligh, and so I happened to join that class. I believe that the English class is the most interesting class I have ever taken, associated with the excellent teacher and the materials.\n\nI remember that there was a good teacher who was a foreigner and had taught Engligh for over 5 years. He encouraged us to keep concern about English whenever we felt as if we wanted to give up. While we felt sleepy, he usually made us laugh and concentrate on our study again. What is the most appreciated one is that he always took care of us. It was the unforgetable event that he brought some medicines after he found one of us sick.\n\n Another point I have to deal with is the materials which the teacher used. Those were about diverse kinds of cultures around the world. Having experience of several cultures, even if in a indirect way, is useful for us, expecially when we go abroad. Moreover, talking about something in English is a real thing. Students in Korea usually learn English for over 10 years, but they cannot speak English at all. Due to the lack of practical programs, they waste their best time, I suppose. By this I mean, it was extremely interesting to learn how to speak English in like a real situation.\n\nTherefore, I cannot still forget the time and also do not hesitate to say that it was the best class I have ever taken, as the teacher was incredible and the materials were really useful in my life."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1190, 2, '\n"Some people believe that a college or university education should be available to all students. Others believe that higher education should be available only to good students. Discuss these views, Which view do you agree with? Explain why."', '"Many high school students, even those who graduated from technical high schools or financial ones, want to enter a university. So the number of universities and colleges increased much as the number of students who want to go to a university increased. Thus, it is said that some universities will have to close down their door because of a lack of students who will attend them.\n \nBut, so what? isn''t it illiteracy that we cared about, not literacy?  Wouldn''t it be better for us to think about how to decrease the universities and their students because there are too many of them rather than we worry about our gloomy future resulted from illiteracy? Plus, Education plays an important role in our society, which is giving ordinary people an opportunity to get a higher position. That means without higher education ordinary people can never be at a higher position, acquire any fame and a lot of money.\n\nAccording to statics, more than two third of the students attending high-ranked universities in Seoul proved to be rich or richer than the average. If it is true, we must admit that poor people cannot be at a high position in society, and make a lot of money in the way he or she pursued, though college degree doesn''t always guarantee high positions or success. And if so, the rich will become richer and the poor, poorer. So I think all education including university education should be always open to all students."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1191, 2, '\nIs it better to enjoy your money when you earn it or is it better to save your money for some time in the future? Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"Many people have some opinion about this topic. Some peple prefer to use money when they earn it than to save it. Others don''t do that. As far as this topic is concerned, I agree to use money when I earn it. Now, there are some reason concerned my advocacy.\n\nIf you enjoy your hobbies, you spend money and time learning and exercising. In my experience, when I learned playing violin, I spent quite much money of my salary learning it. Nevertheless, while learning it, I didn''t think that my salary is spent useless; I understood to play violin, increased my hobby, and had much time for my interest. While learning it, I was so happy, exciting and interesting, so I was satisfied with it.\n\n When I went to collage, my tuitions are so expensive. Moreover, since I lived in dormitory, I paid for feeding, renting for room and so on. For these reasons, I couldn''t depend on my parents to pay all money. So I affected tutors on high school students and worked at a library, a food restaurent and a convienient market etc. I paid some duties by my salary. Although I couldn''t save money, I was happy because of helping my parents and independence from them.\n\nSome people laugh at my way. However, I like to my way and I will do that. I always say ""Present is the most important than any other time."" I strive to do my best in present during my life. How about you? Enjoying present is the most important things of any other thing."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1192, 2, '\n" People learn in different ways . Some people learn by doing things, Other people learn by reading about things, others learn by listening to people talk about things. Which of these methods of learning is best for you&gt; Use specific examples to support your choice."', '"Many people learn in different ways. The method of learnign something varies from people to people. Some prefer to leran by doing things, others prefer to learn by reading or listening. In my opinion, the best way to learn something is by doing things, becasue this method make me understand the point clearly, and because in this way I can really do some things well.\n\nTo begin with,&nbsp;&nbsp;I am able to learn the point clearly by doing somethings. As a whole I can obtain a variety of information by reading materials. However, this knoweldge is usually so superficial that I can not adapt this to the very situations that I want to solve. For example, recently I learned the way to make home pages. I read a lot of books concerning this topics. However, not until I made my own hompages, did I know the exact meaning of the contents of the books. In this experience, I really understand that the only way to learn something clearly is by doing things.\n\nIn addition, I can really do some things well by doing this things. There are a lot of good ways to learn somethings, but in some subjects doing things is the only way to learn somethings such as learning a foreign languages, musical instruments, and so on. \nFor example, I have learned Engish for many years. But in this long time I have not had the chacne to use English as the real languge. I studied Englsh only in the books and cassette tape. Recently, I have the chance to get the English friends. We often meet each other and do a lot of things. In this way, I really understand that English is not a subject but the languge, and I can speak English well. Therefore, by doing something is the good way to learn somehing well.\n\nTo sum up, the best way to learn something is by doing things becasue in this method I can understand the point clearly and I can really do some things well."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1193, 2, '\n"Some people enjoy change, and they look forward to new experiences. Others like their lives to stay the same, and they do not change their usual habits. Compare these two approaches to life. Which approach do you prefer? Explain why?"', '"Many people like change, - change in lifestyle, change in the way of doing something. They are even willing to accept any kinds of challenges. They want to experience various kinds of works and social activities. They are very energetic, outgoing and extrovert people. The reason why they like change is because they are not afraid of failure. They accept failure as threshold on which they can prepare for further leaping.\n\nOn the other hand, those who do not like any change in life are said to be conservative. These kinds of people, they can be classified into two groups -- One that doesn''t like change because they are afraid of failure or, afraid of the possibility of failure. The other group is the one that doesn''t like change because they are not just used to the new way of doing something, but not afraid of it.\n \n I think both of the two kinds are necessary for out society because as in the political parties, they are divided into two groups, one which is radical and another conservative, so that they can harmonize together and any one-sided opinions cannot be taken. \n \nIn my case, I can describe myself as a person who likes change. A person who doesn''t like change is like stagnant water in a swamp, and stagnant water will be spoiled within a few days. Since I don''t want to be stagnant, mediocre in this dog-eat-dog society, I would rather like to change myself to a person who enjoys the change itself, even if I was not such a change-preferring person."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1194, 2, '\n"When people move to another country, some of them decide to follow the customs of the new country. Others prefer to keep their own customs. Compare these two choices. Which one do you prefer? Support your answer with specific details."', '"Many people who move to another country have difficulty in choosing whether to keep their own customs or follow the new customs. Some people prefer the former in an attempt to sustain their identity. Other people prefer the latter for their successful life in foreign country. Undoubtedly, both aspects are important. But, as I will demonstrate through several examples, people moving to another country should adopt and follow the customs of the new country. \n\nThere are some benefits when people keep their customs in a new country. To begin with, it will increase family bond. There are not many people in a new country who truly understand your situation except your family members. Besides, they can sustain their own heritage and their mother tongue. Especially, it is studied that language is likely to disappear if it is not used. Once I met someone from foreign country. His family is from Korea, but he could not speak Korean, even a single word. I felt very strange and thought that he lost his family’s identity.\n\nOn the other hand, there are a lot more benefits when people follow the customs in a new country. Firstly, they can learn a native language faster and make many friends easily. It is generally accepted that it is hard for them to go around the country and to understand more about the country without understanding language. Moreover, they can easily learn cultural and social roles. Living in a new country is very different from traveling. For a short time, they can live without knowing cultural and social roles; however, they should learn cultural and social roles to live for a long time, to be succeed in their life, and to keep successful life. \n\nTo sum up, it is very important for people who move to another country to keep their own customs because it helps them increase family bond, keep family’s heritage and mother tongue. But more importantly, they must learn and adopt the customs in a new country so that they can easily learn foreign language, make friends and make a successful life in a foreign country."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1195, 2, '\nSome people think governments should spend as much money as possible exploring space. Other people disagree and think governments should spend this money for our basic needs on Earth. Which of these two opinions do you agree with? Use specific reasons and details to support your answer.', '"Modern technology has enabled us to land on the Moon., which could have only been imagined to do. ', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1196, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Telephones and email have made communication between people less personal. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"People may meet or talk in person less with the development of telephones and email. However, I don''t agree that telephones and email have made communication between people less personal. Below are the reasons that I base on.\n\nFirst, telephones and email made people keep in touch even though they live far away each other. For example, I live in Canada now, but I talk with my parents on a phone and send email to my friends in South Korea. Using an internet telephone, I can see and talk with them now. I also send pictures to my parents and friends by email which I took in Canada. How would it be possible without telephones and email? \n\nSecondly, people can save a lot of their time to communicate using telephones and email. If one wants to meet another, he or she needs to spend more time to go to a meeting place, eat or drink something such as supper or coffee, and talk with them. People may think that meeting in person is more personal, but even we talk on a phone and send email it would depend on how they talk and send email. Today, we can do many things through internet such as sending a card and picking a letter paper for email, and talk on a phone face to face using a internet phone. \n\nTelephones and email are common to use nowdays. Many peple rely on them and use them every day. Some people think telephones and email have made communication between people less personal, but they have made our communication better personal between far countries and they also have made our time be saved. It depends on us to use telephones and email with our beloved ones so that we can keep in touch with them."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1197, 2, '\nSome people think that the automobile has improved modern life. Others think that the automobile has caused serious problems. What is your opinion? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Most of house have the car. It show us the importance of car. car has became the portion of our life. we use the car when go to office. go to shopping. go to buy stuff. in addition, car is significant not only for indivual vehicle but also for public vehicle. bus and cab accelrerate to live complicate life pattern of modern life. \n\nFirstly. since people have used car , they can go rapidly before. ships, trains, so on are too can go rapidly. but car is using more time than other vehicle. so car is vehicle ajacent to human. in addtion to not only speed but also comfortablity is also useful. because of shoal trips and sporadic accident of humna life as death of kith and kin and hope for going to anywhere, people are uncomfortable. but these matter are sloved for automoble''s advent and development. \n\nsecondly. automoble is special car for people loving car and it''s speed. in modern life as each other have themselvs penchent, somebody preper to performant car show, and to emulate racing car and to own beautiful or antique car. these are never unaccustomed for us but they are familiar to us. in addition to car is means to show attribute of the indivually aesthetic sense. car''s color and design are important as operation as. \n\npeople who say car has many serious problem are unknown of the merit of car. the one of car''s problem is air pollution. but air pollution are not responsible for car. it contain other reason as industry factory. in addition to, air problem of car is being solved. other alternative resource car are incubating. if human gradually solve car''s problem, they can use the car more wisely. and more people will detect the advantage of car"', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1198, 2, '\nSome people think that children should begin their formal education at a very early age and should spend most of their time on school studies. Others believe that young children should spend most of their time playing. Compare these two views. Which view do you agree with? Why', '"People have different opinions about the advantages and disadvantages of early education. Although some insist that early education has a positive effect on young children, I strongly believe that young children should spend most of their time on playing because it can develop their sociability. \n\nOn the one hand, children can achieve brain development through school studies. According to a graduate student'' thesis, young children can receive more information than old people during the same time as computer harddisk is empty. To illusrate, I lived in Seoul where people have lots of interest in early eduation of English. Like other parents, our parents sent me englis language school in six years old. I still remembered the englis word. As my experience demonstrate, It is important that children learn early. \n\nOn the other hand, children can learn about how to blend in well with peer in their school. In contemporary time we get along with a lot of people. So, It is significant for us to understand other''s way of thinking. For this, we should be able to mix well with other people that has different background. Therefore, spending children''s time on playing is better than stuying. \n\nIn summary, I strongly believe that spending children''s time on playing is more meaningful because it can cultivate the sociability."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1199, 2, '\n Some people prefer to eat at food stands or restaurants. Other people prefer to prepare and eat food at home. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"In modern life that ""time is gold"", Whether eat at home or at restaurant is important issue in terms of time management and efficiency. Some people like to eat at home because of comfort mood and less money. Nevertheless, I prefer to eat out because it can save us time and I am able to select food among various foods and costs. \n\nEting at restaurants saves me time. I can enjoy food as soon as I order and even more, I don''t have to waste my time on cooking food. Actually, preparing food to eat at home is very time-consuming task involving buying ingredients, making food and setting the table. On the other hand, at a restaurant, what I have to do to eat something is just ordering some menu. For example, I went to the restaurant near my house with my brother because I was too tired to make some food at home owing to my heavy homeworks. I made an order a pork steak and immediately I can eat it! For me, having trouble with my halfdone homeworks, eating at a restaurant allows me more time to study done. In this manner, I prefer to eat out in that I can save my time. \n\nIn addition, there are a variety of foods and costs at a resataurant. Thus, I have a more chance to select food that I want to eat. I usually eat some routine food which is mainly Kimchi, a Korean food and fried egg. However, I can enjoy a special food eaten at home rarely. As an example, when I went to the foreign restaurant at my father''s birthday, I was able to eat Robster at first in my life! It was so big that my mother maybe couldn''t cook this food if we want to eat it at home. Moreover, costs at a restaurant is as various as the kinds of foods, so I can choose the best food considering my pocket money. \n\nConsequently, although there are advantages when I eat at home such as relax mood, I prefer to eat at a restaurant because not only does it save me time but also I can select fittest menu among various food at a restaurant."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1200, 2, '\nThe government has announced that it plans to build a new university. Some people think that your community would be a good place to locate the university. Compare the advantages and disadvantages of establishing a new university in your community. Use specific details in your discussion.', '"Most people are very sensitive to the government’s plans nowadays. When it comes to constructing a new university in our community, the reaction of people in our community will be the same as other governments’ plans because there are advantages and disadvantages. Through the definite examples, I will demonstrate that I don''t agree with the idea of establishing a new university in our community.\n\nThere are some advantages if a new university is built in our community. To begin with, a lot of students and other people will come to our community so that our local economy will grow and be prosperous. A university is accompanied with not only many people but also other buildings, such as shops and restaurants. As a result of increased population and more building, our local economy will develop and get more revenue. Besides, our local population will be diversified and we can enjoy various customs and events. Lastly, The reputation of our community will be enhanced with this university, especially when the university receives some awards. \n\nOn the other hand, building a university will harm our community in some ways. It is taken for granted that the more people are, the more troubles occur. To begin with, there will be heavy traffic congestion, which hinders people from getting around, especially on weekends, and the crime rate will be getting higher and it will make our community an insecure place. Moreover, environment pollution problem will be caused and will harm our health. These side effects will not only badly affect on our community inward, but also cause the reputation of our community to be going down outward. \n\nTo sum up, it is very important that building a new university will bring many advantages, such as developing our local economy, diversifying local population and enhancing the reputation of our community. But more importantly, the side effects on building a new university is harmful to our community in some ways; heavy traffic congestion, high crime rate and environment pollution. Therefore I am not in favor of the plan to build a new university in our community."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1201, 2, '\nA company has announced that to build a large factory near your community. Discuss the advantages and disadvantages of this new influence on your community. Do you support or oppose thie factory? Explain your position.', '"My community is a famed. As famouse of green mountian and fresh air, many visitors come to my community. If factory is built in my community, the clean environment will be destroied. So I oppose the factory. \n\nIf factory is built in my community, many people can find their job as a worker of the factory. Then a father of my bestfriend who has no job getting a job, my friend can get better life than now. Of course not only a father of my friend but also many other jobless can get their job at the factory. So factory can give my community a advantage. \n\nBut as I told before, my community is very famouse of clean environment and beautiful senery. So my community is managed as a famed. If factory is built, the clean environment will be destroied. And my community will be lose a value as a famed. As a famed, destroied environment is huge disadvantage. Then more people than who get a job in the factory will lost their job. because in my community there are pople who inrolled in siteseeing is much many than jobless. \n\nSo If a company has announced to build a large factory near my community. I’m oppose that factory."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1202, 2, '\n A person you know is planning to move to your town or city. What do you think this person would like and dislike about living in your town or city? Why? Use specific reasons and details to develop your essay.', '"My town is located in the middle of big cities including Seoul, the capital of Korea, and Bundang, the new developed city. This position of town would have a lot of effects on living environment. If a person is planning to move to our town, he would feel convenient in traffic surroundings and natural environment, but it would be hard for him to live in the civilized environment available in a large city. \n\nTo begin with, geographical merits that the town is located between large cities allow people living in our town to move to another city more easily. These days, people tend to act in larger sites because population density is higher, so it is hard to live in a close region near companies or schools. Accordingly, it seems clear that the importance of traffic system is being enhancing. Also, the town around a forest give us good living environment, such as clear air, water, the teacher helping children learn the important role of nature. It could make students more emotional and more pure. \n\nHowever, regional characteristic that the town is far from cities also could give the trouble in that it is difficult to live with city conveniences. According to the improvement of living factors, we tend to spend the time on entertainment including seeing movies, shopping, meeting the friend, and so on. I think it would be harder for people to have these good environments than in cities. \n\nTo sum up, as mentioned above, not only does living in our country give the advantage like traffic convenience, and clear natural environment, but also it could force people not to live in convenient surroundings."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1203, 2, '\nSome high schools require all students to wear school uniforms. Other high schools permit students to decide what to wear to school. Which of these two school policies do you think is better? Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"No one in human society is identical. In other words, people have all different characteristics, preferences and opinions. Especially, when it comes to high schools require all students to wear school uniforms. Personally, I think that high school students must wear school uniforms. To illustrate why I convince my point, I treat only a few significant reasons with my vivid experiences here. \n\nTo begin with, high school students can be hampered from crimes by wearing school uniforms. One survey on donga newspaper says 30% of juveniles crimes decreased after high schools regulate to wear uniforms. Not until I red this report did I realize about requirement of uniforms. To give another example, if one student wearing a uniform want to smoke or go a dance bar, he or she may not be able to do that because many people know he or she is a student as they see the uniform. Consequently, I oppose that school permit students to decide what to wear to school. \n\nNext, high school students can concentrate on their studying. To put it simply, reducing time to select and buy the cloths make it possible for students to study more. For example, when I was a high school student, I did not need buy extra cloths for fasinating me who wear the uniform so that I could involved in my accomplishment. Moreover, they can save the money. By wearing the uniforms, they need to use neither the money nor time. \n\nTo sum up, I agree high schools do not have to require students to decide what to wear. The reasons why I think like this are because they can not only be encumbered from young generation crimes but also save the money and time. It is a good idea that schoos sometimes permit students to decide during festival in school."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1204, 2, '\nWhen people move to another country. Some of them decide to follow the customs of the new country. Others prefer to keep their own customs. Compare these two choices. Which one do you prefer? Support your answer with specific details.', '"Nowadays many people in Korea try to go abroad not only to study but also to live in a new country. When they move into the new country, they may be worried whether they keep their own culture and customs or follow those of the new country. If I were them, I would follow the customs of the new country where I move. Here, I will demonstrate the reasons with definite examples. \n\nOn the one hand, following the customs of the new country allows us to pick up the language easily. To adjust oneself to a new environment, learning language in essencial. Were it not for taking up the language, we would not have a job or friend. For instance when I was in England several years ago, I tried to adapt myself to English customs as soon as possible without any prejudice. After following the new customs, I could make many English friends who I can communicate with. It made my English skill improve. \n\nOn the other hand, keeping their own cusomes prevent them from adjusting themselves to the new circumstances. When people go to the foreign country, they feel unfamiliar and homesick. It can have a bad effect on life and study in abroad. We have to adapt ourselves in the new situations to survive. As old saying, when in Rome, do as the Romans, because the customs we keep can not be accepted in the new country. \n\nTo sum up, although there are benefits when we keep our own customs in a new country, we try to adjust ourselves to new circumstances with following the new customs to live well in a new country."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1205, 2, '\nWhat do you consider to be the most important room in a house? Why is this room more important to you than any other room? Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"Nowadays the importance of the house is increasing greatly. There are a lot of rooms in the house, and each room has its own importance in the house. Some people regard the living room as the most importannt one, while others consider the dining room as the most important one. In my opinion, I think of the computer room as the most important one because I can do some work, enjoy myself and talk with family in this very room. \n\nTo begin with, I am able to do my work in this room. I can search the information through the Internet in order to get a variety of information. This information make it possible for me to keep the pace of my job. Sometimes, I prepare my job report in this very computer room because my job often reguire writing a report. Therfore, computer room is really convenient room for my job. \n\nIn addition, I also play various amusement activities in the computer room, especially like computer games. My apartment is provided with the ADSL service, the information highway, so I can enjoy the computer game freely in this room. Recently I played ""Diablo"" from the blizzard entertaintments. This game is so interesting that I sometimes forget to sleep and eat. I really enjoy this computer game in my computer room, and this give the additional pleasure to me. \n\nFinally, I can talk with my wife in the room. My wife is also interested in the web-surfing. Thus, we are often together in the room. We talk to each other in this room while searching the Internet. This is the precious time for us. \n\nTo sum up, I consider the computer room as the most important room for the above reasons. I can work my job in the computer room, I can get the amusement in the omputer games, and I can spend time with my wife in the room."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1206, 2, '\nParents are the best teachers.', '"Nowadays we have more and more education systems, matrials and skillful teaches as our interests in education is increasing. They can teach our children scientifically and effectively. However I think parents are the best teachers as good supporters and influencial models at present as well as in the past. \n\nFirst, parents are the best supporters for their children. They love their children more than any other teacher and have the most time with their children, So they can realize enough what their children are, what they are interested in, what aptitude they have and so on. Edison, one of the most famous inventors, was poor at school work in his childhood. However his mother knew his son''s own special ability and she helped him do better. Like Edison''s mother, parents can support their children improve their talents. \n\nSecond, parents are the most influencial models. Especially children under school age learn social rules form their parents and they think their parents'' behaviors absolutely right. Therefore they follow as they see. For example they get to know when to cross the street and where to throw away garbage by seeing and experincing with their parents. In other words children can learn naturally how to live and act uprihtly. \n\nIn conclusion, it is certain that there are many good education institute and teachers but parents teach thier children the best by giving good care and supports and life models, which cannot be bought with money. So I wish to say parents are the best teachers."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1207, 2, '\n Some universities require students to take classes in many subjects. Other universities require students to specialize in one subject. Which is better? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Nowadays, our society needs more profesional people. There are many people who concentrate on their own feilds and due to their devouts, our society can be well-organized. Therefore, the specialized education is quite necessary for the university students. In this essay, I will present two reasons and details supprorting my view.\n\nTo begin with, students can learn more deep and professional knowledge though their one major. In other words, university students decided their major when they enter the universities. Their majors can be the best chice for them so they can focus on it with more interests. For example, the recent research of the humanity department of my university showed that the students wanted to study their major more deeply because they believe that the only specialized knowledge can be the most valuable thing in their universtity lives. Studying the several sujects can mean that students can learn only superficial things of the subjects. In this respect, the broad learning of many sucjects cannot give the professional knowledge at all. \n\nSeconld, students can get much help from digging one subject in the university. ', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1208, 2, '\n"When people move to another country, some of them decide to follow the customs of the new country. Others preper to keep their own customs. Compare these two choices. Which one do you preper? Support your answer with specific details."', '"Nowadays, owing to develpment of transfortation, people can move to another country than ever before. Some of them cling to their customs in other countries while others change their life style. In my case, I prefer to follow the customs of the new country since I can get along with the neighbor more rapidly and be adjusted to the new life in another country easily. \n\nFirst, when people admit the customs of the new country and follow them they can be familiar with the neighbor fast as well as can be adapted to the new way of living in the new country. Actually, people have nostelgia when they leave their mother country from time to time. The best choice to avoid it is to be adjusted to a new life and get close to a person living next door. And there is no better way to make a friend than following the traditions of the new country because people tend to feel benevolent with a person having similar traditions which can be called a life style. \n\nCompared with the choice of following customs of another country, there may be some advantages when people cleve to their own customs in a new country; remembering their mother country and showing their own traditions to the others in foreign country. As an exmple, we can think of Indonesians in England. Although they live in a foreign country they keep their cultural life style involving clothes, hair style, and even faith. By doing so, they can not only remind their real country, Indonesia, but also have the effect to exhibit their exotic customs to the English. \n\nTo sum up, while following traditions of the new country when people move to enables people to be familiar with the neighbor and be adjusted to fresh and new life in foreign country, keeping traditions makes it possible for them to remember their cultural habits and show it to the others in a new country. In spite of the merits of maintaining own customs, I preper to make some change on my life style when I move to the other country because of the reasons that I have mentioned above."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1209, 2, '\n Is it more important to be able to work with a group of people on a team or to work independently? Use reasons and specific examples to support your answer.', '"Nowadays, this society needs more people who take the proper jobs and tasks. If there are just a few people to work with, the society can not be well operated. Hence the more people who can work, the more efficient in the estabilishing the taskes. In this essay , I will present a coupple of reasons and details supporting my view. \n\nTO begin with, a group of people can make the taskes in a more fast way. In other words, people can share the jobs and they can make it more quickly than doing alone. For example, in these days, our corporarions are now trying to begin the new work structure that is the team structure in the company not former prependicular and rigid systems. All teams have equall amounts of importance and taskes in the company and there are little stiff atmosphere among the workers any more and the result of the takes is much higher than before. The main cause of this can be the rapid and efficient speed between the worker. In this respect, a group of people can do their works very quickly. \n\nSecond, a group of people can solve the difficulties better and they can also think much better methods in their works. ', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1210, 2, '\n"Some people spend their entire lives in one place. Others move a number of times throughout their lives, looking for a better job, house, community, or even climate. Which do you prefer: staying in one place or moving in search of another place? Use reasons and specific examples to support your opinion."', '"Owing to the development of transfortation, people have broader choice to whether they live in one place or move to another place today. Some people live in one place because of their personality of being safe. However, I preper to move to another place throughout my life because I can experience many cultures and live in better condition. \n\nThrough moving to other places for living, I can obtain many cultural expriences of other countries and this is the reason I preper to move on place to place. The more moving behavior, the more valuable experience. As an example, my uncle , who likes to change his living place, has told me that his life is full of exitement through his cultural experience in other places. He is now living in China and crazy about Cyung keuck, Chinese musical performance. In this respect, moving to other country gives me amusement of experiencing other ways of life. \n\nIn addition, changing living site makes people possible to make a better decision and eventually, it is concerned to the better life. For example, my sister living Seoul, a Korean capital, could have more precious job by moving to Seoul. She once worked for small and bad-pay job as secretay, but after moving to Seoul, she can be the head of a branch. In this manner, people live more valuable life by doing so. \n\nConsequently, I preper to change my living residence because I am able to experience diverse cultures, and ultimately I have chance to live better life."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1211, 2, '\n"In general, people are living longer now. Discuss the causes of this phenomenon. Use specific reasons and details to develop your essay."', '"People actually live longer than before. This situation can be explained for various reasons. I think that the most important reason is the development of medical technology. The other reasons are what people can take more information of health by indivual way and people eat some food benefit to oneself body. \n\nFirstly. The development of medical technology give us much things. Many of diseases unhealed before are healed. Many of diseases unknown before are known to people and doctor. Detecting Reasons and consequences of disease have helped human to win suffering disease. And then human can have more much hoping for life. \n\nSecondly. There are much information and much concerning for health. The young and The old are both stressing their state of the health. They find the mothed for health. For example, I can see running old people at night in high school ground. They does for each other reason that someone need adequate sport, someone must lessen their weight because chubby state will bring other disease. In addition, Many people dose dieting. Foods are very significant for human health. Food even can remedy the disease. and can help to human not having the disease to live longer. \n\nPeople in modern society can live longer for many remedy methods, the information of health, and the their efforts. In future, now unhealed diseases can be healed and more much informations are discovered. People can longer than now."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1212, 2, '\n"""When people succeed, it is because of hard work. Luck has nothing to do with success."" Do you agree or disagree with the quotation above? Use specific reasons and examples to explain your position."', '"People always work very hard to attain success in their chances. However, I think that efforts aren''t everything in success. Luck is a very important factor, also. I strongly believe that success without luck is impossible. Luck help us to acquire a chance and to increase self-confidence.\n \nEven though people make an effort to complete their aims hardly, if luck isn''t allowed to them, they don''t achieve their aims perfectly. When luck is allowed to us, we can have more opportunities and increase a probability of success. For instance, a man has worked to attain a job. Now, he become a good craftsman at his major. However, unfortunetely, he doesn''t have any chance of acquiring a job. Eventually, he doesn''t use his abilities for his major. \n\nAlso, luck gives us increasing self-confidence. A man, who is often lucky, always think ""I can do everything when I want to do it."" When he acts anything, if luck(even though luck is a little) is given to him, he can work easier than he can without luck. For example, during his collage days, he worked hard in his major. And then, when he goes to society, he could get a job with because of helping luck. Now, he enjoys in his office and is satisfied with his life. \n\nPeople don''t always have much luck. However, in their daily lives, with helping luck which is a little, they have a better chance. If you work very hard, you have a trouble without luck. However, remember it. Luck always helps us. The first in success is hard work, and then luck."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1213, 2, '\n".Many people have a close relationship with their pets. These people treat their birds, cats, or other animals as members of their family. In your opinion, are such realtionships good? Why or why not? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer."', '"People have different opinions about intimate relationship with their pets. With regard to this issue, I am of opinion that freindly connection with pets is good because it contribute to relieve loneliness and aware of importace of lives. \n\nMost of all, frendly connection with pets is conductive to alleviate solitude. Everyone agrees that someone who lives alone has loneliness to some degree. To be more specific, When I was freshman, I lived alone with my cat. Whenever I came back my room, I felt deep lonesome feeling. After I live with my cat, my life changes drastically. The cat was my friend who listen my troubles and soothe my weary heart. For this reason, friendship with pets is good for lonesome people. \n\nIn addition, intimate connection wiht pets could help us to know about significancy of lives. It is a common held belief that it is important to understand importance of lives. \nFor example, children who live with pets would see pets'' birth and death. Then they apprehend value of lives. In this respect, deep connection with pets is conductive to understand importance of lives. \n\nAll in all, even though there are other opinions that close relationship with pets, I have every confidence that intimate connection with pets is good for people who need to relive their loneliness and it make people to know significancy of lives."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1214, 2, '\nYou have received a gift of money. The money is enough to buy either a piece of jewelry you like or tickets to a concert you want to attend. Which wound you buy? Use specific reasons and details to support your answer.', '"People sometimes imagine that some money as a gift has been given by someone. If people obtain the money, some people buy an attractive piece of jewelry or other people go to a concert. If I were this case, I will get an attractive piece of jewelry because jewelry is permenant and can change it to money again. \n\nFirstly, I prefer coming by jewelry to attending a concert because jewelry is long-lasting thing. Participating a concert pleases participator for a day or two days at most. However, people having jewelry can enjoy seeing jewelry forever, and well-keeped jewelry inherits it to their children. \n\nSecondly, jewelry is possible to exchange it of money. Out of the blue, a car accident occurs to my son, but I don`t have enough money. If I can alter my jewelry to money in unexpected case like this, my jewelry is used of uncountless value. In unusual case like this, jewelry can resell for most of the original value. \n\nIn my case, some money which is given to me use buying an attractive piece of jewelry. I would rather have jewelry than go to a concert in that jewelry isn`t temporary and can use money."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1215, 2, '\n"You have been told that dormitory rooms at your university must be shared by two students. Would you rather have the university assign a student to share a room with you, or would you rather choose your own roommate? Use specific reasons and details to explain your answer."', '"Presumably, if there is a rule that students who reside in dormitory must share the room with roommate, people may be troubled about someone who live together in school life, roommate. Some students want to have a roommate by university policy, on the other hand, I would like to harness a room in dorm with my acquaintance as far as possible. In this essay, I will mention reasons about my opinion.\n\nTo begin with, I''d rather not room with someone who is a entire stranger to me. If I share my room with this stranger, trust issues would be nervous to me; Therefore, I might suspect my roommate. To illustrate, I fought with my roommate once because of my stolen stuff, when I was freshman of University in Korea. At that time, I was suspicious of him under the unavoidable circumstance, and then, after this incident, there would be made a mental barrier between us. In this respect, sharing room with first faced man might make puzzle school life of students who live in a dormitory. \n\nAnother reason I support is that there are certain types of people whom I cannot room with. Some students would like to smoke in their room, other students tend to keep their room clean or stay up with bright light. No doubt that these kinds of people are not suitable for me due to my opposite tendency and taste. If I maintain other people who have different habits from me, I finally would move to another apartment.\n \n""Birds of feather flock together"", as this old saying goes, people prefer to get along with their acquaintances. For these reason as I have mentioned, it is natural that a student insist he share dormitory''s room with his friend or acquaintance."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1216, 2, '\n It has recently been announced that a new high school may be built in your community. Do you support or oppose this plan? Why? Use specific reasons and details in your answer.', '"School is the place where people called students learn and study something. Besides the school also plays various ralls in society. So building a new high school is very important matter. I think we should builde another new high school in our society. \n\nMost of all, I think that the number of school is not enough in my community. There are about four to six hundread students in one grades in nomal high school. And there are about 35 students in one class. Comparing to the number of teacher there are so many students in one school. It prevent teacher from having students discuss something in class. So it might be very useful in increasing the quality of class. \n\nBesides if a new school were built, it would make various economic adnvantages. Some people would sell books around the school, or someone maybe start a stationery around the school. It help people get more income in various ways. \n\nBuilding a new high school dosen''t mearly mean that the place where students study is made, but it means very important, advantage and profitable station is made. So I support building a new high school."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1217, 2, '\n" Some educators suggest that all elementary, middle school, and high school students should be required to wear school uniforms. What do you think?"', '"School uniforms have several advantages over the common school dress code. The school uniform is simpler, is less expensive, and can be satisfying to students. \n \nFirst of all, the school uniform is simple. It is more convenient. Students don’t have to worry about what to wear to school. They don''t have to worry about whether the day''s temperature is cold or hot, whether they are in ""style"", or what their friends are wearing. Also it looks very neat, when the students are together. They represent their school with neat uniforms very well. \n\nSecond, the students and their parents spend less money on clothing. They only pay for the uniforms, but nothing else. A ""new outfit"" is never needed, a ""special occasion outfit"" is not required. The latest trend does not affect the cost of school clothes. The school uniform is more economic and saves money. However, when the school designs the uniform, it should consider students’ thoughts. The school should present samples and offer a vote to select its uniform. \n\nThe school uniform is for the students, but not for the teachers to wear. The opinion of students about the design of the school uniform is more important than the opinion of any others. Having a choice and a voice makes the uniform more appealing to students. \n \nIn conclusion, the school uniform has many advantages. The uniform makes dressing for school simpler, and the students look better. They don’t have to spend a lot of money for their clothes, and are more satisfied with the uniform that they choose. There is an argument for school uniforms."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1218, 2, '\nSome people pay money for the things they want or need.  Other people trade products or goods for what they need.  Compare the advantages of these two ways of obtaining things.  Which way do you prefer?  Explain why.', '"Since history began, trade has existed as well. Mankind invented the trade and market system because one could not produce all that he or she needed. Thus, in ancient times, our forefathers exchanged goods one another, while later they paid some money for what they wanted. There are both advantages and disadvantages of either paying money or paying products, but I prefer using money for the following two reasons; convenience and value-fixation. \n\nFirst of all, it is more convenient to pay for something with money than with goods in most cases. Let''s assume I were a farmer cropping watermelons. In such case, every time I need something, I have to bring some watermelons with me, which must be a strenuous work. If I use money, however, I can keep some in my purse, and I can visit where I want to go with my hands free. \n\nBesides, money keeps the value of our products lasting. Couldn''t I sell my watermelons, they would lose freshness and get pale. As time goes by, the value would plunder, and I would make far less money than before. However, if I exchanged redundant watermelons with moeny, I don''t need to worry about the value reduction, because I can keep moeny that is equal to their original value. \n\nIn sum, with money, we can not only easily go to market and buy what we want, but also keep the value of our goods unfrailed. Of course, trade with products has also some advantages; we can get what we need just through one-step, and we can save cost in making money. However, I think the benefits of money far outweigh the advantages of barter system, and Therefore, I prefer paying money."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1219, 2, '\n Do you agree or disagree that progress is always good? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Some people believe that progress has always brought about benefits since the prehistoric time. However I do not agree this statement ,in reference to our environment and the nature of human. \n\nHuman beings have made lots of progress in a variety of areas including education, agriculture, and economy. Yet, we should consider our environment which has been getting worse. Many factories have been built almost every domain and polluted soil, water, and air. We might not be able to live when water become entirely polluted, because it is essential to support our body for us whose body consists of more than 70% of water. \n\nAnother point to bear in mind is that human beings are social animals, and so they absolutely need to get along with other people. Due to the high technology, people do not have to go school, go somewhere else to work instead of their house, and attend some meetings. They can actually do it just using their computer in their home. Therefore, people communicate with other people much less than before. It could be possible for our society to be destroyed, because of the lack of relationship.\n\nFor these reasons, I firmly believe that progress is not always good as it has brought about our environment polluted and could ruin our society according to our nature."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1220, 2, '\nSome people say that computers have made life easier and more convenient. Other people say that computers have made life more complex and stressful. What is your opinion? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Some people complain that computers have made their lives complex and stressful even though the computers support many important parts of our lives. Using computers, our lives have been much eaier and more convenient with many tools which were made of computers such as airplan, telephone and internet. \n\nWhen we go to a far country from our nation, we can now arrive in the country in a day. However, before computers were developed, how long did our ancestors take time to make a trip to an other country? It took over 2 months to come to America from Europe. We can save a lot of time. \n\nAs an other expample, we can now talk with our family or close friends face to face using internet phone althogh we live far awar from them. Computers made us keep in touch with our cherished ones. \n\nThe development of internet would be the revolution of computers. We can now find our information very easily and conveniently. Before internet was created, we had to go to library and look at many books to find the information we need. However, if we need to find some answers, we can use searching engines on the internet and the answers come out on the monitor. \n\nComputers are maybe complex to learn first time, but as soon as one learns how to use. There isn''t more convenient and easier. I certainly assert that computers have made our lives easier and convenient as well as they save a lot of our time in many ways."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1221, 2, '\n"Some people enjoy change, and they look forward to new experiences. Others like their lives to stay the same, and they do not change their usual habits. Compare these two approaches to life. Which approach do you prefer? Explain why."', '"Some people enjoy change in they lives so they are likely to have new expriences. However, others like their lives to stay the same. Therefore they tend to try not to change their lives'' style. Both attitudes have apparent benefits. Given that choice, I would like to enjoy many changes in my life for following reasons. \n\nFirst, because a human''s life lasts over 70 years, I would be easily bored about my life without any unexpected change. For example, imangining that there are always stable stats such as going school and getting back home, getting married when it is time to do and then having a baby in my life. i think it is such s tedious life pattern. As a result of that, I may be depressed and get used to normal things. I have only a single given life. I do not let my life go through usual, normal events. \n\nOn the other hand, challangable and unpredictable life patterns give me cheers and insights into my past life. For example, a dramatic change in the life, failure on the college entrance exam was s great obstacle to me. However, I realized that it also gave me the mind that I can overcome and look for it again. Since then, I like to change my living environments such as reallocation of stuffs in the room or having a hobby that I have never done yet. By changing the things around me, I could reorganize my life''s plan and push myself to live lively and affirmatively. \n\nIn conclusion, even if staying the same in the life is lesss dangerous and more stable to get through life time, it can make one''s life tedious and depressed seemmingly. Therefore, I would prefer to take dramatic change in my life."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1222, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Grades (marks) encourage students to learn. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"Many students have received their grades during their school days. Some students received low grades; others received high grades. I think that grades encourage students to learn more fervent. Students who receive low grades endavor to attain higher grades. Moreover, because students must receive grades in universities or institutions, they strive to get better grades. The reason is that companies or markers estimate them by their grades.\n \nIn all schools, students exam regurlarly. After they take examinations, they receive their grades about examinations. Students who get lower grades than other students shy and they strive to attain higher grades than the past. The more they strive, the higher their grades are. Students always strive not to be shy to others due to the low grades. Thus, they are enthusiastic of all things. In the sense, grades help students to reach better situations.\n\nFrankly speaking, despite ircorrect situations, most of the companies, institutions, or academies consider students by their grades. From middle schools to universities, we always have received various kinds of grades. Thus, owners of companies think that applicants'' grades mirror their abilities, and value. For this reason, students strive to get better grades to attain jobs. Grades are the most objective data about themselves. \n\nIn brief, in order to get occupations, and not to be shy to others, students always study hard to get better grades. Grades are not everything but important things of their lives. I strongly believe that better grades equal 90 percent of success."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1223, 2, '\nSome people prefer to eat at food stands or restaurants. Other people prefer to prepare and eat food at home. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Some people may say that eating at food stands or restaurants are better than eating foods at home, because of the convenience, quick service, and the variety of foods. However, through several definite examples, I will demonstrate that eating food at home is better than eating outside. \n\nFirstly, preparing foods is enjoyable. While preparing foods for my family, I feel very pleased and imagine that my family will be contented and pleased by my servings. In deed, after finishing the foods, all of my family members show their pleasant and gracefulness to me. \n\nMoreover, it''s more sanitary. I read a lot of news about unsanitary stands on the street and restaurants. In an attempt to cut down the cost, they sometimes use bad ingredients and also they don’t clean the ingredients properly. I think they don''t have enough moral to serve other people. I am not saying that all the restaurants are unsanitary, but some are really. Owing to these some unsanitary stands and restaurant, I hate to eat foods outside. \n\nLast but not least, I can save the leftovers easily. I can eat the leftovers later or I can share them with my family later. A research shows that the annual waste cost from restaurants is enough to save a number of beggars on the street. It’s really shock to me. In other words, saving cost from my home can save a lot beggars through other manners. \n\nTo sum up, eating outside has good advantages, such as the convenience, quick service, and the variety of foods. However, eating at home is better than outside because it is enjoyable, sanitary, and cost saving. With this great advantage, why not make foods for your family?"', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1224, 2, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? People should read only those books that are about real events, real people, and established facts. Use specific reasons and details to support your opinion."', '"Some people often argue that books with unrealistic content is far from the truth of real world, and that only nonfictions based on the fact are worth reading. I strongly, however, disagree with such point of view for the reasons that will be discussed as follows.\n\nFirst of all, sometimes fictions such as novels and short fables make it easier to understand the real truth. That''s one of the reasons why people like reading novels. Throughout novels, which contain possible situation and imitate the fact, people can not only enjoy the thrill, but also find the solution to the problems they have encountered. In additin to novels, Aesop''s fables shows how the fiction story can be beneficial. In Aesop''s short fables, animals talk and behave like mankind. What an unrealistic they are! Over the ages, however, people have learned much lesson from Aesop''s fables, and that''s why people loved his fables, read them again and again. \n\nMoreover, some books involving the imaginary world have showed some people the way to the future.', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1225, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Parents are the best teachers. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Some people presume that parents are in the most important role for their children’s education. Basically that could be true since children stay their home most of their time. Although parents should be familiar with their children’s academic affair, in my opinion, they are not the best teachers for their children. \n\nGenerally parents expect their children to do what they wanted to do but they couldn’t do when they were young. I know a friend of mine who was forced to enter the law school by their parents although his interest doesn’t go with that. His father was eager to be a lawyer back in his twenties, but he failed. \n\nI also have a friend who wanted to be a journalist but his parents wanted him to be a scientist. And he was forced to enter one of the best science colleges. But he finally gave up his master degree after his 10 years of studying. These examples pinpoint how parents’ misled expectations to their children give their children a great burden in vain. \n\nIn many cases, parents are not good teachers because of their misled expectations. Thanks to it, many children lose their chances to study what they are really interested in."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1226, 2, '\nIt is sometimes said that borrowing money from a friend can harm or damage the friendship. Do you agree? Why or why not? Use reasons and specific examples to explain your answer.', '"Some people think that borrowing money from a friend can not be bad the friendship because it can be useful when friends are in a financial predicament. In my opinion, however, I agree that it can be injurious the friendship. To illustrate why I convince my point, I will treat only a few significant reasons with my vivid experiences here.\n\nAbove all, when I borrow money from a friend, if I do not receive money, the friendship will be broken. Breaking the mutual confidence can not be irrevocable. For example, when I was a university student, I borrowed some money from my friend who I had known her since elementary school. She borrowed some money from me, and I concerned her trouble and did not want to receive money owing to knowing her finance crisis. However, she didn’t pay back the money. As a result, she went out of communication. I didn’t want to receive a debt but wanted to be her correspondent. Nevertheless, she did not make contact with me for sake. The friendship was broken off and it was not easy to be recovered. \n\nSecondly, if someone borrowed money from a friend and did not recover a debt, he would lose his entire friend because other friends kept away from him. In addition, he would have sense of shame for his friends. Once my mother borrowed some money from her friend and did not receive the money, the fact would have spread all over friends. After all, not only does she lose her friend but she also loses trust. \n\nIn conclusion, I have no choice but to agree that borrowing money from a friend can be bad and damage the friendship. The reason why I think like this is because it can make confidence as well as friends lose."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1227, 2, '\n Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? Modern technology is creating a single world culture. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"Some persons agree that development of technology is creating a single world culture and other persons disagree with this. I think modern technology makes the world has a single culture. The people in the world have common culture because of the development of communication skills and transportation vehicles. \n\nFirst, to communicate with the persons in the other countries are easier under the modern technology, and it makes the world as a common culture community. There are a lot of things to contribute to the development of communication, such as telephone and internet. Through these, the people in the world get common knowledge and information. Before I came to America, I used to check the information about here through the internet, and I knew that there is no big difference between my country, the Korea, and the U.S.A. \n\nIndeed, to move from one place to other place is easier than the past under the modern technology. The transportation is well developed and it is very easy to use them. A lot of people travel all over the world, and they affect each other. The way to live and the way to eat and wear has many things common. For example, the Korea has pizza and steak, and the U.S.A. has Korean B.B.Q and sushi. This is the same in the way to wear and think, too. The world has a common culture under the development of technology. \n\nFurthermore, the more and more business are cooperated with other countries, and there are lots of business which have no boundaries of countries. For example, the U.S.A has many Korean companies''s branch such as Samsung, and the Korea has many cooperation from U.S.A, as well. \n\nIn conclusion, I agree with that the development of technology makes it possible to have a common culture in the world, because it makes possible to communicate easily, to move freely, and to cooperate more. In the effect of this, we can share the same culture all over the world."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1228, 2, '\nSome people say that physical excercise should be a equired part of every school day.Other people believe that students sould spend the whole school day on academic studies.Which opinion do you agree with?', '"Students have to learn more something at school than they are in home.And some people think the best way to learn about their study and society is through only srudying academic subjects such as Enlgish,Korean,mathematics and phsycology what have you.However,in today''s world,for people to adjust society more positively they have to have healthy body by joining physical activities.Here ,there are two reasons that make my view convincing. \n\nFirst,as we know,the more we practice physiacal activities the more we can be healthy. This is essential factor for students to spend desirable adolescent period.If they only do study all sroud the clock,their body is getting bad than they can practice outside.Adolescent period play a key role to build up heathy status in human life.Even though they don''t study much of their time, they can keep their health through physical&nbsp;&nbsp;excercise.This also can be the start of their joiful and pleasant social life someday. Thus ,it goes without saying that joining physical practise is significant component to have a rosy future. \n\nin addition,pupils can do know that we all do many things in cooperation with others hrough participating sports game such as football,basket ball etc. We cannot make lttle of joining due to this. We cannot live alone.We are the social animal. Therefore,It is crucial to know that we have to see other people who hold different opinions from one''s own.And for students to solve this sort of problems they have to experience earlier the situations that can cause conflicts.And sporsgame fit that formular well. When I was a middle school student,I was a valleyball player.After ending that game I always realized that I needed more patience. That could be the omportant seed to raise endurance as well as patience. \n\nIn short, this is much-discussed topic between parents.Besides,this can be a matter of coice.That is to say,It depends on the individual.However,I dare to say like this.Physacal excercise is the most important for student''s bright future.Please select cautiously before you set your mind."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1229, 2, '\nThink of the most interesting class you have ever taken. Why did you enjoy this class so much? Use specific reasons and details to explain your answer.', '"The most interesting class I have taken was Japanese Politics. I attended this class last semester, I enjoyed it very much. I learnt about Japan politic''s changing from about 1800 to now. Japan is very close with Korean and it made the class more interesting. We used many materials, videos, computer and so on. The professor was good at teaching and he knew about many interesting stories about Japanese politics. I could learn more exactly and it helped me to understand Japan. \n\nAs Korean, I think we should know about Japan. Japan is very related with us. They are good friends and in competition. Japan has strong power in East so we need to watch them. So learning about Japanese politics is very important and necessary. I knew Japan and Korean has similarities though they has many differences. The interesting thing is that Japan liked American when they were ruled by America. They believed that America made them free. \n\nI had a chance to think about problems and issues between Korea and Japan. Among of them, these countries have problem about prostitutes. I learnt about relationship between America and Japan. America helps Japan to develop but they control Japan not to be stronger than them as the same time. It was very news to me. \n\nI learnt what I should have known. It made me think about national relationship. I could know what I have to do for my country and new things about Japan. I enjoyed this class because of these reasons."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1230, 2, '\n"Do you agree or disagree with the following statement? \nModern technology is creating is a single world culture. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion."', '"The world is heading for the unified community along with globalization. This phenomenon is specified as a single world culture. Modern technology has enabled us to bring about it. \n\nFirst, the development of the communication media has brought common experiences for the world. All the people of the world can contact anyone at any time through the Internet. The world-cup games are projected simultaneously all over the world by the media satellites. The communication technology advancements take us to a similar culture. \n\nSecondly, it is more available for us to travel evrywhere of the world due to the innovations of of transportation. Within 24 hours we can go to the opposite sites of the earth. The mass flow of the global people cause this planet to have the familiar experience, which becomes the basis for the single world culture. \n\nFinally, the evolution process of the world''s countries has traced the general path ac the capitalism has been spread all over the world. All teenagers of the world, except a very few naton, would enjoy the Mcdonald hamburgers and Coca-cokes. Capitalism accompanied by the liberalism would provide the unilateral cultural history. \n\nThe rapid development of communication and transportation in the wide rooted capitalism have another featurre of the worldwide culture. This trends would be more accelerated om the perspective that the culture is the coomon and accumulated recognition of a community."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1231, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? A person should never make an important decision alone. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"There are briefly two different arguments about whether people should make the significant decision alone. Although it seems reasonable that people should make an important decision for themeselves because people have to be reponsible on their own decisons, I believe that people should refer to others'' opinions when they have to decide something important.\n\nFirst, people can take other''s acvices as they make the important decisions because especailly old people''s advices can be usually helpful. In other words, old people''s acvices can be much benefits to the younger people. Mostly, younger people need to be listen to other people because they have little experience and knowledge. In my case, when I had to decide the major of my university, I did not know how to do bacause I have almost no information about the departments of the university and I was worried about my future so seriously at that time. Without my teacher''s diverse information and my parents'' hearty acvices, I doubt that I could make it as facing that important decision of my life. Now, I am so satisfied my decision and I am really appreciated with my parents and teacher. \n\nSecond, people can reduce many mistakes though referring other''s opinions. In other words, people can make their decision in a more efficient way by listening to others. For instance, in my case, I dicied to apply the exchange student program of my university so I needed to the TOEFL grade for the application. I had to study for the TOEFL test, but I had no resources and materials about the TOEFL test. TOEFL was so difficult for me at the fist time that I want to give up the TOEFL and the exchenge student programs. But I went to the private academy for TOEFL and I heard the kind advices from my TOEFL teacher. He said to me that I have to study more and I should make more efforts on the test. Thanks to his invaluable advice, I can study more and I came to know more about the TOEFL than before. If I gave up the TOEFL study at that time, It will be the biggest mistake in my life. In this sense, other people''s acvices and haerty mind can play the most meaningful works on making the important decisions. \n\nIn conclusion, I strongly agree with the idea that people should listen to ther people''s words because old people''s advices can be more advantageous and people can shorten the mistakes."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1232, 2, '\nPeople attend college or university for many different reasons. why do you think people attend college or university?', '"There are numerous reason for attending college. Some people attend college in order to be more educated. And other attend college to get their jobs. Nowadays, many places in society want to person who has specific knowledge of one subject. By and large, poeple go to college(include university) for two reasons that I have said. \n\nPresumably, to be more educated is the best reason why students want to go to the college. not a few students wanted to go on to further study in their special subject when they attended the (junior)high school. In my case, when I was junior high school student, I feel like boasting my intellectual rigor of mathematic to friends of mine, but I''m not good students because I don''t like all school subjects without mathematic. So I really wanted to go to college to study only mathematic. Similarly, colleges allow students to develop an expertise in a given area. \n\nThe day is past when a person without a college degree could make a notable success of himself. It means, not a whole but most, a college degree has become a condition which workers should have. it goes without saying that a person works himself. The college assists these people in terms of these points. colleges provide training and experiences that can be applied to a student''s career. And, Students can use career placement center in colleges to help get a job as well. In these manners, the college degree is the key to get one''s success with one''s effort.\n \nI have explained detailed reasons for why student desire to go college. Surely, There are existed more reasons why go to college such as one''s friend go to college so that one should :-) (it mean, by one''s competitive spirit). But this does not mean that a college degree by itself guarantee success. Not only well cultivated one''s knowledge but also strong willness would guarantee success."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1233, 2, '\n"In some countries, people are no longer allowed to smoke in many public places and office buildings. Do you think this is a good rule or a bad rule? Use specific reasons and details to support your position."', '"There are many public places for using as several usages such as parks, libraries, and even working offices. Therefore people of the several classes come together in there. Some people may be very young and even baby to go out to follow mom. And others may be old people and a patient having some diseases. In there places, if some people smoke, many people feel inconvenient for that. So acting to smoke in the public office must be controlled. \n\nAbove all, most smokers do not realized at that others dislike a smoke smell. They only claim their smoking rights. Of course, they have not only a right to smoke, but also a duty not to behavior them a bad feel. My department, for example/TR>, has supplied a study room for undergraduate students. Most students have studied and spent most school time with their friends in there. However, some students have enjoyed smoking out door of study room in hall. Another one has complained about their smoking acting, but they have neglected it. So vice-president got some complains and said not to smoke indoor. \n\nMoreover, smoking can give severe disease more nonsmokers than smokers. Many researches have showed this fact. I saw the movie that introduced a girl who had a cancer of lung. She was just 19 years old, and must fierce her neck tiny hole for treatment. Her father was severe smoker and had always cigarette his fingers in home. Their home was full of smoke all the time. \n\nIn conclusion, smoking make our body worst, even we can have some ill for it. And smoking in the public places can give some bad feeling to others. Therefore the government has to make some rule about controlling smoking at least in the public places."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1234, 2, '\n"The twentieth century saw great change. In your opinion, what is one change that should be remembered about the twentieth century? Use specific reasons and details to explain your choice."', '"There are several great achievements made in the twentieth century. And our lives has been changed a lot because of them. Everyone may have different ideas which was the most significant change. Some people might think exploring space was the most important event in 20th century. Others might think vivid colored TV was the most impressive invention. However, I believe it was the internet network that should be remembered as the greatest change in 20th century. \n\nNowadays, there is no doubt how much the internet has changed our lives. First of all, we could assess to enormous information. It means we are no longer controlled by the government or the media like before. For example, in Korea, there was president election 2 years ago. The election was a lot different from previous ones. At the time we could get enough information from the internet, not passively accept from the newspaper or TV. In other words, we could participate in that with more objective information about the candidates. We could have a chance to distinguish which candidate was suitable for that job. The government could not control people by using mass media any more. We could actively get information from the internet and figure out which one is reliable. \n\nBesides, because of the internet network, we could contact with many people on the internet network. It provides us opportunities to broaden our point of view a lot. For example, if I want to talk about the situation happening in America, like anti-terror campaign, I can even talk with American on the internet. And also I can share my opinion with others freely on-line community. We can hardly get the chance to talk many people who have different interest, ideas and values in reality. Therefore, this is so amazing that if I want, I can talk a variety of people. Of course there is also disadvantages, such as intervening private life of celebrities However, I still think unless we abuse the internet in that way, we could take a lot of advantage of it. \n\nIn conclusion, the internet network has changed our lives a lot, compared with before. It provides us with huge amount of information available. And also it encourages us to enhance our point of view by talking with variety of people on-line network. There are still many changes made in 20th century, However, I believe the internet network was the most significant achievement in that it is related with the change of our source of information, from newspaper or TV to internet."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1235, 2, '\n"In general, people are living longer now. Discuss the causes of this phenomenon. Use specific reasons and details to develop your essay."', '"These days, there are a lot of old people in our society. Sometimes, the aging of the people in a society causes problems like the difficulty in an employment, and the isolation of old people. Why are people living longer now? Although there are lots of reasons, I think the development of medical technology and the increase in exercise time are main causes. \n\nTo begin with, because of the development of medical technology, people can be healed in hospitals. Since the birth of human beings, people always want to live longer, so it makes many improvements in the medical and drug realms. Today, by go to hospitals, we can easily find the disease we have, and it is possible to treat most of diseases. Like this, the development of medical treatment allows humans to live longer. \n\nMoreover, according to the improvement of life quality, people could spend time on entertainments such sports as hiking, swimming, soccer, jogging, so it has a good effect on human health. ', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1236, 2, '\n Some people prefer to spend time with one or two close friends. Others choose to spend time with a large number of friends. Compare the advantages of each choice. Which of these two ways of spending time do you prefer? Use specific reasons to support your answer.', '"', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1237, 2, '\nSome people prefer to get up early in the morning and start the days work. Others prefer to get up later in the day and work until late at night. Which do you prefer? Use specific reasons and examples to support your choice.', '"I actually support people to get up early and to work at the days for various reason. I consider that the health, The pattern of life are reasons for my supporting. Although some people might think that nocturnal working need sometimes for some people but it is their own thinking not for everyone. \n\nFirstly. The health are most important for all people. The methods of keeping the health are various. I think that foundation of them is to be people to get up early and to work at days. When people gets up at early morning, they can have more light head feelings then it helps people working more effectively than nocturnal working. \n\nSecondly. Our bodies are made for acting at days and for sleeping, taking a break at night. If people act at night in contrast of our bodies pattern, this will give people bad condition for spoiling body pattern. For examples, I experienced this situation at my university vacation. Because I woke up approximately at 1~2 pm, can not sleep well at night. I spended my plying computers at night and reading the books. After the half of a month, I had a little headache and ennui. \n\nTo sum up, people who get up early and work at the days having literally good habitation. They are more activating, and have good condition to work, play."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1238, 2, '\nSome people prefer to live in a small town. Others prefer to live in a big city. Which place would you prefer to live in? Use specific reasons and details to support your answer.', '"Today, more and more people tend to go to big cities for their living or wish to change their home town into a big city. Big cities provides people abundant modern facilities and active living with many other people. Thus living in a big city seems to be attractive. However, I would like to live in a small town for following reasons. \n\nOne reason is that big cities are not good for my health. The pollution caused by gasoline and noise is nearly inevitable in most of big cities. Many people in big cities suffer from diseases originated from air pollution. Croweded people and cars in big cities cause a lot of stress and even can be a reason of mental disorder. On the other hand, small towns are reletively free from the pollution compared with big cities because of the low population and small number of cars. \n\nThe other reason is that it is easier to make friendships with neoghbors in small cities. In big cities, people have difficulty in talking with their neighbors because of busy life. In addition, high crime rate in many big cities keep people from making good relationship with other people. In small towns, people can know their neighbors easily, and can help each other when they have some hard house work. Community in a small town is more active and beneficial for members in the town.\n\nBy these reasons, healthy and cheerful life is possible in small towns. Some people can say that living in a small town means loss of successful and wealthy life, but idyllic and easy life is more successul than stressful and unhealthy life. Therefore, I would select a small town and suggest a small life to my friends."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1239, 2, '\nYou have the opportunity to visit a foreign country for two weeks. Which country would you like to visit? Use specific reasons and details to explain your choice.', '"Visiting another country is a common thing in these days. Many people desire to have a chance to visit a foreign country because it gives them unfogettable memory in their life. In my case, I want to visit Canada for two reasons; first, I want to feel comfortable and imagine how the novelist wrote ''Anne of Green Gables'' in Prince Edward Island where is the back-ground of the novel. Second, I could see the Niagara Falls in Canada and learn greatness of the nature.\n\nBeing the back-ground of the novel, ''Anne of Green Gables'', Prince Edward Island may be picturesque place, and I can feel comfortable and imagine how the novelist''s life goes on. Since I am crazy about the work, it would be never forgotten if I have the chance to visit Canada. I think two weeks are enough time for going around the place, and imagining life of the novelist. In this respect, I want to visit Canada, especially Prince Edward Island. \n\nIn addition, Niagara Falls in Canada is the reason why I want to visit Canada, because I could feel immense of the nature through seeing Niagara Falls. I have heard that Niagara Falls is the senicest falls in the world. Moreover, everyone who sees Niagara Falls surprises of its magnitude. I think visiting Canada to see Niagara Falls is more worth for me than visiting other countries in that it could teach me how the nature majestic is. I believe that the experience would be good for me for sure, since I have not felt the greatness of the nature in small country, where I am living now, Korea. \n\nTo sum up, if I had the opportunity to visit another country for two weeks, then I would go Canada because I could be moderate in Prince Edward Island, Canada, which was the back-ground of the novel I have mentioned as well as make an illusion about the novelist''s life. Also, I could visit Niagara Falls which is the most beautiful falls and realize how the nature great is."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1240, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Teachers should be paid according to how much their students learn. Give specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"We pay some money to school and the money becomes teachers'' salary and maintenance fee of school. If teachers get paid according to how much their students learn, the teachers would prepare more and try to teach more eagerly as well as be kinder. Therefore, I insist teachers should get paid following amount of their students'' knowledge gotten from the teachers.\n \nFirst of all, if teachers are paid according to how much their students learn, they will prepare contents they will teach better and try to teach more pricely. We can see some teachers who just read and explain a text book without some knowledge or information from their head. The teachers are not elligeable to get much money. One of my high school teahcers, a literature teacher, was always a little bit soked with drink. We could smell it and he just made us read a text book during classes. For university examination, we had to study by ourselves agian. \n\nSecondly, the teachers being paid with students'' knowledge getting from them will be kinder to and consider more their sudents. For getting much money, they have to gather more students and the relationship with students has to be good. When I was a university sudent, a philosophy teacher was nice and kind enough to gather so much students. The first closing class was his. Philosophy is now easy but his hand outs and explain were understandable easily and his manner for many questions from students was always considerous and neat.\n\nIn conclude, I think it is a good way to improve teachers'' passion and students'' knowledge that teachers get paid according to how much their students learn. Teachers will prepare many sources for their classes and they will try to manage students to understand better. Moreover, they will treat students better. If this system will be adjusted, students and teachers as well as schools are developed more."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1241, 2, '\nSome high schools require all students to wear school uniforms. Other high schools permit students to decide what to wear to school. Which of these two school policies do you think is better? Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"Wearing school uniforms is such a luxury for high school students, I think. Plus, for the students who are on the way to adulthood, wearing school uniforms can be a kind of a barrier that prevents them from thinking freely. We keep on saying to them that they should learn how to think differently, how to do away with the matrix of fixed thought. But how? do we have a right to say that to them, while we''re recommending wearing school uniforms which is the source of fixed thought? I don''t think so. School uniforms are just school uniforms. No more, no less. I hear some people insist that wearing school uniforms keeps students from committing a crime while they are in it. But that''s a nonsensical idea. I have seen many students smoking at the back of the school fence, many students bully students of other schools on the street. \n\nSecondly, when I attended a high school I didn''t know how much money was spent for me from my parents. Now that I became an adult and think freely of those things, well, I was such a money-biting insect. I always kept on asking for money of my parents, money for textbooks, bus fare and things that I needed and wanted.\n \nEspecially for those families with less income, it can be a burden for the parents to buy their sons or daughters a pair of school uniform on top of the things they necessarily need. They are already suffering school tuition, expenses for books and other various expenses for their children, so they must be under pressure of supporting their children. So, I insist that school uniform policy should be withdrawn at least for economical reasons."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1242, 2, '\nPeople do many different things to stay healthy. What do you do for good health? Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"When people think good health, they often envision difficultly it. Some people prefer to swim and other people prefer to play the tennis. In my opinion, however, I choose jogging in the morning and low fat diet. To illustrate why I convince my point, I will treat only a few significant reasons with my vivid experiences here. \n\nTo begin with, jogging in the morning improves body. According to the Healthy Times, the best-known healthy journal in Korea, jogging improves the cardiopulmonary function. In addition it prevents both hypertension and diabetes. Nowadays, adult people get sick owing to insufficiency of health in Korea. It is known that only 24% of adult people take exercise, thus people must get exercise. . In addition, not only can jogging in the morning breathe in fresh air but also can not need no tools of exercise. Jogging only need time and diligence. Therefore I suggest jogging in the morning. \n\nSecondly, eating a low fat food helps you healthy. These days, people eat fast-food which can be eaten easily. Thus people eat high fat food so their health is gradually bad. According to the Josun-Ilbo which is the best-known newspaper in Korea, eating a low fat food prevents both diabetes and colon cancer. For example, once my father was got diabetes so he was very pained. However, he was got a prescription filled and controlled diet. After a few months, he could regain him health.\n\nIn conclusion, given the chance of selecting for good health I would choose jogging in the morning and eating a low fat food. The reason why I think like is because not only can excises improve health, but controlling of food also can prevent illness."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay` VALUES(1243, 2, '\nSome people prefer to live in a small town. Others prefer to live in a big city. Which place would you prefer to live in? Use specific reasons and details to support your answer.', '"Whether people live in a big city or a small town can be a heatedly discussed issue. Because there are some advantages in both of two situations, it is not easy to choose one of them. However, I like to live in a big city. With specific examples and examinations, I support my opinions. \n\nA small city like a rural area can give you fresh air. It has less pollution than a big city. You can walk though forests in the morning, or swim in a stream not polluted. With fresh air, you are healthy. As a matter of fact, when I lived in a big city, I have some diseases about skins. My doctor said I should live in unpolluted areas as a small city. So I moved rural areas where my grandparents live. Now I get over my diseases. \n\nHowever, there are more uncomfortable things in a small town than in a big city. It is so hard to find not only facilities for fun but also medical offices in a small town. In my town, I should walk for an hour to get some medicines from a doctor. If you are in an emergency situation, you cannot be treated in a small town as quickly as in a big city. As you know, in a big city is many medical offices. When you are seriously wounded, you can go hospital quickly, and save your life. \n\nIn conclusion, you can find some advantage in a small city. However, it is not comfortable. It takes so many hours to do something. You can live more conveniently in a big city. Because of these reasons I prefer to live in a big city."', '2013-12-19 15:09:21', 'Tagging', 'essay', 'Y');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(1, 1144, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>There may be many plants that is important in every country. Although there are a lot of essential plants in Korea, I think a white cabbage is the most critical plant to the people in my country because of some reasons; a white cabbage is used for making Kimchi, a Korean tranditional food and curing a cold and flu, in Korea.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>A white cabbage is the main part of making a Korean conventional food; Kimchi.</MI1> <SI1>Kimchi has been eaten by Korean people for a long time and actually is a basic side dish in Korea. <TR>In fact</TR>, all most Korean family has eaten Kimchi even today. <TR>Besides</TR>, now Kimchi has been exported to other countries such as Japan and China, and make an amazing profit to my country. <EX><TR>To illustrate</TR>, according to the Korea Trade Institution, Kimchi takes 50 percent of all export in agriculture.</EX> <TR>In this respect</TR>, a white cabbage is important plant to my country.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>In addition</TR>, a white cabbage is used for folk remedy in Korea. </MI2> <SI2>An old book about folk remedy in Korea, Myungsimbogam, represents that a white cabbage is good for curing a cold and flu. <TR>Actually</TR>, it is common method to cure a cold or flu by by boiling a white cabbage with water in Korea. <EX><TR>As an example</TR>, when I was a high school student I couldn''t to see a doctor due to the lack of time. In Korea, high school student must study hard to enter the university, thus doesn''t have time to be prescribed some drug. At that time, my mother boiled a white cabbage with water and have me drink it. Surprisingly, I was able to be good in shape because of the effect of a white cabbage.</EX> <TR>Thus</TR>, I believe that a white cabbage is essential plant being used for healing.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>Consequently</TR>, I strongly believe that a white cabbage is critical plant in my country in that people make Kimchi, a long-historical and fundamental food in Korea using a white cabbage as well as use it for remedy of a cold and flu.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. The structure and balance of the essay between its parts move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is complete with a position and a good preview of the main points as well as being strong.  There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(2, 1145, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>According to the development of technology, students can take lesson more information and learn it faster. Some people disagree with this situation but I agree because it can share technological information from Internet and learn more easily through TV and radio.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, Internet can make share people many technologies.</MI1> <SI1>If I want to know scientific technology or semiconductor, I can know instantly it through Internet search. Even I can know much information on the other side of the globe and ask though e-mail. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, when I was high school student I had to take assignment with a large encyclopedia or in a library. It took a long time and couldn’t give correct information.</EX> <TR>In addition</TR>, with limited time I couldn’t search enough information. <TR>However</TR>, the more developed is Internet, the easier is searching information and it can be used anytime and anywhere. As a result many students reduced their time and can search correct information.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2>Another reason, TV and radio can help students study easily.</MI2> <SI2><TR>As broadcast is various and useful programs are established, we can increase chance indirect experience. In addition, as a professional program is made we can study with a small amount of money. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, when I was elementary school I liked insect. <TR>However</TR>, I didn’t have chance to meet an insect because I lived in Seoul, metropolitan and capital of Korea. I often saw “World of insect” on TV and it filled my curiosity and was interesting.</EX> <TR>In addition</TR>, people in Seoul have very high concerns about education. <TR>Thus</TR> annual private educational expanses are spent much. If professional education program is made, not only reduce would private educational expanse but also people would increase chance studying a second language such as English and French.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, with the development of technology, today students can learn more information and learn it faster. <TR>Also</TR>, Internet can make them search on the other side of the globe, and TV and radio can help them easy to study with less spending. <TR>So</TR> I agree this statement.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. The is no real structure or balance to move the essay from one portion of the essay to the next. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(3, 1146, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"2","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>During my school days, I often studied myself about physics, mathematics, and so on. Some people insist that students should have teachers and be learned by a teacher better. Others think students study themselves somewhat. I prefer to second advocacy than first it.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><MI1><TR>First of all</TR>, teachers couldn''t adjust to all students.</MI1> <SI1>Some students need teaching more, other students need considerable expertise in a class. <EX><TR>For instance</TR>, in a class, if a student needs more explanation about a easy problem, and if another student asks a more advanced problem, what will a teacher do? A teacher wants to teach all students'' curiosities, however, the time providing a teacher will not be infinite. <TR>Thus</TR>, students who want to learn more things about their questions study themselves during free times.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second<TR>, students don''t develop their characteristics.</MI2> <SI2>In a uniform class, all students learn and act the same things. Though a student wants to act different ways, the student has to allow a teacher''s teaching. I heard that some children living in the U.S don''t go to school. Instead, they learn something to want at their home. Of famous scientists, some scientists, including Einstein, Edison and so on, didn''t go to elementary or middle school. <TR>However</TR>, they could grow up so nice.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In short</TR>, I disagree with the fact that students always have a teacher. This is because they don''t develop their characteristics well and learn better about extra courses. <TR>However</TR>, I don''t think that students must not have a teacher. I believe that one of the best ways to improve educational environments is that two ways are mixed.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(4, 1147, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"2","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Given the chance that my school should choose to buy computers or books, some people choose books because they can increase thinking ability. In my opinion, however, I choose computers because they can be basic for education. In addition they can be used to find for searching enormous information.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, these days computers are basic in job as well as education.</MI1> <SI1>Many schools are used to education though computers and it is more efficient for students. <EX><TR>According to the Josun-Ilbo</TR>, the best-known newspaper in Korean, nowadays elementary school must practice image education for students to elevate ability.</EX> Students also like these method much more because it is easy and interesting. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, my son who is elementary school doesn’t like education of school.</EX> He learned image education though computer, and then began to have an interest on school education. <TR>Moreover</TR> computer’s skill is foundation to business. Most of companies make file using computer and give and take e-mail and files. <TR>Thus</TR> I recommend computers.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, people can search information though internet.</MI2> <SI2>Internet includes more information than books do. <TR>Therefore</TR> when you want some information you are able to find them though internet. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, once I must make a paper about M&A. <TR>At first</TR>, I was very embarrassed because I did not know economics which was not my major.</EX> <TR>However</TR> I could finish and won the praise of many people through computer.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, if my school has enough money to purchase either computers or book my school should choose computers. The reason why I think like this is because not only can computers be standard in education and job, but they also can be used to search information.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(5, 1148, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Some schools usually teach only boys and girls under their regulations. These system has some advantages in enhancing the learning productivity, however, coed school should be recommended due to the following reasons.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, coeducational system can help the sound development of student''s emotions.</MI1> <SI1>In the wake of studying together, boys could take naturally girls'' emotional advantages. <EX><TR>According to some studies</TR>, children who are raised in the co-ed schools have shown less violent characteristics than the otherwise.</EX> Coeducation is necessary for the healthy growth of the students.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, students can recognize the other-sex friends better through the attending together.</MI2> <SI2>The half of all the humans are women for men and vice-versa. The education system which separates boys and girls would distort the conception of theirs over the human. Coeducation is required for the children when it is viewed of recognition development process.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>Finally</TR>, God created men and women who must live together.</MI3> <SI3>Men and women are given birth to respect and cooperate each other, not for the purpose of separating themselves. All the lives on this planet are getting along with one another regardless of the sex. Coeducation is appropriate for the will of God''s creation.</SI3></BO3>\n\n<CO>Boys and girls are distinguishable for the role of the human beings, however, not separable from each other. Coeducational system is more beneficial to the wellbeing and sound development of students than the another.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(6, 1149, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"2","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"1","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>The choice is difficult whether governments should spend money improving either roads or public transportation. Personally, I agree to develop public transportation. When governments develop that, the air pollution of a city and rates of using natural resources are waned. Moreover, citizens'' welfare is increased.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><MI1><TR>First of all</TR>, if governments improve the quality of public transportation, like increasing buses, taxis, and subways, citizens feel more comfortable.</MI1> <SI1><TR>Especially</TR>, during rush hour, people aren''t hustled by others and don''t feel angry any more. <TR>Moreover</TR>, because of increasing public transportation, a city can earn more transportation fees than the past. <TR>So</TR>, a city makes an effort to develop citizens'' welfare and qualities of a city. <TR>Thus</TR>, citizens feel more happy, comfortable, and refresh.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Also<TR>, if governments increase the number of public transportation, people use them more than the past.</MI2> <SI2><TR>Therefore</TR>, in the present, one of the greatest social problems, the air pollution is decreased. <TR>In addition</TR>, another great social problem, deficiency of natural resources is solved automatically. If public transportation is more comfortable than the present, people won''t often use their own cars. <TR>Thus</TR>, the air pollution is waned and rates of using natural resources are decreased, also.</SI2></BO2>\n \n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, if governments improve public transportation, our lives in a city are more comfortable. We don''t have any chance of being stressed by public transportation because of crowding in a bus and a subway. <TR>Moreover</TR>, environment will be cleaner than the present. <TR>Thus</TR>, we feel more comfortable.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There are no transitions in this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(7, 1150, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"2","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"3","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>There is an argument whether athletes and entertainers should earn such a huge amount of money. I am writing to say that they deserve it, with regard to their efforts and characteristics of their jobs.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First of all</TR>, it is true that people living in the world have their unique talents.</MI1> <SI1><TR>However</TR>, the development of their abilities depends on how many efforts they make for a certain period, usually when in school. There must have been many distractions which made them confused, disturbed, or uncomfortable before they become successful. Yet, they have finally overcome difficult situations. I ,therefore, agree that they deserve high salaries ,because it is only fair that people should earn money as much as they dedicate.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>, there are some disadvantages of being both athletes and entertainers.</MI2> <SI2>For athletes, it could be fatal if they get physical problems, such as backache, or obesity. There might be nothing to do with them. <TR>Therefore</TR>, with consideration of this they should earn money enough to be able to live, for the case that they lose their physical abilities. For entertainers, they are always under pressure, because people watch them wherever they go and whatever they do. As a result, they feel much more stressed than ordinary people. By this I mean, they also deserve earning more money than normal people, because they usually suffer from illnesses mentally.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>For these reasons</TR>, I strongly believe that entertainers and athletes deserve a huge earning as they make greater efforts and could get physical or mental illnesses more easily than ordinary people.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(8, 1151, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>There is important to meet a variety of people in my life. In the university life, we can also meet several people when we participate in club activity or have some classes. If we have a plan to live in the dormitory, we also have a chance to meet a new people unwillingly. In the dormitory life, I think more good point that we are assigned a new friend as these following reasons.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Above all</TR>, we have a chance to meet a new friend.</MI1> <SI1>She may study another thing. She can be older or younger woman than me. If she comes from others country, she can show me different cultures and languages. When I met a new roommate at second grade, she was ready to go to study abroad. From her, I heard many things related to studying in USA. After then, I become to have a dream to go to new country as they can show me more lager world.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, meeting with a variety of people make me flexible.</MI2> <SI2>As we know, no one has the same habits and interests. Sometimes, her behavior makes me angry and also I can make her inconvenient. My roommate and I have another life time, and so I used to go to room when she already sleep. Then she used to wake up for me. We sometimes battled for it. <TR>Of course</TR>, we tried to have a harmonious point to us.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, a chance to meet a new roommate has some good part to us. It make us more flexible and to have a wide sight in the society. <TR>Therefore</TR> I would like to be assigned roommate by the university in order to meet new people.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(9, 1152, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"2","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>""Hurry up! Hurry up, please!!"" This sentence is sometimes famous and becomes social issue in Korea. What do you think so? I always remind myself of slow pace and surplus. These conditions help us in a daily life. Two reasons are listed by the following paragraph.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>If you do somthing in a hurry, like preparing a presentation or studying an exam, you may be hurry up.</MI1> <SI1><TR>However</TR>, your working is clumsy, and you are so embarrased. In this case, I always think ""Slow is the best."" If I must do something in a hurry, at first, I effort to become pacify ,and then I think my duties slowly and deliberately. What I couldn''t think because of embarrasing is realized. Moreover, I can think better solutions or ways than when I was upset. ""Don''t hurry and become pacify"" is my first advocacy.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>In the present</TR>, because of developing many technology, a lot of things are much faster than past.</MI2> <SI2><TR> So</TR>, many people want that allthings become faster and faster. If poeple don''t have much time, they feel angry, impolite and upset. People anger their around people in that they lay in shortage of times. However, more think, people are not worried about a shortage of times. If they think different way, like the fact that they have much time even though not having much time, they are more lavish in the life.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>Now, we find two fortes. Surplus in a life is more important than any other thing. Surplus make our life lavish and happy. As the saying goes, ""If you are in a hurry, you circumvent</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(10, 1153, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"2","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"3","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>""Television is an idiot box."" It is a widely known fact. <TR>However</TR>, most people cannot stop watching TV. The reason is that it also includes positive effects although someone is addicted by it. In other words, it has both positive side and negative side.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>In the one hand</TR>, television provides us with a great variety of information.</MI1> <SI1><TR>For instance</TR>, Headline News is updated everyday. Watching it, we catch what we need. Though we gain news from newspapers, TV is more effective to know it exactly like the proverb ‘Seeing is believing’. This summer, it rained cats and dogs, so there was fIood in some areas. We felt problems of sufferers from the flood vividly as watching disaster situation. There was a poll, ‘which mass media is the most credible?’ TV was the first credible one.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>In addition</TR>, we have a great indirect experience through just watching TV at home.</MI2> <SI2>If we long for seeing Europe, we can also see it. People who have never been to abroad even know what other countries look like. <TR>Besides</TR>, we recognize how people in different classes live. After acknowledging it, some people help the poor abate their pains as contributing money or others to them.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>Otherwise</TR>, it makes side effects.</MI3> <SI3>Some experts say that one of the most important factors of increasing juvenile crime is TV. <TR>In fact</TR>, some adolescents imitated to commit crimes through TV. Last winter, a high school student blew grenade out in a public place. <TR>Consequently</TR>, one person who passed there got hurt severely. The youth stated that he just wanted to experiment the same way that he watched on TV. <TR>Yet</TR>, TV is not responsible for his crime perfectly. His parents should have controlled him.</SI3></BO3>\n\n<CO><TR>Like the common fact that ‘TV is harmful for us’, it may cause bad effects if we use it in wrong ways. <TR>Nevertheless</TR>, it is the one of the most useful invents because we obtain benefits as using it effectively. <TR>Therefore</TR>, the effect of it is up to attitudes of its viewers.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There is an optimal amout of transitionary words in this essay helping with the flow and reading of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(11, 1154, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>A person has met many people through his or her life. Someone of them become good friend to a person sometimes. No one want to be a friend with a person who he or she doesn''t like. To be a friend to someone, he or she should have characteristic, such as humor, reliability or intelligence. Although some people want most intelligence or something in a friend, what I most want in my friend is reliability because I can be offered by my friend in hard situation and tell my secret without hesitation.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, I can ask for help to my reliable friend when I get in difficult circumstance.</MI1> <SI1><TR>As the saying goes, ''A friend in need is a friend indeed''. I''ll take an examples of my experience related to this; since I live on my own, I have no choice but borrow some money when I have no money. One day, I needed money urgently because my pet became sick. <TR>However</TR>, some of my friends hesitated to lend money to me. At that time, a friend of mine gives me some money for curing my pet. What made me surprise is that not all friends could be help for me in harsh circumstance. <TR>In this manner</TR>, I want reliability most in a friend in that only reliable friend could give a hand in severe situation.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, I can tell my secret to my trustful friend and this is the reason why I regard reliability as the most wanted characteristic in my friend.</MI2> <SI2><TR> It is not easy to say something like a secret to someone because the secret could be spilled out. <TR>Nonetheless</TR>, it is easier to tell a secret to a trustful friend because a person is sure that a reliable friend never spii the beans. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, I have some secrets of my familly.</EX> <TR>However</TR>, I couldn''t tell about this though I want someone who listen to my secret and understand me. At that time, I met a friend who is trustful and could tell my secret. In this respect, because a reliable friend can hear my secret and I have no doubt that my friend doesn''t say my secret to the others, I want reliability most in a friend.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, I want someone who is reliable to be my friend than any other type of people in that a reliable friend of mine gives me a help in difficult environment and I can say my secret with no hesitation.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(12, 1155, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"5","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"3","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Although there are many restaurants in modern society, people are inclined to cook some food at home because they think food made in a restaurant are not as good as that made at home. <TR>Nonetheless</TR>, I prefer eat out because it is convenient not to make some food and I can taste food which is rare to eat.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>Through eating out, I can be free from making some food.</MI1> <SI1>Cooking some food is the most arduous and annoying house task, so I always want to escape the situation to cook, and eating something at the restaurant is the most efficient method to be free from the task. <EX><TR>As an example</TR>, I was tired because of my heavy homeworks, but I had to cook since my mother went to shopping.</EX> At that time, my brother and I went to the restaurant near my house and ordered a pork steak. It is hard to say how I was relieved because I did not have to make food. <TR>In this manner</TR>, eating out makes me convenient not to cook some food.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>In addition</TR>, I can eat exotic food by going somewhere to eat.</MI2> <SI2>As a rule, it is seldom to eat foreign food at home. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, I went to the restaurant with my family, because the day was my father''s birthday.</EX> We were able to eat Robster and it was too big to prepare at home. <TR>Thus</TR>, I prefer to eat food at a restaurant in that I can taste food which is rarely seen and eaten in usual.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>Consequently</TR>, I preper to eat out for some reasons; convenience not to make food and chance to experience new and fresh food for me.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is complete with a position and a good preview of the main points as well as being strong.  There is an optimal amout of transitionary words in this essay helping with the flow and reading of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(13, 1156, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"4","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"2","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>As a customer We have many chances to complain on a certain events or products on a daily basis. Some people like to complain by writing a letter. <TR>However</TR>, the others like to speak face to face on matters. In my case, I prefer to write a letter for the reason of relationship for the future and organizing systematically.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Firstly</TR>, I believe, the basic reason of writing complaint letter is advising bad conditions of the company to be fixed as a customer and also partner.</MI1> <SI1>Once I purchased holed clothes in a department store. Right after I found that, I ran into the shop and complained about that hole. Being overly reacted on that matter, I couldn''t control my anger and it made me spoke out harsh words. Eventually, this led me not to go and buy from there. <TR>Thus</TR>, Rushing into that matter without considering is evident to damage the relationship between customer and company.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>, Writing a complain letter can be more organized and arranged.</MI2> <SI2>Usually when we write letter, we tend to make a summary what we will say and take unnecessary words off from the list. It contributes for you to say the essential part of the damage that you have. Similarly, one organized letter can be over thousands of words.&nbsp;&nbsp;and well arranged complaint letter can make the relationship stronger than before.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, as the saying goes: Silence is gold. I confirm that the well organized letter and advising complaint letter for the future aspects will achieve more than gold does.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is complete with a position and a good preview of the main points. It could be made stronger, however. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are no examples in this essay. The supporting points are much too vague and lacking in strength. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(14, 1157, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>As I am growing up, I have a plenty of money to enjoy some activities, such as viewing a sports game, attending rock concert. Some people who have money like me enjoy themselves by attending a live performance, while others don''t. In my case, I am disagree with the opinion that a live performance is more fun than watching the same performance on television because I can not concentrate on the game, see the stage and singer, and listen to well, especially in case of music concert.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, owing to less concentration, I am disagree that a live show more joyous than watching the same show on television.</MI1> <SI1>For being more delightful, concentration on the performance is the basic factor. I''ll take an example of my experience related to this; in 2002, the Asian games were held in Korea and I went to gymnagium for watching a real game, female soccer between North Korea and South Korea. <TR>At that time</TR>, although I wanted to join together with other people I couldn''t concentrate on the game because of noise. It is needless to say that I couldn''t enjoy the game. I regreted that it would have been more fun if I had seen the sports game on television. <TR>In this manner</TR>, watching the same game or show on television is more enjoyable.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, I can see the stage and singer''s face as well as hear songs well when I watch a music concert on television.</MI2> <SI2><EX><TR>For example</TR>, when watching a Jaurim''s concert, a famous rock musician in Korea, I could see her face very well and listen to her moderate voice exactly.</EX> Not interrupted by anyone, I had a special time by watching a music concert program on television at that time. In this respect, I disagree with the statement attending a live show is more delightful than watching the same show on television.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, I am against going to a live performance in person to gain much pleasure in that I can not concentrate on the performance and actually, I can see stage and listen to the sound of the show more perfectly by watching television.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(15, 1158, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"4","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"3","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>As the old saying - A sound mind in a sound body - goes, it is very important to maintain health and people do many different things to stay healthy. They run in a park, go to a gym, climb a mountain, take a special nutrient medicine. Among them, as far as I am concerned, I will do a regular exercise and have a balanced diet for good health,</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, needless to say, a regular exercise is the most important thing to be healthy.</MI1> <SI1><TR>Many people do their exercises to keep in shape, but often do not exercise regularly. <EX>The studies have shown that a regular exercise, <TR>for example</TR> running or swimming everyday or twice a day, is more efficient than doing it 3 days consecutively and resting 4 days in a week.</EX> The regular exercise makes the muscles of our body developed continuously and be healthy.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, with a regular exercise, a well-balanced diet also plays an important role to stay healthy.</MI2> <SI2>Like fuel of an engine, foods which we eat and drink are energy sources of our activity and exercise. If they consist of a biased diet, <EX><TR>For example</TR> a fat-riched fastfood</EX>, they cannot provide enough energy that our muscles need. <TR>Then</TR>, although we exercise regularly, our body cannot be developed well because the lack of necessary nutrition ingredients: hydrocarbon, protein, and vitamin.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In sum</TR>, I would say that doing a regular exercise and having a balanced diet are what I will do for good health, as I have mentioned above. With a harmony of these two things, we will be able to keep our bodies in good shapes.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is complete with a position and a good preview of the main points. It could be made stronger, however. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(16, 1159, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"2","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Between a traditional and a modern house, if I should choose one, I would select a traditional house. Of course, a traditional house has many not only advantages but also disadvantages. Howeve, I prefer to live in a traditional house because of following two reasons.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>A wall doesn''t exist or is very low.</MI1> <SI1><TR>Moreover</TR>, it is made up of wood, so ,if you want to destroy it, you always do it. <TR>However</TR>, because of this wall, our ancestors are familiar with neighborhood. <TR>Moreover</TR>, it means that they always welcome strangers or visitors. If a wall , like modern it, is made up of stone, concrete and iron, probably our ancestors don''t make friendly releationship with neighborhood or visitors. This is the first reason why I prefer to live in a traditional house.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Usually</TR>, a traditional house has a ample courtyard and ground to cultivate vegetables or fruits.</MI2> <SI2><TR>Nowadays</TR>, many people raise their pets in an apartment. <TR>However</TR>, it is very impolite and insolent to their neighborhood. If you live in a traditional house which have a sufficent ares to raise pets, you do it without disturbing. It helps your childred to improve their emotion and friendship with other living things. <TR>Moreover</TR>, you cultivate vegetables and fruits yourself.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>If I am asked ""Which prefer do you live in a traditional or modern house?"", I always say ""I want to have a traditional house."" In that, I raise my pets freely, farm vegetables myself, and more learn about living things. It''s a fantastic and exciting. <TR>First of all</TR>, in modern society in which love, friendship, etc. are disappeared, we could learn more things which are not educated in school.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are no examples in this essay. The supporting points are much too vague and lacking in strength. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(17, 1160, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"3","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Both going on vacation and buying a car seem attractive enough for me to make a tough decision. <TR>However</TR>, in my case, I would suggest my friend to buy a car. It is because that a car would bring two speicific advatages : convenience and preparation for a financial problem.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, my friend can go anywhere with a car.</MI1> <SI1><TR> In other words</TR>, he does not need to take public transportaion, meaning convenience. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, last Christmas season, I was at a shopping mall buying lots of Christmas gifts. After I finished my shopping, I realized I bought so many gifts that it was too heavy to carry.</EX> <TR>Unfortunately</TR>, because I had no car at that time, I had to take a bus with all my lugage. That heavy burden annoyed me and I desired to have a car. This experience shows how people can have benefit with a car.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, buying a car may be a great solution for unexpected problems.</MI2> <SI2>Because I can sell my car amytime, I may use this advantage for my financial problem in the future. <EX><TR>For instance</TR>, three years ago, one of my cousins ran out of business unexpectedly. He scoured many ways to overcome this predicament but there was only one way to concuer his situation: selling his property.</EX> <TR>Thus</TR>, he solved everything including his car and was able to start a new business.This example shows another advantage of having a car.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>From what has been mentioned above, I firmly believe that buying a car is more beneficial than going on vacation. I strongly suggest my friend not to spend the money on temporary excitement, vacation, but to purchase a car.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(18, 1161, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"2","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"2","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Businesses is work to make a profit. If people force to work without their own profits, nobody would not work. <TR>However</TR>, for busubesses'' profit, using of bad sources, faking by wrong information, or afflicting employees illegally sould be punished.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>In the news paper, an article says, ""A lot of big companies like Nike hire under age people for the companies'' selfish profit.""</MI1> <SI1>The companies do even not pay minimum paypent which is seven dollar per hour, and press to work the workers for more than 12 hours.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Of course</TR>, I understand businesses can work well on&nbsp;&nbsp;their profit, but the profit should be on the right way for human being.</MI2> <SI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, the under age workers in the article are also one of the member who works for his or her company, but the company''s profit is not fairly shared for all of the members.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>Thus</TR>, I disagree with that businesses should do ""anything"" they can make a profit; I agree with that businesses can make their profit if the profit is made fairly, legally, and conscientiously.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are no examples in this essay. The supporting points are much too vague and lacking in strength. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(19, 1162, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"2","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Computers and books do the same thing if you think about the fact that they both give information. But books are much better when you compare the effectiveness between those two. So I strongly recommend the school to buy books instead of computers.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Firstly</TR>, computers need to be upgraded while books don’t.</MI1> <SI1> A computer becomes a thing of the past unless you keep upgrading them every 3 years or so. But books do not need to be upgraded. As a matter of fact, there are many novels that have been read from a hundred years ago and that are still being read – Tom Sawyer, Robinson Crusoe, Sherlock Homles. These books do not become a bunch of useless paper a few years later unlike computers which become heavy useless metal.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, schools do not need computers.</MI2> <SI2>Almost all the students have their own personal computers at home with better devices that they use all day after coming home from school. And they already use the computer very well without the school and teachers helping them. But students do not have enough books to read at home. So the school should provide what the students really need.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>Last of all</TR>, only one person can use one computer at a time and even that person cannot use the computer any longer than one class.</MI3> <SI3> But if you use the money to buy twenty 5$ books instead of one 1000$ computer, a lot more people can use the information at the same time for as long as they want. As you can see, this is much more effective because you already have 600 books that everybody can use instead of 30 computers that only one person can use at a time and have to go in a couple of years.</SI3></BO3>\n\n<CO>People say that students aren’t reading enough books nowadays. But this is partially the teachers’ and school’s fault because they were buying computers which has a life cycle of few years, which students already have at home, and which could have been 20 books per computer instead.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(20, 1163, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Due to long commuting distance between their school and home, or due to financial problems, many students have to live with their roommates in a boarding house to save money. But it is not easy to find an appropriate person for your roommate and even harder for you to set those qualities for a good roommate because it completely depends on what kind of school life you are going to have.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Yet</TR> when it generally comes to the important qualities in choosing a roommate,</MI1> <SI1> it is needless to say that you should choose a person who doesn''t make any noise and problems because it will be very annoying if he or she tries to do something very noisy when you are about to study. And it''s even more with the case when you are taking exams at school. Suppose that you have to study hard for the mid-term exam but your roommate keeps on talking on the phone for many hours. How annoying it would be! So I will choose being quiet is the most important factor among the qualities of a good roommate.</SI1></BO1>\n \n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>, being clean is also an important quality of a good roommate.</MI2> <SI2>If the roommate is the kind of person who keeps on making a mess in your room, you''ll just end up cleaning your room everyday, which is waste of time. Meeting a roommate who pursuits cleanness as the top priority in his life makes your dormitory life refreshing and satisfying, I think.</SI2></BO2>\n \n<CO>There is one thing that you should keep in your mind. That is, you should not demand your roommate be clean and quiet when you make a mess and a noise, which will just make your roommate hatred towards you. Before you demand such things from your roommate, be a silent and clean roommate yourself <TR>First</TR>!</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(21, 1164, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"3","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Exploring outer space can not be done by a few people, a company or a labratory because it requires a lot of money, advanced technology and a long period of performing projects. <TR>Thus</TR>, it is smoetimes said that aids of governments are essential for completing the lagre projects. <TR>However</TR>, I think that spending money for exploring outer space is not a prior duty of governments.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>There are still many basic needs to be solved in our world, Earth.</MI1> <SI1>Not a few problems in our world and society are so serious and emergent that governments should be in a major role to slove them. Environmental crisis, poverty, diseases, war and other issues are always around us. For governments, the first thing to do is settling the better world for all people. <TR>Thus</TR>, it is not proper to invest for outer space without solving basic needs on Earth.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Other important reason to oppose spending much money for exploring outer space is that the exploring can be used for military purpose.</MI2> <SI2><TR>Actually</TR>, some countries are competing with each other to have the most dominant power to conquer the outer space. Sending sattelites and other space facilities are necessary for expanding range to search information of opponent countries. <TR>Thus</TR>, if it is not for the pure science research, exploring space is not desirable for making peace of world.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, governments should as much money as possible for important problems for people instead of investing for outer space. If the reason of the exploring is mainly for military purpose, the choice of governments is much more apperant. It should be reminded that governments exist for people, society and world on Earth.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(22, 1165, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Generally, children learn a lot of knowleadge from their parents. <TR>However</TR>, I disagree with that parents are the best teacher, since there are some problems for parents to teach their children. <TR>For instance</TR>, most parents have a limited quality of knowleadge and a limited suppy of free time to teach thier own children. So I strongly believe that teachers are more good at teaching children.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, many parensts are not specialized on teaching someone else.</MI1> <SI1>Some of them might have only basic knowleadge which is not enough to teach their children. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, a boy who wants to know thow to differntiate, and if his parents haven''t learned differnetiation, he will be not able to learn it from his parents.</EX> <TR>However</TR>, a Mathematics teacher can teach the boy about not only differentiation but also integration, because he or she has mathematical knowleadge. Since teachers uaually have a higher level of knowleadge, teachers are more helpful for children.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, most of parents are too busy for doing their jobs.</MI2> <SI2>They don''t even have time for having conversation with their children. <TR>On the other hand</TR>, teachers are always waiting for children to teach them about what they know. They also want to help children about anything. For teachers, teaching children is their job. They are trained to educate children which means they are the best teachers. <TR>Recently</TR>, both Mom and Dad are working in the number of families, which makes it harder for them to teach their children.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, I disagree with that parents are the best teacher. They don''t have much knowleadge to teach special fields such as Biology, Chemistry, Accounting and so on. They are not free enough from their jobs or housework to help their children. Well- trained teachers, who love children as much as children''s parents, are the best teachers in the world.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. The is no real structure or balance to move the essay from one portion of the essay to the next. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(23, 1166, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"2","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Grades denote student statements of the studying. Statement of the student is significant for student who receives good grades or middle grades or bad grades. I consider that grades are not all but important things because they are almostly impartial consequence.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Firstly</TR>. Grades can give student the pleasing.</MI1> <SI1>It activate to student to encourage studying. The students who take mathmatics grade A are happpy because that is a fair consequence for their effort. And then they can determine that in more much effort they will be good student than now.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>. On the other hand, there are pupils.</MI2> <SI2>They might be study a little or nothing. they also receive impartial consequence for their efforts. they maybe sad or nonchalant. Sad students must resolve the problem. And then if they want. they can be good students. The others indifferent students and not resolving the problem are not almost solved by grades and other.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>Marks for students are always accompanied during student periods. Students who receive this fact can be good students . They are genious not sagacious. They will know the quality of efforts and theirselves happyness. This is actually expensive for students.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are no examples in this essay. The supporting points are much too vague and lacking in strength. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(24, 1167, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Here in Korea, to enter a college or university, students stay up nights and go into the dog eat do world. The thing is students are only concerning on getting high scores and it eventually turns into no good to anyone. If a good student in this above statement means that of korea, I don''t agree with a statement that only a good student should be allowed to get high-level education.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, What is a good student?</MI1> <SI1><TR> I am sure that a good student is the person who is eager to learn no matter how his or her grade is good because the point is how arduous they are. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, a good student in korea is the one having good number on their report card.</EX> I''ve seen a lot of them whom are so used to choosing right answers on exams without knowing and even thinking the procedures. <TR>Thus</TR>, I believe the chance of education should go to everyone who wants to learn even if the person is not titled as a good student.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Additionally</TR>, endowing the chance of learning to all is an important factor which leads into whole nation grows.</MI2> <SI2>Being taught by academically, social members in a country will form their values through education generally. The one that has given the chance to people to learn is a country but after all, the one that will get its result is a nation itself. Once I read a article about a man who was so poor in his childhood that couldn''t get the proper education. <TR>However</TR>, with the help of government, succeeding all academic courses, gives back all the money he has earn to his patron. Similarly, investing the money to grow the person who needs to country is not useless.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>,&nbsp;&nbsp;when it comes to high education, I believe, the chance should go to all equally because it is a wise way of invest for the purpose of growing the intelligent, and also nourishing a real good student without the matters of number.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(25, 1168, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"3","si":"2","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>I have lived here, a small town since family came near the Seoul. While Seoul is big city, my town, Suwon is so old and small city but developing. Many people like to live in a big city like Seoul, <TR>However</TR> others hope to live in a small town, like me. Although both them have good parts, more people live to a small village as it has clean environment and kind neighbors.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>Big cities have lots factories, transportations and apartments where people live.</MI1> <SI1>Most factories and methods of transportation make bad air and contribute to the pollution. Also people take out their fluent garbage. Otherwise small towns have a little them relativity. In my case, I felt very pollution in there when I went to go big city. In my nose, it is very dirty and has black dust. My collar became the black by polluting materials. But in my town, I need not clean my shirts everyday.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2> We will meet very kind people when I live in a small town.</MI2> <SI2>Nowadays many people do not greet to neighbors and even they do not know who live next door. When my family moved to now home, neighborhood came to my home firstly and say hello to us. They sometimes gave us their making food. When I had a celebrating for graduation, they gave a pleasure to me and were happy with my family.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>I heard that many older persons want to live in a small town and go to the hometown. Most hometowns are so small. As these towns give fresh air and have more chances to meet kind people. So I would like to live in a small town if I have chance to select my habitat.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. The is no real structure or balance to move the essay from one portion of the essay to the next. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  There are no examples in this essay. The supporting points are much too vague and lacking in strength. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(26, 1169, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>I oppose that borrowing money from friends can harm my friendship. It is because that lending money from them may be a great solution for my financial situation and paying back their money shows my responsibility.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, borrowing money from my friends is sometimes very helpful, especially, for the emergent situation.</MI1> <SI1><EX><TR>For example</TR>, last Christmas season, I was at a shopping mall looking for the Christmas gifts for my parents.</EX> Accidentally, I lost my debit card there. Because the day was Dec.24th, it was the only time to buy the gifts. <TR>Thus</TR>, I borrowed money from my friends and I was able to finish my shopping on the same day. In other words, with the money that I borrowed from them, I solved an unexpected problem.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, as I pay back the money, I may become a responsible person.</MI2> <SI2>If I do not pay back their money on time, I will be blamed and my friendship will be harmed. On the other hand, repaying the money will show how I feel about their aid. <EX><TR>For instance</TR>, after the last Christmas season, I pay backed the money to my friends right away. I even added interest because I really appreciated their help.</EX> My friends were also surprised by my behavior and impressed. My experience shows another advantage of borrowing money from the friends.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>From what has been mentioned above, I strongly oppose the idea: borrowing money form a friend can harm the friendship. I do not believe that money, which belongs to a human-made substance, is much less important than any abstract subjects, my friendship.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(27, 1170, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"2","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"3","si":"4","style":"5","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>If I decided to live in dormitory, I would rather have the university assign a student to share a room with me. Some people might think it would be uncomfortable to share a room with someone unknown. And they would possibly prefer to choose their own roommate. <TR>However</TR>, I still can see some merits to share a room with an unfamiliar person.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Obviously</TR>, it would not be easy to live with a stranger.</MI1> <SI1><TR>At first</TR>, I would feel awkward. But I could use this situation as an opportunity. I mean, as we know, I can hardly get a chance to live with someone unknown. <TR>Actually</TR>, In my case, I have never lived with someone, who is not my family member. So If I had shared a room with someone unknown, I would be able to learn how to live with people cooperatively. <EX><TR>In other words</TR>, I would be more considerate and tolerate so as to get along with her well.</EX> This experience would be very valuable in my life. Sometimes, my individualistic characteristic can appear to others as indifferent. But If I had a chance to regard for other''s feeling deliberately, I guess that would be helpful to improve my characteristics positively.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2>&nbsp;&nbsp;And there is another reason I would have a university assign a student as my roommate.</MI2> <SI2>I have seen so many cases, once friends lived together, and <TR>Then</TR> they had big conflicts. <TR>Finally</TR>, they stop keeping touch each other. If I chose my roommate, I would definately want to live with my friend because I would not need to take care of my roommate too much. I could freely behave and relax in my room. This was the biggest mistake of most of unhappy roommates. They wanted to live with a friend so as to feel comfortable. But this caused a lot of problems, because they did not take care of each other while they were in the same room. Frankly speaking, I guess I would make the same mistake if I were in that situation. And I do not have any confidence to make much efforts on living with my friend harmoniously. I think this is ironic. I feel so free to be with my friend so I can hardly take care of her a lot. So I would rather prefer living with a student assigned by a university.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, there is no doubt that living with someone is difficult. But after the time, I am certain we would be able to learn something significant. In my case, I guess I would be able to learn how to respect other''s feelings and get along with other cooperatively. Even though, there must be some disadvantages to share a room with a student assigned by a university, I would like to try this. That is because I believe this would bring me more desirable effects.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(28, 1171, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"5","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>If I have a chance to be away from my home for a year, I would like to take a laptop computer besides clothing and personal care items. A computer is very important in my life and all of my daily activities are going on with my not book computer. Through several definite examples, I will demonstrate that a laptop computer is the best thing that I would like to bring with me for my a-year trip.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, I can mail to my family and friends using my laptop computer.</MI1> <SI1>With the help of the Internet, it is very easy to correspond with my family and friends. Once I was in Canada for 1 year, I used to use e-mail to contact my family and friends. It is very fast and cheap. <TR>Besides</TR>, there are some kinds of messenger service, which enable people to chat in the Internet. I usually chat with my family and friends with messenger service. It is free of charge and real time.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, it is very easy to get the travel site information through the Internet.</MI2> <SI2>There are a lot of web sites that are provided by travelers, travel companies and local government agencies. I can make a use of it not only for gathering the general site information but also for cutting down my travel expense by adopting the best way to travel, which a lot of former travelers have been experienced. Before taking a trip, I usually visit website to get information. But for a 1-year-long trip, I would like to bring my laptop with me and check the information day by day whenever I want to move another place.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>Last but not least</TR>, I can record my journey. It is one of my hobbies to keep the record of my journey.</MI3> <SI3>There will be a lot of things that I want to memorize, but I cannot remember all happenings and all information. Using my laptop computer, I can write down my daily schedule, my feelings about the places that I visit or stay. After returning from the trip, it helps me to review and recall my trip.</SI3></BO3>\n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, if I bring a laptop computer, I can have a lot of benefits from it. I can get a lot of information about the travel place, I can send and get mail easily, and I can keep the record of my journey. With these great advantages, why not take a laptop computer to your trip?</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is complete with a position and a good preview of the main points as well as being strong.  There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(29, 1172, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"2","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>If I received money as a gift from somebody, I would buy a piece of jewelry. There are several reasons why I want to buy the jewelry rather than to go the concert. Here I will demonstrate the reasons with definite examples.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, a piece of jewerly can be a fortune.</MI1> <SI1>Anybody has a possibility to be in difficulties in his/her life. When people are financially trapped, they can sell the jewelry they own to have a liquidity. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, when I was a high school student, my father''s business was almost bankrupt due to korea''s financial recession.</EX> At that time, many people in korea lost their jobs and business owners downsized their companies and employees. My father was no exception. <TR>However</TR>, the jewrly my mother possessed helped my father to save his business. From this exprience, I realized the jewerly is valuable for our rainy days. <TR>Therefore</TR>, I prefer buying a piece of jewelry to attending concert.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, I can watch the concert on TV even though it is not vivider than on the spot.</MI2> <SI2>As the technology in audios and videos is getting developed, we have better chances to see&nbsp;&nbsp;performances and listen to the music through the media than ever. Whenever we turn on the TV, we can meet many celebrities who we may wish to meet. <TR>For instance</TR>, when I went to the concert of Jo Sung-mo, one of the most famous singers in Korea a few years ago, I was really disapointed because I was too far from the stage to see and enjoy the concert. Watching it on TV was much better at that time. <TR>Therefore</TR>, I would rather buy the jewerly than go to the concert.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In short</TR>, If I have a money received from someone as a gift, I would buy the jewerley because I can use it when I have a financial difficulty. <TR>In addition</TR>, I can enjoy the concert through TV or radio.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(30, 1173, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"3","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>If my school has received a gift of money, I recomme my school to spend this money in the exchange of the old computers. I think in university it is the most effective way to invest money in the computer systems. There are three reasons: we can accquire the information fast through the computer, and the computer make us do various tasks, and we can get the job easily for the computers.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, I recommend my school to spend this money in the exchange of the old computers.</MI1> <SI1><TR>Nowadays</TR>, the importance of getting information is increasing greatly. Today is the day of the imformation. Especially, through the Internet we can get a variety of the information fast and wide. <TR>However</TR>, the computer systems in my university are so out of date that I can not obtain the information fast. Many students in the university complain about the slowness of the Internet due to the out of date computers. <TR>Therefore</TR>, I strongly believe that the brand new computers can make it possible for us to get the informatio fast and wide, and this can add to the prestige of my unversity.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2>Apart from the covenience of the Internet, the new computer can make the students do a lot of things.</MI2> <SI2>There are many things for us to do by computers. As a whole, most of the students make the reports by computers, and some of the students use the computers for their graphic designs. <TR>However</TR>, the brand new computers are so expensive that many students can not afford to buy it. As for my university, although the computers system is rather out of date, many students want to use this. <TR>Thus</TR>, the computer rooms are always packed with the students, and many students wasted their time in waiting the lines. <TR>Therefore</TR>, I recommend my school should buy more computers to satisfy the need of the students.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>Finally</TR>, the computers are also useful for getting the job of the students.</MI3> <SI3><TR>Nowadays</TR>, many firms want to recruit those students who are expert in the computer skill. If my university is well furnished with the new computers, the students are able to get the precious experience with it. <TR>Thus</TR>, the students of my university get the more opportunity to have the good jobs.</SI3></BO3>\n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, investing money in the computer systems is the most effective way in my university because we can accquire the information fast through the computers, and because the computers make us do various tasks, and because we can get the job easily. Why not buying the computers?</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(31, 1174, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>In general, people are not satisfied with what they have. In many religions, because of this tendency, people can never feel happy. Perhaps, that is true. But the other side of the coin of the fact is that people have developed themselves so as to get something more. I mean this tendency encourages people to try harder to develop themselves in both positive way and negative way. So I think it is worth thinking about the reason people are never satisfied with what they have.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Nowadays</TR>, it has been a boom of lottery in Korea.</MI1> <SI1><TR>Surprisingly, according to the statistics, there were some rich people, more than average, won the first prize. In other words, even though they were considered rich enough, they bought a lottery. Why is that?? I think it is because people normally compare a person, having something more or better than them, with themselves. <TR>Therefore</TR>, in spite of being considered rich, as long as there is more rich person, he or she can never be satisfied with what they have. Actually, most of human being has a kind of instinct to be better than others. So they can not give up trying to get more than others. In this respect, people can never reach the peak of their hope or goal in whole life.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2>In academic field, this tendency could play an important role.</MI2> <SI2>People want to know something more than others. They are never satisfied with what they have already known. So, they try to study many scientific aspects and social events. I guess people base this tendency on basic curiosity. When they are born, they do not have any knowledge of the world, such as the reason, if they touch hot water, they feel hurt. But as they are growing up, they have learnt a lot from experience or books. But these sources are also not enough to fulfill their basic curiosity. So because of their curiosity, people can never been satisfied with what they have already known. They need something new and different from previous knowledge.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, it has both positive and negative aspects that people can not satisfied with what they have. But I think both aspects are kinds of basic human instinct. I mean people want to be better than someone else so they want to get something more. And also, people have much curiosity to know about the world so they try to have more knowledge. I think that is why people can never stop trying to get something more and different.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. The structure and balance of the essay between its parts move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(32, 1175, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"3","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>In general, the knowledge can be divided into two types: natural knowledge and social knowledge. Science and math are important components of former, while history and literature are essential parts of the latter. We may find that our personal interests draw us to one field of study more than any other. But I believe that no one can argue that it is more important to study any of these fields over the others.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, only complete knowledge can make a really knowledgeable man/woman.</MI1> <SI1>We know that the world consists of not only the object studied by the subject like science and math, but also invisible things studied by the subjects like history and literature. Lack of knowledge will lead to an incomplete view about the world. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, a student specializing in the mathematics will need in-depth understanding of philosophy and its history.</EX></SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>, the social knowledge and natural knowledge are both necessary for the continuation of our civilization.</MI2> <SI2>Science and mathematics form the foundation of all our physical structures. Without these fields we could not have buildings, automobiles, airplanes and all the myriad machines necessary for them to run successfully. <TR>However</TR>, without understanding of the world and humanism earned from the social knowledge, the civilization could be dangerous. As science develop, the horror of a mass destruction weapon is getting to increase. If we don’t learn the value of life from the literature and a risk of such weapon from the history, the third world war can happen on the earth again.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, I disagree that it is more important for students to study history and literature than to study science and mathematics. The world and its history cannot be divided into neat categories. I think that it is essential to have a balance in the study of the natural and social knowledge.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(33, 1176, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>In Korea, most high school students have to wear school uniforms. <TR>However</TR>, I&nbsp;&nbsp;think that the students need to decide what to wear to school because it is part of education and the cost of uniforms is expensive.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, the students could learn about how to express themselves while they choose their clothes.</MI1> <SI1><TR> In general</TR>, clothes are very important in that people can know about others throughout not only their impression but also their clothes. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, if I met someone who wear jeans, I could guess that he likes comfortable things.</EX> <TR>Thus</TR>, people need to learn how to express themselves with clothes and what kind of design and color suit for themselves. Even though reading, writing and studying is more necessary for students, thinking about themselves is also important.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Furthermore</TR>, some parents have to spend a lot of money to buy their children''s uniform because it is very expensive.</MI2> <SI2>In Korea, the cost of uniforms is about two hundred thousand one and it is almost same as suits for adults. <TR>Also</TR>, students throw away their uniform after graduating school. If they wear freely, a lot of money could be saved or used for more effective things. When stuents have things which they like to wear anywhere, they could use them long enough.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>Even though school uniform have many merits, I think that students need to choose how to wear and think about what clothes suit for them because it is sort of learning themselves and they could save money. If Korean student wear as they want to do, they could feel more free about themselves.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(34, 1177, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"3","si":"2","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>In our daily work of lives, we always have our supervisors who control us, scold us, and predict orders to us. And by them, our works can be enjoyable or hateful. So I think some important qualities which a good supervisor must have are objectiveness and a sense of responsibility among several qualities.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, a good and admirable supervisor should have objectiveness.</MI1> <SI1>In most our business lives, we are judged by the efforts that we have invested and the results that we have got. So unless they are judged objectively by the supervisor whom we work for, we cannot feel a sense of accomplishment and will not follow the orders from our boss. <TR>Then</TR> it will be evident that our work office or factory cannot get the progress because our effort and capability are not admitted well.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, a sense of responsibility is needed to a good boss.</MI2> <SI2>We, as a human, do not everything perfectly and may fail or make a mistake. At that time, a good supervisor should be able to hide our small faults and even take all responsibility for us. In doing so, we will trust him and can work better for him.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>From these two reasons, I feel that a good supervisor should have both objectiveness and a sense of responsibility in order to lead his followers well. From him, we can learn the valuable things which we should know to become a good business man, and our work will be enjoyable working with him. Furthermore, we will be able to be the ideal model as a good boss to our would-be followers in the future.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  There are no examples in this essay. The supporting points are much too vague and lacking in strength. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(35, 1178, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>In the consequence of technical development, things have changed a lot. So as to this change, human-beings live longer than the past. Of course there are a lot of reasons, I think both the improvement of medical techniques and the nutritional diet tables cause this phenomenon. To illustrate why I convince my point, I will treat only a few significant reasons with my vivid experience as follows.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Above all<TR>, I want to point out break-though development in medical techniques.</MI1> <SI1><EX><TR>For example</TR>, according to a medical magazine, surveyed in 2003, human-beings'' median life span is 88 years old.</EX> This scrutiny shows the life span has increased more 20 years than the past. It causes the development in treatment for patient. <TR>Therefore</TR>, I am of the idea that improved medical techniques help this phenomenon.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2> Another reason is eating habit.</MI2> <SI2>As human-being live in comfortable circumstance, they have concerned with the nutrition in foods. So, when people think of profusions, they often envision nutrition which these foods contain. And, they usually have habitual eating time for their health. <TR>In addition</TR>, they prefer to eat vegetables, rather than to eat meat. Because vegetables prevent fat, and enable people to clean their blood. In other words, to eat nutritious and balanced diet tables keep them more healthful. <TR>Thus</TR> I think balanced and nutritious diet tables help for people to live longer than the past.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>All in all</TR>, I strongly think that human-beings live longer than the past. The reason why I think like this is not only because the medical techniques have improved, but also the diet tables have more nutritious than the past. Of course there are a lot of reasons to consider, I believe there is no substitution for afore-mentioned things.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(36, 1179, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"4","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"3","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>In the past in Korea, children were valuable workers. <TR>Therefore</TR>, parents had the tendency to have more children. In the course of time, <TR>However</TR>, parents had fewer kids than before and seemed to cherish them. That is to say, children were hardly expected to become a energy source. <TR>However</TR>, if kids did not help household chores, they would not lose the important factors such as the relation and respect.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR> of all, household things need conversation.</MI1> <SI1>It means that the relation between family members could be better than before through talking about each other. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, my father was always a being hard to say something related with family affairs. But, as time has passed, I had the chance to settle this chilly relationship through having a dialogue from simple to complex.</EX> Now, I have the good relationship with my father. If I did not assist household matters, it would be impossible for me to recover this situation.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Next</TR>, housing chores such as doing a laundry and dishes are not simple.</MI2> <SI2><TR>However</TR>, If I did not directly practice them, it would be impossible for me to know how complex they are and what kinds of knowhow I need to settle the problem. Although they do not appear complex, they have a procedure and method. Only parents know this kinds of the procedure and method. As learning them, I came to respect our parents again.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>To make a story to short, as a coin has two side, there are pros and cons about bring children to clean house chores. Although, now it is not in the past, other sorts of mediums make us to earn important components including relationship between family members and respect for their parents. If I did not choice them, I would maybe earn merit; good relationship and reverence.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is complete with a position and a good preview of the main points. It could be made stronger, however. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(37, 1180, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"1","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>In these days, gamers tend to increase gradually. Some people say playing games don''t have benefits at all; I don''t think that. Through playing games, I could learn about coordinating. <TR>In addition</TR>, I delete stress which I received in daily lives.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><MI1>Have you ever play a on-line game?</MI1> <SI1> On-line games are developed recentely. What''s the on-line game? The definition of a on-line game is that through an Internet, they play a game with other people. They can chat and play with other players. So, if they want to play with others nice and interesting, they must keep politness. In this situation, they can learn about politeness.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2> For a long time, ancestors have played games, for they wanted to treat stress.</MI2> <SI2>While they worked, studied&nbsp;&nbsp;and so on hard, they had suffered from stress. So, many games have been developed in many countries. <EX><TR>For instance</TR>, our ancestors in Korea had many games, playing four traditional musical instruments, Ca-jyun Nol-yi etc.</EX> When they watched them, they felt exting, fun, extreme and so on. Through games, they treated stress received in daily lives.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>I think that if persons play games, they can much learn about lives. Above mentioned it, they can learn politeness and eliminate stress. I want to tell you; if you have a problem in lives, how about playing a games some of the times? I think that you say ""that''s a good idea!."".</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. There is no thesis statement. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(38, 1181, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"5","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>In these days, higher education can be available to all student in Korea because the recognition that people who want to be educated are eligible to study spreads society. <TR>However</TR>, some people say that higher education should be prepared for good student. In my opinion, college or university education should be open to all student in that education should be fair in any case and we could discover some talents we miss.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, education should be open to every student because everyone has the right to be educated.</MI1> <SI1>I think, if the society does not gives people who want to study the chance to be informed, it is not for the everyone. It could be said unfair society. <TR>For example</TR>, Choseun Dinasity, Korea 500 years ago, gives the right to be educated only to selected people, Yangban. <TR>However</TR>, there is no difference between selected people and non-selected people <TR>In fact</TR>. Although non-selected people had the right to be educated, people at that times didn''t know how important the right is. <TR>Consequently</TR>, Choseun Dinasity had fallen down slowly. Does the society at these days make that mistake, too? <TR>In this manner</TR>, though it sounds theoretically, because everyone has the right to be informed education should be given to every student.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, if we offer higher education to good student we can''t find the talents we omit.</MI2> <SI2>Some students who are proved ''not good'' could have some talents in other areas. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, a friend of mine who couldn''t go to university because of her low grade in high school possesses the ability to draw something like people''s face and movement artically.</EX> <TR>Nevertheless</TR>, she was not admitted to study art more since she was not successful in mathematics and science. <TR>In this respect</TR>, I think higher education should be available to every student in that we can see the capacity which can be lament now.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, I think higher education should be offered to every student because of the right to be educated in modern society and the ability we could miss. The more education, the more talents we could discover.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is complete with a position and a good preview of the main points as well as being strong.  There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(39, 1182, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"2","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>It becomes to be a heatedly debated issue whether governments should spend exploring outer space or not. Some people hold the opinion that spending money for our basic needs on the Earth. <TR>However</TR>, others insist that exploring outer space is quite important for people in that maybe there are some intelligent lives in space. If I should choose one of these positions, I choose the latter. I have specific reasons to support my argument.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>As you know, Earth’s resources such as gas, coal and iron is limited.</MI1> <SI1><EX><TR>According to some article of some scientific newspapers</TR>, we will use all of resources we have within 100 years.</EX> Some scientists say that big wars for obtaining resources will start. It is a catastrophe to all. <TR>However</TR>, we have one solution through exploring outer space. There are 7 planets in our system and there are a lot of stars in our galaxy. In some planets or stars, there are good resources we can use. Exploring outer space not only give us resources but also prevent our catastrophe.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2> Another reason that can be seen by every one is meteolites.</MI2> <SI2>There are a lot of meteolites between planets. Most of the meteolites are far away from the earth, but some can be close to the earth. As you know, before advent of human beings, Earth is the dinosaur’s world. But when a single large meteolites clash with Earth, they were extinct. It can recur to human beings. To preclude impact of meteolites, it is worthy to spend money for exploring outer space.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>Admittedly</TR>, to explore outer space we should spend so much money. <TR>However</TR> considering exploring space is what we do to survive. I believe it is wiser to spend as much money as possible exploring outer space.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(40, 1183, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"1","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>It causes many advantages to build a large factory near my community; such as more jobs and increased revenue. <TR>However</TR>, it has another aspect; environmental problems, congested traffic. In my view, I approve to build a factory near my town. Now, let''s look into my opinions.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><MI1>If a company has announced to build a large factory near a town, residents living in a town oppose to build it at first.</MI1> <SI1><TR>They think that a factory destroy their environments such as air, water, and plant. <TR>Moreover</TR>, due to the fact that more trucks drive in a town than the past, traffics of the town are more increased. <TR>Thus</TR>, people feel more uncomfortable and they regret to permit to build a factory.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>On the other hands</TR>, if a company building a factory invests more money to develop roads in a town, to purifying environment and to eliminate industrial waste, residents are more fresh and comfortable.</MI2> <SI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, a factory pays many revenue to a local government. <TR>Therefore</TR>, a local government invests more money to improve residents'' welfare. <TR>If so</TR>, community grow more fast and quality of residents'' lives develop better; such as more fresh environment, comfortable town, and a lot of amenities. <TR>Also</TR>, young people''s employment opportunities increase, too.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, if a factory engage to build purifying systems of environment, I always agree to build it. There are a lot of advantages. Benefits are greater than dangers. I support to build a factory and hope that readers accord my opinion.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. There is no thesis statement. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(41, 1184, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"2","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"3","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>It is difficult to choose whether goverments should spend money improving either roads or public transportation. Personally, I agree to develop public transportation. When goverments do that, air pollution of a city and rates of using natural resource are waned. <TR>Moreover</TR>, citizens'' welfare is increased.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR> of all, if goverments improve qualities of public transportation, like increasing buses, taxis, and subways, citizens feel more comfortable.</MI1> <SI1><TR>Especially</TR>, during rush hour, people aren''t hustled by others and don''t feel angry more. <TR>Moreover</TR>, because of increasin public transportation, a city can earn more transportation fee than the past. So, a city makes an effort to develop citizens'' welfare and qualities of a city. <TR>Thus</TR>, citizens feel more happy, comfortable, and fresh.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Also</TR>, if goverments increase a number of public transportation, people use them more than the past.</MI2> <SI2><TR>Therefore</TR>, in the present, one of the great social problems, air pollution are decreased. <TR>In addition</TR>, another great social problem, deficiency of natural resource are solved automatically. If public transportation are more comfortable than the present, people don''t often use their own cars. <TR>Thus</TR>, air pollution are waned and rates of using natural resource are decreased, too.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, if goverments improve public transportation, our lives in a city are more comfortable. We don''t have any chance of stressing by public transportation because of crowding in bus and subway. <TR>Moreover</TR>, environments will be clearer than the present. <TR>Thus</TR>, we feel more fresh.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There is an optimal amout of transitionary words in this essay helping with the flow and reading of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(42, 1185, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>It is easy for young people to get influenced by the media. Nowdays young kids spend more times watching movies or television than they spend times with thier family, they learn things that are inappropriate for themselves, such as taking drugs or smoking cigarettes at the young age. For young girls, they get to have the wrong definetion of being pretty from the idol movie stars among the young girls.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>My friend''s brother, Eric is a fifth grade kid who thinks of himself as one of the coolest persons in the school.</MI1> <SI1>His behaviors towards his friends or teachers are very impolite, and he believes that smoking cigarettes and taking drugs with several older kids in the school are the only way to become popular. Whenever his sister, Marta tries to talk to him about his behaviors in the school, one of the famous lines that has always been come out of his mouth is, ""I do those kinds of things because I saw people doing on television shows or movies and they seemed cool."" He has gotten some immoral ideas of being a popular, good student through the unintelligent TV programs or movies.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2> My younger sister has been complaining about her body shape and face, lately.</MI2> <SI2>She skips the meals to get skinny like a stick, and urges my parents to let her have a plastic surgery so that she can be satisfied with much bigger eyes, a higher nose, thicker lips, and a smaller face than all of hers. All the famous stars on television or movies have the perfact image-the Barbie doll type, and these young girls definetely believe that in order to be called as a beauty, they need to look a like superstars. They do not pay attention how to be healthy, they only care about how to look beautiful to the people.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>There are many unintelligent programs and movies that can lead young people''s mind into the bad direction. Since young people does not have the ability to judge what is wrong or bad, young kids tends to take wrong inpressions from what they see on TV and movies. In some what ways, Media needs to concentrate on better contents for young people.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. The is no real structure or balance to move the essay from one portion of the essay to the next. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(43, 1186, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>It is often argued that having a large factory in my community has more advantages or more disadvantages. The following essay outlines the pros of building this in my community and the cons of.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>One of the most outstanding cons is that it can lead to serious pullution in my town, including water, soil, and air pollution.</MI1> <SI1><TR>As a result</TR>, it can possibly affect the ecosystem badly, which should be preserved safely. It is possible that we might not be able to drink, breathe, or raise some vegetables in our land.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2> There also must be more people in my town than ever, when we decided to agree to build a large factory.</MI2> <SI2>The more people there are, the more problems there are. Like this sentence just mentioned, there will be more crimes ,because criminals usually go common places where people are bustling to get a better chance to steal money readily.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>However</TR>, it could be helpful for the economy of my town to have such a large factory.</MI3> <SI3>When we had a large factory, people around our town would assemble ,and so consequently they would have to spend their money to buy something to eat, to entertain themselves, or to support their families.</SI3></BO3>\n\n<CO><TR>To conclude</TR>, although it can contribute to develop the economy of my community, I firmly believe that the disadvantages of having a large factory clearly outweighs the advantages of it as it can bring about the ruin of our ecosystem and lead to more crimes.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(44, 1187, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>It is true that society has been developed a lot in so many areas, such as education, environment, and entertainment. This advancement has brought us opportunities to enjoy ourselves indoors. Actually more than two-thirds of people in my country spend leisure time indoors, usually doing computer games. I, <TR>However</TR>, do not think that spending free time inside is mroe favorable than doing it outside, with regard to more benefits it can bring to us.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR> of all, people can make friends more easily when they do sport.</MI1> <SI1> It is an absolutely good way to get on well with other people through sport. <TR>Moreover</TR>, doing sport can improve our health, even though it needs physical efforts. People do not have to consider their health seriously which is becoming a great issue in society.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2> All people who own their company also has to spend their time outdoors.</MI2> <SI2>They are supposed to have the leadership which is a really important skill to run their companies. By means of doing sport, they can make the leadership stronger than ever. <TR>Therefore</TR>, even if their companies are put into a difficult situation, they can get over it with the strong leadership.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>However</TR>, some people believe that it is also a good way to spend their free time playing computer games without any distractions.</MI3> <SI3><TR>I, <TR>Nevertheless</TR>, do not assert this statement. They become isolated although they do not realize it, and as a result they can probably loss their social skills.</SI3></BO3>\n\n<CO><TR>For these reasons</TR>, I can say that I prefer to spend my free time outdoors without hesitation, and I strongly believe that people should spend their time outdoors as there are definitely more benefits and nobody should be isolated from society.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There is an adequate number of transitions in this essay though not optimal. Either too many or too few transitions can get in the way or otherwise detract from the reading of this essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(45, 1188, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"3","si":"2","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>It is widely accepted that the most important animal is a dog in my country. The following essay explains why I think a dog is the most improtant animal.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To start with</TR>, a dog is more familiar with human beings than any other animal.</MI1> <SI1>It is really a crucial point to my country which has become a industrial country. People living in a complex country usually feel lonely, so they tend to find something enough to make them joyful. I believe that a dog is really suitable for it, as a result more than one-thirds of people in my country have dogs, especially in a complex city.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2> Another point to bear in mind is that a dog can prevent my house from robbery.</MI2> <SI2><TR>Actually</TR>, there are some reports about these cases. <TR>Therefore</TR>, when an owner has a dog, the owner can pay less attention for the house while the owner is out of the house, because of the dog which is always attentive. <TR>Moreover</TR>, having a dog can be educational for children. Due to the lack of friendship with other children, children might not learn social skills. Even though a dog is not a human beings, it might be helpful for children to get along with other pepple.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>For these reasons</TR>, I firmly believe that a dog is the most important animal as having it can obstruct people from feeling lonely and it can keep a house safely.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  There are no examples in this essay. The supporting points are much too vague and lacking in strength. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(46, 1189, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>It was a really exciting experience to get into an English conversation class in a private institute, located in near my home. As soon as I got out of military service, I decied to learn how to speak Engligh, and so I happened to join that class. I believe that the English class is the most interesting class I have ever taken, associated with the excellent teacher and the materials.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>I remember that there was a good teacher who was a foreigner and had taught Engligh for over 5 years.</MI1> <SI1>He encouraged us to keep concern about English whenever we felt as if we wanted to give up. While we felt sleepy, he usually made us laugh and concentrate on our study again. What is the most appreciated one is that he always took care of us. It was the unforgetable event that he brought some medicines after he found one of us sick.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2> Another point I have to deal with is the materials which the teacher used.</MI2> <SI2>Those were about diverse kinds of cultures around the world. Having experience of several cultures, even if in a indirect way, is useful for us, expecially when we go abroad. <TR>Moreover</TR>, talking about something in English is a real thing. Students in Korea usually learn English for over 10 years, but they cannot speak English at all. Due to the lack of practical programs, they waste their best time, I suppose. By this I mean, it was extremely interesting to learn how to speak English in like a real situation.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>Therefore</TR>, I cannot still forget the time and also do not hesitate to say that it was the best class I have ever taken, as the teacher was incredible and the materials were really useful in my life.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(47, 1190, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"4","si":"2","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Many high school students, even those who graduated from technical high schools or financial ones, want to enter a university. So the number of universities and colleges increased much as the number of students who want to go to a university increased. <TR>Thus</TR>, it is said that some universities will have to close down their door because of a lack of students who will attend them.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><MI1>But, so what? isn''t it illiteracy that we cared about, not literacy?</MI1> <SI1> Wouldn''t it be better for us to think about how to decrease the universities and their students because there are too many of them rather than we worry about our gloomy future resulted from illiteracy? Plus, Education plays an important role in our society, which is giving ordinary people an opportunity to get a higher position. That means without higher education ordinary people can never be at a higher position, acquire any fame and a lot of money.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<CO><TR>According to statics</TR>, more than two third of the students attending high-ranked universities in Seoul proved to be rich or richer than the average. If it is true, we must admit that poor people cannot be at a high position in society, and make a lot of money in the way he or she pursued, though college degree doesn''t always guarantee high positions or success. And if so, the rich will become richer and the poor, poorer. So I think all education including university education should be always open to all students.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There are no examples in this essay. The supporting points are much too vague and lacking in strength. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(48, 1191, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"3","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"3","si":"2","style":"4","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Many people have some opinion about this topic. Some peple prefer to use money when they earn it than to save it. Others don''t do that. As far as this topic is concerned, I agree to use money when I earn it. Now, there are some reason concerned my advocacy.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>If you enjoy your hobbies, you spend money and time learning and exercising.</MI1> <SI1>In my experience, when I learned playing violin, I spent quite much money of my salary learning it. <TR>Nevertheless</TR>, while learning it, I didn''t think that my salary is spent useless; I understood to play violin, increased my hobby, and had much time for my interest. While learning it, I was so happy, exciting and interesting, so I was satisfied with it.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2> When I went to collage, my tuitions are so expensive.</MI2> <SI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, since I lived in dormitory, I paid for feeding, renting for room and so on. For these reasons, I couldn''t depend on my parents to pay all money. So I affected tutors on high school students and worked at a library, a food restaurent and a convienient market etc. I paid some duties by my salary. Although I couldn''t save money, I was happy because of helping my parents and independence from them.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO>Some people laugh at my way. <TR>However</TR>, I like to my way and I will do that. I always say ""Present is the most important than any other time."" I strive to do my best in present during my life. How about you? Enjoying present is the most important things of any other thing.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  There are no examples in this essay. The supporting points are much too vague and lacking in strength. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(49, 1192, '{"ibc":"4","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Many people learn in different ways. The method of learnign something varies from people to people. Some prefer to leran by doing things, others prefer to learn by reading or listening. In my opinion, the best way to learn something is by doing things, becasue this method make me understand the point clearly, and because in this way I can really do some things well.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>To begin with,&nbsp;&nbsp;I am able to learn the point clearly by doing somethings.</MI1> <SI1>As a whole I can obtain a variety of information by reading materials. <TR>However</TR>, this knoweldge is usually so superficial that I can not adapt this to the very situations that I want to solve. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, recently I learned the way to make home pages. I read a lot of books concerning this topics.</EX> <TR>However</TR>, not until I made my own hompages, did I know the exact meaning of the contents of the books. In this experience, I really understand that the only way to learn something clearly is by doing things.</SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>In addition</TR>, I can really do some things well by doing this things.</MI2> <SI2>There are a lot of good ways to learn somethings, but in some subjects doing things is the only way to learn somethings such as learning a foreign languages, musical instruments, and so on. \n<TR>For example</TR>, I have learned Engish for many years. But in this long time I have not had the chacne to use English as the real languge. I studied Englsh only in the books and cassette tape. Recently, I have the chance to get the English friends. We often meet each other and do a lot of things. In this way, I really understand that English is not a subject but the languge, and I can speak English well. <TR>Therefore</TR>, by doing something is the good way to learn somehing well.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, the best way to learn something is by doing things becasue in this method I can understand the point clearly and I can really do some things well.</CO>"', 'This is an above average quality essay. There is adequate structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis statement is only partially complete as it either makes only a position or provides a preview of the main points, not both as required. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. The supporing ideas in the body paragraphs are forceful and support the thesis statement but have trouble connecting through to the conclusion. There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(50, 1193, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"2","topic":"3","coherence":"4","transition":"2","mi":"3","si":"3","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Many people like change, - change in lifestyle, change in the way of doing something. They are even willing to accept any kinds of challenges. They want to experience various kinds of works and social activities. They are very energetic, outgoing and extrovert people. The reason why they like change is because they are not afraid of failure. They accept failure as threshold on which they can prepare for further leaping.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>On the other hand</TR>, those who do not like any change in life are said to be conservative.</MI1> <SI1>These kinds of people, they can be classified into two groups -- One that doesn''t like change because they are afraid of failure or, afraid of the possibility of failure. The other group is the one that doesn''t like change because they are not just used to the new way of doing something, but not afraid of it.</SI1></BO1>\n \n<BO2><MI2> I think both of the two kinds are necessary for out society because as in the political parties, they are divided into two groups, one which is radical and another conservative, so that they can harmonize together and any one-sided opinions cannot be taken.</MI2></BO2> \n \n<CO><TR>In my case</TR>, I can describe myself as a person who likes change. A person who doesn''t like change is like stagnant water in a swamp, and stagnant water will be spoiled within a few days. Since I don''t want to be stagnant, mediocre in this dog-eat-dog society, I would rather like to change myself to a person who enjoys the change itself, even if I was not such a change-preferring person.</CO>"', 'This is a below average quality essay. There is minimal structure between the parts of the essay to move the essay from the introduction thru to the conclusion. The thesis is fragmented and separated throughout the introduction and does not constitute a statement. There are minimal and inadequate transitions in this essay hurting the flow of the essay. The main ideas in the body paragraphs are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the thesis.  There are  very few examples in this essay. The supporting points are still a bit vague and do not have sufficient strength to support the main points.  There were many word choice issues as well as errors in punctuation and grammar.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(51, 1194, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>Many people who move to another country have difficulty in choosing whether to keep their own customs or follow the new customs. Some people prefer the former in an attempt to sustain their identity. Other people prefer the latter for their successful life in foreign country. <TS>Undoubtedly, both aspects are important. But, as I will demonstrate through several examples, people moving to another country should adopt and follow the customs of the new country.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1>There are some benefits when people keep their customs in a new country. <SI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, it will increase family bond. There are not many people in a new country who truly understand your situation except your family members. Besides, they can sustain their own heritage and their mother tongue. Especially, it is studied that language is likely to disappear if it is not used. <EX>Once I met someone from foreign country. His family is from Korea, but he could not speak Korean, even a single word. I felt very strange and thought that he lost his family’s identity.</EX></SI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>On the other hand</TR>, there are a lot more benefits when people follow the customs in a new country.</MI1> <SI2><TR>Firstly</TR>, they can learn a native language faster and make many friends easily. It is generally accepted that it is hard for them to go around the country and to understand more about the country without understanding language. <TR>Moreover</TR>, they can easily learn cultural and social roles. Living in a new country is very different from traveling. <TR>For a short time</TR>, they can live without knowing cultural and social roles; </TR>however</TR>, they should learn cultural and social roles to live for a long time, to be succeed in their life, and to keep successful life.</SI2><BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, it is very important for people who move to another country to keep their own customs because it helps them increase family bond, keep family’s heritage and mother tongue. But more importantly, they must learn and adopt the customs in a new country so that they can easily learn foreign language, make friends and make a successful life in a foreign country.</CO>"', 'A very good essay. Nice job!');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(52, 1195, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"0","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>Modern technology has enabled us to land on the Moon., which could have only been imagined to do. <TSThe government is trying to pour its budget in exploring the outer space. It is very difficult, however, to achieve the goal for the time being due to following problems.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO><MI><TR>First</TR>, there are many works for humans to fight on earth like famines, unconquered diseases and discrepancies between nations.</MI1> <SI1>Many problems caused by the economic imbalances among countries and among people have forced us to care for the poor. The welfare enhancement through stabilization policy should be implemented by the governments, which cost it a lot of efforts and money.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2>The costs of enlarging our territory out of earth are too excessive compared with its benefits.</MI2> <SI2>There are few countries like U.S. which dare to think of boosting its plans. Because there are little synergy effect and cooperation of countries, the exploring countries should take much burden in the project.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>Finally</TR>, the uncertainty of the space-traveling scheme is too high.</MI3> <SI3>High cost investment without the expected considerable returns would be fatal loss that is not desired. <TR>For now</TR>, exploring outer space is like a gambling or a lottery. It is not undesirable for government to rush into this uncertain games.</SI3></BO3>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, government should reconsider the outer space exploring project, instead it must spend this money for our basic needs on Earth. The present overwhelming problems to be solved bestow our government with mission to take them on the basis that government is responsible for the nation''s demands.</CO>"', 'Your essay is pretty good, but you really need to have a thesis statement! Your main points are very strong, but you could use some more support for your arguments, possibly some examples or something a little clearer than what you have.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(53, 1196, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>People may meet or talk in person less with the development of telephones and email. <TS>However, I don''t agree that telephones and email have made communication between people less personal. Below are the reasons that I base on.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, telephones and email made people keep in touch even though they live far away each other.</MI1> <SI1><EX>For example, I live in Canada now, but I talk with my parents on a phone and send email to my friends in South Korea. Using an internet telephone, I can see and talk with them now. I also send pictures to my parents and friends by email which I took in Canada.</EX> How would it be possible without telephones and email?</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>, people can save a lot of their time to communicate using telephones and email.</MI2> <SI2>If one wants to meet another, he or she needs to spend more time to go to a meeting place, eat or drink something such as supper or coffee, and talk with them. People may think that meeting in person is more personal, but even we talk on a phone and send email it would depend on how they talk and send email. <TR>Today</TR>, we can do many things through internet such as sending a card and picking a letter paper for email, and talk on a phone face to face using a internet phone.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO>Telephones and email are common to use nowdays. Many peple rely on them and use them every day. Some people think telephones and email have made communication between people less personal, but they have made our communication better personal between far countries and they also have made our time be saved. It depends on us to use telephones and email with our beloved ones so that we can keep in touch with them.</CO>"', 'An excellent essay! Take the transition out of your thesis statement and add a quick summary of your reasons to make it perfect.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(54, 1197, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"0","topic":"4","coherence":"3","transition":"4","mi":"3","si":"3","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN>Most of house have the car. It show us the importance of car. car has became the portion of our life. <TS>we use the car when go to office. go to shopping. go to buy stuff. in addition, car is significant not only for indivual vehicle but also for public vehicle. bus and cab accelrerate to live complicate life pattern of modern life.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO><MI1><TR>Firstly</TR>. since people have used car , they can go rapidly before. ships, trains, so on are too can go rapidly.</MI> but car is using more time than other vehicle. so car is vehicle ajacent to human. <SI1>in addtion to not only speed but also comfortablity is also useful. because of shoal trips and sporadic accident of humna life as death of kith and kin and hope for going to anywhere, people are uncomfortable. but these matter are sloved for automoble''s advent and development.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>secondly<TR>. automoble is special car for people loving car and it''s speed.</M2> <SI2>in modern life as each other have themselvs penchent, somebody preper to performant car show, and to emulate racing car and to own beautiful or antique car. these are never unaccustomed for us but they are familiar to us. in addition to car is means to show attribute of the indivually aesthetic sense. car''s color and design are important as operation as.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO>people who say car has many serious problem are unknown of the merit of car. the one of car''s problem is air pollution. but air pollution are not responsible for car. it contain other reason as industry factory. in addition to, air problem of car is being solved. other alternative resource car are incubating. if human gradually solve car''s problem, they can use the car more wisely. and more people will detect the advantage of car</CO>"', 'Your essay is all right, but it is missing a thesis statement and the writing is a bit confusing. Also, I think you could probably think of a stronger point to advocate cars than just that some motor heads like fancy ones.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(55, 1198, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"4","coherence":"5","transition":"4","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>People have different opinions about the advantages and disadvantages of early education. <TS>Although some insist that early education has a positive effect on young children, I strongly believe that young children should spend most of their time on playing because it can develop their sociability.</IN></TS> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>On the one hand</TR>, children can achieve brain development through school studies.</MI1> <SI1>According to a graduate student'' thesis, young children can receive more information than old people during the same time as computer harddisk is empty. <EX><TR>To illusrate</TR>, I lived in Seoul where people have lots of interest in early eduation of English. Like other parents, our parents sent me englis language school in six years old. I still remembered the englis word.</EX> As my experience demonstrate, It is important that children learn early.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>On the other hand</TR>, children can learn about how to blend in well with peer in their school.</MI2> <SI2>In contemporary time we get along with a lot of people. So, It is significant for us to understand other''s way of thinking. <TR>For this</TR>, we should be able to mix well with other people that has different background. <TR>Therefore</TR>, spending children''s time on playing is better than stuying.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In summary</TR>, I strongly believe that spending children''s time on playing is more meaningful because it can cultivate the sociability.</CO>"', 'You have a very good organizational style and clear writing. That is great. I think your second main idea could be a little bit better. You are talking about it generally - try to talk about it more in terms of school vs. play. Also, your second main paragraph has a few too many transitions. They can distract from your point.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(56, 1199, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"4","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>In modern life that ""time is gold"", Whether eat at home or at restaurant is important issue in terms of time management and efficiency. Some people like to eat at home because of comfort mood and less money. Nevertheless, I prefer to eat out because it can save us time and I am able to select food among various foods and costs.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1>Eting at restaurants saves me time.</MI1> <SI1>I can enjoy food as soon as I order and <TR>even more</TR>, I don''t have to waste my time on cooking food. <TR>Actually</TR>, preparing food to eat at home is very time-consuming task involving buying ingredients, making food and setting the table. <TR>On the other hand</TR>, at a restaurant, what I have to do to eat something is just ordering some menu. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, I went to the restaurant near my house with my brother because I was too tired to make some food at home owing to my heavy homeworks. I made an order a pork steak and immediately I can eat it! <TR>For me</TR>, having trouble with my halfdone homeworks, eating at a restaurant allows me more time to study done.</EX></SI1> <TR>In this manner</TR>, I prefer to eat out in that I can save my time.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>In addition</TR>, there are a variety of foods and costs at a resataurant</MI2>. <SI2><TR>Thus</TR>, I have a more chance to select food that I want to eat. I usually eat some routine food which is mainly Kimchi, a Korean food and fried egg. <TR>However</TR>, I can enjoy a special food eaten at home rarely. <EX><TR>As an example</TR>, when I went to the foreign restaurant at my father''s birthday, I was able to eat Robster at first in my life! It was so big that my mother maybe couldn''t cook this food if we want to eat it at home.</EX> <TR>Moreover</TR>, costs at a restaurant is as various as the kinds of foods, so I can choose the best food considering my pocket money.</SI2><BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>Consequently</TR>, although there are advantages when I eat at home such as relax mood, I prefer to eat at a restaurant because not only does it save me time but also I can select fittest menu among various food at a restaurant.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! Take the transition out of your thesis statement to make it stronger. Also, watch your transitions - you are using a few too many.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(57, 1200, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>Most people are very sensitive to the government’s plans nowadays. When it comes to constructing a new university in our community, the reaction of people in our community will be the same as other governments’ plans because there are advantages and disadvantages. <TS>Through the definite examples, I will demonstrate that I don''t agree with the idea of establishing a new university in our community.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>There are some advantages if a new university is built in our community. <TR>To begin with</TR>, a lot of students and other people will come to our community so that our local economy will grow and be prosperous.</MI1> <SI1>A university is accompanied with not only many people but also other buildings, such as shops and restaurants. As a result of increased population and more building, our local economy will develop and get more revenue. <TR>Besides</TR>, our local population will be diversified and we can enjoy various customs and events. Lastly, The reputation of our community will be enhanced with this university, especially when the university receives some awards.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>On the other hand</TR>, building a university will harm our community in some ways.</MI> <SI2>It is taken for granted that the more people are, the more troubles occur. <TR>To begin with</TR>, there will be heavy traffic congestion, which hinders people from getting around, especially on weekends, and the crime rate will be getting higher and it will make our community an insecure place. <TR>Moreover</TR>, environment pollution problem will be caused and will harm our health. These side effects will not only badly affect on our community inward, but also cause the reputation of our community to be going down outward.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, it is very important that building a new university will bring many advantages, such as developing our local economy, diversifying local population and enhancing the reputation of our community. <TR>But more importantly</TR>, the side effects on building a new university is harmful to our community in some ways; heavy traffic congestion, high crime rate and environment pollution. Therefore I am not in favor of the plan to build a new university in our community.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! I think it would be a little stronger if you talked a little more about why you personally disagree with this idea.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(58, 1201, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"4","coherence":"3","transition":"5","mi":"3","si":"3","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN>My community is a famed. As famouse of green mountian and fresh air, many visitors come to my community. <TS>If factory is built in my community, the clean environment will be destroied. So I oppose the factory.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1>If factory is built in my community, many people can find their job as a worker of the factory.</MI1> <SI1>Then a father of my bestfriend who has no job getting a job, my friend can get better life than now. Of course not only a father of my friend but also many other jobless can get their job at the factory. So factory can give my community a advantage.</SO1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>But as I told before</TR>, my community is very famouse of clean environment and beautiful senery. So my community is managed as a famed. If factory is built, the clean environment will be destroied.</MI2> <SI2>And my community will be lose a value as a famed. As a famed, destroied environment is huge disadvantage. Then more people than who get a job in the factory will lost their job. because in my community there are pople who inrolled in siteseeing is much many than jobless.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO>So If a company has announced to build a large factory near my community. I’m oppose that factory.</CO>"', 'This essay is just all right. You need to make the language a little clearer and add some more examples or research. Example: when bringing up pollution, studies and research are excellent support.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(59, 1202, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN>My town is located in the middle of big cities including Seoul, the capital of Korea, and Bundang, the new developed city. This position of town would have a lot of effects on living environment. <TS>If a person is planning to move to our town, he would feel convenient in traffic surroundings and natural environment, but it would be hard for him to live in the civilized environment available in a large city.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, geographical merits that the town is located between large cities allow people living in our town to move to another city more easily.</MI1> <SI1>These days, people tend to act in larger sites because population density is higher, so it is hard to live in a close region near companies or schools. <TR>Accordingly</TR>, it seems clear that the importance of traffic system is being enhancing. Also, the town around a forest give us good living environment, such as clear air, water, the teacher helping children learn the important role of nature. It could make students more emotional and more pure.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>However</TR>, regional characteristic that the town is far from cities also could give the trouble in that it is difficult to live with city conveniences.</MI2> <SI2>According to the improvement of living factors, we tend to spend the time on entertainment including seeing movies, shopping, meeting the friend, and so on.</SI2> I think it would be harder for people to have these good environments than in cities.</BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, as mentioned above, not only does living in our country give the advantage like traffic convenience, and clear natural environment, but also it could force people not to live in convenient surroundings.</CO>"', 'This is a pretty good essay, but I think your second main paragraph needs some work. It is a little unclear.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(60, 1203, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"3","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN>No one in human society is identical. In other words, people have all different characteristics, preferences and opinions. Especially, when it comes to high schools require all students to wear school uniforms. <TS>Personally, I think that high school students must wear school uniforms. To illustrate why I convince my point, I treat only a few significant reasons with my vivid experiences here.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, high school students can be hampered from crimes by wearing school uniforms.</MI1> <SI1><EX>One survey on donga newspaper says 30% of juveniles crimes decreased after high schools regulate to wear uniforms.</EX> Not until I red this report did I realize about requirement of uniforms. <EX><TR>To give another example</TR>, if one student wearing a uniform want to smoke or go a dance bar, he or she may not be able to do that because many people know he or she is a student as they see the uniform.</EX> <TR>Consequently</EX>, I oppose that school permit students to decide what to wear to school.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Next</TR>, high school students can concentrate on their studying.</MI1> <SI1><TR>To put it simply</TR>, reducing time to select and buy the cloths make it possible for students to study more. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, when I was a high school student, I did not need buy extra cloths for fasinating me who wear the uniform so that I could involved in my accomplishment.</EX> <TR>Moreover</TR>, they can save the money. By wearing the uniforms, they need to use neither the money nor time.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, I agree high schools do not have to require students to decide what to wear. The reasons why I think like this are because they can not only be encumbered from young generation crimes but also save the money and time. It is a good idea that schoos sometimes permit students to decide during festival in school.</CO>"', 'This is a pretty good essay. Some of your wording is a little confusing (ex. Last sentence of your first main body paragraph). Take the transition out of your thesis statement to make it better.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(61, 1204, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>Nowadays many people in Korea try to go abroad not only to study but also to live in a new country. When they move into the new country, they may be worried whether they keep their own culture and customs or follow those of the new country. If I were them, I would follow the customs of the new country where I move. Here, I will demonstrate the reasons with definite examples.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>On the one hand</TR>, following the customs of the new country allows us to pick up the language easily.</MI1> <SI1>To adjust oneself to a new environment, learning language in essencial. Were it not for taking up the language, we would not have a job or friend. <EX><TR>For instance</TR> when I was in England several years ago, I tried to adapt myself to English customs as soon as possible without any prejudice. After following the new customs, I could make many English friends who I can communicate with. It made my English skill improve.</EX></SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>On the other hand<TR/>, keeping their own cusomes prevent them from adjusting themselves to the new circumstances</MI2>. <SI2>When people go to the foreign country, they feel unfamiliar and homesick. It can have a bad effect on life and study in abroad. We have to adapt ourselves in the new situations to survive. As old saying, when in Rome, do as the Romans, because the customs we keep can not be accepted in the new country.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, although there are benefits when we keep our own customs in a new country, we try to adjust ourselves to new circumstances with following the new customs to live well in a new country.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! Your thesis statement needs to be a little more independent.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(62, 1205, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>Nowadays the importance of the house is increasing greatly. There are a lot of rooms in the house, and each room has its own importance in the house. Some people regard the living room as the most importannt one, while others consider the dining room as the most important one. <TS><TR>In my opinion</TR>, I think of the computer room as the most important one because I can do some work, enjoy myself and talk with family in this very room.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, I am able to do my work in this room.</MI1> <SI1>I can search the information through the Internet in order to get a variety of information. This information make it possible for me to keep the pace of my job. <TR>Sometimes</TR>, I prepare my job report in this very computer room because my job often reguire writing a report. Therfore, computer room is really convenient room for my job.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>In addition</TR>, I also play various amusement activities in the computer room, especially like computer games.</MI2> <SI2><EX>My apartment is provided with the ADSL service, the information highway, so I can enjoy the computer game freely in this room. Recently I played ""Diablo"" from the blizzard entertaintments. This game is so interesting that I sometimes forget to sleep and eat. I really enjoy this computer game in my computer room, and this give the additional pleasure to me.</EX></SI2></BO2> \n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>Finally</TR>, I can talk with my wife in the room.</MI3> <SI3>My wife is also interested in the web-surfing. <TR>Thus</TR>, we are often together in the room. We talk to each other in this room while searching the Internet. This is the precious time for us.</SI3></BO3> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, I consider the computer room as the most important room for the above reasons. I can work my job in the computer room, I can get the amusement in the omputer games, and I can spend time with my wife in the room.</CO>"', 'A good essay. Nice work!');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(63, 1206, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>Nowadays we have more and more education systems, matrials and skillful teaches as our interests in education is increasing. They can teach our children scientifically and effectively. <TS><TR>However</TR> I think parents are the best teachers as good supporters and influencial models at present as well as in the past.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, parents are the best supporters for their children.</MI1> <SI1>They love their children more than any other teacher and have the most time with their children, So they can realize enough what their children are, what they are interested in, what aptitude they have and so on. <EX>Edison, <TR>one of the most famous inventors</TR>, was poor at school work in his childhood. <TR>However</TR> his mother knew his son''s own special ability and she helped him do better.</EX> Like Edison''s mother, parents can support their children improve their talents.</SI1><BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, parents are the most influencial models.</MI2> <SI2>Especially children under school age learn social rules form their parents and they think their parents'' behaviors absolutely right. <TR>Therefore</TR> they follow as they see. <EX><TR>For example</TR> they get to know when to cross the street and where to throw away garbage by seeing and experincing with their parents.</EX> In other words children can learn naturally how to live and act uprihtly.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, it is certain that there are many good education institute and teachers but parents teach thier children the best by giving good care and supports and life models, which cannot be bought with money. So I wish to say parents are the best teachers.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! Take the transition out of your thesis statement to make it stronger.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(64, 1207, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>Nowadays, our society needs more profesional people. There are many people who concentrate on their own feilds and due to their devouts, our society can be well-organized. <TR>Therefore</TR>, the specialized education is quite necessary for the university students. In this essay, I will present two reasons and details supprorting my view.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, students can learn more deep and professional knowledge though their one major.</MI1> <SI1><TR>In other words</TR>, university students decided their major when they enter the universities. Their majors can be the best chice for them so they can focus on it with more interests. <TR><EX>For example</TR>, the recent research of the humanity department of my university showed that the students wanted to study their major more deeply because they believe that the only specialized knowledge can be the most valuable thing in their universtity lives. Studying the several sujects can mean that students can learn only superficial things of the subjects.</EX> <TR>In this respect</TR>, the broad learning of many sucjects cannot give the professional knowledge at all.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Seconld</TR>, students can get much help from digging one subject in the university.</MI2> <SI2><TRIn other words</TR>, almost all university students want to get jobs after graduating the university and,for the jobs, more specailized information and knowledge is just crucial thing. <EX><TR>For instance<TR>, my sister''s major is the early children education and she studied her major for four years and she became the teacher of the kindergarden in my comminity. In my case, my major is English literature, so I am making an every effort to get good grades on it. In this respect, concentrating one major can bring the better job opportunities in the future.</EX></SI2><BO2> \n\n<CO><TR><In conclusion</TR>, I firmly agree with the idea that university students should be focus of the one subject because students can get more profesional knowledge and information and they cal also get more help to find the suitable jobs in their future. The specialized knowledge and the better opportunities for the jobs are closely connected each other.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! Take the transition out of your thesis statement to make it stronger.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(65, 1208, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>Nowadays, owing to develpment of transfortation, people can move to another country than ever before. Some of them cling to their customs in other countries while others change their life style. <TS><TR>In my case</TR>, I prefer to follow the customs of the new country since I can get along with the neighbor more rapidly and be adjusted to the new life in another country easily.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, when people admit the customs of the new country and follow them they can be familiar with the neighbor fast as well as can be adapted to the new way of living in the new country.</MI1> <SI1><TR>Actually<TR>, people have nostelgia when they leave their mother country from time to time. The best choice to avoid it is to be adjusted to a new life and get close to a person living next door. And there is no better way to make a friend than following the traditions of the new country because people tend to feel benevolent with a person having similar traditions which can be called a life style.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO1><MI2>Compared with the choice of following customs of another country, there may be some advantages when people cleve to their own customs in a new country; remembering their mother country and showing their own traditions to the others in foreign country.</MI2> <SI2><EX><TR>As an exmple<TR/>, we can think of Indonesians in England. Although they live in a foreign country they keep their cultural life style involving clothes, hair style, and even faith. By doing so, they can not only remind their real country, Indonesia, but also have the effect to exhibit their exotic customs to the English.</EX></SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, while following traditions of the new country when people move to enables people to be familiar with the neighbor and be adjusted to fresh and new life in foreign country, keeping traditions makes it possible for them to remember their cultural habits and show it to the others in a new country. In spite of the merits of maintaining own customs, I preper to make some change on my life style when I move to the other country because of the reasons that I have mentioned above.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! Nice work!');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(66, 1209, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>Nowadays, this society needs more people who take the proper jobs and tasks. <TS>If there are just a few people to work with, the society can not be well operated. Hence the more people who can work, the more efficient in the estabilishing the taskes. In this essay , I will present a coupple of reasons and details supporting my view.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>TO begin with</TR>, a group of people can make the taskes in a more fast way.</MI1> <SI1><TR>In other words</TR>, people can share the jobs and they can make it more quickly than doing alone. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, in these days, our corporarions are now trying to begin the new work structure that is the team structure in the company not former prependicular and rigid systems. All teams have equall amounts of importance and taskes in the company and there are little stiff atmosphere among the workers any more and the result of the takes is much higher than before.</EX> The main cause of this can be the rapid and efficient speed between the worker. <TR>In this respect</TR>, a group of people can do their works very quickly.</SI1><BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, a group of people can solve the difficulties better and they can also think much better methods in their works.</MI2> <SI2><In doing the several works, people can face a lot of problems so that people should solve them. If people can speak their own solutions on the propblems, people can find out the best solution for it. Moreover, people can pick up the more excellent means for their works quickly. <EX><TR>In my case</TR>, when I had to do my presentation, my friends and I made a team and we could find written materials and oral resources on the topic, so I can make my presentation in a satisfied way. I really appreciated with my friends because without them, I seriously doubt that I could make it that much.</EX> In this sense, many people''s wisdom can solve the difficult situation more quickly and they can yield better ideas.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, the grouip of people can be more beneficial because group of people can cooperate their work more rapidly and they can find out much better solutions on the problems and ideas on the ponderous situation. Due to these reasons, present society needs more fast and well-organized teams more and more for better efficiency.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! Take the transition out of your thesis statement to make it stronger.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(67, 1210, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"4","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>Owing to the development of transfortation, people have broader choice to whether they live in one place or move to another place today. Some people live in one place because of their personality of being safe. <TS>However, I preper to move to another place throughout my life because I can experience many cultures and live in better condition.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1>Through moving to other places for living, I can obtain many cultural expriences of other countries and this is the reason I preper to move on place to place.</MI1> <SI1>The more moving behavior, the more valuable experience. <TR><EX>As an example</TR>, my uncle , who likes to change his living place, has told me that his life is full of exitement through his cultural experience in other places. He is now living in China and crazy about Cyung keuck, Chinese musical performance.</EX> <TR>In this respect</TR>, moving to other country gives me amusement of experiencing other ways of life.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>In addition</TR>, changing living site makes people possible to make a better decision and eventually, it is concerned to the better life.</MI2> <SI2><EX><TR>For example</TR>, my sister living Seoul, a Korean capital, could have more precious job by moving to Seoul. She once worked for small and bad-pay job as secretay, but after moving to Seoul, she can be the head of a branch.</EX> <TR>In this manner</TR>, people live more valuable life by doing so.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>Consequently</TR>, I preper to change my living residence because I am able to experience diverse cultures, and ultimately I have chance to live better life.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! Take the transition out of your thesis statement to make it stronger. Also, try to make your conclusion a little longer.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(68, 1211, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>People actually live longer than before. This situation can be explained for various reasons. I think that the most important reason is the development of medical technology. The other reasons are what people can take more information of health by indivual way and people eat some food benefit to oneself body.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Firstly</TR>. The development of medical technology give us much things.</MI1> <SI1>Many of diseases unhealed before are healed. Many of diseases unknown before are known to people and doctor. Detecting Reasons and consequences of disease have helped human to win suffering disease. And then human can have more much hoping for life.</SI1><BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>. There are much information and much concerning for health.</MI> <SI2>The young and The old are both stressing their state of the health. They find the mothed for health. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, I can see running old people at night in high school ground. They does for each other reason that someone need adequate sport, someone must lessen their weight because chubby state will bring other disease.</EX> <TR>In addition</TR>, Many people dose dieting. Foods are very significant for human health. Food even can remedy the disease. and can help to human not having the disease to live longer.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO>People in modern society can live longer for many remedy methods, the information of health, and the their efforts. <TR>In future</TR>, now unhealed diseases can be healed and more much informations are discovered. People can longer than now.</CO>"', 'Your essay is good, but it needs more support - especially the first main body paragraph. Medicine is a huge topic, so talk about it some more. Add some examples to both paragraphs.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(69, 1212, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>People always work very hard to attain success in their chances. <TS><TR>However</TR>, I think that efforts aren''t everything in success. Luck is a very important factor, also. I strongly believe that success without luck is impossible. Luck help us to acquire a chance and to increase self-confidence.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><MI1>Even though people make an effort to complete their aims hardly, if luck isn''t allowed to them, they don''t achieve their aims perfectly.</MI1> <SI1>When luck is allowed to us, we can have more opportunities and increase a probability of success. <EX><TR>For instance</TR>, a man has worked to attain a job. <TR>Now</TR>, he become a good craftsman at his major. <TR>However</TR>, unfortunetely, he doesn''t have any chance of acquiring a job. <TR>Eventually</TR>, he doesn''t use his abilities for his major.</EX></SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Also</TR>, luck gives us increasing self-confidence.</MI1> <SI2>A man, who is often lucky, always think ""I can do everything when I want to do it."" When he acts anything, if luck(even though luck is a little) is given to him, he can work easier than he can without luck. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, during his collage days, he worked hard in his major. And then, when he goes to society, he could get a job with because of helping luck.</EX> <TR>Now</TR>, he enjoys in his office and is satisfied with his life.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO>People don''t always have much luck. <TR>However<TR>, in their daily lives, with helping luck which is a little, they have a better chance. If you work very hard, you have a trouble without luck. However, remember it. Luck always helps us. The first in success is hard work, and then luck.</CO>"', 'This is a very good essay! Your main points are excellent. Your second example is a bit awkward since it is hypothetical and not real. You are in danger of using too many transitions, so be careful.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(70, 1213, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>People have different opinions about intimate relationship with their pets. <TR>With regard to this issue</TR>, I am of opinion that freindly connection with pets is good because it contribute to relieve loneliness and aware of importace of lives.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Most of all</TR>, frendly connection with pets is conductive to alleviate solitude.</MI1> <SI1>Everyone agrees that someone who lives alone has loneliness to some degree. <EX><TR>To be more specific</TR>, When I was freshman, I lived alone with my cat. Whenever I came back my room, I felt deep lonesome feeling. After I live with my cat, my life changes drastically. The cat was my friend who listen my troubles and soothe my weary heart.</EX> <TR>For this reason</TR>, friendship with pets is good for lonesome people.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>In addition</TR>, intimate connection wiht pets could help us to know about significancy of lives.</MI2> <SI2>It is a common held belief that it is important to understand importance of lives. \n<EX><TR>For example</TR>, children who live with pets would see pets'' birth and death. Then they apprehend value of lives.</EX> <TR>In this respect</TR>, deep connection with pets is conductive to understand importance of lives.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>All in all</TR>, even though there are other opinions that close relationship with pets, I have every confidence that intimate connection with pets is good for people who need to relive their loneliness and it make people to know significancy of lives</CO>."', 'An excellent essay! Great work!');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(71, 1214, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>People sometimes imagine that some money as a gift has been given by someone. If people obtain the money, some people buy an attractive piece of jewelry or other people go to a concert. If I were this case, I will get an attractive piece of jewelry because jewelry is permenant and can change it to money again.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Firstly</TR>, I prefer coming by jewelry to attending a concert because jewelry is long-lasting thing.</MI1> <SI1>Participating a concert pleases participator for a day or two days at most. <TR>However</TR>, people having jewelry can enjoy seeing jewelry forever, and well-keeped jewelry inherits it to their children.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly<TR>, jewelry is possible to exchange it of money.</MI2> <SI2><EX><TR>Out of the blue</TR>, a car accident occurs to my son, but I don`t have enough money. If I can alter my jewelry to money in unexpected case like this, my jewelry is used of uncountless value. In unusual case like this, jewelry can resell for most of the original value.</EX></SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In my case</TR>, some money which is given to me use buying an attractive piece of jewelry. I would rather have jewelry than go to a concert in that jewelry isn`t temporary and can use money.</CO>"', 'This essay is pretty short, but I think you explain yourself quite well. Good job! Your thesis statement could be a little stronger if you change the transition in it to say what the situation is.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(72, 1215, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>Presumably, if there is a rule that students who reside in dormitory must share the room with roommate, people may be troubled about someone who live together in school life, roommate. Some students want to have a roommate by university policy, on the other hand, I would like to harness a room in dorm with my acquaintance as far as possible. In this essay, I will mention reasons about my opinion.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with<TR>, I''d rather not room with someone who is a entire stranger to me.</MI> <SI1>If I share my room with this stranger, trust issues would be nervous to me; <TR>Therefore</TR>, I might suspect my roommate. <EX><TR>To illustrate</TR>, I fought with my roommate once because of my stolen stuff, when I was freshman of University in Korea. At that time, I was suspicious of him under the unavoidable circumstance, and then, after this incident, there would be made a mental barrier between us.</EX> In this respect, sharing room with first faced man might make puzzle school life of students who live in a dormitory.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2>Another reason I support is that there are certain types of people whom I cannot room with.</MI2> <SI2>Some students would like to smoke in their room, other students tend to keep their room clean or stay up with bright light. No doubt that these kinds of people are not suitable for me due to my opposite tendency and taste. If I maintain other people who have different habits from me, I finally would move to another apartment.</SI2></BO2>\n \n<CO>""Birds of feather flock together"", as this old saying goes, people prefer to get along with their acquaintances. For these reason as I have mentioned, it is natural that a student insist he share dormitory''s room with his friend or acquaintance.</CO>"', 'This essay is pretty good. I''m not sure what you mean by first faced man, though. Also, taking out or changing the transition in your thesis statement will make it stronger. Instead of what you have, you could put something like Personally.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(73, 1216, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"3","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>School is the place where people called students learn and study something. Besides the school also plays various ralls in society. So building a new high school is very important matter. I think we should builde another new high school in our society.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Most of all<TR>, I think that the number of school is not enough in my community.</MI1> <SI1>There are about four to six hundread students in one grades in nomal high school. And there are about 35 students in one class. Comparing to the number of teacher there are so many students in one school. It prevent teacher from having students discuss something in class. So it might be very useful in increasing the quality of class.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Besides</TR> if a new school were built, it would make various economic adnvantages. <SI2>Some people would sell books around the school, or someone maybe start a stationery around the school. It help people get more income in various ways.</SI2> \n\n<CO>Building a new high school dosen''t mearly mean that the place where students study is made, but it means very important, advantage and profitable station is made. So I support building a new high school.</CO>"', 'This essay is a great start. Your points are really good, but I feel they need a little more support to make them really stand out.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(74, 1217, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"4","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>School uniforms have several advantages over the common school dress code. The school uniform is simpler, is less expensive, and can be satisfying to students.</TS></IN> \n \n<BO1><MI1><TR>First of all</TR>, the school uniform is simple. It is more convenient. <SI1>Students don’t have to worry about what to wear to school. They don''t have to worry about whether the day''s temperature is cold or hot, whether they are in ""style"", or what their friends are wearing. Also it looks very neat, when the students are together. They represent their school with neat uniforms very well.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, the students and their parents spend less money on clothing. <SI2>They only pay for the uniforms, but nothing else. A ""new outfit"" is never needed, a ""special occasion outfit"" is not required. The latest trend does not affect the cost of school clothes. The school uniform is more economic and saves money. <TR>However</TR>, when the school designs the uniform, it should consider students’ thoughts. The school should present samples and offer a vote to select its uniform.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<BO3><MI3>The school uniform is for the students, but not for the teachers to wear.</MI3> <SI3>The opinion of students about the design of the school uniform is more important than the opinion of any others. Having a choice and a voice makes the uniform more appealing to students.</SI3></BO3> \n \n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, the school uniform has many advantages. The uniform makes dressing for school simpler, and the students look better. They don’t have to spend a lot of money for their clothes, and are more satisfied with the uniform that they choose. There is an argument for school uniforms.</CO>"', 'This is a very good essay. Try to add something to your introduction so that it doesn''t make up your entire thesis statement. Also, your third paragraph is off topic. I suggest taking it out.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(75, 1218, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>Since history began, trade has existed as well. Mankind invented the trade and market system because one could not produce all that he or she needed. <TR>Thus</TR>, in ancient times, our forefathers exchanged goods one another, while later they paid some money for what they wanted. <TR>There are both advantages and disadvantages of either paying money or paying products, but I prefer using money for the following two reasons; convenience and value-fixation.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First of all</TR>, it is more convenient to pay for something with money than with goods in most cases.</MI1> <SI1>Let''s assume I were a farmer cropping watermelons. <TR>In such case</TR>, every time I need something, I have to bring some watermelons with me, which must be a strenuous work. If I use money, <TR>however</TR>, I can keep some in my purse, and I can visit where I want to go with my hands free.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Besides</TR>, money keeps the value of our products lasting. <SI2>Couldn''t I sell my watermelons, they would lose freshness and get pale. <TR>As time goes by</TR>, the value would plunder, and I would make far less money than before. <TR>However</TR>, if I exchanged redundant watermelons with moeny, I don''t need to worry about the value reduction, because I can keep moeny that is equal to their original value.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In sum</TR>, with money, we can not only easily go to market and buy what we want, but also keep the value of our goods unfrailed. <TR>Of course</TR>, trade with products has also some advantages; we can get what we need just through one-step, and we can save cost in making money. <TR>However</TR>, I think the benefits of money far outweigh the advantages of barter system, and <TR>Therefore</TR>, I prefer paying money.</CO>"', 'An absolutely excellent essay. Great work.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(76, 1219, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"3","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>Some people believe that progress has always brought about benefits since the prehistoric time. <TR>However</TR> I do not agree this statement ,in reference to our environment and the nature of human.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1>Human beings have made lots of progress in a variety of areas including education, agriculture, and economy. <MI1><TR>Yet</TR>, we should consider our environment which has been getting worse.</MI> <SI1>Many factories have been built almost every domain and polluted soil, water, and air. We might not be able to live when water become entirely polluted, because it is essential to support our body for us whose body consists of more than 70% of water.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2>Another point to bear in mind is that human beings are social animals, and so they absolutely need to get along with other people.</MI2> <SI2>Due to the high technology, people do not have to go school, go somewhere else to work instead of their house, and attend some meetings. They can actually do it just using their computer in their home. <TR>Therefore</TR>, people communicate with other people much less than before. It could be possible for our society to be destroyed, because of the lack of relationship.</SI2>\n\n<CO><TR>For these reasons</TR>, I firmly believe that progress is not always good as it has brought about our environment polluted and could ruin our society according to our nature.</CO>"', 'Your main points seem to be awfully far apart topic-wise. I can see why you''ve chosen them, but they might be too dissimilar to put together. Even so, if you do use them, you need to add a lot more support, especially to the first main body paragraph. Also, try to add more to your introduction so it isn''t your entire thesis statement.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(77, 1220, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN>Some people complain that computers have made their lives complex and stressful even though the computers support many important parts of our lives. <TS><TR>Using computers</TR>, our lives have been much eaier and more convenient with many tools which were made of computers such as airplan, telephone and internet.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1>When we go to a far country from our nation, we can now arrive in the country in a day.</MI1> <TR>However</TR>, <SI1>before computers were developed, how long did our ancestors take time to make a trip to an other country? It took over 2 months to come to America from Europe. We can save a lot of time.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><SI2><EX><TR>As an other expample</TR>, we can now talk with our family or close friends face to face using internet phone althogh we live far awar from them.</EX></SI2> <MI2>Computers made us keep in touch with our cherished ones.</MI2></BO2> \n\n<BO3><MI3>The development of internet would be the revolution of computers. <SI3>We can now find our information very easily and conveniently. Before internet was created, we had to go to library and look at many books to find the information we need. <TR>However</TR>, if we need to find some answers, we can use searching engines on the internet and the answers come out on the monitor.</SI3></BO3> \n\n<CO>Computers are maybe complex to learn first time, but as soon as one learns how to use. There isn''t more convenient and easier. I certainly assert that computers have made our lives easier and convenient as well as they save a lot of our time in many ways.</CO>"', 'This essay is pretty good, but I would take out the first main body essay - it doesn''t fit with the rest of your essay. Concentrate on the most obvious computer-related things. Also, you really need to add a LOT more support to your main body paragraphs.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(78, 1221, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>Some people enjoy change in they lives so they are likely to have new expriences. <TR>However</TR>, others like their lives to stay the same. Therefore they tend to try not to change their lives'' style. Both attitudes have apparent benefits. <TR>Given that choice</TR>, I would like to enjoy many changes in my life for following reasons.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, because a human''s life lasts over 70 years, I would be easily bored about my life without any unexpected change.</MI1> <SI1><EX><TR>For example</TR>, imangining that there are always stable stats such as going school and getting back home, getting married when it is time to do and then having a baby in my life. i think it is such s tedious life pattern. <TR>As a result of that</TR>, I may be depressed and get used to normal things.</EX> I have only a single given life. I do not let my life go through usual, normal events.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>On the other hand</TR>, challangable and unpredictable life patterns give me cheers and insights into my past life.</MI2> <SI2><EX><TR>For example</TR>, a dramatic change in the life, failure on the college entrance exam was s great obstacle to me. <TR>However</TR>, I realized that it also gave me the mind that I can overcome and look for it again. <TR>Since then</TR>, I like to change my living environments such as reallocation of stuffs in the room or having a hobby that I have never done yet. By changing the things around me, I could reorganize my life''s plan and push myself to live lively and affirmatively.</EX></SI2><BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, even if staying the same in the life is lesss dangerous and more stable to get through life time, it can make one''s life tedious and depressed seemmingly. <TR>Therefore</TR>, I would prefer to take dramatic change in my life.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! In your thesis statement, clarify the choice - what is it?');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(79, 1222, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"4","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"4"}', '"<IN>Many students have received their grades during their school days. Some students received low grades; others received high grades. <TS>I think that grades encourage students to learn more fervent. Students who receive low grades endavor to attain higher grades. <TR>Moreover</TR>, because students must receive grades in universities or institutions, they strive to get better grades. The reason is that companies or markers estimate them by their grades.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><SI>In all schools, students exam regurlarly. After they take examinations, they receive their grades about examinations. Students who get lower grades than other students shy and they strive to attain higher grades than the past. The more they strive, the higher their grades are. Students always strive not to be shy to others due to the low grades. <TR>Thus</TR>, they are enthusiastic of all things.</SI1> <MI1><TR>In the sense</TR>, grades help students to reach better situations.</MI1></BO1>\n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Frankly speaking</TR>, despite ircorrect situations, most of the companies, institutions, or academies consider students by their grades.</MI12> <SI2>From middle schools to universities, we always have received various kinds of grades. <TR>Thus</TR>, owners of companies think that applicants'' grades mirror their abilities, and value. For this reason, students strive to get better grades to attain jobs. Grades are the most objective data about themselves.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In brief</TR>, in order to get occupations, and not to be shy to others, students always study hard to get better grades. Grades are not everything but important things of their lives. I strongly believe that better grades equal 90 percent of success.</CO>"', 'This is a very good essay! Try to make sure your main points are made at the beginning of your paragraphs.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(80, 1223, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>Some people may say that eating at food stands or restaurants are better than eating foods at home, because of the convenience, quick service, and the variety of foods. <TR>However</TR>, through several definite examples, I will demonstrate that eating food at home is better than eating outside.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Firstly</TR>, preparing foods is enjoyable.</MI1> <SI1>While preparing foods for my family, I feel very pleased and imagine that my family will be contented and pleased by my servings. <EX><TR>In deed</TR>, after finishing the foods, all of my family members show their pleasant and gracefulness to me.</EX></SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, it''s more sanitary.</MI2> <SI2>I read a lot of news about unsanitary stands on the street and restaurants. In an attempt to cut down the cost, they sometimes use bad ingredients and also they don’t clean the ingredients properly. I think they don''t have enough moral to serve other people. I am not saying that all the restaurants are unsanitary, but some are really. Owing to these some unsanitary stands and restaurant, I hate to eat foods outside.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>Last but not least</TR>, I can save the leftovers easily.</MI3> <SI3>I can eat the leftovers later or I can share them with my family later. <EX>A research shows that the annual waste cost from restaurants is enough to save a number of beggars on the street.</EX> It’s really shock to me. In other words, saving cost from my home can save a lot beggars through other manners.</SI3></BO3> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, eating outside has good advantages, such as the convenience, quick service, and the variety of foods. <TR>However</TR>, eating at home is better than outside because it is enjoyable, sanitary, and cost saving. With this great advantage, why not make foods for your family?</CO>"', 'This is mostly a good essay. Take the transition out of your thesis statement to make it stronger and add some more support to your main ideas (which are very good). I would delete the last sentence of your third main body paragraph as it is false logic. Finally, try to avoid asking questions in test essays.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(81, 1224, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"0","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TR>Some people often argue that books with unrealistic content is far from the truth of real world, and that only nonfictions based on the fact are worth reading. I strongly, <TR>however</TR>, disagree with such point of view for the reasons that will be discussed as follows.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First of all</TR>, sometimes fictions such as novels and short fables make it easier to understand the real truth.</MI1> <SI1>That''s one of the reasons why people like reading novels. <TR>Throughout novels</TR>, which contain possible situation and imitate the fact, people can not only enjoy the thrill, but also find the solution to the problems they have encountered. <EX><TR>In additin to novels</TR>, Aesop''s fables shows how the fiction story can be beneficial. In Aesop''s short fables, animals talk and behave like mankind. What an unrealistic they are! Over the ages, <TR>however</TR>, people have learned much lesson from Aesop''s fables, and that''s why people loved his fables, read them again and again.</EX></SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, some books involving the imaginary world have showed some people the way to the future.</MI2 <SI2>Stirred up by the imaginary and fantastic world, many children determine what they will do in their adulthood, and become leading scientists. <TR>Thus</TR>, the scientists advance the science and technology, and finally come true their imaginary world, beginning from the motivation of the unrealistic fiction. We can find such inventions everywhere in our life; robots, spaceships, computers, and so on.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In short</TR>, even books on fiction world are worth reading. They have made their own contributions to the world. Even if they seem to be nonsense, who knows if those books will contribute the development of our future?</CO>"', 'This is a great essay. Add a thesis statement and it will be perfect!');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(82, 1225, '{"ibc":"3","thesis":"4","topic":"4","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"4","si":"5","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN>Some people presume that parents are in the most important role for their children’s education. Basically that could be true since children stay their home most of their time. <TS>Although parents should be familiar with their children’s academic affair, <TR>in my opinion</TR>, they are not the best teachers for their children.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO><MI1>Generally parents expect their children to do what they wanted to do but they couldn’t do when they were young.</MI1> <SI1><EX>I know a friend of mine who was forced to enter the law school by their parents although his interest doesn’t go with that. His father was eager to be a lawyer back in his twenties, but he failed.</EX><SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><SI2>I also have a friend who wanted to be a journalist but his parents wanted him to be a scientist. And he was forced to enter one of the best science colleges. But he finally gave up his master degree after his 10 years of studying.</SI2> <MI2>These examples pinpoint how parents’ misled expectations to their children give their children a great burden in vain.</MI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In many cases</TR>, parents are not good teachers because of their misled expectations. <TR>Thanks to it</TR>, many children lose their chances to study what they are really interested in.</CO>"', 'This is a good essay, but if you are only going to make one point, you need to put that point in your thesis statement also. Your two main body paragraphs are talking about the same thing, so put them together into one body paragraph. Can you think of any other points you can make in a second paragraph?');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(83, 1226, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"4","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"4","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>Some people think that borrowing money from a friend can not be bad the friendship because it can be useful when friends are in a financial predicament. In my opinion, however, I agree that it can be injurious the friendship. To illustrate why I convince my point, I will treat only a few significant reasons with my vivid experiences here.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Above all</TR>, when I borrow money from a friend, if I do not receive money, the friendship will be broken.</MI1> <SI1>Breaking the mutual confidence can not be irrevocable. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, when I was a university student, I borrowed some money from my friend who I had known her since elementary school. She borrowed some money from me, and I concerned her trouble and did not want to receive money owing to knowing her finance crisis. <TR>However</TR>, she didn’t pay back the money. <TR>As a result</TR>, she went out of communication. I didn’t want to receive a debt but wanted to be her correspondent. Nevertheless, she did not make contact with me for sake. The friendship was broken off and it was not easy to be recovered.</EX></SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>, if someone borrowed money from a friend and did not recover a debt, he would lose his entire friend because other friends kept away from him. <TR>In addition</TR>, he would have sense of shame for his friends.</MI1> <EX>Once my mother borrowed some money from her friend and did not receive the money, the fact would have spread all over friends. <TR>After all</TR>, not only does she lose her friend but she also loses trust.</EX></SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, I have no choice but to agree that borrowing money from a friend can be bad and damage the friendship. The reason why I think like this is because it can make confidence as well as friends lose.</CO>"', 'This essay is pretty good, but your second main paragraph is pretty weak. I don''t think your mother''s example can be applied to everyone. It seems like something that could be different for everyone. Can you think of a stronger point? Also, take one of the transitions out of your thesis statement (I suggest however). You don''t need two together.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(84, 1227, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN>Some persons agree that development of technology is creating a single world culture and other persons disagree with this. <TS>I think modern technology makes the world has a single culture. The people in the world have common culture because of the development of communication skills and transportation vehicles.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, to communicate with the persons in the other countries are easier under the modern technology, and it makes the world as a common culture community.</MI1> <SI1>There are a lot of things to contribute to the development of communication, such as telephone and internet. <TR>Through these</TR>, the people in the world get common knowledge and information. <EX><TR>Before I came to America</TR>, I used to check the information about here through the internet, and I knew that there is no big difference between my country, the Korea, and the U.S.A.</EX></SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2>Indeed, to move from one place to other place is easier than the past under the modern technology.</MI2> <SI2>The transportation is well developed and it is very easy to use them. A lot of people travel all over the world, and they affect each other. The way to live and the way to eat and wear has many things common. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, the Korea has pizza and steak, and the U.S.A. has Korean B.B.Q and sushi.</EX> This is the same in the way to wear and think, too. The world has a common culture under the development of technology.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>Furthermore</TR>, the more and more business are cooperated with other countries, and there are lots of business which have no boundaries of countries.</MI3> <SI3><EX><TR>For example</TR>, the U.S.A has many Korean companies''s branch such as Samsung, and the Korea has many cooperation from U.S.A, as well.</EX></SI3></BO3> \n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion, I agree with that the development of technology makes it possible to have a common culture in the world, because it makes possible to communicate easily, to move freely, and to cooperate more. <TR>In the effect of this</TR>, we can share the same culture all over the world.</CO>"', 'This is an excellent essay. Nice work!');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(85, 1228, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"3","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"3","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Students have to learn more something at school than they are in home.And some people think the best way to learn about their study and society is through only srudying academic subjects such as Enlgish,Korean,mathematics and phsycology what have you.<TR>However</TR>,in today''s world,for people to adjust society more positively they have to have healthy body by joining physical activities.Here ,there are two reasons that make my view convincing.</TS></IN> \n\n<CO><MI1><TR>First</TR>,as we know,the more we practice physiacal activities the more we can be healthy.</MI1> <SI1>This is essential factor for students to spend desirable adolescent period.If they only do study all sroud the clock,their body is getting bad than they can practice outside.Adolescent period play a key role to build up heathy status in human life.Even though they don''t study much of their time, they can keep their health through physical&nbsp;&nbsp;excercise.This also can be the start of their joiful and pleasant social life someday. <TR>Thus</TR> ,it goes without saying that joining physical practise is significant component to have a rosy future.</SI></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>in addition</TR>,pupils can do know that we all do many things in cooperation with others hrough participating sports game such as football,basket ball etc.</MI2> <SI2>We cannot make lttle of joining due to this. We cannot live alone.We are the social animal. <TR>Therefore</TR>,It is crucial to know that we have to see other people who hold different opinions from one''s own.And for students to solve this sort of problems they have to experience earlier the situations that can cause conflicts.And sporsgame fit that formular well. <EX>When I was a middle school student,I was a valleyball player.After ending that game I always realized that I needed more patience.</EX> That could be the omportant seed to raise endurance as well as patience.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In short</TR>, this is much-discussed topic between parents.<TR>Besides</TR>,this can be a matter of coice.<TR>That is to say</TR>,It depends on the individual.<TR>However</TR>,I dare to say like this.Physacal excercise is the most important for student''s bright future.Please select cautiously before you set your mind.</CO>"', 'Your main points are good, but your support is a little bit confusing. Can you give more examples? Also, take the transition out of your thesis statement to make it stronger.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(86, 1229, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>The most interesting class I have taken was Japanese Politics. I attended this class last semester, I enjoyed it very much. I learnt about Japan politic''s changing from about 1800 to now. Japan is very close with Korean and it made the class more interesting. We used many materials, videos, computer and so on. The professor was good at teaching and he knew about many interesting stories about Japanese politics. I could learn more exactly and it helped me to understand Japan.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>As Korean</TR>, I think we should know about Japan.</MI1> <SI1>Japan is very related with us. They are good friends and in competition. Japan has strong power in East so we need to watch them. So learning about Japanese politics is very important and necessary. I knew Japan and Korean has similarities though they has many differences. The interesting thing is that Japan liked American when they were ruled by America. They believed that America made them free.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2>I had a chance to think about problems and issues between Korea and Japan.</MI2> <SI2><TR>Among of them</TR>, these countries have problem about prostitutes. I learnt about relationship between America and Japan. America helps Japan to develop but they control Japan not to be stronger than them as the same time. It was very news to me.</SI2><BO2> \n\n<CO>I learnt what I should have known. It made me think about national relationship. I could know what I have to do for my country and new things about Japan. I enjoyed this class because of these reasons.</CO>"', 'A very interesting and well written essay! Japan was ruled by America? That''s news to me.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(87, 1230, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>The world is heading for the unified community along with globalization. This phenomenon is specified as a single world culture. Modern technology has enabled us to bring about it.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, the development of the communication media has brought common experiences for the world. <SI1>All the people of the world can contact anyone at any time through the Internet. The world-cup games are projected simultaneously all over the world by the media satellites. The communication technology advancements take us to a similar culture.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>, it is more available for us to travel evrywhere of the world due to the innovations of of transportation. <SI2>Within 24 hours we can go to the opposite sites of the earth. The mass flow of the global people cause this planet to have the familiar experience, which becomes the basis for the single world culture.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<BO3><MI3><TR>Finally</TR>, the evolution process of the world''s countries has traced the general path ac the capitalism has been spread all over the world. <SI3>All teenagers of the world, except a very few naton, would enjoy the Mcdonald hamburgers and Coca-cokes. Capitalism accompanied by the liberalism would provide the unilateral cultural history.</SI3> \n\n<CO>The rapid development of communication and transportation in the wide rooted capitalism have another featurre of the worldwide culture. This trends would be more accelerated om the perspective that the culture is the coomon and accumulated recognition of a community.</CO>"', 'A good essay! Short, but to the point. Nice job.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(88, 1231, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"4","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>There are briefly two different arguments about whether people should make the significant decision alone. Although it seems reasonable that people should make an important decision for themeselves because people have to be reponsible on their own decisons, I believe that people should refer to others'' opinions when they have to decide something important.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>First</TR>, people can take other''s acvices as they make the important decisions because especailly old people''s advices can be usually helpful.</MI1> <SI1>In other words, old people''s acvices can be much benefits to the younger people. Mostly, younger people need to be listen to other people because they have little experience and knowledge. <EX><TR>In my case</TR>, when I had to decide the major of my university, I did not know how to do bacause I have almost no information about the departments of the university and I was worried about my future so seriously at that time. Without my teacher''s diverse information and my parents'' hearty acvices, I doubt that I could make it as facing that important decision of my life.</EX> <TR>Now</TR>, I am so satisfied my decision and I am really appreciated with my parents and teacher.</SI></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Second</TR>, people can reduce many mistakes though referring other''s opinions.</MI2> <SI2>In other words, people can make their decision in a more efficient way by listening to others. <EX><TR>For instance, in my case</TR>, I dicied to apply the exchange student program of my university so I needed to the TOEFL grade for the application. I had to study for the TOEFL test, but I had no resources and materials about the TOEFL test. TOEFL was so difficult for me at the fist time that I want to give up the TOEFL and the exchenge student programs. But I went to the private academy for TOEFL and I heard the kind advices from my TOEFL teacher. He said to me that I have to study more and I should make more efforts on the test. Thanks to his invaluable advice, I can study more and I came to know more about the TOEFL than before.</EX> If I gave up the TOEFL study at that time, It will be the biggest mistake in my life.</SI2> In this sense, other people''s acvices and haerty mind can play the most meaningful works on making the important decisions.</BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, I strongly agree with the idea that people should listen to ther people''s words because old people''s advices can be more advantageous and people can shorten the mistakes.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! At the beginning of your second example, take out one of the transitions - you don''t need both.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(89, 1232, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"4","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN>There are numerous reason for attending college. <TS>Some people attend college in order to be more educated. And other attend college to get their jobs. <TR>Nowadays</TR>, many places in society want to person who has specific knowledge of one subject. </TR>By and large</TR>, poeple go to college(include university) for two reasons that I have said.</TS> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Presumably</TR>, to be more educated is the best reason why students want to go to the college.</TR> <SI1>not a few students wanted to go on to further study in their special subject when they attended the (junior)high school. <EX><TR>In my case</TR>, when I was junior high school student, I feel like boasting my intellectual rigor of mathematic to friends of mine, but I''m not good students because I don''t like all school subjects without mathematic. So I really wanted to go to college to study only mathematic.</EX> <TR>Similarly</TR>, colleges allow students to develop an expertise in a given area.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2>The day is past when a person without a college degree could make a notable success of himself. <MI2>It means, <TR>not a whole but most</TR>, a college degree has become a condition which workers should have.</MI2> <SI2>it goes without saying that a person works himself. The college assists these people in terms of these points. colleges provide training and experiences that can be applied to a student''s career. And, Students can use career placement center in colleges to help get a job as well. In these manners, the college degree is the key to get one''s success with one''s effort.</SI2></BO2>\n \n<CO>I have explained detailed reasons for why student desire to go college. <TR>Surely</TR>, There are existed more reasons why go to college such as one''s friend go to college so that one should :-) (it mean, by one''s competitive spirit). But this does not mean that a college degree by itself guarantee success. Not only well cultivated one''s knowledge but also strong willness would guarantee success.</CO>"', 'This is a pretty good essay. Your first example doesn''t really apply since you are talking about yourself as a middle school student and this essay is about college. Also, do not use emoticons in a test essay!');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(90, 1233, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"0","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>There are many public places for using as several usages such as parks, libraries, and even working offices. Therefore people of the several classes come together in there. Some people may be very young and even baby to go out to follow mom. And others may be old people and a patient having some diseases. In there places, if some people smoke, many people feel inconvenient for that. So acting to smoke in the public office must be controlled.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Above all</TR>, most smokers do not realized at that others dislike a smoke smell.</MI1> <SI1>They only claim their smoking rights. Of course, they have not only a right to smoke, but also a duty not to behavior them a bad feel. <EX>My department, <TR>for example/TR>, has supplied a study room for undergraduate students. Most students have studied and spent most school time with their friends in there. <TR>However</TR>, some students have enjoyed smoking out door of study room in hall. Another one has complained about their smoking acting, but they have neglected it. So vice-president got some complains and said not to smoke indoor.</EX></SI1><BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, smoking can give severe disease more nonsmokers than smokers.</MI2> <SI2>Many researches have showed this fact. <EX>I saw the movie that introduced a girl who had a cancer of lung. She was just 19 years old, and must fierce her neck tiny hole for treatment. Her father was severe smoker and had always cigarette his fingers in home. Their home was full of smoke all the time.</EX></SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, smoking make our body worst, even we can have some ill for it. And smoking in the public places can give some bad feeling to others. Therefore the government has to make some rule about controlling smoking at least in the public places.</CO>"', 'This is a very good essay, but you need a thesis statement! Also, I think your second body paragraph needs one more sentence to give the example closure.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(91, 1234, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>There are several great achievements made in the twentieth century. And our lives has been changed a lot because of them. Everyone may have different ideas which was the most significant change. Some people might think exploring space was the most important event in 20th century. Others might think vivid colored TV was the most impressive invention. <TR>However</TR>, I believe it was the internet network that should be remembered as the greatest change in 20th century.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Nowadays, there is no doubt how much the internet has changed our lives.</MI1> <SI1><TR>First of all</TR>, we could assess to enormous information. It means we are no longer controlled by the government or the media like before. <EX><TR>For example</TR>, in Korea, there was president election 2 years ago. The election was a lot different from previous ones. At the time we could get enough information from the internet, not passively accept from the newspaper or TV. In other words, we could participate in that with more objective information about the candidates. We could have a chance to distinguish which candidate was suitable for that job. The government could not control people by using mass media any more. We could actively get information from the internet and figure out which one is reliable.</EX></SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Besides<TR>, because of the internet network, we could contact with many people on the internet network.</MI2> <SI2>It provides us opportunities to broaden our point of view a lot. <EX><TR>For example, if I want to talk about the situation happening in America, like anti-terror campaign, I can even talk with American on the internet. And also I can share my opinion with others freely on-line community.</EX> We can hardly get the chance to talk many people who have different interest, ideas and values in reality. <TR>Therefore</TR>, this is so amazing that if I want, I can talk a variety of people. Of course there is also disadvantages, such as intervening private life of celebrities <TR>However</TR>, I still think unless we abuse the internet in that way, we could take a lot of advantage of it.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO>In conclusion, the internet network has changed our lives a lot, compared with before. It provides us with huge amount of information available. And also it encourages us to enhance our point of view by talking with variety of people on-line network. There are still many changes made in 20th century, <TR>However</TR>, I believe the internet network was the most significant achievement in that it is related with the change of our source of information, from newspaper or TV to internet.</CO>"', 'A very good essay! Take the transition out of your thesis statement to make it stronger.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(92, 1235, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"5","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN>These days, there are a lot of old people in our society. Sometimes, the aging of the people in a society causes problems like the difficulty in an employment, and the isolation of old people. <TS>Why are people living longer now? Although there are lots of reasons, I think the development of medical technology and the increase in exercise time are main causes.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, because of the development of medical technology, people can be healed in hospitals.</MI1> <SI1>Since the birth of human beings, people always want to live longer, so it makes many improvements in the medical and drug realms. <TR>Today</TR>, by go to hospitals, we can easily find the disease we have, and it is possible to treat most of diseases. <TR>Like this</TR>, the development of medical treatment allows humans to live longer.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Moreover</TR>, according to the improvement of life quality, people could spend time on entertainments such sports as hiking, swimming, soccer, jogging, so it has a good effect on human health.</MI2> <SI2><TRActually</TR>, there are numerous people enjoy body building, swimming, or jogging after studies, or works. <EX><TR>From my experience</TR>, I often go to sports center in the evening in order to make the body healthy. Even though I have gone to the health convenience for 2 months, I can feel better.</EX></SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, as mentioned above, there are many causes which make people live longer, and I think the development of medical technology and the investment in exercise are the most important reasons that affect on human life spans.</CO>"', 'This is a pretty good essay, but I think you need to add more support to your argument. You could definitely add more examples and statistics. You say a lot of studies have been done on the effect of exercise? Ok, cite one. Don''t make the reader take your word for it. Finally, take out one of the transitions in your conclusion. You don''t need two.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(93, 1236, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><Through our life, friends are taking an important role. <TS>Given the choice, some people prefer to spend time with a few close friends, while others prefer to spend most of their time with a lot of friends. <TR>Undoubtedly</TR>, both aspects are advantageous. <TR>Nonetheless</TR>, as I will demonstrate through several definite examples, spending time with a large number of friends are more advantageous.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>On the one hand</TR>, getting together with a few friends has several benefits.</MI1> <SI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, it is easy to keep the secret with one or two close friends. <TR>Generally</TR>, the secret tends to be easily broken if many people are involved in the secret. <TR>Besides</TR>, a few close friends are better when someone is in a difficult situation. There is a Korean saying that one true friend is as much worth as one hundred friends. <EX><TR>From my personal experience</TR>, I felt there was only one close friend who really cared for me when I got stuck in a trouble.</EX> <TR>Furthermore</TR>, when it comes to making a decision, their opinions are seldom scattered. <EX>I used to go to movies on Saturday night with one of my close friends. There was no conflict between us. Even if our opinions are quite different, we made a decision in a short manner.</EX></SI1</BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>On the other hand</TR>, spending time with a large number of friends give us a lot of advantages.</MI2> <SI2>It enables us to share a variety of background and experience. <TR>Generally</TR>, most people have their own backgrounds and experiences, which are different from each other. <TR>On top of that</TR>, each person has a different opinion on the same matters. We can experience different perspectives with a variety of friends. <TRBesides</TR>, some sports needs more than 2 people, such as basketball, soccer, and so on. It is possible to enjoy these kinds of sports and group activities with a large number of friends. <EX><TR>Moreover</TR>, there is a general Korean saying that happiness is increasing twice and sadness is lessening half when more people are involved.</EX> It is true because humans are social animals so that their feelings are added and lessened when more people are being together.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, it is advantageous to hang around with a few close friends in terms of secrecy, true friends and quick decision; <TR>however</TR> spending time with a large number of friends is more advantageous in terms of sharing experience, playing sports and the Korean saying. <TR>Therefore</TR> I prefer to spend most of my time with many friends.</CO>"', 'This essay is pretty good, but I think you need to explain your examples a little more, especially in your first main body paragraph. Also, you are in danger of using too many transitions. Start by taking the transition out of your thesis statement to make it stronger.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(94, 1237, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"3","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"4","si":"3","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>I actually support people to get up early and to work at the days for various reason. I consider that the health, The pattern of life are reasons for my supporting. Although some people might think that nocturnal working need sometimes for some people but it is their own thinking not for everyone.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Firstly</TR>. The health are most important for all people.</MI1> <SI1>The methods of keeping the health are various. I think that foundation of them is to be people to get up early and to work at days. When people gets up at early morning, they can have more light head feelings then it helps people working more effectively than nocturnal working.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>. Our bodies are made for acting at days and for sleeping, taking a break at night.</MI2> <SI2>If people act at night in contrast of our bodies pattern, this will give people bad condition for spoiling body pattern. <EX><TR>For examples</TR>, I experienced this situation at my university vacation. Because I woke up approximately at 1~2 pm, can not sleep well at night. I spended my plying computers at night and reading the books. After the half of a month, I had a little headache and ennui.</EX></SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, people who get up early and work at the days having literally good habitation. They are more activating, and have good condition to work, play.</CO>"', 'Your essay is all right, but it is a little short. Your first main paragraph is especially weak. Getting up early is healthier than going to bed late, you say? Ok. Prove it. Also, try to strengthen your thesis statement by briefly saying what the ''various reasons'' are.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(95, 1238, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"5","usage":"5"}', '"<IN><TS>Today, more and more people tend to go to big cities for their living or wish to change their home town into a big city. Big cities provides people abundant modern facilities and active living with many other people. Thus living in a big city seems to be attractive. <TR>However</TR>, I would like to live in a small town for following reasons.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1>One reason is that big cities are not good for my health.</MI1> <SI1>The pollution caused by gasoline and noise is nearly inevitable in most of big cities. Many people in big cities suffer from diseases originated from air pollution. Croweded people and cars in big cities cause a lot of stress and even can be a reason of mental disorder. <TR>On the other hand</TR>, small towns are reletively free from the pollution compared with big cities because of the low population and small number of cars.</SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2>The other reason is that it is easier to make friendships with neoghbors in small cities.</MI2> <SI2>In big cities, people have difficulty in talking with their neighbors because of busy life. <TR>In addition</TR>, high crime rate in many big cities keep people from making good relationship with other people. In small towns, people can know their neighbors easily, and can help each other when they have some hard house work. Community in a small town is more active and beneficial for members in the town.</SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>By these reasons</TR>, healthy and cheerful life is possible in small towns. Some people can say that living in a small town means loss of successful and wealthy life, but idyllic and easy life is more successul than stressful and unhealthy life. <TR>Therefore</TR>, I would select a small town and suggest a small life to my friends.</CO>"', 'This is a very well-written essay! You could make your thesis statement a little stronger by taking out thus and briefly stating your reasons. Also, your main points and support are very good, but if you added some examples or research, they would be even better.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(96, 1239, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"5","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"4","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>Visiting another country is a common thing in these days. Many people desire to have a chance to visit a foreign country because it gives them unfogettable memory in their life. <TR>In my case</TR>, I want to visit Canada for two reasons; <TR>first</TR>, I want to feel comfortable and imagine how the novelist wrote ''Anne of Green Gables'' in Prince Edward Island where is the back-ground of the novel. <TR>Second</TR>, I could see the Niagara Falls in Canada and learn greatness of the nature.</TS></IN>\n\n<BO1><MI1>Being the back-ground of the novel, ''Anne of Green Gables'', Prince Edward Island may be picturesque place, and I can feel comfortable and imagine how the novelist''s life goes on.</MI1> <SI1>Since I am crazy about the work, it would be never forgotten if I have the chance to visit Canada. I think two weeks are enough time for going around the place, and imagining life of the novelist.</SI1> <TR>In this respect</TR>, I want to visit Canada, especially Prince Edward Island.</BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>In addition</TR>, Niagara Falls in Canada is the reason why I want to visit Canada, because I could feel immense of the nature through seeing Niagara Falls.</MI2> <SI2>I have heard that Niagara Falls is the senicest falls in the world. <TR>Moreover</TR>, everyone who sees Niagara Falls surprises of its magnitude. I think visiting Canada to see Niagara Falls is more worth for me than visiting other countries in that it could teach me how the nature majestic is. I believe that the experience would be good for me for sure, since I have not felt the greatness of the nature in small country, where I am living now, Korea.</SI2><BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>To sum up</TR>, if I had the opportunity to visit another country for two weeks, then I would go Canada because I could be moderate in Prince Edward Island, Canada, which was the back-ground of the novel I have mentioned as well as make an illusion about the novelist''s life. <TR>Also</TR>, I could visit Niagara Falls which is the most beautiful falls and realize how the nature great is.</CO>"', 'This is a pretty good essay. One small thing: your use of In this respect is incorrect. Try For this reason.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(97, 1240, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"4","topic":"4","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"4","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>We pay some money to school and the money becomes teachers'' salary and maintenance fee of school. If teachers get paid according to how much their students learn, the teachers would prepare more and try to teach more eagerly as well as be kinder. <TR>Therefore</TR>, I insist teachers should get paid following amount of their students'' knowledge gotten from the teachers.</TS></IN>\n \n<BO1><MI1><TR>First of all</TR>, if teachers are paid according to how much their students learn, they will prepare contents they will teach better and try to teach more pricely.</MI1> <SI1>We can see some teachers who just read and explain a text book without some knowledge or information from their head. The teachers are not elligeable to get much money. <EX>One of my high school teahcers, a literature teacher, was always a little bit soked with drink. We could smell it and he just made us read a text book during classes. For university examination, we had to study by ourselves agian.</EX></SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly<TR>, the teachers being paid with students'' knowledge getting from them will be kinder to and consider more their sudents.</MI2> <SI2>For getting much money, they have to gather more students and the relationship with students has to be good. <EX>When I was a university sudent, a philosophy teacher was nice and kind enough to gather so much students. The first closing class was his. Philosophy is now easy but his hand outs and explain were understandable easily and his manner for many questions from students was always considerous and neat.</EX></SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclude</TR>, I think it is a good way to improve teachers'' passion and students'' knowledge that teachers get paid according to how much their students learn. Teachers will prepare many sources for their classes and they will try to manage students to understand better. <TR>Moreover</TR>, they will treat students better. If this system will be adjusted, students and teachers as well as schools are developed more.</CO>"', 'This is a pretty good essay, although I don''t see what your second example has to do with the topic, since your teacher wasn''t getting paid according to how much you learned.  Can you think of a different example, or try harder to link that one to the topic? Also, take the transition out of your thesis statement to make it stronger.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(98, 1241, '{"ibc":"2","thesis":"0","topic":"5","coherence":"3","transition":"5","mi":"3","si":"4","style":"3","usage":"3"}', '"<IN><TS>Wearing school uniforms is such a luxury for high school students, I think. <TR>Plus</TR>, for the students who are on the way to adulthood, wearing school uniforms can be a kind of a barrier that prevents them from thinking freely. We keep on saying to them that they should learn how to think differently, how to do away with the matrix of fixed thought. But how? do we have a right to say that to them, while we''re recommending wearing school uniforms which is the source of fixed thought? I don''t think so. School uniforms are just school uniforms. No more, no less. I hear some people insist that wearing school uniforms keeps students from committing a crime while they are in it. But that''s a nonsensical idea. I have seen many students smoking at the back of the school fence, many students bully students of other schools on the street.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>Secondly<TR>, when I attended a high school I didn''t know how much money was spent for me from my parents.</MI1> <SI1><EX>Now that I became an adult and think freely of those things, well, I was such a money-biting insect. I always kept on asking for money of my parents, money for textbooks, bus fare and things that I needed and wanted.</EX></SI1></BO1>\n \n<CO>Especially for those families with less income, it can be a burden for the parents to buy their sons or daughters a pair of school uniform on top of the things they necessarily need. They are already suffering school tuition, expenses for books and other various expenses for their children, so they must be under pressure of supporting their children. So, I insist that school uniform policy should be withdrawn at least for economical reasons.</CO>"', 'Your organization needs work. When you write an essay for a test, make sure you have an introduction, at least one main body paragraph and a conclusion. Your main body paragraph(s) need to have one main point and the rest of the paragraph is support for that main point. This essay has some good points, but they are so disorganized that it is difficult to follow your argument.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(99, 1242, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"0","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"3","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>When people think good health, they often envision difficultly it. Some people prefer to swim and other people prefer to play the tennis. In my opinion, <TR>however</TR>, I choose jogging in the morning and low fat diet. To illustrate why I convince my point, I will treat only a few significant reasons with my vivid experiences here.</TS><IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1><TR>To begin with</TR>, jogging in the morning improves body.</MI1> <SI1><EX>According to the Healthy Times, the best-known healthy journal in Korea, jogging improves the cardiopulmonary function. In addition it prevents both hypertension and diabetes.</EX> <TR>Nowadays</TR>, adult people get sick owing to insufficiency of health in Korea. It is known that only 24% of adult people take exercise, thus people must get exercise. . <TR>In addition</TR>, not only can jogging in the morning breathe in fresh air but also can not need no tools of exercise. Jogging only need time and diligence.</SI1> Therefore I suggest jogging in the morning.</BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>Secondly</TR>, eating a low fat food helps you healthy.</MI2> <SI2><TR>These days</TR>, people eat fast-food which can be eaten easily. Thus people eat high fat food so their health is gradually bad. <EX>According to the Josun-Ilbo which is the best-known newspaper in Korea, eating a low fat food prevents both diabetes and colon cancer. <TR>For example</TR>, once my father was got diabetes so he was very pained. However, he was got a prescription filled and controlled diet. After a few months, he could regain him health.</EX></SI2></BO2>\n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, given the chance of selecting for good health I would choose jogging in the morning and eating a low fat food. The reason why I think like is because not only can excises improve health, but controlling of food also can prevent illness.</CO>"', 'For the most part, this essay is very good. You need a thesis statement and you need to watch your transitions. You are using too many of them.');
INSERT INTO `essay_others` VALUES(100, 1243, '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"2","topic":"5","coherence":"4","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"4","usage":"4"}', '"<IN><TS>Whether people live in a big city or a small town can be a heatedly discussed issue. Because there are some advantages in both of two situations, it is not easy to choose one of them. <TR>However</TR>, I like to live in a big city. With specific examples and examinations, I support my opinions.</TS></IN> \n\n<BO1><MI1>A small city like a rural area can give you fresh air.</MI1> <SI1>It has less pollution than a big city. You can walk though forests in the morning, or swim in a stream not polluted. With fresh air, you are healthy. <EX><TR>As a matter of fact</TR>, when I lived in a big city, I have some diseases about skins. My doctor said I should live in unpolluted areas as a small city. So I moved rural areas where my grandparents live. Now I get over my diseases.</EX></SI1></BO1> \n\n<BO2><MI2><TR>However</TR>, there are more uncomfortable things in a small town than in a big city.</MI1> <SI1>It is so hard to find not only facilities for fun but also medical offices in a small town. <EX><TR>In my town</TR>, I should walk for an hour to get some medicines from a doctor.</EX> If you are in an emergency situation, you cannot be treated in a small town as quickly as in a big city. <TR>As you know</TR>, in a big city is many medical offices. When you are seriously wounded, you can go hospital quickly, and save your life.</SI2></BO2> \n\n<CO><TR>In conclusion</TR>, you can find some advantage in a small city. <TR>However</TR>, it is not comfortable. It takes so many hours to do something. You can live more conveniently in a big city. Because of these reasons I prefer to live in a big city.</CO>"', 'This is a pretty good essay, but you need to make your thesis statement stronger.');
