INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(15, 2, 13, 1, '\n"It has been said, ""Not everything that is learned is contained in books."" Compare and contrast knowledge gained from experience with knowledge gained from books. In your opinion, which source is more important? Why? "', '"          People learn constantly from their birth to death. Not only school education or books but also things we see, hear, touch are good materials to get knowledge. Among them, I think knowledge of experience is more important than knowledge of books because of its durability, and it teaches us precious values like cooperation and flexibility. \n         \n               First, we hardly forget what we learn from our own experience. For example, we learn importance of money and difficulty of earning money in capitalistic society by studying economics through books. Also, we memorize how money circulates between producer and consumer written in textbooks. However, we usually forget about it as time passes. On the other hand, we can learn hardship of gaining money or way of profiting in person through part-time job. The reason is that they are more practical, and as we learn it using five senses. In short, knowledge of experience are more important because it''s unforgettable.   \n        Secondly, knowledge of experience offers a sense of cooperation and flexibility which are important to build up one''s character. Even if we can gain boundless knowledges studying books about astronomy, mathematics, and so on, it''s no use if we bury ourselves in pedantic or impractical theory neglecting the value of cooperative spirit and flexibility, which can be gained by social experience like contacting directly with other people and various circumstances. To sum up, getting knowledge from experience is good to develop cooperative and flexible attitude.     \n         \n                In conclusion, if I have to choose between knowledge gained from experience and knowledge gained from books, I would choose the former. The reason is that it''s lasts longer, and gives us cooperative and flexible mind. However, what we don''t have to forget is that both knowledges of experience and books must be in balance.   "', 'People learn constantly from their birth to death. Not only school education or books but also things we see, hear, touch are good materials to get knowledge. Among them, I think knowledge of experience is more important than knowledge of books because of its durability, and it teaches us precious values like cooperation and flexibility. <br>         <br>               First, we hardly forget what we learn from our own experience. For example, we learn importance of money and difficulty of earning money in capitalistic society by studying economics through books. Also, we memorize how money circulates between producer and consumer written in textbooks. However, we usually forget about it as time passes. On the other hand, we can learn hardship of gaining money or way of profiting in person through part-time job. The reason is that they are more practical, and as we learn it using five senses. In short, knowledge of experience are more important because it''s unforgettable.   <br>        Secondly, knowledge of experience offers a sense of cooperation and flexibility which are important to build up one''s character. Even if we can gain boundless knowledges studying books about astronomy, mathematics, and so on, it''s no use if we bury ourselves in pedantic or impractical theory neglecting the value of cooperative spirit and flexibility, which can be gained by social experience like contacting directly with other people and various circumstances. To sum up, getting knowledge from experience is good to develop cooperative and flexible attitude.     <br>         <br>                In conclusion, if I have to choose between knowledge gained from experience and knowledge gained from books, I would choose the former. The reason is that it''s lasts longer, and gives us cooperative and flexible mind. However, what we don''t have to forget is that both knowledges of experience and books must be in balance.', 'People learn constantly from their birth to death. Not only school education or books but also things we see, hear, touch are good materials to get knowledge. Among them, I think knowledge of experience is more important than knowledge of books because of its durability, and it teaches us precious values like cooperation and flexibility. <br>         <br>               First, we hardly forget what we learn from our own experience. For example, we learn importance of money and difficulty of earning money in capitalistic society by studying economics through books. Also, we memorize how money circulates between producer and consumer written in textbooks. However, we usually forget about it as time passes. On the other hand, we can learn hardship of gaining money or way of profiting in person through part-time job. The reason is that they are more practical, and as we learn it using five senses. In short, knowledge of experience are more important because it''s unforgettable.   <br>        Secondly, knowledge of experience offers a sense of cooperation and flexibility which are important to build up one''s character. Even if we can gain boundless knowledges studying books about astronomy, mathematics, and so on, it''s no use if we bury ourselves in pedantic or impractical theory neglecting the value of cooperative spirit and flexibility, which can be gained by social experience like contacting directly with other people and various circumstances. To sum up, getting knowledge from experience is good to develop cooperative and flexible attitude.     <br>         <br>                In conclusion, if I have to choose between knowledge gained from experience and knowledge gained from books, I would choose the former. The reason is that it''s lasts longer, and gives us cooperative and flexible mind. However, what we don''t have to fo