INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(16, 2, 14, 1, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Television has destroyed communication among friends and family. Use specific reasons and examples to support your opinion.', '"People have invented new machines and materials to make our life more convenient and joyful. Among them, television is one of the most effective inventions. In my opinion, I don''t agree with the statement television has destroyed communication among friends and family because it gives people common subjects to talk about and time to get together.\n         \n              First of all, a family can have time to be with by watching television. These days, each individual is busy doing his/her own work and has different interest. However, after dinner, most family gather in the living room to watch TV. In my case, my family has talked about each others'' daily life while watching television together. On the contrary, when my father puts the television away to prevent my eyesight from weakening, my family members did their own business in their own room. Shortly, television provides time to communicate with family.     \n\n        Moreover, we can get some topics of conversation from television. There are lots of interesting and up-to-date informations that most people can share and enjoy. For example, a popular soup opera ''A lover of Paris'' of SBS provided intimate and funny subjects to talk with friends. Also, television shows us about current issues so that we can discuss about it. In summary, whether that kind of topics are vulgar or not, it''s certain that television helps people communicate with others by giving common interests and topics.     \n         \n                 In conclusion, I think television is serviceable stuff in the aspect of helping people communicate with their family and friends by giving chances and subjects to talk. Lastly, what I want to suggest is that people should control themselves to do not addict to watching television, and use it wisely to have better communication with others. "', 'People have invented new machines and materials to make our life more convenient and joyful. Among them, television is one of the most effective inventions. In my opinion, I don''t agree with the statement television has destroyed communication among friends and family because it gives people common subjects to talk about and time to get together.<br>         <br>              First of all, a family can have time to be with by watching television. These days, each individual is busy doing his/her own work and has different interest. However, after dinner, most family gather in the living room to watch TV. In my case, my family has talked about each others'' daily life while watching television together. On the contrary, when my father puts the television away to prevent my eyesight from weakening, my family members did their own business in their own room. Shortly, television provides time to communicate with family.     <br><br>        Moreover, we can get some topics of conversation from television. There are lots of interesting and up-to-date informations that most people can share and enjoy. For example, a popular soup opera ''A lover of Paris'' of SBS provided intimate and funny subjects to talk with friends. Also, television shows us about current issues so that we can discuss about it. In summary, whether that kind of topics are vulgar or not, it''s certain that television helps people communicate with others by giving common interests and topics.     <br>         <br>                 In conclusion, I think television is serviceable stuff in the aspect of helping people communicate with their family and friends by giving chances and subjects to talk. Lastly, what I want to suggest is that people should control themselves to do not addict to watching television, and use it wisely to have better communication with others.', 'People have invented new machines and materials to make