INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(22, 2, 20, 1, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? A person''s childhood years (the time from birth to twelve years of age) are the most important years of a person''s life. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"   Almost people don''t remember their childhood years; what they did, what they thought, and what happened. They were too young to remember everything. When we forgot the old memories, the only way to find out what happened before is to ask to our parents and our acquaintances who have known us since we were so young. our old memories are fading away even right now. Then, do the childhood years mean nothing? Absolutley not. \n\n        Firstly, the period that we got socialized is our childhood year. It means important. We learn the customs of the community which we belong to. That is, we learn who we are, what we have to, and what our society is. From learning things like this, we get a position of our society. And then, we can play our roles in the society. Through interaction with other people in the society, each of  us makes personality. It a part of the concept of socializaion. All these things happen in our childhood years. \n\n        Secondly, we get some tools needed for social activities. One of the most important thing is language. we have at least one language that is used our society, And, we speak our mother tongue. The era that we learn the language is also our childhood year. Moreover, we learn basic knowledge concerned science and mathematics in the elementary school, which is needed for the study and research that we are going to do. So, we have to take some tools like language and basic knowledge for our future. Unintentionally, and naturally, we learn those things in our childhood years. \n\n        Conclusively, if some person has bad time in the childhood years, his all life would be unhappy. It may not true, but he has more chance to be unhappy than normal people. It is because that something wrong in childhood years can influence to his life; bad socializazion or lack of knowledge. In short, childhood years can determine the whole life. So, the most important years of a person''s life are the childhood years. "', 'Almost people don''t rem<strike>ember their childhood years; what they did, what they thought, and what happened. They were too young to remember everything. When we forgot the old memories, the only way </strike>to find out what happened before is to ask to our parents and our acquaintances who have known us since we were so young. our old memories are fading away even right now. Then, do the childhood years mean nothing? Absolutley not. <br><br>        Firstly, the period that we got socialized is our childhood year. It means important. We learn the customs of the community which we belong to. That is, we learn who we are, what we have to, and what our society is. From learning things like this, we get a position of our society. And then, we can play our roles in the society. Through interaction with other people in the society, each of  us makes personality. It a part of the concept of socializaion. All these things happen in our childhood years. <br><br>        Secondly, we get some tools needed for social activities. One of the most important thing is language. we have at least one language that is used our society, And, we speak our mother tongue. The era that we learn the language is also our childhood year. Moreover, we learn basic knowledge concerned science and mathematics in the elementary school, which is needed for the study and research that we are going to do. So, we have to take some tools like language and basic knowledge for our future. Unintentionally, and naturally, we learn those things in our childhood years. <br><br>        Conclusively, if some person has bad time in the childhood years, his all life would be unhappy. It may not true, but he has more chance to be unhappy than normal pe