INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(26, 2, 24, 1, '\nSome people prefer to spend time with one or two close friends. Others choose to spend time with large number of friends. Compare the advantages of each choice. Which of these two ways of spending time do you prefer? Use specific reasons to support your answer.', '"When we spend time with large number of friends, we get the chance to meet various kinds of people. This ables us to train social skill to easily adapt ourselves to different culture or taste. Also, gathering involving many people have a exciting atmosphere that can''t be found in groups of small number of people. But I prefer to spend time with one or two close friends for the following reasons. \n\n  Firstly, spending time with small number of friends provides the comfort and intimacy that gathering of many people might lack. We often feel distressed from the overloaded work and become annoyed with so many people making noises in the restaurant. The comfort and intimacy we get from the gatherings of small number of people might relax our fatigue. \n\n  Secondly, during the time spending with one or two close friends, we can talk about serious matters and share useful information. Such serious problems seem hard to be shared among large number of people. Talking about problems with one or two close friends might be a good way to release the pressure of the problems. We might even realize the key to the next step of solving the problem. \n\n  Although there are a lot of advantages in spending time with many friends, I think the advantages of meeting one or two close friends overweigh them. And that is why I prefer to spend time with small number of friends. "', 'When we spen<strike>d time with large number of friends, we get the chance to meet various kinds of people. This ables us to train social skill to easily adapt ourselves to different culture or taste. Also, g</strike>athering involving many people have a exciting atmosphere that can''t be found in gr