INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(27, 2, 25, 1, '\n Is the ability to read and write more important today than in the past? Why or why not?', '"Recently, our society is getting more and more complex and developed. There are so many attractive matters that we can see, hear and feel that it is easy for us to believe that reading and writing are not important as ever before. However, as far as I know, reading and writing are basic and fundamental tools for expressing oneself and understanding others because they help us arrange one''s thought. In addition, as before, the most important way to give others information is not TV show or radio talk show, but reading materials such as journal or books. Thus, I think reading and writing are more important, and here are some reasons for my decision. \n\nFirst, it is usually helpful for us to write down what we think or imagine. This is because we can not wirte about something without considering and re-arranging one''s idea. For example, every time I prepare test, without re-arranging class note, I could not make a good resualt. It seems that while I try to write down what I read form my class note, text book or some kind of material, the process of writing helps me establish heirachy of knowledge, which make it easy for me to memorize or understand information. \n\nSecond, although seeing, hearing and feeling are important tools of understanding complex and huge amount of information, reading and writng are also important to transper one''s knowledge or thought to others. This is because such media as TV, radio and movie can not be easily and deeply understood because we can not memorize or understand them relativly short period time. We can read or write until we fully understand or express. However, due to its speed and duration, it is hard for us to concentrate on that matter. \n\nIn sum, althogh traditional way of understanding and expressing, reading and writing, seems somewhat outdated, they are fundamental and crucial tools of interacting with others. Think of the world without no chance to read or write. How can you express or understand your own or others'' knowledge, information, feeling and so forth?   "', 'Recently, our society<strike> is getting more and more complex and developed. There are so many attractive matters that we can see, hear and feel that it is easy for us to believe that reading and writing are not important as ever before. However, as far as I know, reading and writing are basic and fundamental tools for expressing oneself and understanding others because</strike> they help us arrange one''s thought. In addition, as before, the most important way to give others information is not TV show or radio talk show, but reading materials such as journal or books. Thus, I think reading and writing are more important, and here are some reasons for my decision. <br><br>First, it is usually helpful for us to write down what we think or imagine. This is because we can not wirte about something without considering and re-arranging one''s idea. For example, every time I prepare test, without re-arranging class note, I could not make a good resualt. It seems that while I try to write down what I read form my class note, text book or some kind of material, the process of writing helps me establish heirachy of knowledge, which make it easy for me to memorize or understand information. <br><br>Second, although seeing, hearing and feeling are important tools of understanding complex and huge amount of information, reading and writng are also important to transper one''s knowledge or thought to others. This is because such media as TV, radio and movie can not be easily and deeply understood because we can not memorize or understand them relativly short period time. We can read or write until we fully understand or express. However, due to its speed and duration, it is hard for us to concentrate on that matter. <br><br>In sum, althogh traditional way of understanding and expressing