INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(733, 3, 1181, 2, '\nSome people believe that a college or university education should be available to all students. Others believe that higher education should be available only to good students. Discuss these views. Which view do you agree with? Explain why.', '"In these days, higher education can be available to all student in Korea because the recognition that people who want to be educated are eligible to study spreads society. However, some people say that higher education should be prepared for good student. In my opinion, college or university education should be open to all student in that education should be fair in any case and we could discover some talents we miss.\n\nFirst, education should be open to every student because everyone has the right to be educated. I think, if the society does not gives people who want to study the chance to be informed, it is not for the everyone. It could be said unfair society. For example, Choseun Dinasity, Korea 500 years ago, gives the right to be educated only to selected people, Yangban. However, there is no difference between selected people and non-selected people In fact. Although non-selected people had the right to be educated, people at that times didn''t know how important the right is. Consequently, Choseun Dinasity had fallen down slowly. Does the society at these days make that mistake, too? In this manner, though it sounds theoretically, because everyone has the right to be informed education should be given to every student.\n\nSecond, if we offer higher education to good student we can''t find the talents we omit. Some students who are proved ''not good'' could have some talents in other areas. For example, a friend of mine who couldn''t go to university because of her low grade in high school possesses the ability to draw something like people''s face and movement artically. Nevertheless, she was not admitted to study art more since she was not successful in mathematics and science. In this respect, I think higher education should be available to every student in that we can see the capacity which can be lament now.\n\nTo sum up, I think higher education should be offered to every student because of the right to be educated in modern society and the ability we could miss. The more education, the more talents we could discover."', '"In these days, higher education can be available to all student in Korea because the recognition that people who want to be educated are eligible to study spreads society. However, some people say that higher education should be prepared for good student. In my opinion, college or university education should be open to all student in that education should be fair in any case and we could discover some talents we miss.<br><br>First, education should be open to every student because everyone has the right to be educated. I think, if the society does not gives people who want to study the chance to be informed, it is not for the everyone. It could be said unfair society. For example, Choseun Dinasity, Korea 500 years ago, gives the right to be educated only to selected people, Yangban. However, there is no difference between selected people and non-selected people In fact. Although non-selected people had the right to be educated, people at that times didn''t know how important the right is. Consequently, Choseun Dinasity had fallen down slowly. Does the society at these days make that mistake, too? In this manner, though it sounds theoretically, because everyone has the right to be informed education should be given to every student.<br><br>Second, if we offer higher education to good student we can''t find the talents we omit. Some students who are proved ''not good'' could have some talents in other areas. For example, a friend of mine who couldn''t go to university because of her low grade in high school possesses the ability to draw something like people''s face and movement artically. Nevertheless, she