gt;<span class=''mi'' tag=''MI2''>&lt;MI2&gt;<span class=''tr'' tag=''TR''>&lt;TR&gt;Moreover&lt;/TR&gt;</span>, some books involving the imaginary world have showed some people the way to the future.</MI2 <span class=''si'' tag=''SI2''>&lt;SI2&gt;Stirred up by the imaginary and fantastic world, many children determine what they will do in their adulthood, and become leading scientists. <span class=''tr'' tag=''TR''>&lt;TR&gt;Thus&lt;/TR&gt;</span>, the scientists advance the science and technology, and finally come true their imaginary world, beginning from the motivation of the unrealistic fiction. We can find such inventions everywhere in our life; robots, spaceships, computers, and so on.&lt;/SI2&gt;</span>&lt;/BO2&gt;</span> \n\n<span class=''co'' tag=''CO''>&lt;CO&gt;<span class=''tr'' tag=''TR''>&lt;TR&gt;In short&lt;/TR&gt;</span>, even books on fiction world are worth reading. They have made their own contributions to the world. Even if they seem to be nonsense, who knows if those books will contribute the development of our future?&lt;/CO&gt;</span>"', 'This is a great essay. Add a thesis statement and it will be perfect!', '{"ibc":"5","thesis":"0","topic":"5","coherence":"5","transition":"5","mi":"5","si":"5","style":"5","usage":"5"}', 1, 0, 'essay', 'Tagging', 0, 0, '2013-12-20 23:49:06', '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
INSERT INTO `tag_essay` VALUES(777, 3, 1225, 2, '\nDo you agree or disagree with the following statement? Parents are the best teachers. Use specific reasons and examples to support your answer.', '"Some people presume that parents are in the most important role for their children’s education. Basically that could be true since children stay their home most of their time. Although parents should be familiar with their children’s academic affair, in my opinion, they are not the best teachers for their children. \n\nGenerally parents expect their children to do what they wanted to do but they couldn’t do when they were young. I know a friend of mine who was forced to enter the law school by their parents although his interest doesn’t go with that. His father was eager to be a lawyer back in his twenties, but he failed. \n\nI also have a friend who wanted to be a journalist but his parents wanted him to be a scientist. And he was forced to enter one of the best science colleges. But he finally gave up his master degree after his 10 years of studying. These examples pinpoint how parents’ misled expectations to their children give their children a great burden in vain. \n\nIn many cases, parents are not good teachers because of their misled expectations. Thanks to it, many children lose their chances to study what they are really interested in."', '"Some people presume that parents are in the most important role for their children’s education. Basically that could be true since children stay their home most of their time. Although parents should be familiar with their children’s academic affair, in my opinion, they are not the best teachers for their children. <br><br>Generally parents expect their children to do what they wanted to do but they couldn’t do when they were young. I know a friend of mine who was forced to enter the law school by their parents although his interest doesn’t go with that. His father was eager to be a lawyer back in his twenties, but he failed.